4GParam_Defs4G Parameter DefinitionsThe table below contains an alphabetical 
listing of 4G System parameters, along with definitions for each 
      parameter.NOTE:
      This document is a work in progress – parameter names and related 
      definitions will be added as they are completed.


      Version: 684C
      Updated: 12/4/2025


      Name Comment 
      AAT Ambient Air Temp 
      AAT_def AAT default value 
      AAT_source Source input selector switch for ambient air temperature 
      measurement 
      AAT_UEGO_PHstart Ambient air temperature at preheat start 
      abs_5V_supply 5V supply absolute voltage - part of EOL Parameter Burn 
      Mode; computed from a 5V ratiometric A/D conversion during EOL burn. 
      accel_flt Filtered crankshaft acceleration 
      accel_flt_thd Threshold for filtered crankshaft acceleration to signify an 
      expansion stroke has occurred during engine cranking 
      accel_instant Instantaneous engine acceleration, valid after crank 
      synchronization. 
      ACLT_EGRclr_Lmin Estimated auxiliary coolant flow through the EGR cooler 
      (equal to the intercooler bypass flow). 
      ACLT_EGRclr_min_Lmin Minimum heat exchanger flow rate required to avoid 
      thermal shock / damage to the heat exchangers. 
      ACLT_intby_dT_halt If the actual temperature is within +/- this amount of 
      the target temperature, the valve command is frozen until the temperature 
      error exceeds the 'resume' deadzone below. 
      ACLT_intby_dT_res If control updates are halted and the difference between 
      the actual and target temperatures exceed this amount (+ or -), control 
      updates will resume. 
      ACLT_intby_ena Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow split 
      output channel. 
      ACLT_intby_I_accum Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow 
      split integral accumulator. 
      ACLT_intby_Ki Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow split 
      CL Ki gain. 
      ACLT_intby_Kp Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow split 
      CL Kp gain. 
      ACLT_intby_Lmin_CL Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow 
      split total closed-loop correction. 
      ACLT_intby_T_cmd Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow 
      split temperature target. This is calculated as the maximum of the 
      auxiliary coolant temperature and the post-intercooler dew point, plus the 
      temperature target offset. 
      ACLT_intby_T_error Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow 
      split temperature error. 
      ACLT_intby_T_ofs Offset added to the auxiliary coolant control 
      intercooler/EGR cooler flow split temperature target 
      ACLT_intby_vlv_act Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow 
      split valve actual position. 
      ACLT_intby_vlv_cmd Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow 
      split valve command. 
      ACLT_intby_vlv_def This position is commanded to the intercooler/EGR valve 
      prior to engine shutdown. It is mainly used to guarantee valve and 
      auxiliary coolant operation following a cold shutdown, where the valves 
      could potentially freeze shut.

      0% = no intercooler bypass (full EGR cooler flow)
      100% = full radiator bypass (no EGR cooler flow) 
      ACLT_intby_vlv_halt Indicates the intercooler/EGR valve control is halted 
      due to a temperature error within the calibrated deadzone. 
      ACLT_intby_vlv_max Maximum intercooler bypass valve position. 
      ACLT_intby_vlv_min Minimum intercooler bypass valve position. 
      ACLT_intclr_dTh Intake air temperature drop (actual) through the 
      intercooler. 
      ACLT_intclr_dTh_ff Intake air temperature drop (desired, used for the 
      feedforward control term) through the intercooler. 
      ACLT_intclr_dTi Air-water temperature difference at the inlet to the 
      intercooler. 
      ACLT_intclr_eff Intercooler (actual) effectiveness. 
      ACLT_intclr_eff_ff Intercooler (desired, used for the feedforward control 
      term) effectiveness. 
      ACLT_intclr_Lmin Total control intercooler volumetric flow rate. 
      ACLT_intclr_Lmin_ff Feedforward control intercooler volumetric flow rate. 
      ACLT_intclr_mdotx Actual ratio of air mixture to water flow in the 
      intercooler. 
      ACLT_intclr_Q Estimated heat rejection to the intercooler. 
      ACLT_intclr_Qff Requested heat rejection to the intercooler, used for the 
      feedforward control term. 
      ACLT_intclr_Qmax Maximum possible heat rejection from the intercooler. 
      ACLT_intclr_Q_dT_max Intercooler heat transfer per degree of coolant 
      thermal margin 
      ACLT_intTlim_Amin Absolute minimum intercooler coolant flow. 
      ACLT_intTlim_crct Flow correction factor for calculating the intercooler 
      coolant flow required to limit outlet temperature. 
      ACLT_intTlim_crctdcy Minimum intercooler coolant flow correction factor 
      decay rate 
      ACLT_intTlim_crctini Initial minimum intercooler coolant flow correction 
      factor 
      ACLT_intTlim_crctmin Minimum intercooler coolant flow correction factor. 
      ACLT_intTlim_crct_Kp Kp gain for the intercooler coolant flow correction. 
      The gain is applied to the flow correction after each excursion above the 
      maximum outlet temperature, based on the final integral value. 
      ACLT_intTlim_I_accum Intercooler coolant over-temperature flow correction 
      integral. 
      ACLT_intTlim_I_decay Intercooler coolant over-temperature flow correction 
      integral decay rate. 
      ACLT_intTlim_Ki Ki gain for correcting intercooler coolant outlet 
      temperature when it exceeds the maximum temperature. 
      ACLT_intTlim_Kp Kp gain for correcting intercooler coolant outlet 
      temperature when it exceeds the maximum temperature. 
      ACLT_intTlim_maxLmin Maximum allowed flow rate to the intercooler for 
      coolant outlet temperature limiting. 
      ACLT_intTlim_minLmin Intercooler coolant flow required to prevent the 
      intercooler coolant outlet temperature from exceeding the maximum 
      temperature. 
      ACLT_intTlim_OOA_dT Specifies how many degrees above the "Projected outlet 
      temperature limit" (EGRAux page) the intercooler projected outlet 
      temperature must exceed to latch the "Intercooler temperature limiting out 
      of authority" diagnostic. 
      ACLT_intTlim_pctmax Maximum flow authority for intercooler coolant outlet 
      temperature limiting as a percentage of the maximum potential flow to the 
      intercooler when the intercooler/EGR cooler split valve is closed. 
      ACLT_intTlim_trst_th Threshold of heat transfer per thermal margin for 
      increasing confidence in the flow correction factor. 
      ACLT_intTlim_trust Confidence that the flow correction factor can be 
      reduced. At 100%, the flow correction factor decreases by the calibrated 
      rate, and the confidence resets to 0%. 
      ACLT_intTlim_trust_d Time for the flow correction confidence to decrease 
      to 0%. Confidence decreases when the heat transfer per thermal margin is 
      below the threshold. 
      ACLT_intTlim_trust_i Time for the flow correction confidence to increase 
      to 100%. Confidence increases when the heat transfer per thermal margin is 
      above the threshold. 
      ACLT_intTlim_T_max Maximum intercooler coolant outlet temperature. 
      ACLT_pump_Lmin Coolant flow through the auxiliary cooling loop. 
      ACLT_pump_max_Lmin Effective coolant flow through the auxiliary cooling 
      loop, limited by flow restrictions in the intercooler and EGR cooler. 
      ACLT_radby_dT_halt If the actual temperature is within +/- this amount of 
      the target temperature, the valve command is frozen until the temperature 
      error exceeds the 'resume' deadzone below. 
      ACLT_radby_dT_res If control updates are halted and the difference between 
      the actual and target temperatures exceed this amount (+ or -), control 
      updates will resume. 
      ACLT_radby_ena Auxiliary coolant control radiator bypass output channel. 
      ACLT_radby_I_accum Auxiliary coolant control radiator bypass integral 
      accumulator. 
      ACLT_radby_Ki Auxiliary coolant control radiator bypass CL Ki gain. 
      ACLT_radby_Kp Auxiliary coolant control radiator bypass CL Kp gain. 
      ACLT_radby_Lmin_CL Auxiliary coolant control radiator bypass total 
      closed-loop correction. 
      ACLT_radby_T_cmd Auxiliary coolant control radiator bypass temperature 
      target. 
      ACLT_radby_T_error Auxiliary coolant control radiator bypass temperature 
      error. 
      ACLT_radby_vlv_act Auxiliary coolant control radiator bypass valve actual 
      position. 
      ACLT_radby_vlv_cmd Auxiliary coolant control radiator bypass valve 
      command. 
      ACLT_radby_vlv_def This position is commanded to the radiator bypass valve 
      prior to engine shutdown. It is mainly used to guarantee valve and 
      auxiliary coolant operation following a cold shutdown, where the valves 
      could potentially freeze shut.

      0% = no bypass (full radiator flow)
      100% = full radiator bypass 
      ACLT_radby_vlv_halt Indicates the radiator bypass valve control is halted 
      due to a temperature error within the calibrated deadzone. 
      ACLT_radby_vlv_max Maximum radiator bypass valve position. 
      ACLT_radby_vlv_min Minimum radiator bypass valve position. 
      ACLT_rad_Lmin Total control radiator volumetric flow rate. 
      ACLT_rad_Lmin_ff Feedforward control radiator volumetric flow rate. 
      ACSB_APSdelta Delta voltage from the current min PS value to initiate 
      closed-stop braking. PS values above this delta will not cause any braking 
      action under any condition. 
      ACSB_ena H-Bridge A Closed Stop Braking (CSB) Elimination enable switch 
      ACSB_Kd This value is multiplied by the difference between the actual 
      dPS/dt and the limit values defined by the min/max PS PSdt parameters and 
      the current PS (from min to min+delta). For example, if the current dPS/dt 
      = -200 %/s, the actuator is about to impact the closed-stop, and the min 
      PS PSdt parameter is -100 %/s, then for a Kd value of 1.0 %/%*sec, the 
      contribution to the braking force will be +100%. 
      ACSB_max_APSdt dPS/dt value at the max PS (full-closed plus closed-stop PS 
      delta) position above which no braking action will occur. This must be a 
      value strictly < 0 and should be more negative than the min PS PSdt value. 

      ACSB_min_APSdt dPS/dt value at the min PS (full-closed) position above 
      which no braking action will occur. This must be a value strictly < 0. 
      ACT Auxiliary coolant temperature (ACT). 
      active_FPP_mode Current FPP mode. This is either FPP_mode or FPP2_mode 
      depending on FPPdual_pedal and the status of the BRAKE input 
      active_fuel_device Current fuel device (Injection, EPR, CFV, PWM) 
      active_fuel_loc Current active fuel device location 
      ACT_ena Auxiliary coolant temperature (ACT) channel. 
      ACT_hi_RPMmin Minimum engine speed fault condition for the "ACT 
      temperature high" diagnostic 
      ACT_hi_Tmax Auxiliary coolant temperature threshold fault condition for 
      the "ACT temperature high" diagnostic 
      ACT_hi_wait Minimum engine run time fault condition for the "ACT 
      temperature high" diagnostic 
      ACT_Taux_cal Auxiliary coolant temperature (ACT) temperature calibration 
      table. 
      ACT_vdr Auxiliary coolant temperature (ACT) pullup resistor value. 
      AC_ctl_chan AC clutch relay output channel AUX_PWM 
      AC_ctl_max_RPM Max RPM for AC clutch relay to be ON 
      AC_ctl_min_ECT Min ECT for AC clutch relay to be ON 
      AC_ctl_min_RPM Min RPM for AC clutch relay to be ON 
      AC_ctl_mode Determines if Boost TEI events should temporarily disable the 
      AC clutch relay output 
      AC_ctl_mode_t AC remains off for this minimum amount 
      AC_ctl_state AC current state of the clutch relay output PWM 
      AC_hi_pres_cfg A/C high pressure switch Aux DIG input configuration. 
      AC_hi_pres_chan Input channel for the A/C high pressure switch. 
      AC_idle_rpm AC ON elevates idle to this RPM 
      AC_sw_chan AC request switch input channel.
      When configured as 'CAN - PGN 65284', then the switch input is obtained 
      from SPN 64927 in ECI PGN 65284, 42303, or 42284.
      When configured as 'CAN - PGN 65295', then the switch input is obtained 
      from SPN 64795 in ECI PGN 65295, 42304, or 42305. 
      AC_sw_chan_cfg If an Aux DIG is selected for the input, this value 
      determines the active logic state(s). The Default values are:
      Aux DIG1 = Gnd
      Aux DIG2 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG3 = Gnd
      Aux DIG4 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG5 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG6 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG7 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG8 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG9 = Gnd
      Aux DIG10 = Gnd
      Aux DIG11 = Gnd
      Aux DIG12 = Gnd
      Aux DIG13 = Gnd
      Aux DIG14 = Gnd
      Aux DIG15 = Gnd
      Aux DIG16 = Gnd
      Aux DIG17 = Gnd
      Aux DIG18 = Gnd
      Aux DIG19 = Gnd
      Gov1 = Gnd
      Gov2 = Gnd 
      AC_sw_stat AC request switch input status (0=Inactive, 1=Active, 
      2=Error/Fault, 3=Not Configured). 
      Adapt1_valid_cnt Valid adaptive counts (Bank 1) 
      Adapt2_valid_cnt Valid adaptive counts (Gasoline Bank 2) 
      AdaptMAP 2D interpolation table MAP (X-axis) input values 
      AdaptMAPNG 2D interpolation table MAP (NG engines) (X-axis) input values 
      AdaptMAPP 2D interpolation table MAP (LP engines) (X-axis) input values 
      AdaptRPM 2D interpolation table rpm (y-axis) input values 
      AdaptRPMNG 2D interpolation table rpm (NG engines) (y-axis) input values 
      AdaptRPMP 2D interpolation table rpm (LPG engines) (y-axis) input values 
      AdaptTbl1 2D Interpolation Table: Gasoline Adaptive Learn Bank 1 
      AdaptTbl2 2D Interpolation Table: Gasoline Adaptive Learn Bank 2 
      AdaptTblNG 2D Interpolation Table: NG Adaptive Learn 
      AdaptTblP 2D Interpolation Table: LPG Adaptive Learn 
      Adapt_dzone Gasoline: Adaptive Learn Dead Zone Limit 
      adapt_ena If 'Enabled', normal 'Adaptive Learn' mode is entered when the 
      proper conditions exist. If 'Disabled', 'Adaptive Learn' mode will never 
      be switched on under any circumstances (although 'Closed Loop' mode 
      functions normally). This feature is typically used for stationary engine 
      applications. 
      adapt_fuel_rpm_dz Adaptive learn table updates will be disabled when a 
      discrete governor is active, Adapt RPM Source is set to "Desired RPM", and 
      the difference between the actual RPM and the desired RPM is greater than 
      this threshold. 
      adapt_fuel_rpm_src This variable determines the fuel adaptive learn table 
      lookup RPM source.

      If "Actual RPM" is selected or a discrete governor is not active, then the 
      current RPM of the engine is used for the fuel adaptive table lookup.

      If "Desired RPM" is selected and the discrete governor is active, then the 
      desired RPM value is used to perform the fuel adaptive table lookups. 
      Adapt_neg_lim Gasoline: Adaptive Learn BM minimum (negative) allowed 
      Adapt_pos_lim Gasoline: Adaptive Learn BM maximum (positive) allowed 
      Adapt_start_wait Time from start until adaptive mode is enabled. This 
      value must be longer than 'EGO start wait'. 
      Adapt_stepmax Gasoline: Adaptive Learn Step Maximum 
      adapt_store_EE This switch determines whether the adaptive learn tables 
      (gasoline, LPG, and NG) are retained in battery supported memory or 
      permanent memory.

      In battery supported memory, the adaptive tables will be cleared if the 
      battery power is removed from the ECM.

      In permanent memory, a key-on reset sequence must be performed to clear 
      the tables. 
      Adapt_valid +/- error tolerance of actual versus commanded equivalence 
      ratio before allowing adaptive updates. This tolerance must be held for 
      Adapt_valid_cycles before actual updates will begin. 
      Adapt_wait Number of valid (determined by Adapt_valid) closed loop update 
      cycles required before allowing adaptive updates. 
      ADDRCLAIM2_cnt Address claiming activity (counts) - CAN channel 2 
      ADDRCLAIM3_cnt Address claiming activity (counts) - CAN channel 3 
      ADDRCLAIM_cnt Address claiming activity (counts) - CAN channel 1 
      ADIG10_max AUX digital 10 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG10_min AUX digital 10 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG11_max AUX digital 11 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG11_min AUX digital 11 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG12_max AUX digital 12 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG12_min AUX digital 12 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG13_max AUX digital 13 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG13_min AUX digital 13 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG14_max AUX digital 14 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG14_min AUX digital 14 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG15_max AUX digital 15 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG15_min AUX digital 15 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG16_max AUX digital 16 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG16_min AUX digital 16 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG17_max AUX digital 17 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG17_min AUX digital 17 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG18_max AUX digital 18 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG18_min AUX digital 18 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG19_max AUX digital 19 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG19_min AUX digital 19 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG1_max AUX digital 1 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 
      ADIG1_min AUX digital 1 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG20_max AUX digital 20 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG20_min AUX digital 20 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG21_max AUX digital 21 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG21_min AUX digital 21 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG22_max AUX digital 22 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG22_min AUX digital 22 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG23_max AUX digital 23 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG23_min AUX digital 23 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG24_max AUX digital 24 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG24_min AUX digital 24 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG25_max AUX digital 25 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 

      ADIG25_min AUX digital 25 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG2_max AUX digital 2 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 
      ADIG2_min AUX digital 2 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG3_max AUX digital 3 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 
      ADIG3_min AUX digital 3 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG4_max AUX digital 4 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 
      ADIG4_min AUX digital 4 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG5_max AUX digital 5 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 
      ADIG5_min AUX digital 5 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG6_max AUX digital 6 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 
      ADIG6_min AUX digital 6 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG7_max AUX digital 7 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 
      ADIG7_min AUX digital 7 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG8_max AUX digital 8 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 
      ADIG8_min AUX digital 8 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      ADIG9_max AUX digital 9 high voltage fault - max voltage entry condition 
      ADIG9_min AUX digital 9 low voltage fault - min voltage entry condition 
      AEM_hard_Ilim Actuator hardware current limit - HBA 
      AEM_I Estimated current - HBA 
      AEM_Kv Actuator Kv constant - HBA 
      AEM_L Actuator loop L - HBA 
      AEM_R Actuator loop R - HBA 
      AEM_V_diode Actuator voltage supply diode - HBA 
      AFBdt H-Bridge A (HBA) position sensor feedback derivative term 
      AFBdt_n PSdt calculation PS linear least-squares window. More points 
      yields a quieter and more accurate derivative, but introduces more time 
      lag. Fewer points has the opposite effect. 
      AFBdt_xLP Post interpolation low-pass filter constant for PSdt. 
      AFILTdP Air filter final filtered delta-P 
      AFILTdP_cyl_events Enter the number of cylinder events to use for AFILTdP 
      measurement windowing. Lower values result in faster sensor response, 
      higher values minimize the engine-related pulsations. Set this value to 
      0.0 to disable cylinder event based windowing. Otherwise, this value must 
      be >= 1 if cylinder and the max window is limited to 2ms.
      NOTE: This option requires hardware support and is not supported on all 
      input channels. 
      AFILTdP_Dz This is the cutoff for the cubic deadzone on the air filter 
      delta-P sensor, applied prior to low-pass filtering. If the difference 
      between the instantaneous dP and low-passed dP reading is below this 
      value, the error is reduced via a cubic deadzone before being applied to 
      the low-passed dP. 
      AFILTdP_ena Air filter delta pressure sensor input channel 
      AFILTdP_inst Air filter raw delta-P 
      AFILTdP_Paux_cal Air filter delta-P sensor transfer function 
      AFILTdP_tau This is the low-pass time constant applied to the air filter 
      delta-P low-pass/cubic deadzone filter. 
      AFILT_dP_C Air Filter Model: AF flow rate delta P scaling 
      AFILT_dP_chan Selects the digital input channel used for an air filter 
      differential pressure sensor. 
      AFILT_dP_chan_cfg If an Aux DIG is selected for the input, this value 
      determines the active logic state(s). An active state for this input 
      indicates that the differential pressure across the air filter is high. 
      The Default values are:

      Aux DIG1 = Gnd
      Aux DIG2 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG3 = Gnd
      Aux DIG4 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG5 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG6 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG7 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG8 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG9 = Gnd
      Aux DIG10 = Gnd
      Aux DIG11 = Gnd
      Aux DIG12 = Gnd
      Aux DIG13 = Gnd
      Aux DIG14 = Gnd
      Aux DIG15 = Gnd
      Aux DIG16 = Gnd
      Aux DIG17 = Gnd
      Aux DIG18 = Gnd
      Aux DIG19 = Gnd
      Gov1 = Gnd
      Gov2 = Gnd 
      afs_crkdly_cycs If the ECT is between the upper and lower (exclusive) 
      thresholds above, the fuel and/or spark will be inhibited (delayed) for 
      this number of engine cycles during starting on alternate-fuels (LPG and 
      NG). Note that this is engine CYCLES - NOT revolutions. Therefore, for a 
      4-stroke engine, 1.50 cycles is 3 revolutions. 
      afs_crkdly_ECT This value sets the upper bound of the ECT range over which 
      the fuel and/or spark will be inhibited for a defined number of engine 
      cycles during starting on alternate-fuels (LPG and NG). 
      afs_crkdly_ECTlo This value sets the lower bound of the ECT range over 
      which the fuel and/or spark will be inhibited for a defined number of 
      engine cycles during starting on alternate-fuels (LPG and NG). 
      afs_crkdly_fs This feature allows an ECT range to be specified over which 
      the fuel and/or spark will be inhibited for a defined number of engine 
      cycles during starting on alternate-fuels (LPG and NG). 
      AFT_dewpt_CL1pre Tx Bank 1 pre dew point indication 
      AFT_dewpt_CL1pst Tx Bank 1 post dew point 
      AFT_dewpt_CL2pre Tx Bank 2 pre dew point indication 
      AFT_dewpt_CL2pst Tx Bank 2 post dew point 
      AF_UEGO Calculated Air/Fuel Ratio (UEGO1 sensor) 
      AF_UEGO2 Calculated Air/Fuel Ratio (UEGO2 sensor) 
      AF_UEGO3 Calculated Air/Fuel Ratio (UEGO3 sensor) 
      AF_UEGO4 Calculated Air/Fuel Ratio (UEGO4 sensor) 
      AGS_req1 Current position of grille #1. 
      ALfltG_MAPmax Gasoline: Adaptive Learn Fault maximum MAP boundary 
      ALfltG_MAPmin Gasoline: Adaptive Learn Fault minimum MAP boundary 
      ALfltG_RPMmax Gasoline: Adaptive Learn Fault maximum RPM boundary 
      ALfltG_RPMmin Gasoline: Adaptive Learn Fault minimum RPM boundary 
      ALfltN_MAPmax NG: Adaptive Learn Fault maximum MAP boundary 
      ALfltN_MAPmin NG: Adaptive Learn Fault minimum MAP boundary 
      ALfltN_RPMmax NG: Adaptive Learn Fault maximum RPM boundary 
      ALfltN_RPMmin NG: Adaptive Learn Fault minimum RPM boundary 
      ALfltP_MAPmax LPG: Adaptive Learn Fault maximum MAP boundary 
      ALfltP_MAPmin LPG: Adaptive Learn Fault minimum MAP boundary 
      ALfltP_RPMmax LPG: Adaptive Learn Fault maximum RPM boundary 
      ALfltP_RPMmin LPG: Adaptive Learn Fault minimum RPM boundary 
      ALLP_dzone LPG: Adaptive Learn Dead Zone Limit 
      ALLP_hi LPG: Adaptive Learn BM maximum (positive) allowed 
      ALLP_K LPG: Adaptive Learn Gain 
      ALLP_lo LPG: Adaptive Learn BM minimum (negative) allowed 
      ALLP_stepmax LPG: Adaptive Learn Step Maximum 
      ALLP_valid +/- error tolerance of actual versus commanded equivalence 
      ratio before allowing adaptive updates. This tolerance must be held for 
      Adapt_valid_cycles before actual updates will begin. 
      ALLP_wait Number of valid (determined by Adapt_valid) closed loop update 
      cycles required before allowing adaptive updates. 
      allspeed_rpm Final FPP engine speed command applicable when configured for 
      all-speed control mode. May be different from FPP allspeed rpm after 
      applying additional limits. 
      ALNG_dzone NG: Adaptive Learn Dead Zone Limit 
      ALNG_hi NG: Adaptive Learn BM maximum (positive) allowed 
      ALNG_K NG: Adaptive Learn Gain 
      ALNG_lo NG: Adaptive Learn BM minimum (negative) allowed 
      ALNG_stepmax NG: Adaptive Learn Step Maximum 
      ALNG_valid +/- error tolerance of actual versus commanded equivalence 
      ratio before allowing adaptive updates. This tolerance must be held for 
      Adapt_valid_cycles before actual updates will begin. 
      ALNG_wait Number of valid (determined by Adapt_valid) closed loop update 
      cycles required before allowing adaptive updates. 
      alphaN_ena This switch computes an alpha-N based MAP estimate using TPS, 
      RPM, and BP and may additionally enable utilizing that estimate as the MAP 
      source based on NG base phi and post-cat phi table values used in a unique 
      way. 
      alphaN_interp Alpha-N MAP estimation strategy 4-D table interpolation % 
      (100% = base table, 0% = post-cat table) 
      alphaN_MAPf Alpha-N MAP estimation strategy MAP estimate 
      alternator_chg_V Voltage threshold to indicate alternator is charging when 
      the alternator monitor input is used to monitor a charge indication 
      signal. When the input voltage is higher than this value, the J1939 
      alternator status is reported as "charging". 
      alt_coilkill_ena The coil kill diagnostic feature can be enabled/disabled 
      using this control in alternate fuel modes. 
      AL_erase_req Clear adaptive memory command button 
      AL_hi Currently active Adaptive Learn upper limit (gasoline only) 
      AL_lo Currently active Adaptive Learn upper limit (gasoline only) 
      AL_nonzero Adaptive Learn state - confirmation indicator for the "Clear 
      Adaptive" button 
      AL_temp_wait_mul Multiple of T_delay to wait after a transient/FSO before 
      re-enabling adaptive-learn. 
      AL_temp_wait_tmr temporary wait time before re-implementing adaptive-learn 
      in ms 
      AMTSA_dec_torq_est Parameter adjusts the broadcasted actual engine torque 
      (SPN 513) during the decreasing TSC1 torque limit at the beginning of an 
      AMT upshift. When set to 0%, the broadcasted engine torque is not modified 
      and is equal to the estimated engine torque. When parameter is set to 
      100%, the broadcasted engine torque is modified and is set equal to the 
      desired engine torque (typically equal to the AMT's requested torque 
      limit). When parameter is between 0% and 100%, then the broadcasted torque 
      is interpolated. This parameter is only applicable when "AMT shift assist" 
      is not set to 'Disabled' and the AMT sends TSC1 torque limits during 
      upshifts. 
      AMTSA_down_dis_FSO When set to 'Enabled', parameter temporarily disables 
      fuel shutoff when a downshift is pending/in progress. 
      AMTSA_ena Parameter enables the AMT shift assistance feature (AMTSA). When 
      set to 'Enabled', shift assistance detects AMT upshift events and provides 
      various system modifications to improve the smoothness of the shift. 
      Currently, only AMTs that send TSC1 torque limit requests during an 
      upshift are supported. The upshift should start with a torque limit to 
      reduce the engine torque, followed by a speed request to synchronize the 
      engine speed, and finally another torque limit to increase engine torque. 
      The actual and desired gears (SPNs 523 and 524 in ETC2, ECI PGN 61572) are 
      used to determine if the shift is an upshift. The 'AMT selection' must be 
      enabled. The source address of the AMT is determined by 'AMT selection'. 
      AMTSA_loadlim Current load limit for AMT shift assistance. 
      AMTSA_loadlim_ena Enables load limiting for AMT shift assistance. 
      AMTSA_loadlim_gear Transmission gear used for calculating the load limit 
      for AMT shift assistance. 
      AMTSA_minnom AMT shift assist's EGR min/nom fraction request. 
      AMTSA_minnom_ena Parameter enables EGR min/nom fraction limiting during an 
      AMT upshift. When parameter is set to 'Enabled', the EGR min/nom fraction 
      is limited to the gear-based "Min/Nom Target" value in the "AMT Upshift 
      Assist Decreasing Torque" table during the decreasing TSC1 torque limit. 
      The EGR min/nom fraction is slewed to the target over the "AMT shift 
      assist EGR min/nom slew time". Parameter is only applicable when "AMT 
      shift assist" is not set to 'Disabled'. 
      AMTSA_minnom_time Configures the amount of time to slew the EGR min/nom 
      fraction to the AMT shift assist target during an AMT upshift. Only 
      applicable when "AMT shift assist EGR min/nom" is set to 'Enabled'. 
      AMTSA_state AMT shift assist state:
      0 = 'Disabled' - feature disabled (AMTSA_ena or AMT_select disabled)
      1 = 'Gear Not Available' - gear data not available or gear unknown
      2 = 'Gear Data Error' - gear data in error
      3 = 'Engine Stopped' - engine is not running or key is off
      4 = 'Park or Neutral' - actively (or desired to be) in park or neutral
      5 = 'Inactive' - waiting for upshift
      6 = 'Verifying Shift' - received torque limit, waiting up to 120ms for 
      desired gear to change
      7 = 'Verifying Shift Wait' - shift verification failed, wait for gear to 
      change or torque limit to decrease
      8 = 'Upshift - Decreasing Torque' - upshift in progress, AMT is decreasing 
      engine torque
      9 = 'Upshift - Speed Sync Wait' - upshift in progress, waiting for AMT to 
      synchronize engine speed
      10 = 'Upshift - Syncing Speed' - upshift in progress, AMT is synchronizing 
      engine speed
      11 = 'Upshift - Torque Increase Wait' - upshift in progress, waiting for 
      AMT to increase engine torque
      12 = 'Upshift - Increasing Torque' - upshift in progress, AMT is 
      increasing engine torque
      13 = 'Launch - Decreasing Torque' - launch in progress, AMT is decreasing 
      engine torque
      14 = 'Launch - Syncing Speed' - launch in progress, AMT is synchronizing 
      engine speed
      15 = 'Launch - Increasing Torque' - launch in progress, AMT is increasing 
      engine torque
      16 = 'Downshift - Decreasing Torque' - downshift in progress, AMT is 
      decreasing engine torque
      17 = 'Downshift - Syncing Speed' - downshift in progress, AMT is 
      synchronizing engine speed
      18 = 'Downshift - Increasing Torque' - downshift in progress, AMT is 
      increasing engine torque 
      AMTSA_TPSd_filt_ena Enables TPS command filtering during an AMT upshift. 
      When set to 'Decrease Only', the TPS command (TPS_cmd_pct) is filtered at 
      the beginning of an upshift when the AMT sends a TSC1 torque limit to 
      decrease the engine torque. The filter's tau is equal to the gear-based 
      "TPSd Filter Tau" value in the "AMT Upshift Assist Decreasing Torque" 
      table. The duration of the filtering is limited to the gear-based "TPSd 
      Filter Max Time" table value.

      When set to 'Increase Only', TPS command filtering only occurs during the 
      increasing TSC1 torque limit at the end of an upshift. The filter's tau 
      and max time are determined by the gear-based values in the "AMT Upshift 
      Assist Increasing Torque" table.

      When set to 'Both', then TPS command filtering occurs during decreasing 
      and increasing torque limits.

      This parameter is only applicable when "AMT shift assist" is not set to 
      'Disabled' and the AMT sends TSC1 torque limits during upshifts. 
      AMTSA_WGPd_ena Parameter enables wastegate pressure limiting during an AMT 
      upshift. When parameter is set to 'Enabled', the wastegate pressure is 
      limited to the gear-based "WGPd Max" value in the "AMT Upshift Assist 
      Increasing Torque" table during the increasing TSC1 torque limit. The 
      limit is applied to bst_WGPdi which is the wastegate actuator desired 
      pressure from the TIP control loop. Parameter is only applicable when "AMT 
      shift assist" is not set to 'Disabled'. 
      AMT_Gov3_acc_init Some AMT's use TSC1 for the shift process. Following a 
      TSC1 load limit to no-load, a brief TSC1 full authority speed control 
      target is sent to synchronize the engine and transmission.

      When transitioning to Gov3 speed control with a TSC1 speed request from 
      the source address specified by "AMT selection", the Gov3 integrator will 
      be reset to this value to prevent unwanted load spikes due to stored 
      history in the integral accumulator. Set to -1 to disable. Typical values 
      are 1-10%.

      Parameter only applicable when "AMT selection" is not 'Disabled'. 
      AMT_Gov3_acc_maxload Maximum engine load for the Gov3 integrator reset 
      described by parameter "AMT TSC1 Gov3 initial integrator". This is 
      intended to prevent unpredictable governor behavior and only allow 
      integrator resetting at low load operation. Parameter only applicable when 
      "AMT selection" is not 'Disabled'. 
      AMT_Gov3_gain_down Parameter determines the Gov3 gain selection to use 
      during the speed synchronization phase of an AMT downshift. When set to 
      'Default', Gov3 gains are determined based on the "Governor gain 
      selection" on the Governor worksheet as well as the "'Remote speed request 
      throttle gov parameters" on the Comms worksheet. Otherwise, the Gov3 gains 
      are overridden with this parameter's calibrated gain set when the AMT 
      sends a TSC1 speed control request during a downshift. A downshift is 
      detected using SPN 574 in ETC1 and SPNs 523 and 524 in ETC2. Gov3 gains 
      will only be overridden if the specified SPNs are received and valid. 
      AMT_Gov3_gain_lnch Parameter determines the Gov3 gain selection to use 
      during an AMT vehicle launch. When set to 'Default', Gov3 gains are 
      determined based on the "Governor gain selection" on the Governor 
      worksheet as well as the "'Remote speed request throttle gov parameters" 
      on the Comms worksheet. Otherwise, the Gov3 gains are overridden with this 
      parameter's calibrated gain set when the AMT sends a TSC1 speed control 
      request during a launch. A launch is detected using SPN 574 in ETC1 and 
      SPNs 523 and 524 in ETC2. Gov3 gains will only be overridden if the 
      specified SPNs are received and valid. 
      AMT_Gov3_gain_up Parameter determines the Gov3 gain selection to use 
      during the speed synchronization phase of an AMT upshift. When set to 
      'Default', Gov3 gains are determined based on the "Governor gain 
      selection" on the Governor worksheet as well as the "'Remote speed request 
      throttle gov parameters" on the Comms worksheet. Otherwise, the Gov3 gains 
      are overridden with this parameter's calibrated gain set when the AMT 
      sends a TSC1 speed control request during an upshift. An upshift is 
      detected using SPN 574 in ETC1 and SPNs 523 and 524 in ETC2. Gov3 gains 
      will only be overridden if the specified SPNs are received and valid. 
      AMT_input_speed ETC1 transmission input shaft speed 
      AMT_neut_coast_CCVS Parameter configures the broadcasted CCVS message 
      values whenever cruise control is suspended by the clutch. When "AMT 
      neutral coasting" is enabled, cruise control is temporarily suspended 
      while the clutch pedal is depressed. When clutch is released, cruise 
      control will automatically resume. This parameter configures the CCVS 
      status while cruise control is suspended. When parameter is set to 
      'Inactive (Default)', then the following SPNs values are broadcasted while 
      cruise control is suspended by the clutch:
      SPN 527 (cruise control state) = 0 (off/disabled)
      SPN 595 (cruise control active) = 0 (inactive)
      SPN 596 (cruise control enable switch) = 1 (enabled)
      SPN 86 (cruise control set speed) = maximum roadspeed limit
      When clutch is released, the roadspeed setpoint will initialize to the 
      current roadspeed and slew up to the setpoint prior to suspension (typical 
      resume behavior).

      When parameter is set to 'Active and Holding', then the following SPNs 
      values are broadcasted while cruise control is suspended by the clutch:
      SPN 527 (cruise control state) = 1 (holding)
      SPN 595 (cruise control active) = 1 (active)
      SPN 596 (cruise control enable switch) = 1 (enabled)
      SPN 86 (cruise control set speed) = roadspeed setpoint before cruise 
      control was suspended
      When clutch is released, the roadspeed setpoint will remain unchanged. 
      AMT_neut_coast_mode Enables neutral coasting with the WABCO AMT. Cruise 
      control will not be disengaged when the transmission is in neutral while 
      the operator has selected a gear, and cruise control can be temporarily 
      suspended while the clutch pedal is depressed. 
      AMT_output_speed ETC1 transmission output shaft speed 
      AMT_RSC_suspend Indicates WABCO AMT Suspend Cruise status. AMT neutral 
      coasting must be set to "WABCO" to use this feature. 
      AMT_select Parameter configures the AMT's source address. Application 
      specific AMT parameters are utilized when TSC1 requests with the specified 
      source address are received. 
      AMT_shift_in_process ECT1 transmission shift in process indicator 
      AMT_speed_purpose The purpose for an AMT TSC1 speed control request:
      0 = 'Inactive'
      1 = 'Active - Exit Neutral'
      2 = 'Active - Launch'
      3 = 'Active - Upshift'
      4 = 'Active - Downshift'
      5 = 'Active - Unknown' 
      AMT_torq_lmt Received AMT TSC1 torque limit. AMT source address determined 
      based on 'AMT selection' parameter. 
      AOSB_APSdelta Delta voltage from the current min PS value to initiate 
      open-stop braking. PS values below this delta will not cause any braking 
      action under any condition. 
      AOSB_ena H-Bridge A Output device Open Stop Braking (OSB) Elimination 
      enable switch 
      AOSB_Kd This value is multiplied by the difference between the actual 
      dPS/dt and the limit values defined by the min/max PS PSdt parameters and 
      the current PS (from max to max-delta). For example, if the current dPS/dt 
      = +200 %/s, the actuator is about to impact the open-stop, and the min PS 
      PSdt parameter is +100 %/s, then for a Kd value of 1.0 %/%*sec, the 
      contribution to the braking force will be -100%. 
      AOSB_max_APSdt dPS/dt value at the min PS (full-open minus open-stop PS 
      delta) position below which no braking action will occur. This must be a 
      value strictly > 0 and should be more positive than the min PS PSdt value. 

      AOSB_min_APSdt dPS/dt value at the max PS (full-open) position below which 
      no braking action will occur. This must be a value strictly > 0. 
      APD1_max "AUX analog Pull-Down 1 high voltage" Fault's Aux PD max 
      threshold. Note: this value is ignored if channel is being used for oil 
      quality sensing. 
      APD1_min AUX analog Pull-Down 1 low voltage fault - Aux PD min threshold 
      APD2_max "AUX analog Pull-Down 2 high voltage" fault - Aux PD max 
      threshold 
      APD2_min "AUX analog Pull-Down 2 low voltage" fault - Aux PD min threshold 

      APD3_max "AUX analog Pull-Down 3 high voltage" fault - Aux PD max 
      threshold 
      APD3_min "AUX analog Pull-Down 3 low voltage" fault - Aux PD min threshold 

      APS12ctl_choice HBridge A In the case of a TPS1/TPS2 mismatch, this switch 
      designates which TPS input is to be utilized 
      APS12pct_hi HBA - APS1 higher than APS2 fault entry condition threshold 
      percentage 
      APS12pct_lo HBA - APS1 lower than APS2 fault entry condition threshold 
      percentage 
      APS1_def HBA - PS1 sensor voltage corresponding to non-controlled 
      (limp-home) position 
      APS1_full HBA - position sensor 1 full open voltage 
      APS1_full_def HBA - Voltage corresponding to throttle plate at open stop 
      APS1_full_init HBA - Limit voltage calculated from PS1 full default 
      (indicates a theoretical position from open stop in the closed direction) 
      APS1_idle HBA - position sensor 1 idle voltage 
      APS1_idle_def HBA - Voltage corresponding to throttle plate at closed stop 

      APS1_idle_init HBA - Limit voltage calculated from PS1 idle default 
      (indicates a theoretical position from closed stop in the open direction) 
      APS1_learn_tau HBA - Time constant used to learn the idle or full voltages 
      for the PS1 sensor. 
      APS1_learn_wait HBA - The wait time before the controller begins to learn 
      the idle or full voltages for the PS1 sensor. 
      APS1_max HBA - APS1 high voltage fault max voltage entry condition 
      APS1_min HBA - APS1 low voltage fault min voltage entry condition 
      APS1_pct HBA - position sensor 1 percent 
      APS1_rawfilt HBA - Position Sensor 1 feedback (filtered) 
      APS1_source HBridge A Throttle Position Source 1 Input 
      APS2ctl_allow HBridge A When dual pot TPS is utilized, this switch allows 
      the use of TPS2 if a TPS1 voltage out of range condition (FAULT) occurs 
      APS2_angle_at_full HBA - Used for throttles that have a PS2 feedback that 
      reaches full voltage before 100% opening 
      APS2_def HBA - PS2 sensor voltage corresponding to non-controlled 
      (limp-home) position 
      APS2_full HBA - position sensor 2 full open voltage 
      APS2_full_init HBA - Limit voltage calculated from PS2 full default 
      (indicates a theoretical position from open stop in the closed direction) 
      APS2_idle HBA - position sensor 2 idle voltage 
      APS2_idle_init HBA - Limit voltage calculated from PS2 idle default 
      (indicates a theoretical position from closed stop in the open direction) 
      APS2_learn_tau HBA - Time constant used to learn the idle or full voltages 
      for the PS2 sensor. 
      APS2_learn_wait HBA - The wait time before the controller begins to learn 
      the idle or full voltages for the PS2 sensor. 
      APS2_max HBA - APS2 high voltage fault max voltage entry condition 
      APS2_min HBA - APS2 low voltage fault min voltage entry condition 
      APS2_pct HBA - position sensor 2 percent 
      APS2_rawfilt HBA - Position Sensor 2 feedback (filtered) 
      APS2_source HBridge A Throttle Position Source 2 Input 
      APSdualpot_ena HBridge A Switch: Enables the use of dual (redundant) 
      position feedback control 
      APSerr_maxVbat Obsoleted parameter 
      APSerr_minVbat HBA - minimum battery voltage entry condition for Unable to 
      reach higher/lower APS faults. 
      APSerr_neg HBA - Unable to reach lower APS fault target-actual percentage 
      threshold. Exceeding this threshold for the duration, battery voltage and 
      run mode entry conditions sets the fault. 
      APSerr_pos HBA - Unable to reach higher APS fault target-actual percentage 
      threshold. Exceeding this threshold for the duration, battery voltage and 
      run mode entry conditions sets the fault. 
      APSerr_run_mode HBA - run mode entry condition for Unable to reach 
      higher/lower APS faults. This parameter should be set to stopped or 
      cranking for systems where an unable-to-reach position error will prevent 
      the engine from reaching an underspeed/running status. 
      APSerr_wait HBA - minimum duration entry condition for Unable to reach 
      higher/lower APS faults. 
      APSraw_LP High-speed anti-aliasing low-pass time constant for the raw PS 
      feedback voltage. 
      APS_cmd_AD HBA Throttle position command (volts) 
      APS_cmd_pct HBA Throttle position command (%) 
      APS_EE_store HBA EEPROM restore enable switch. If enabled, the idle/full 
      offsets will be stored in EEPROM and restored on power-on. 
      APS_learn_EE_ofst PS learn EEPROM offset. This value specifies a small 
      offset that is applied to the learn value prior to storing a successful 
      learn in EEPROM. Using a non-zero value here prevents the EEPROM value 
      from being the absolute min/max value ever seen during a learn sequence. 
      APS_learn_full_lim HBA PS learn full limit. Limit voltage calculated from 
      PS1 full default (indicates a theoretical position beyond open stop in the 
      open direction) 
      APS_learn_full_ofst HBA PS learn full offset. Defines the offset applied 
      to the full default for the learn algorithm. 
      APS_learn_full_seek HBA PS learn full seek. Defines the actuator %open 
      limit to start the full learn algorithm. 
      APS_learn_idle_lim Limit voltage calculated from HBA PS1 idle default 
      (indicates a theoretical position beyond closed stop in the closed 
      direction) 
      APS_learn_idle_ofst HBA - Defines the offset applied to the idle default 
      for the learn algorithm. 
      APS_learn_idle_seek HBA - Defines the actuator %open limit to start the 
      idle learn algorithm. 
      APS_pct HBA throttle position (percent) 
      APS_step_max HBA - Used for 3-phase motor control only used when PS1 is 
      set to a feedback option based on "steps".

      asw_can_err_cnt Aggregate error counter tracking errors in the Simulink 
      application software CAN Transmit and Receive functionality. 
      asw_can_err_code Bitfield error code tracking errors in the Simulink

      autocrk_reset When enabled, a valid start signal will reset the auto-crank 
      system (after reaching cumulative crank-time limit, engine stall, engine 
      shutdown, etc.). If this option is disabled, a key-cycle is required to 
      reset the auto-crank system. Auto-crank must be enabled and the "Start 
      signal input" must not be set to "Disabled (key-on)" for this feature to 
      work. 
      autocrk_starttmr If enabled, the auto-crank timer will wind-up whenever 
      the starter is engaged. The default strategy is to only wind-up the 
      auto-crank timer when engine speed is detected. This option should only be 
      used in auto-crank mode, and not in starter lockout mode. 
      autocrk_trig When "Starter control mode" is set to 'N/O Auto-crank mode', 
      this selects the input channel that will "trigger" an auto-crank cycle to 
      begin attempting to start the engine. If this value is set to 'Disabled 
      (key-on)', then an auto-crank start attempt will begin as soon as 
      key-switch power is on.

      When "Starter control mode" is set to 'N/O Starter-Lockout Pass-thru' 
      mode, starting will be inhibited until a signal is seen on this input. If 
      this value is set to 'Disabled (key-on)', then starting will be allowed as 
      soon as key-switch power is on.

      When applicable, this input is also used by the "Transmission in-gear 
      override limit" feature to detect extended cranking. 
      autocrk_trig_valid Indicates the start command status. 
      autocrk_trig_windup Determines how the auto-crank wind-up timer triggers 
      auto-crank events.

      If set to 'When zero', the start signal engages auto-crank when the engine 
      is stopped. Thereafter, the start signal is ignored, and an auto-crank 
      event is triggered whenever the wind-up timer is zero.

      If set to 'Override', an auto-crank event is triggered whenever the 
      wind-up timer is zero and the start signal is valid. The crank limiter 
      wind-up time limit will be ignored for an active auto-crank event while 
      the start signal remains valid.

      If set to 'Start signal when zero', an auto-crank event is triggered 
      whenever the wind-up timer is zero and the start signal is valid.

      For all settings, the cumulative crank-time limit will still be enforced, 
      and a key-cycle is required to re-initialize cranking once the cumulative 
      crank-time limit is reached. 
      AutoKVMargin AutoKV margin 
      AutoKVReq AutoKV desired 
      AutoKVReq_dec AutoKV decrement 
      AutoKVReq_inc AutoKV increment 
      AutoKVReq_min AutoKV minimum

      AutoKV_TankSetpt AutoKV Tank Setpoint 
      AutoKV_tmr AutoKV timer

      Aux_PWM9_manual AUX PWM9 Output Manual Mode request selector 
      AUX_start_chan This switch enables engine start via an auxiliary input. 
      The output is implemented on the 'starter lockout' control pin but with 
      inverse logic to the starter lockout. This input is only functional if the 
      "Starter control mode" is set to 'N/O Auto-Crank Mode' or 'N/O 
      Starter-Lockout Pass-Thru'.

      Auto-crank is not implemented for this input method. If the "Starter 
      control mode" is normally 'N/O Auto-Crank Mode' then starter control will 
      operate as if in the 'N/O Starter-Lockout Pass-Thru' mode while this input 
      is active (e.g. the starter will only remain on while this input is held 
      active).

      AUX_start_chan_cfg If an Aux DIG is selected for the input, this value 
      determines the active logic state(s).
      The Default values are:
      Aux DIG1 = Gnd
      Aux DIG2 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG3 = Gnd
      Aux DIG4 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG5 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG6 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG7 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG8 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG9 = Gnd
      Aux DIG1 = Gnd
      Aux DIG11 = Gnd
      Aux DIG12 = Gnd
      Aux DIG13 = Gnd
      Aux DIG14 = Gnd
      Aux DIG15 = Gnd
      Aux DIG16 = Gnd
      Aux DIG17 = Gnd
      Aux DIG18 = Gnd
      Aux DIG19 = Gnd
      Gov1 = Gnd
      Gov2 = Gnd 
      AUX_start_sw_stat Auxiliary start switch input status (0=Inactive, 
      1=Active, 2=Error/Fault, 3=Not Configured). 
      AUX_stop_chan This switch enables engine stop via an auxiliary input. 
      AUX_stop_chan_cfg If an Aux DIG is selected for the input, this value 
      determines the active logic state(s).
      The Default values are:
      Aux DIG1 = Gnd
      Aux DIG2 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG3 = Gnd
      Aux DIG4 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG5 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG6 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG7 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG8 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG9 = Gnd
      Aux DIG1 = Gnd
      Aux DIG11 = Gnd
      Aux DIG12 = Gnd
      Aux DIG13 = Gnd
      Aux DIG14 = Gnd
      Aux DIG15 = Gnd
      Aux DIG16 = Gnd
      Aux DIG17 = Gnd
      Aux DIG18 = Gnd
      Aux DIG19 = Gnd
      Gov1 = Gnd
      Gov2 = Gnd 
      AUX_stop_occurred EDIS LED indicating that the engine was stopped due to 
      an auxiliary stop request 
      AUX_stop_sw_stat Auxiliary stop switch input status (0=Inactive, 1=Active, 
      2=Error/Fault, 3=Not Configured). 
      AUX_TACH_alloc AUX TACH allocation indications with values indicating type 
      of output allocated 
      AUX_TACH_conflict AUX TACH alloc conflict indications (0 = no conflict 
      found) 
      AWARNblk_ini This is the initial blink/pulse on-time that will be used for 
      the first pulse following an open-output transfer to another channel. 
      AWARNblk_off A warning may cause a continuous output activation or a 
      blinking/pulsing output. Set this parameter to a non-zero value to enable 
      blinking; set to zero for continuous illumination. 
      AWARNblk_on Duration of warning light illumination per repetition 
      AWARNblk_reps Number of warning light illumination repetitions. 
      AWARN_chan Audible warning output selection - hard vs. soft warning 
      AWARN_ena This switch controls which whether an audible alert will be 
      issued when a new non-audible (soft or hard) warning or MIL occurs. In 
      order for an audible alert to be issued, the audible alert channel must be 
      currently unused, and the engine must be running for more than 3 seconds. 
      AWP_ctl_ECT_min Auxiliary water pump control is disabled when the engine 
      coolant temperature is below this threshold. 
      AWP_ctl_ena Enables or disables auxiliary water pump control 
      AWP_ctl_state Auxiliary water pump control state 
      AWP_motor_status Motor running state of the auxiliary water pump. If the 
      motor is running, forward or reverse direction is also indicated. 
      AWP_restart_runtime This parameter specifies the amount of time the 
      auxiliary water pump will continue to run after the engine is restarted 
      following an EBC1 stop engine event. This parameter is ignored if 
      auxiliary water pump control is disabled. 
      AWP_rpmd When auxiliary water pump control is enabled, this parameter 
      specifies the commanded auxiliary water pump motor speed when the pump is 
      turned on. 
      AWP_status Auxiliary water pump controller status. Normal operation, 
      shutdown, derate, and overspeed status codes are internal states reported 
      by the smart auxiliary water pump over CAN. 
      A_BM1 Adaptive Learn Correction 1 - interpolated from Adaptive Table Bank 
      1 
      A_BM2 Adaptive Learn Correction 2 - interpolated from Gasoline Adaptive 
      Table Bank 2 
      basespk_adv Spark advance used when the ECM is placed in 'base spark' 
      diagnostic mode. 
      basespk_ena This switch determines what input channel/method is used to 
      place the engine into a fixed base diagnostic spark timing mode. 
      basespk_MAP MAP above which the use of 'base spark' advance defined above 
      will not be allowed. In other words, the engine must be below this speed 
      to use the diagnostic 'base spark' advance value. 
      basespk_rpm Engine speed above which the use of 'base spark' advance 
      defined above will not be allowed. In other words, the engine must be 
      below this speed to use the diagnostic 'base spark' advance value. 
      base_crct_final final base fuel multiplier used for PW calculation 
      base_fuel1_final final bank1 base fuel (without wall-wetting) used for PW 
      calculation 
      base_fuel2_final final bank2 base fuel (without wall-wetting) used for PW 
      calculation 
      BCSB_BPSdelta Delta voltage from the current min PS value to initiate 
      closed-stop braking. PS values above this delta will not cause any braking 
      action under any condition. 
      BCSB_ena H-Bridge B Closed Stop Braking (CSB) Elimination enable switch 
      BCSB_Kd This value is multiplied by the difference between the actual 
      dPS/dt and the limit values defined by the min/max PS PSdt parameters and 
      the current PS (from min to min+delta). For example, if the current dPS/dt 
      = -200 %/s, the actuator is about to impact the closed-stop, and the min 
      PS PSdt parameter is -100 %/s, then for a Kd value of 1.0 %/%*sec, the 
      contribution to the braking force will be +100%. 
      BCSB_max_BPSdt dPS/dt value at the max PS (full-closed plus closed-stop PS 
      delta) position above which no braking action will occur. This must be a 
      value strictly < 0 and should be more negative than the min PS PSdt value. 

      BCSB_min_BPSdt dPS/dt value at the min PS (full-closed) position above 
      which no braking action will occur. This must be a value strictly < 0. 
      BEM_hard_Ilim Actuator hardware current limit - HBB 
      BEM_I Estimated current - HBB 
      BEM_Kv Actuator Kv constant - HBB 
      BEM_L Actuator loop L - HBB 
      BEM_R Actuator loop R - HBB 
      BEM_V_diode Actuator voltage supply diode - HBB 
      BFBdt H-Bridge B (HBB) position sensor feedback derivative term 
      BFBdt_n PSdt calculation PS linear least-squares window. More points 
      yields a quieter and more accurate derivative, but introduces more time 
      lag. Fewer points has the opposite effect. 
      BFBdt_xLP Post interpolation low-pass filter constant for PSdt. 
      BIP_CAD_offset_cyl1 Crank angle injection timing offset based on learned 
      BIP value - cyl 1 
      BIP_CAD_offset_cyl2 Crank angle injection timing offset based on learned 
      BIP value - cyl 2 
      BIP_CAD_offset_cyl3 Crank angle injection timing offset based on learned 
      BIP value - cyl 3

      BIP value - cyl 4

      BIP_cyl8 Filtered learned BIP value - cyl 8 
      BIP_dIinj_thld Rate of change of injection current during decay from peak 
      to hold level above which BIP event is detected 
      BIP_enabled Enables diesel unit control valve beginning of injection 
      period (BIP) detection 
      BIP_interval_ms Time interval to elapse between requests for BIP detection

      BLST_cntr_head_ena Monitors and communicates ballast level sensor voltage

      BM1_crct Total fuel correction - bank 1

      Bootblock_Enable_raw Bootblock_Enable raw voltage 
      BOSB_BPSdelta Delta voltage from the current min PS value to initiate 
      open-stop braking. PS values below this delta will not cause any braking 
      action under any condition. 
      BOSB_ena H-Bridge B Output device Open Stop Braking (OSB) Elimination 
      enable switch 
      BOSB_Kd This value is multiplied by the difference between the actual 
      dPS/dt and the limit values defined by the min/max PS PSdt parameters and 
      the current PS (from max to max-delta). For example, if the current dPS/dt 
      = +200 %/s, the actuator is about to impact the open-stop, and the min PS 
      PSdt parameter is +100 %/s, then for a Kd value of 1.0 %/%*sec, the 
      contribution to the braking force will be -100%. 
      BOSB_max_BPSdt dPS/dt value at the min PS (full-open minus open-stop PS 
      delta) position below which no braking action will occur. This must be a 
      value strictly > 0 and should be more positive than the min PS PSdt value. 

      BOSB_min_BPSdt dPS/dt value at the max PS (full-open) position below which 
      no braking action will occur. This must be a value strictly > 0.

      BPs Standard Barometric Pressure 
      BPS12ctl_choice HBridge B In the case of a TPS1/TPS2 mismatch, this switch 
      designates which TPS input is to be utilized 
      BPS12pct_hi HBB - BPS1 higher than BPS2 fault entry condition threshold 
      percentage 
      BPS12pct_lo HBB - BPS1 lower than BPS2 fault entry condition threshold

      BPS1_def HBB - PS1 sensor voltage corresponding to non-controlled

      BPS1_full_def HBB - Voltage corresponding to throttle plate at open stop

      (indicates a theoretical position from open stop in the closed direction) 
      BPS1_idle HBB - position sensor 1 idle voltage 
      BPS1_idle_def HBB - Voltage corresponding to throttle plate at closed stop 

      BPS1_idle_init HBB - Limit voltage calculated from PS1 idle default 
      (indicates a theoretical position from closed stop in the open direction) 
      BPS1_learn_tau HBB - Time constant used to learn the idle or full voltages 
      for the PS1 sensor. 
      BPS1_learn_wait HBB - The wait time before the controller begins to learn 
      the idle or full voltages for the PS1 sensor. 
      BPS1_max HBB - BPS1 high voltage fault max voltage entry condition 
      BPS1_min HBB - BPS1 low voltage fault min voltage entry condition 
      BPS1_pct HBB - position sensor 1 percent 
      BPS1_rawfilt HBB - Position Sensor 1 feedback (filtered) 
      BPS1_source HBridge B Throttle Position Source 1 Input 
      BPS2ctl_allow HBridge B When dual pot TPS is utilized, this switch allows 
      the use of TPS2 if a TPS1 voltage out of range condition (FAULT) occurs 
      BPS2_angle_at_full HBB - Used for throttles that have a PS2 feedback that 
      reaches full voltage before 100% opening 
      BPS2_def HBB - PS2 sensor voltage corresponding to non-controlled 
      (limp-home) position 
      BPS2_full HBB - position sensor 2 full open voltage 
      BPS2_full_init HBB - Limit voltage calculated from PS2 full default 
      (indicates a theoretical position from open stop in the closed direction) 
      BPS2_idle HBB - position sensor 2 idle voltage 
      BPS2_idle_init HBB - Limit voltage calculated from PS2 idle default 
      (indicates a theoretical position from closed stop in the open direction) 
      BPS2_learn_tau HBB - Time constant used to learn the idle or full voltages 
      for the PS2 sensor. 
      BPS2_learn_wait HBB - The wait time before the controller begins to learn 
      the idle or full voltages for the PS2 sensor. 
      BPS2_max HBB - BPS2 high voltage fault max voltage entry condition 
      BPS2_min HBB - BPS2 low voltage fault min voltage entry condition 
      BPS2_pct HBB - position sensor 2 percent 
      BPS2_rawfilt HBB - Position Sensor 2 feedback (filtered)
