      output #1 on - relational operator (select from <, >, <=, >=, =, <> or 
      Ignored) 
      cfgout_OilPoff Oil Pressure entry condition for turning configurable 
      output #1 off - calibratable comparison value 
      cfgout_OilPon Oil Pressure entry condition for turning configurable output 
      #1 on - calibratable comparison value 
      cfgout_on_wait Persistence entry condition (in seconds) for turning 
      configurable output #1 on 
      cfgout_PD1loff AUX analog input (PD1) entry condition for turning 
      configurable output #1 off - relational operator (select from <, >, <=, 
      >=, =, <> or Ignored) 
      cfgout_PD1lon AUX analog input (PD1) entry condition for turning 
      configurable output #1 on - relational operator (select from <, >, <=, >=, 
      =, <> or Ignored) 
      cfgout_PD1off AUX analog input (PD1) entry condition for turning 
      configurable output #1 off - calibratable comparison value 
      cfgout_PD1on AUX analog input (PD1) entry condition for turning 
      configurable output #1 on - calibratable comparison value 
      cfgout_PU1loff AUX analog input (PU1) entry condition for turning 
      configurable output #1 off - relational operator (select from <, >, <=, 
      >=, =, <> or Ignored) 
      cfgout_PU1lon AUX analog input (PU1) entry condition for turning 
      configurable output #1 on - relational operator (select from <, >, <=, >=, 
      =, <> or Ignored) 
      cfgout_PU1off AUX analog input (PU1) entry condition for turning 
      configurable output #1 off - calibratable comparison value 
      cfgout_PU1on AUX analog input (PU1) entry condition for turning 
      configurable output #1 on - calibratable comparison value 
      cfgout_RPMloff RPM entry condition for turning configurable output #1 off 
      - relational operator (select from <, >, <=, >=, =, <> or Ignored) 
      cfgout_RPMlon RPM entry condition for turning configurable output #1 on - 
      relational operator (select from <, >, <=, >=, =, <> or Ignored) 
      cfgout_RPMoff RPM entry condition for turning configurable output #1 off - 
      calibratable comparison value 
      cfgout_RPMon RPM entry condition for turning configurable output #1 on - 
      calibratable comparison value 
      cfgout_running Engine running state - configurable output #1 
      cfgout_state Current state - configurable output #1 
      cfgout_stopped Engine stopped state - configurable output #1 
      cfgout_Vbatloff Battery Voltage entry condition for turning configurable 
      output #1 off - relational operator (select from <, >, <=, >=, =, <> or 
      Ignored) 
      cfgout_Vbatlon Battery Voltage entry condition for turning configurable 
      output #1 on - relational operator (select from <, >, <=, >=, =, <> or 
      Ignored) 
      cfgout_Vbatoff Battery Voltage entry condition for turning configurable 
      output #1 off - calibratable comparison value 
      cfgout_Vbaton Battery Voltage entry condition for turning configurable 
      output #1 on - calibratable comparison value 
      CFVI_cur_cal_mod Current CFV calibration model number and rev level 
      CFVI_cur_HW_mod Current CFV hardware model number and rev level 
      CFVI_cur_SW_mod Current CFV software model number and rev level 
      CFVI_flash_wr_force Flag to cause writing of the flash parameters into the 
      CFV 
      CFVI_flash_wr_left Number of flash writes left availble in the CFV during 
      this power-cycle 
      CFV_cal_state Cal/Param communication state machine value 
      CFV_ctltype_act CFV control type feedback (Flow Command / Fixed 
      Press/Pos/Flow / Force Command / Offline) 
      CFV_ctltype_cmd CFV control type command (Flow Command / Fixed 
      Press/Pos/Flow / Force Command / Offline) 
      CFV_dis_restrict This is the effective area of all restrictions downstream 
      of a CFV up to and including the fuel introduction ports. This effective 
      area (i.e. Cd * A) is used to compute the backpressure on the CFV relative 
      to the fuel discharge environment pressure as measured and communicated by 
      the ECM back to the CFV (i.e. TIP or MAP). 
      CFV_FSO_cmd Indicates whether fuel shut off should be commanded to the CFV 

      CFV_fuel_calc This switch determines the source of the fuel flow 
      calculation for the CFV. In 'Speed-density + dMAP/dt' mode, the intake 
      manifold filling portion of the total flow is computed using the intake 
      volume and the filtered dMAP/dt signal.
      In 'Throttle-model based' mode, the compressible flow through the 
      throttle-body using the MAP and TIP pressure signals are used during 
      transients and speed-density is only used during steady-state operation.
      These calculations are controlled by the parameters in the 'Throttle-Model 
      Based Throttle-Body Fueling' section.
      When specific MAP faults are enabled and faulted, the fuel flow 
      calculation is automatically switched from 'Throttle-model based' to 
      'Speed-density + dMAP/dt'. Refer to "Fuel mode MAP fault reaction" on the 
      'DiagConfig' worksheet for more details. 
      CFV_intF_bits CFV internal fault bit pattern - in lower 3 bytes 
      CFV_man_mode CFV manual mode - select from Auto, Manual Pressure, Manual 
      Flow, Manual Press+Flow, Manual Press+Position, Manual Duty-Cycle, Manual 
      Offline 
      CFV_mdot_act CFV reported mdot fuel flow 
      CFV_mdot_act_pct CFV reported mdot fuel flow percentage of CFV Full scale 
      (CFV_mdot_FS) 
      CFV_mdot_choke After-start fuel enrichment contribution to the CFV fuel 
      flow command. 
      CFV_mdot_cmd CFV commanded mdot fuel flow 
      CFV_mdot_cmd_pct CFV commanded mdot fuel flow percentage of CFV Full scale 
      (CFV_mdot_FS) 
      CFV_mdot_FS This is the full-scale fuel mass flow rate in g/sec used for a 
      CFV based continuous injection system. Fuel flow commands are transmitted 
      as a % of this value in order to properly scale the dynamic range of the 
      valve. A typical value of 32.0 g/sec will satisfy all installations up to 
      approximately 600 bhp. 
      CFV_mdot_pct_err CFV actual fuel flow vs. commanded flow error in pct of 
      commanded 
      CFV_mdot_pct_hi Difference between the commanded and actual CFV gaseous 
      fuel flow rate as a percentage of the commanded rate. The actual flow rate 
      must be greater than the commanded rate by this percentage. 
      CFV_mdot_pct_lo Difference between the commanded and actual CFV gaseous 
      fuel flow rate as a percentage of the commanded rate. The actual flow rate 
      must be less than the commanded rate by this percentage. NOTE: must be 
      negative number. 
      CFV_mdot_pct_rms The RMS is calculated from a rolling history of the CFV 
      gaseous fuel flow error values. The flow error is defined as the 
      difference between the commanded and actual fuel flow rate as a percentage 
      of the commanded rate. NOTE: The RMS percentage must be expressed as a 
      positive number. 
      CFV_param_differ CFV internal parameter matching status - 0=all params 
      match, 1=at least 1 param does not match 
      CFV_param_NA_cnt CFV Param-O-CAN index not-available counter for either 
      timed-out or N/A index response paramocan requests 
      CFV_param_upload upload parameters from CFV/EPR to ECM when requested by 
      the user 
      CFV_Pdis_margin_kPa This is a differential positive pressure that is added 
      to the fuel discharge environment pressure (i.e. TIP or MAP) of a CFV fuel 
      system. This differential pressure is used to compensate for pressure 
      pulsations at the fuel introduction point to allow computation of 
      worst-case choking conditions across the CFV valve orifice. This value 
      will typically be 2 to 3 psid with 3 psid being recommended. 
      CFV_Pdis_min This is the minimum fuel discharge environment pressure (i.e. 
      TIP or MAP) sent by the ECM to the CFV. By limiting the minimum discharge 
      environment pressure, the calculated interstage pressure command is 
      limited. Limiting the minimum interstage pressure command can be used to 
      help improve interstage pressure control at low engine loads. Note: the 
      "CFV discharge pressure pulsation margin" is added after this parameter 
      limits the discharge environment pressure. 
      CFV_Pin_def_psig This is the estimated inlet gage pressure to the CFV. A 
      typical value is 85 psig. This value may help the CFV optimize its 
      performance through gain scaling, ... 
      CFV_Preg_HiExp Difference between the commanded and actual CFV internal 
      gaseous fuel regulation pressure on the positive (high) side that will 
      trigger a fault. 
      CFV_Preg_LoExp Difference between the commanded and actual CFV internal 
      gaseous fuel regulation pressure on the negative (low) side that will 
      trigger a fault. NOTE: Must be a negative number. 
      CFV_P_act_DC CFV 1st stage pressure-control duty-cycle in % 
      CFV_P_act_I CFV 1st stage pressure actuator current in amps 
      CFV_P_act_kPa CFV Interstage actual pressure 
      CFV_P_cmd_kPa CFV interstage pressure control command computed in the ECM 
      from the actual and error terms in kPa 
      CFV_P_err_acc CFV low-pass filtered interstage pressure error used for low 
      fuel pressure derate. 
      CFV_P_err_kPa CFV Interstage pressure control error = (commanded pressure 
      - actual pressure) 
      CFV_P_man_DC CFV manually commanded 1st stage pressure-control duty-cycle 
      in % 
      CFV_P_man_kPa CFV manually commanded interstage pressure in kPa 
      CFV_status CFV status (Comm Lost, OK, Fault) 
      CFV_strtf_hold_cyc CFV starting fuel enrichment hold time. Full CFV 
      starting fuel enrichment is applied for this number of engine cycles 
      before the fuel flow command begins to be slewed back toward the base 
      command. 
      CFV_strtf_mult CFV starting fuel enrichment multiplier. The base fuel flow 
      command is multiplied by this value during starting, until the number of 
      engine cycles set by "CFV starting fuel crank cycles" is reached. 
      CFV_strtf_reset_tm Sets the minimum time that must elapse after CFV 
      starting fuel enrichment was applied before it can become active again. 
      This should be set large enough to prevent flooding the engine when it is 
      cranked multiple times without starting. This minimum time will not apply 
      if the engine starts successfully. 
      CFV_strtf_slew Sets the rate at which CFV starting fuel enrichment is 
      slewed out and the fuel flow command returns to its normal value. 
      CFV_Tfuel_degK CFV interstage fuel temperature 
      CFV_x_act CFV actual valve position 
      CFV_x_act_DC CFV actual valve actuator duty cycle 
      CFV_x_act_I CFV actual valve actuator current 
      CFV_x_cmd CFV internal command position 
      CFV_x_err CFV internal position control error 
      CFV_x_man CFV manual valve position 
      CFV_x_man_DC CFV manual valve actuator duty cycle 
      choke_add_mode Specifies which "Choke Fuel Adder" tables are used for the 
      various fuel types and fuel admission devices.

      Gasoline always uses the "Primary Choke Fuel Adder" table.

      When setting is 'Primary = Gasoline', after-start fuel enrichment is 
      disabled for gaseous fuels.

      When setting is 'Primary = Gasoline & Non-DEPR Gaseous', the following 
      gaseous fuel admission devices use the "Primary Choke Fuel Adder" table:
      Pulse Injection
      Continuous Injection
      MFG (only when "MFG fuel calculation mode" is not 'MFA mass flow')

      When setting is 'Primary = Gasoline, Secondary = Gaseous', the following 
      gaseous fuel admission devices use the "Secondary Choke Fuel Adder" table:
      Pulse Injection
      Continuous Injection
      MFG (only when "MFG fuel calculation mode" is not 'MFA mass flow')
      Carburetion (only when "Carburetor fuel trim device type" is 
      'MegaJector/EPR')

      Bi-fuel engines requiring after-start enrichment for both gasoline and 
      gaseous fuels must use 'Primary = Gasoline, Secondary = Gaseous'.

      When fuel is gasoline, choke fuel is added while cranking and running. 
      When fuel is gaseous and permitted by this setting, choke fuel is added 
      only while running. 
      CHT Cylinder Head Temperature 
      CHTc CHT span. See description of "CHT / ECT Estimate" for a description 
      of this value. 
      CHTcrank Equivalent Cylinder Head Temperature 
      CHTcrank_ceil CHTcrank ceiling (maximum value allowed) 
      CHTcrank_delt CHTcrank delta temperature from CHT (deg F) 
      CHTcrank_deltmax CHTcrank delta maximum limit 
      CHTcrank_Kdn CHTcrank decreasing rate 
      CHTcrank_Kup CHTcrank increasing rate 
      CHTdt Electronic Thermostat Control: CHT rate of change (degF/sec) 
      CHTo CHT offset. See description of "CHT / ECT Estimate" for a description 
      of this value. 
      CHTo_tau CHT tau (time constant). See description of "CHT / ECT Estimate" 
      for a description of this value. 
      CHT_def Default value of cylinder head temperature 
      CHT_ECT_est Set this switch according the physical sensor attached to the 
      'ECT' input on the ECM (either the CHT sensor or the ECT sensor). The 
      other (non-present) parameter will be estimated. 
      CHT_HiExp CHT higher than expected 1 fault - CHT threshold entry condition 

      CHT_HiExp2 CHT higher than expected 2 fault - CHT threshold entry 
      condition 
      CHT_HiExp2_rpm CHT higher than expected 2 fault - RPM threshold entry 
      condition 
      CHT_HiExp2_wait CHT higher than expected 2 fault - run-time threshold 
      entry condition 
      CHT_HiExp_rpm CHT higher than expected 1 fault - RPM threshold entry 
      condition 
      CHT_HiExp_wait CHT higher than expected 1 fault - run-time threshold entry 
      condition 
      CHT_s Standard operating Cylinder Head Temperature (CHT). 
      CHT_tau CHT offset tau (at start). See description of "CHT / ECT Estimate" 
      for a description of this value. 
      CHT_vdr CHT sensor input channel pullup resistor resistance value 
      CIP Air filter outlet/Compressor Inlet Pressure 
      CIT Compressor inlet temperature. 
      CL1_CBT_hot Flag to indicate whether CBT has exceeded threshold on this 
      key cycle 
      CL1_FSO_occurred Flag to indicate whether lean FSO has occurred on this 
      key cycle 
      CL1_perturb CL perturbation (from phi=1.0), bank 1 (%) 
      CL1_phi_error Phi error (bank 1). Difference between desired phi and 
      measured phi 
      CL1_postcat_hi_th Minimum phi for persistent post-cat phi control. 
      CL1_postcat_lo_th Maximum phi for persistent post-cat phi control. 
      CL1_post_phi_ROL Post-catalyst phi control mode 
      CL1_post_SS_status TWC ROL steady-state vs. transient mode indication 
      CL1_ROL_win_n_th Minimum post-cat phi for ROL control. 
      CL1_ROL_win_p_th Maximum post-cat phi for ROL control. 
      CL2_E Closed loop perturbation excursion, bank 2 (%) 
      CL2_Hn Closed Loop perturbation hold (negative side of waveform), bank 2 
      CL2_Hp Closed Loop perturbation hold (positive side of waveform), bank 2 
      CL2_perturb CL perturbation (from phi=1.0), bank 2 (%) 
      CL2_phi_error Phi error (bank 2). Difference between desired phi and 
      measured phi 
      CL2_wave_RMS CL2 perturbation wave RMS 
      CLacq_lmt_step Limits the fast closed-loop step following a successful EGO 
      switch event to the original closed-loop block multiplier. Enabling this 
      option prevents the closed-loop block multiplier from 
      increasing/decreasing from its original value after a lean/rich ramp. 
      CLBM1_EGO_o Closed Loop Block Multiplier + perturbation at EGO (bank 1) 
      CLBM2_EGO_o Closed Loop Block Multiplier + perturbation at EGO (bank 2) 
      CLfltG_MAPmax Gasoline: Upper MAP limit associated with Fault Limit, 
      CL_BM_max 
      CLfltG_MAPmin Gasoline: Lower MAP limit associated with Fault Limit, 
      CL_BM_min 
      CLfltG_RPMmax Gasoline: Maximum engine speed limit associated with Fault 
      Limit, CL_BM_max 
      CLfltG_RPMmin Gasoline: Lower engine speed limit associated with Fault 
      Limit, CL_BM_min 
      CLfltN_MAPmax NG: Upper MAP limit associated with Fault Limit, CLNG_hi 
      CLfltN_MAPmin NG: Lower MAP limit associated with Fault Limit, CLNG_lo 
      CLfltN_RPMmax NG: Maximum engine speed limit associated with Fault Limit, 
      CLNG_hi 
      CLfltN_RPMmin NG: Lower engine speed limit associated with Fault Limit, 
      CLNG_lo 
      CLfltP_MAPmax LPG: Upper MAP limit associated with Fault Limit, CLLP_hi 
      CLfltP_MAPmin LPG: Lower MAP limit associated with Fault Limit, CLLP_lo 
      CLfltP_RPMmax LPG: Maximum engine speed limit associated with Fault Limit, 
      CLLP_hi 
      CLfltP_RPMmin LPG: Lower engine speed limit associated with Fault Limit, 
      CLLP_lo 
      CLInactiveFlag Closed Loop Inactive Source Indication Flag.
      Manual forcing of CL Inactive.
      CL Waveform exceeded authority limits.
      CL Enable map forced system into OL mode. 
      CLLP_CM_min_RMS NG: EGO RMS Fault Condition 
      CLLP_CM_preRMSatt CM pre-cat EGO RMS attenuation (LPG) 
      CLLP_CM_waveRMSatt LPG: Fault Condition (EGO RMS > CL Waveform RMS * 
      CLLP_CM_waveRMSatt) 
      CLLP_hi LPG Fault Condition. Maximum (positive) allowed CL BM 
      CLLP_hi_postcat LPG: Post Catalyst Delta Phi max (positive value) 
      CLLP_K Proportional gain that is applied to the Phi error to determine the 
      rate of closed-loop correction required (for LPG engines). 
      CLLP_Kiv_n_postcat LPG: Post Catalyst Kiv decreasing limit 
      CLLP_Kiv_p_postcat LPG: Post Catalyst Kiv increasing limit 
      CLLP_Ki_n_postcat LPG: Post Catalyst Ki decreasing limit 
      CLLP_Ki_n_ROL LPG: ROL control Ki gain negative error 
      CLLP_Ki_p_postcat LPG: Post Catalyst Ki increasing limit 
      CLLP_Ki_p_ROL LPG: ROL control Ki gain positive error 
      CLLP_Kp_n_postcat LPG: Post Catalyst Kp decreasing limit 
      CLLP_Kp_n_ROL LPG: ROL control Kp gain negative error 
      CLLP_Kp_p_postcat LPG: Post Catalyst Kp increasing limit 
      CLLP_Kp_p_ROL LPG: ROL control Kp gain positive error 
      CLLP_K_acquire LPG: Closed Loop Acquire Gain 
      CLLP_lo LPG Fault Condition. Minimum (negative) allowed CL BM 
      CLLP_lo_postcat LPG: Post Catalyst Delta Phi min (negative value) 
      CLLP_postcat_ena LPG Post Catalyst Control (Enable/Disable) 
      CLLP_postcat_gain LPG postcat gain selection 'Single-Point' or 
      'Table-Based'. 
      CLLP_postcat_winndlt This parameter is added to "ROL window low offset" 
      and the post-cat target phi to define a lower threshold for transitioning 
      to post-cat phi control. The purpose of this adder is to provide some 
      hysteresis to the first ROL post cat window when transitioning between ROL 
      and post-cat phi control. 
      CLLP_postcat_winpdlt This parameter is added to "ROL window high offset" 
      and the post-cat target phi to define an upper threshold for transitioning 
      to post-cat phi control. The purpose of this adder is to provide some 
      hysteresis to the first ROL post cat window when transitioning between ROL 
      and post-cat phi control. 
      CLLP_post_fastwr_tm This is the time that the closed loop fuel control 
      will be continuous when crossing between ROL temporary (mode 2) and 
      post-cat persistent (mode 1). 
      CLLP_ROLend_fastwrtm This is the time that the closed loop fuel control 
      will be continuous when crossing between ROL persistent (mode 0) and 
      post-cat temporary (mode 3). 
      CLLP_ROLend_tm_mode Parameter determines when the "Post-cat Temp Phi cont 
      CL time" parameter is used when changing the closed loop fuel control from 
      ROL persistent (mode 0) to post-cat temporary (mode 3). When set to 'Lean 
      Only', the "Post-cat Temp Phi cont CL time" is only used when crossing the 
      lower limit. When set to 'Lean or Rich', the "Post-cat Temp Phi cont CL 
      time" is used when crossing either the lower or upper limit. 
      CLLP_ROL_reinit_ena Enable re-initialization of ROL state to set point on 
      transition to ROL control 
      CLLP_ROL_reinit_hi Value at which to re-initialize ROL state on transition 
      to post-cat phi control - high 
      CLLP_ROL_reinit_lo Value at which to re-initialize ROL state on transition 
      to post-cat phi control - low 
      CLLP_ROL_res_dly LPG: ROL control resume delay after transition from 
      post-cat phi control 
      CLLP_ROL_trans_mode Parameter determines behavior when transitioning 
      between ROL and post-cat closed loop fuel control.

      When set to 'Legacy', transition between controllers is smooth, without 
      step changes in output.

      When set to 'Enhanced - Unidirectional', transition from ROL to post-cat 
      control accounts for ROL state re-initialization and will contain a step 
      change in output that reflects ROL state's error. Transition from post-cat 
      to ROL control will also contain a step change as ROL integrator is reset 
      to 0 upon transition.

      When set to 'Enhanced - Bidirectional', transition from ROL to post-cat 
      control is the same behavior as 'Enhanced - Unidirectional'. However, 
      transition from post-cat to ROL control will be smooth and without a step 
      change in output. 
      CLLP_ROL_win_n LPG: ROL SS control window lower limit, relative to 
      post-cat target phi 
      CLLP_ROL_win_p LPG: ROL SS control window upper limit, relative to 
      post-cat target phi 
      CLLP_rst_postcat This switch determines whether or not a non-zero post-cat 
      delta-phi value remains in effect and/or intact whenever the engine enters 
      an RPM/MAP area with post-cat control disabled by specifying a 0.000 
      post-cat phi target. The default mode of operation is for the post-cat 
      delta-phi to remain in use even though it is not being updated in the 
      region. The second mode is for any existing delta-phi to be remembered, 
      but not be used while in this region. The remembered value will be 
      reinstated as soon as the engine leaves the disabled post-cat region. The 
      third mode is for any existing delta-phi to be completely reset to zero in 
      this region. 
      CLLP_SS_dly LPG: Delay after adaptive count valid before transition to 
      steady-state control 
      CLLP_stepmax LPG: Closed Loop Max Step Allowed 
      CLLP_TD_EGOsw_ena Activates CL acquisition mode when the EGO fails to 
      switch within 1 transport delay of either a rich-lean or lean-rich CL 
      perturb transition. 
      CLLP_TD_enable Enable the transport delay model-based CL acquisition mode. 
      If an invalid CL duty cycle is detected, this mode ramps the CL multiplier 
      until an EGO transition is detected. 
      CLLP_TD_max_n During transport delay-based CL acquisition, the maximum 
      allowed overshoot in the lean direction. 
      CLLP_TD_max_p During transport delay-based CL acquisition, the maximum 
      allowed overshoot in the rich direction. 
      CLLP_TD_mdota Disables fast closed-loop acquire mode at low mass air flow 
      rates. Setting this parameter to '0' allows fast closed-loop to remain 
      enabled under all operating conditions. 
      CLLP_TD_sw_offset Acquisition mode is triggered when the EGO fails to 
      switch within transport delay * (1 + switch delay offset)of a lean-rich or 
      rich-lean CL perturbation. Positive values slow the response for allowfor 
      more transport delay error before triggering acqusition mode. 
      CLLP_TD_sw_pct Initial CL_BM step size when the EGO fails to switch, given 
      as a percent of the total EGO switching excursion 
      CLNG_CM_min_RMS LPG: EGO RMS Fault Condition 
      CLNG_CM_preRMSatt CM pre-cat EGO RMS attenuation (NG) 
      CLNG_CM_waveRMSatt NG: Fault Condition (EGO RMS > CL Waveform RMS * 
      CLNG_CM_waveRMSatt)

      CLNG_hi_postcat NG: Post Catalyst Delta Phi min (positive value)

      CLNG_Kiv_n_postcat NG: Post Catalyst Kiv decreasing limit 
      CLNG_Kiv_p_postcat NG: Post Catalyst Kiv increasing limit 
      CLNG_Ki_n_postcat NG: Post Catalyst Ki decreasing limit 
      CLNG_Ki_n_ROL NG: ROL control Ki gain negative error 
      CLNG_Ki_p_postcat NG: Post Catalyst Ki increasing limit 
      CLNG_Ki_p_ROL NG: ROL control Ki gain positive error 
      CLNG_Kp_n_postcat NG: Post Catalyst Kp decreasing limit 
      CLNG_Kp_n_ROL NG: ROL control Kp gain negative error 
      CLNG_Kp_p_postcat NG: Post Catalyst Kp increasing limit 
      CLNG_Kp_p_ROL NG: ROL control Kp gain positive error 
      CLNG_K_acquire NG : CL_acquire Gain (K) 
      CLNG_lo NG Fault Condition. Minimum (negative) allowed CL BM

      CLNG_postcat_ena NG Post Catalyst Control (Enable/Disable) 
      CLNG_postcat_gain NG postcat gain selection 'Single-Point' or 
      'Table-Based'. 
      CLNG_postcat_winndlt This parameter is added to "ROL window low offset" 
      and the post-cat target phi to define a lower threshold for transitioning 
      to post-cat phi control. The purpose of this adder is to provide some 
      hysteresis to the first ROL post cat window when transitioning between ROL 
      and post-cat phi control. 
      CLNG_postcat_winpdlt This parameter is added to "ROL window high offset" 
      and the post-cat target phi to define an upper threshold for transitioning 
      to post-cat phi control. The purpose of this adder is to provide some 
      hysteresis to the first ROL post cat window when transitioning between ROL 
      and post-cat phi control. 
      CLNG_post_fastwr_tm This is the time that the closed loop fuel control 
      will be continuous when crossing between ROL temporary (mode 2) and 
      post-cat persistent (mode 1). 
      CLNG_ROLend_fastwrtm This is the time that the closed loop fuel control 
      will be continuous when crossing between ROL persistent (mode 0) and 
      post-cat temporary (mode 3). 
      CLNG_ROLend_tm_mode Parameter determines when the "Post-cat Temp Phi cont 
      CL time" parameter is used when changing the closed loop fuel control from 
      ROL persistent (mode 0) to post-cat temporary (mode 3). When set to 'Lean 
      Only', the "Post-cat Temp Phi cont CL time" is only used when crossing the 
      lower limit. When set to 'Lean or Rich', the "Post-cat Temp Phi cont CL 
      time" is used when crossing either the lower or upper limit. 
      CLNG_ROL_reinit_ena Enable re-initialization of ROL state to set point on 
      transition to ROL control 
      CLNG_ROL_reinit_hi Value at which to re-initialize ROL state on transition 
      to post-cat phi control - high 
      CLNG_ROL_reinit_lo Value at which to re-initialize ROL state on transition 
      to post-cat phi control - low 
      CLNG_ROL_res_dly NG: ROL control resume delay after transition from 
      post-cat phi control 
      CLNG_ROL_trans_mode Parameter determines behavior when transitioning 
      between ROL and post-cat closed loop fuel control.

      When set to 'Legacy', transition between controllers is smooth, without 
      step changes in output.

      When set to 'Enhanced - Unidirectional', transition from ROL to post-cat 
      control accounts for ROL state re-initialization and will contain a step 
      change in output that reflects ROL state's error. Transition from post-cat 
      to ROL control will also contain a step change as ROL integrator is reset 
      to 0 upon transition.

      When set to 'Enhanced - Bidirectional', transition from ROL to post-cat 
      control is the same behavior as 'Enhanced - Unidirectional'. However, 
      transition from post-cat to ROL control will be smooth and without a step 
      change in output. 
      CLNG_ROL_win_n NG: ROL SS control window lower limit, relative to post-cat 
      target phi 
      CLNG_ROL_win_p NG: ROL SS control window upper limit, relative to post-cat 
      target phi 
      CLNG_rst_postcat This switch determines whether or not a non-zero post-cat 
      delta-phi value remains in effect and/or intact whenever the engine enters 
      an RPM/MAP area with post-cat control disabled by specifying a 0.000 
      post-cat phi target. The default mode of operation is for the post-cat 
      delta-phi to remain in use even though it is not being updated in the 
      region. The second mode is for any existing delta-phi to be remembered, 
      but not be used while in this region. The remembered value will be 
      reinstated as soon as the engine leaves the disabled post-cat region. The 
      third mode is for any existing delta-phi to be completely reset to zero in 
      this region. 
      CLNG_SS_dly NG: Delay after adaptive count valid before transition to 
      steady-state control 
      CLNG_stepmax NG: Closed Loop Max Step Allowed 
      CLNG_TD_EGOsw_ena Activates CL acquisition mode when the EGO fails to 
      switch within 1 transport delay of either a rich-lean or lean-rich CL 
      perturb transition. 
      CLNG_TD_enable Enable the transport delay model-based CL acquisition mode. 
      If an invalid CL duty cycle is detected, this mode ramps the CL multiplier 
      until an EGO transition is detected. 
      CLNG_TD_max_n During transport delay-based CL acquisition, the maximum 
      allowed overshoot in the lean direction. 
      CLNG_TD_max_p During transport delay-based CL acquisition, the maximum 
      allowed overshoot in the rich direction. 
      CLNG_TD_mdota Disables fast closed-loop acquire mode at low mass air flow 
      rates. Setting this parameter to '0' allows fast closed-loop to remain 
      enabled under all operating conditions. 
      CLNG_TD_sw_offset Acquisition mode is triggered when the EGO fails to 
      switch within transport delay * (1 + switch delay offset)of a lean-rich or 
      rich-lean CL perturbation. Positive values slow the response for allowfor 
      more transport delay error before triggering acquisition mode. 
      CLNG_TD_sw_pct Initial CL_BM step size when the EGO fails to switch, given 
      as a percent of the total EGO switching excursion 
      CLN_phidt_hi_postcat NG: Post Catalyst dphi/dt max limit (positive value) 
      CLN_phidt_lo_postcat NG: Post Catalyst dphi/dt min limit (negative value) 
      CLpLP_Emax LP: CL Perturbation Excursion Maximum 
      CLpLP_Emin LP: CL Perturbation Excursion Minimum 
      CLpLP_Rn_def LP: Default CL Lean (negative) Ramp 
      CLpLP_Rp_def LPG: Default CL Rich (positive) Ramp 
      CLpNG_Emax NG: CL Perturbation Excursion Maximum 
      CLpNG_Emin NG: CL Perturbation Excursion Minimum 
      CLpNG_Rn_def NG: Default CL Lean (negative) Ramp 
      CLpNG_Rp_def NG: Default CL Rich (positive) Ramp 
      CLp_E Closed loop perturbation excursion, bank 1 (%) 
      CLp_Emax Gasoline: CL Perturbation Excursion Maximum 
      CLp_Emin Gasoline: CL Perturbation Excursion Minimum 
      CLp_fastwr_cs_CBT This is the CBT threshold which the CBT model must 
      surpass during a cold start that will allow the switch back to normal 
      switching mode. This is only active if cold start mode is active. 
      CLp_fastwr_cs_state Cold start operation state. Possible indications:
      - "Disabled": cold start emissions mode is disabled in the calibration
      - "Wait for start": engine is stopped, or has been running for less than 3 
      seconds
      - "Inactive": after engine start, ECT was above the threshold for cold 
      start operation
      - "Active": after engine start, ECT was below the threshold for cold start 
      operation
      - "Timed out": the engine was running longer than the maximum calibrated 
      time for cold start operation
      - "Complete": CBT exceeded the "Cold start continuous phi CBT threshold", 
      and fast acquire mode will no longer be activated by cold start operation 
      CLp_fastwr_ena CL UEGO perturb disable; While operating in CL switching 
      mode with a pre-cat UEGO sensor, this feature will temporarily disable the 
      perturbations and switch to a continuous CL update mode for rapid CL 
      convergence. 
      CLp_fastwr_lean_err When a CL update is performed, if the phi error is 
      greater than this amount in the lean direction, the perturbations are 
      disabled and CL UEGO perturbation disable mode will engage. The CL "step" 
      taken when the system engages via this method is determined by the lean 
      initial step parameter below. 
      CLp_fastwr_lean_step When a CL update is performed, if the phi error is 
      greater than the amount above in the lean direction, the perturbations are 
      disabled and CL UEGO perturbation disable mode will engage. The CL "step" 
      taken when the system engages via this method is determined by this 
      parameter. 
      CLp_fastwr_MAPdt CL UEGO MAPdt engage; If perturbations are active and 
      abs(MAPdt_dz) is above this limit, CL UEGO transient perturbation mode 
      will engage. 
      CLp_fastwr_mdot_min This parameter can be used to disable this mode at low 
      flow conditions (e.g. idle). 
      CLp_fastwr_mincyc CL UEGO min engagement; Once engaged, the fast CL UEGO 
      mode will stay engaged for at least this number of cycles. 
      CLp_fastwr_phierr CL UEGO phi error disengage; Once engaged, the phi error 
      must be below this limit in order for the mode to disengage. 
      CLp_fastwr_rich_err When a CL update is performed, if the phi error is 
      greater than this amount in the rich direction, the perturbations are 
      disabled and CL UEGO perturbation disable mode will engage. The CL "step" 
      taken when the system engages via this method is determined by the rich 
      initial step parameter below. 
      CLp_fastwr_rich_step When a CL update is performed, if the phi error is 
      greater than the amount above in the rich direction, the perturbations are 
      disabled and CL UEGO perturbation disable mode will engage. The CL "step" 
      taken when the system engages via this method is determined by this 
      parameter. 
      CLp_fastwr_status CL UEGO mode status (Inactive, Active: Phi Rich, Active: 
      Phi Lean, Active: MAPdt, Active: TWC Diag, Active: TWC Enrich, Active: 
      Cold Start, Active: TWC Lean/Rich) 
      CLp_Hn Closed Loop perturbation hold (negative side of waveform), bank 1 
      CLp_Hp Closed Loop perturbation hold (positive side of waveform), bank 1 
      CLp_lean_DC This is the maximum lean duty cycle limit. 
      CLP_phidt_hi_postcat LPG: Post Catalyst dphi/dt max limit (positive value) 

      CLP_phidt_lo_postcat LPG: Post Catalyst dphi/dt min limit (negative value) 

      CLp_rich_DC This is the maximum rich duty cycle limit. 
      CLp_Rn_def Gasoline: Default CL Lean (negative) Ramp 
      CLp_Rp_def Gasoline: Default CL Rich (positive) Ramp 
      CLp_tau CL Perturbation Waveform Period 
      CLp_tau_def Default time period for one rich excursion and one lean 
      excursion 
      CLp_wave_RMS CL1 perturbation wave RMS 
      clutch_depressed Logical indicating the status of the clutch pedal 
      clutch_fault Logical indicating the clutch pedal switch is in a fault 
      condition 
      clutch_sw Clutch pedal sensor / input channel selection switch 
      clutch_sw_config Clutch pedal configuration (Bi-state/Tri-state 
      open=released; Tri-state open=depressed; Aux DIG +V=released; Aux DIG 
      +V=depressed) 
      CL_bank_mode Closed-loop bank control mode (disabled, single, dual, 
      average) 
      CL_BM1 Closed Loop Block Multiplier - bank 1 
      CL_BM2 Closed Loop Block Multiplier - bank 2 
      CL_BM_max Gasoline Fault Condition. Maximum (positive) allowed CL BM 
      CL_BM_min Gasoline Fault Condition. Minimum (negative) allowed CL BM 
      CL_CM_min_RMS Gasoline: EGO RMS Fault Limit 
      CL_CM_preRMSatt Gasoline catalyst monitor diagnostic entry condition: 
      EGO3/4 RMS > EGO1/2 RMS 
      CL_CM_waveRMSatt Gasoline: Fault Condition (EGO RMS > CL Waveform RMS * 
      CL_CM_waveRMSatt) 
      CL_control_type CL Control Type (Switch EGO/UEGO or Continuous (UEGO only) 

      CL_dis_Gsln Pre Catalyst Gasoline CL Switch (Enabled/Disabled) 
      CL_dis_LP LPG Closed Loop Control (Enable/Disable) 
      CL_dis_NG Pre Catalyst NG CL Switch (Enabled/Disabled) 
      CL_ena_value CL enable table output value in 0 -> 1 logical 
      CL_fuellev_low Low fuel monitoring status. When set to 'OK', either low 
      fuel monitoring is disabled or the specified input source for the active 
      fuel type is not indicating low fuel. When set to 'Low Fuel', the 
      specified input source for the active fuel is indicating low fuel. 
      CL_fuellev_mon When set to other than 'Disabled' and fuel is low, then AL 
      updates are inhibited and various faults can be inhibited from updating. A 
      low-fuel condition is determined by the selected input source(s) and 
      active fuel type. Some inputs sources are restricted to specific fuel 
      types.

      Available Input Sources:
      1) Fuel pressure switch / FP switch - refers to "Fuel pressure sensor 
      switch" on Inputs worksheet (IODI_fuel_pressure).
      2) Fuel level input - refers to "Fuel level input configuration" on Inputs 
      worksheet (fuellev_in_ena).
      3) FTPM - Fuel Tank Pressure Monitoring - refers to "Fuel tank pressure 
      monitoring mode" on Inputs worksheet (FTPM_mode).
      4) Gaseous Fuel Level (FLEV) Monitoring - refers to "Gaseous fuel level 
      monitoring" on Outputs worksheet (FLEV_ena).
      5) J1939 gasoline low fuel level - refers to SPN 64921 in ECI PGN 42346.
      6) NMHG J1939 - refers to SPN 65447 in ECI PGN 65296.
      7) Low Fuel Pressure Derate - refers to feature on Derate worksheet.

      The following groups of faults can be inhibited individually:
      1) CL low and CL high faults (fuel_mon_CL_lmt)
      2) CL control at limit faults (fuel_mon_CL_ctl_lmt)
      3) EPR / CFV low regulated pressure faults (fuel_mon_EPR_low)
      4) Low fuel pressure faults (fuel_mon_pres_low)
      5) Boost control faults (fuel_mon_boost)
      6) Pre-catalyst O2 sensor out of range fault (fuel_mon_precat_OOR) 
      CL_hi Currently active CL upper limit 
      CL_hi_postcat Gasoline: Post Catalyst Delta Phi max (positive value) 
      CL_HW_disable This switch indicates the current status of a closed loop 
      disabling hardware input. 
      CL_HW_dis_cfg This switch allows the selection of a hardware input pin 
      with an internal pullup resistor as an open-loop forcing signal when 
      grounded. 
      CL_inact_force force CL to the inactive state if it is already in 
      closed-loop mode 
      CL_Kiv_n_postcat Gasoline: Post Catalyst Kiv decreasing limit 
      CL_Kiv_p_postcat Gasoline: Post Catalyst Kiv increasing limit 
      CL_Ki_n_postcat Gasoline: Post Catalyst Ki decreasing limit

      CL_Ki_p_ROL Gasoline: ROL control Ki gain positive error 
      CL_Kp_n_postcat Gasoline: Post Catalyst Kp decreasing limit

      CL_Kp_p_postcat Gasoline: Post Catalyst Kp increasing limit 
      CL_Kp_p_ROL Gasoline: ROL control Kp gain positive error

      CL_lo_postcat Gasoline: Post Catalyst Delta Phi min (negative value)

      CL_phi_lmt_MAPmax CL air/fuel ratio control at limit - too rich'

      CL_phi_lmt_MAPmin CL air/fuel ratio control at limit - too rich' 
      diagnostic - MAP lower limit threshold

      Postcat phi lower limit threshold 
      CL_postcat_ena Gasoline Post Catalyst Control (Enable/Disable) 
      CL_postcat_gain Gasoline postcat gain selection 'Single-Point' or 
      'Table-Based'. 
      CL_postcat_winndlt This parameter is added to "ROL window low offset" and 
      the post-cat target phi to define a lower threshold for transitioning to 
      post-cat phi control. The purpose of this adder is to provide some 
      hysteresis to the first ROL post cat window when transitioning between ROL 
      and post-cat phi control. 
      CL_postcat_winpdlt This parameter is added to "ROL window high offset" and 
      the post-cat target phi to define an upper threshold for transitioning to 
      post-cat phi control. The purpose of this adder is to provide some 
      hysteresis to the first ROL post cat window when transitioning between ROL 
      and post-cat phi control. 
      CL_post_fastwr_tm This is the time that the closed loop fuel control will 
      be continuous when crossing between ROL temporary (mode 2) and post-cat 
      persistent (mode 1). 
      CL_ROLend_fastwrtm This is the time that the closed loop fuel control will 
      be continuous when crossing between ROL persistent (mode 0) and post-cat 
      temporary (mode 3). 
      CL_ROLend_tm_mode Parameter determines when the "Post-cat Temp Phi cont CL 
      time" parameter is used when changing the closed loop fuel control from 
      ROL persistent (mode 0) to post-cat temporary (mode 3). When set to 'Lean 
      Only', the "Post-cat Temp Phi cont CL time" is only used when crossing the 
      lower limit. When set to 'Lean or Rich', the "Post-cat Temp Phi cont CL 
      time" is used when crossing either the lower or upper limit. 
      CL_ROL_reinit_ena Enable re-initialization of ROL state to set point on 
      transition to ROL control 
      CL_ROL_reinit_hi Value at which to re-initialize ROL state on transition 
      to post-cat phi control - high 
      CL_ROL_reinit_lo Value at which to re-initialize ROL state on transition 
      to post-cat phi control - low 
      CL_ROL_res_dly Gasoline: ROL control resume delay after transition from 
      post-cat phi control 
      CL_ROL_trans_mode Parameter determines behavior when transitioning between 
      ROL and post-cat closed loop fuel control.

      When set to 'Legacy', transition between controllers is smooth, without 
      step changes in output.

      When set to 'Enhanced - Unidirectional', transition from ROL to post-cat 
      control accounts for ROL state re-initialization and will contain a step 
      change in output that reflects ROL state's error. Transition from post-cat 
      to ROL control will also contain a step change as ROL integrator is reset 
      to 0 upon transition.

      When set to 'Enhanced - Bidirectional', transition from ROL to post-cat 
      control is the same behavior as 'Enhanced - Unidirectional'. However, 
      transition from post-cat to ROL control will be smooth and without a step 
      change in output. 
      CL_ROL_win_n Gasoline: ROL SS control window lower limit, relative to 
      post-cat target phi 
      CL_ROL_win_p Gasoline: ROL SS control window upper limit, relative to 
      post-cat target phi 
      CL_rst_postcat This switch determines whether or not a non-zero post-cat 
      delta-phi value remains in effect and/or intact whenever the engine enters 
      an RPM/MAP area with post-cat control disabled by specifying a 0.000 
      post-cat phi target. The default mode of operation is for the post-cat 
      delta-phi to remain in use even though it is not being updated in the 
      region. The second mode is for any existing delta-phi to be remembered, 
      but not be used while in this region. The remembered value will be 
      reinstated as soon as the engine leaves the disabled post-cat region. The 
      third mode is for any existing delta-phi to be completely reset to zero in 
      this region. 
      CL_SS_dly Gasoline: Delay after adaptive count valid before transition to 
      steady-state control 
      CL_start_wait Closed loop start wait time - buffer to ensure stable 
      operation 
      CL_stepmax Gasoline: Closed Loop Max Step Allowed 
      CL_switch_type CL Switching Type (Legacy Asymmetric, Corrected Asymmetric, 
      or Symmetric) 
      CL_TD_EGOsw_ena Activates CL acquisition mode when the EGO fails to switch 
      within 1 transport delay of either a rich-lean or lean-rich CL perturb 
      transition. 
      CL_TD_enable Enable the transport delay model-based CL acquisition mode. 
      If an invalid CL duty cycle is detected, this mode ramps the CL multiplier 
      until an EGO transition is detected. 
      CL_TD_max_n During transport delay-based CL acquisition, the maximum 
      allowed overshoot in the lean direction. 
      CL_TD_max_p During transport delay-based CL acquisition, the maximum 
      allowed overshoot in the rich direction. 
      CL_TD_mdota Disables fast closed-loop acquire mode at low mass air flow 
      rates. Setting this parameter to '0' allows fast closed-loop to remain 
      enabled under all operating conditions. 
      CL_TD_sw_offset Acquisition mode is triggered when the EGO fails to switch 
      within transport delay * (1 + switch delay offset)of a lean-rich or 
      rich-lean CL perturbation. Positive values slow the response for allowfor 
      more transport delay error before triggering acqusition mode. 
      CL_TD_sw_pct Initial CL_BM step size when the EGO fails to switch, given 
      as a percent of the total EGO switching excursion 
      CL_temp_wait_mul Multiple of T_delay to wait after a transient/FSO before 
      re-enabling closed-loop. 
      CL_temp_wait_tmr temporary wait time before re-implementing closed-loop in 
      ms 
      CM1_RMScomp Catalyst monitor (bank 1) current RMS limit 
      CM1_RMSsrc Catalyst monitor (bank 1) comparison source 
      CM2_RMScomp Catalyst monitor (bank 2) current RMS limit 
      CM2_RMSsrc Catalyst monitor (bank 1) comparison source 
      CM_inphase_act Catalyst monitoring - 0=normal bank1/2 CL operation, 
      1=active in-phase bank1/2 CL operation 
      CM_post_delt_CBT Catalyst Bed Temperature upper limit entry condition for 
      both "Post-catalyst delta-phi at max/min limit" faults. 
      CM_post_delt_mdot Post Catalyst Mass Air Flow upper limit entry condition 
      for both "Post-catalyst delta-phi at max/min limit" faults. 
      CM_post_delt_phi_hi Offset below the post-catalyst delta-phi max creating 
      the upper limit for "Post-catalyst delta-phi at max limit" fault. 
      CM_post_delt_phi_lo Offset above the post-catalyst delta-phi min creating 
      the lower limit for "Post-catalyst delta-phi at min limit" fault. 
      CM_unresp_FSO_tm Time in FSO threshold for Post-catalyst sensor 
      unresponsive faults for bank 1 and 2. If a post-cat EGO sensor voltage 
      above the calibrated threshold is seen after the engine has been in FSO 
      for at least this long, the fault latch counter will begin to count up. 
      CM_unresp_maxV EGO voltage threshold for Post-catalyst sensor unresponsive 
      faults for bank 1 and 2. If the minimum time in FSO has been met and a 
      voltage above this value is seen from the post-cat EGO, the fault latch 
      counter will begin to count up. 
      CM_unresp_min_MAP Minimum MAP threshold for Post-catalyst sensor 
      unresponsive faults for bank 1 and 2 on exit from FSO. 
      CM_unresp_min_phi Specifies the minimum pre-catalyst equivalence ratio 
      threshold for the Catalyst Monitor sensor 1/2 unresponsive diagnostics. 
      CM_unresp_min_RPM Minimum RPM threshold for Post-catalyst sensor 
      unresponsive faults for bank 1 and 2 on exit from FSO. 
      CM_unresp_nstoich_en Specifies when to evaluate whether the phi command is 
      within normal closed-loop excursion limits. If set to "before FSO", the 
      phi command is only checked at entry to fuel shut-off. If set to "during 
      FSO", the phi command is checked continuously during fuel shut-off. This 
      setting only exists to preserve backwards compatibility and should be set 
      to "before FSO" in new calibrations. 
      CM_unresp_phi_tm Post-catalyst sensor unresponsive faults for bank 1 and 
      2. Maximum time to wait for a switch back to a rich condition after 
      exiting FSO. If the post-cat EGO voltage does not go above the calibrated 
      threshold within this time after FSO, and the MAP and RPM entry conditions 
      are met, the fault will immediately latch. 
      CM_unresp_pst_sw EGO voltage threshold for Post-catalyst sensor 
      unresponsive faults for bank 1 and 2 on exit from FSO. If the post-cat EGO 
      voltage does not go above this value within the calibrated time after 
      exiting FSO, and the MAP and RPM entry conditions are met, the fault will 
      immediately latch. 
      coil10_adv_cyl Cylinder 10 (firing order) advance spark offset

      Coil_turns Coil turns used by MAP KV 
      coldstrt_ECT Cold start mode will be active if the ECT latched at engine 
      start is below this threshold. If ECT is greater than or equal to this 
      value at engine start, then cold start mode will be disabled. 
      coldstrt_max_tm Maximum time that cold start mode is allowed to be active. 
      If timer is exceeded, cold start mode will disable and return to normal 
      operation regardless of individual CBT thresholds. 
      coldstrt_mode Enable switch for cold start emissions mode that controls 
      enhanced FSO enrichment, continuous phi control on cold start, and post 
      cat control disabled on cold start. If enabled, the mode is only active 
      once per engine cycle. 
      coldstrt_state Cold start operation state. Possible indications:
      - "Disabled": cold start emissions mode is disabled in the calibration
      - "Wait for start": engine is stopped, or has been running for less than 3 
      seconds
      - "Inactive": after engine start, ECT was above the threshold for cold 
      start operation
      - "Active": after engine start, ECT was below the threshold for cold start 
      operation
      - "Timed out": the engine was running longer than the maximum calibrated 
      time for cold start operation
      - "Complete": all features met their conditions for exiting cold start 
      operation 
      controller_flash Indicates the type of flash in the target Electronic 
      Control Unit (ECU). 
      controller_type Indicates the type of the target system that will be 
      controlled by the electronic control unit (ECU). 
      cooldown_ena Parameter enables cool down before shutdown requests to be 
      processed. A cool down/shut down sequence is requested using ECI PGN 
      42351, SPN 64866. Once a request is received, the cool down sequence will 
      initiate. After completion, the engine will shut down.

      A cool down sequence is as follows:
      1). Engine speed is ramped down from the initial speed to the target 
      speed, "Cool down speed". The ramp rate is configured using "Cool down 
      speed ramp rate". The governor is selected using "Cool down governor 
mode".
      2). Once engine speed has ramped to the target, the "Cool down min time" 
      is evaluated. If the minimum time has elapsed since the start of the cool 
      down, then the cool down temperatures are evaluated, "Cool down min 
      temperature #1" and "Cool down min temperature #2". The logic for 
      determining if the temperatures are cooled down is configured using "Cool 
      down temperature logic".
      3). Once the minimum time has elapsed and the temperatures have cooled, 
      the engine will shut down.

      The "Cool down max time" is used to limit the length of a cool down. If 
      the maximum time has elapsed since the start of the cool down, the engine 
      will shut down. 
      cooldown_gov_mode Determines which governor to use during a cool down. 
      When 'Active Gov' is selected, the active governor prior to the cool down 
      will be used during the cool down. The only exception is if the active 
      governor is Max Gov, then Min Gov is used. 
      cooldown_logic Parameter determines the temperature logic for terminating 
      a cool down.

      When configured as 'OR', the cool down terminates when either "Cool down 
      temperature #1" or "Cool down temperature #2" is below its respective 
      minimum value. If one temperature is disabled or faulted, then the other 
      temperature must fall below its respective minimum value.

      When configured as 'AND', the cool down terminates when both cool down 
      temperatures are below their respective minimum values. If one temperature 
      is disabled or faulted, then the other temperature must fall below its 
      respective minimum value.

      If both temperatures are disabled or faulted, then the cool down will 
      terminate based on the minimum cool down time, "Cool down min time". 
      cooldown_rpm Target cool down speed. When cool down initiates, the engine 
      speed is ramped to this parameter's value at a specified rate, "Cool down 
      speed ramp rate". 
      cooldown_rpmdt Engine speed ramp rate when ramping from the initial speed 
      at the beginning of a cool down to the target speed, "Cool down speed". 
      cooldown_state Cool down state. 
      cooldown_temp1 The first of two cool down temperatures used to terminate a 
      cool down. If "Cool down temperature #1" is configured to 'Disabled', this 
      parameter is not used. 
      cooldown_temp1_ena Configures the temperature source for the first cool 
      down temperature. When set to 'Disabled', the "Cool down min temperature 
      #1" is not used to determine when to terminate a cool down. 
      cooldown_temp2 The second of two cool down temperatures used to terminate 
      a cool down. If "Cool down temperature #2" is configured to 'Disabled', 
      this parameter is not used. 
      cooldown_temp2_ena Configures the temperature source for the second cool 
      down temperature. When set to 'Disabled', the "Cool down min temperature 
      #2" is not used to determine when to terminate a cool down. 
      cooldown_time_max Maximum allowed cool down duration. Parameter is 
      enforced throughout the entire cool down sequence. 
      cooldown_time_min Minimum cool down duration. Parameter is only enforced 
      after the speed has ramped to the target speed, "Cool down speed". The 
      cool down time is measured from the beginning of cool down cycle and 
      includes speed ramping. Ramping may take longer than this parameter, 
      depending on the engine speed when cool down initiates, the target speed - 
      "Cool down speed", and the ramp rate - "Cool down speed ramp rate". 
      CoolingH2OExpected Expected cooling water flow at a given engine speed 
      CoolingH2OFlowRate Actual cooling water flow at the current engine speed 
      CoolingH2OLow_pct Cooling water flow lower than expected' diagnostic - low 
      water flow percentage entry condition.

      COP Compressor outlet pressure 
      COT Compressor outlet temperature 
      COT_ena Compressor outlet temperature sensor input source 
      COT_hi_hyst Hysteresis to apply to the "COT higher than expected" COT 
      fault condition when latching the fault. For the fault condition to be 
      true, the COT must exceed the fault threshold plus this value. This does 
      not apply to fault unlatching.

      For example, if the COT threshold is set to 200 deg F and the hysteresis 
      is set to 20 deg F, the COT must exceed 220 deg F to latch the fault 
      provided the other fault conditions are also true. To unlatch the fault, 
      the COT must be 200 deg F or less. 
      COT_mdl Compressor outlet modeled temperature 
      COT_Taux_cal Calibration table selection for Compressor Outlet Temperature 
      (COT) input 
      COT_vdr Pullup resistor value for Compressor Outlet Temperature (COT) 
      input 
      crank_capture Capture edge (rising or falling) used for crank sensing. 
      Falling edges strongly recommended 
      crank_cnt_diag crank input diagnostic rolling tooth counter used by 
      crank/cam diagnostics 
      crank_cnt_diag_crk Crank input diagnostic rolling tooth counter used by 
      cam1 loss fault when engine is in cranking mode. 
      crank_cycles Number of engine cycles since the start of engine cranking 
      crank_gap_large_x This parameter should only be modified with EControls 
      permission. 
      crank_HW_cfg Crank input hardware interface configuration. 
      crank_latch_cnt start duty-cycle tracking variable for cranking limit 
      function 
      crank_LFP_lim_mult Multiplier used to effectively reduce the "Crank 
      limiter wind-up time" when the fuel pressure is low. Value cannot be 
      greater than 1. Only applicable when "Low fuel pressure crank limiter 
      behavior" is not set to 'Disabled'. 
      crank_LFP_mode Determines if the crank limiter wind-up and wind-down times 
      are adjusted when the fuel pressure is low. 

      When set to 'Modify wind-up time only' and the fuel pressure sensor switch 
      input indicates low fuel pressure, the "Crank limiter wind-up time" is 
      multiplied by the "Low fuel pressure crank wind-up multiplier", 
      effectively reducing the wind-up time.

      When set to 'Modify wind-up/down times' and the fuel pressure sensor 
      switch input indicates low fuel pressure, then the following occurs:
      1. The "Crank limiter wind-up time" is multiplied by the "Low fuel 
      pressure crank wind-up multiplier", effectively reducing the wind-up time.
      2. The "Crank limiter wind-down time" is multiplied by the "Low fuel 
      pressure crank wind-down multiplier", effectively increasing the wind-down 
      time.

      When set to 'Disabled', no modifications are made to wind-up and wind-down 
      times. 
      crank_LFP_open_wait If the "Low fuel pressure crank limiter pressure 
      source" is set to "Secondary fuel rail (LPG)", this value determines the 
      amount of delay after the fuel supply is turned on before the fuel 
      pressure is evaluated. 
      crank_LFP_Ptgt The low fuel pressure crank limiter target pressure. If the 
      Secondary Fuel Rail pressure is below the target, the low fuel pressure 
      crank limiter wind-up and wind-down multipliers will be active. 
      crank_LFP_Ptgt_LED Indicates fuel_type is LPG and the Secondary Fuel Rail 
      pressure is below the target so the low fuel pressure crank limiter 
      impacts to the wind-up and wind-down multipliers are active. 
      crank_LFP_Ptgt_mult If the "Low fuel pressure crank limiter pressure 
      source" is set to "Secondary fuel rail (LPG)", this value sets the 
      crank_LFP_Ptgt_mult used in the pressure evaluation:

      if FPin_I2 < ((MAP+1 bar) * crank_LFP_Ptgt_mult) then
      low fuel pressure is TRUE 
      crank_LFP_rst_mult Multiplier used to effectively increase the "Crank 
      limiter wind-down time" when the fuel pressure is low. Value cannot be 
      less than 1. Only applicable when "Low fuel pressure crank limiter 
      behavior" is set to 'Modify wind-up/down times'. 
      crank_LFP_src Selects the fuel pressure source and associated logic to 
      determine if the fuel pressure is low, and if the crank limiter wind-up 
      and wind-down times should be adjusted. 

      IODI fuel pressure switch - the "Fuel pressure sensor switch" on the 
      'Inputs' worksheet must be configured.

      Secondary fuel rail (LPG) - the FPin_I2 fuel pressure will be used when 
      the fuel type is LPG. Low fuel pressure will be calculated:

      if FPin_I2 < ((MAP+1 bar) * crank_LFP_Ptgt_mult) then
      low fuel pressure is TRUE 
      crank_lim_ena This switch engages the crank limiter function to either 
      prevent starter damage or allow auto-cranking.

      There are fundamentally two different modes of operation:

      1) Starter-Lockout Mode: This mode assumes that the starter solenoid 
      signal originates from a key-switch in the START position and passes 
      through a NORMALLY CLOSED (N/C) or NORMALLY OPEN (N/O) relay that may be 
      controlled by the ECM. In this mode, the ECM will open the starter control 
      relay to prevent over-cranking the engine according to the timer 
      parameters below. In pass-through mode, the starter will not engage unless 
      an active start signal is received.

      2) Auto-Crank Mode: This mode assumes that the starter solenoid signal 
      originates from a key-switch in the ON position and passes through a 
      NORMALLY OPEN (N/O) relay that may be closed by the ECM. The ECM can be 
      configured to crank the engine whenever switch power is on or only 
      following a "request to start" type trigger signal - which can be 
      configured using the software switch below labeled "Start signal input". 
      crank_lim_wt While the engine is cranking (or if the starter is on in 
      auto-crank mode and the “Auto-crank starter-on wind-up” option is Enabled) 
      a timer is incremented. Once this timer reaches this configured value the 
      starter will be disabled. This limits the maximum amount of time the 
      engine will be cranked in a single attempt. The wind-up limit does not 
      apply to remote start attempts. 
      crank_mag_dec_tau Low pass time constant for sensing the falling edges of 
      the crank teeth 
      crank_mag_inc_tau Low pass time constant for sensing the rising edges of 
      the crank teeth 
      crank_mag_maxpct Limits the PWM trigger level output to this percentage of 
      the adaptive trigger level measurement. Generally, 80% provides reasonably 
      robust performance. 
      crank_mag_trig_min Amplitude, multiply by 2 for peak-to-peak voltage 
      trigger. 
      crank_min_pw Enter the minimum pulse width. Pulses smaller than this will 
      be rejected and treated as noise. This value should be < 6.4us. Set this 
      parameter to zero to disable the noise cancellation feature. 
      crank_rise_trigger Crank rising trigger level 
      Crank_rpm RPM at which the controller recognizes that the engine has begun 
      turning. Any RPM less than this is considered a STOPPED engine. 
      crank_rst_mode Specifies when the crank limit timers should be reset. When 
      set to the default, "Reset at key off":
      - While the key switch is off, "Crank limiter duty-cycle" is set to 0% and 
      "Cumulative crank-time" is reset.
      - When "Starter control mode" is set to "N/O Starter-Lockout Pass-Thru", 
      the "Cumulative crank-time" is reset each time the "Start signal input" 
      toggles.

      When set to "Decay after key off":
      - While the key is off, "Crank limiter duty-cycle" unlatches normally.
      - "Cumulative crank-time" is reset only when the key is off.

      When set to "Decay from 100% after engine stop":
      - "Crank limiter duty-cycle" is momentarily set to 100% whenever the 
      engine stops, whether caused by key off, stall, or failed crank attempt.
      - "Crank limiter duty-cycle" only decays while the engine is stopped.
      - "Cumulative crank-time" is reset only when the key is off.

      The recommended setting is "Decay after key off" to prevent bypassing 
      crank limits by cycling the key switch. 
      crank_rst_wt While the starter is off, a timer is kept and once the 
      calibrated “Crank limited wind-down time” has passed the next engine start 
      attempt may be performed or, depending on configuration, the auto-crank 
      functionality may restart. This ensures a certain amount of time passes 
      in-between start attempts. The timer is reset based on the selection for 
      "Crank limiter reset mode". The wind-up limit does not apply to remote 
      start attempts. 
      crank_SD_latch This software switch controls behavior of the starter 
      control relay when the starter control mode is set to 'Auto-Crank' 
      following an engine diagnostic shutdown event.

      If this switch is set to 'Disabled', then the engine will immediately 
      begin a restart the next time an auto-crank trigger is detected.

      If the "Start signal input" is set to 'Disabled (key-on)', then the engine 
      will immediately begin a restart after the engine has stopped if the 
      key-switch power remains on.

      If this switch is set to 'Enabled', then the engine will NOT begin a 
      restart following an engine diagnostic shutdown the next time a start 
      signal is detected until key-switch power is cycled off and back on. 
      crank_skip_teeth Used on high tooth count flywheels to select the number 
      of teeth to skip. The skipped teeth will be counted and shown in CCDL, but 
      will not be used to trigger ignition or fueling. 
      crank_tooth_CAD Most recent crank tooth edge position in absolute CAD 
      crank_tooth_cnt engine tooth counter, value is between [0, 
      teeth_per_cycle] where teeth_per_cycle = 720*CAD_per_tooth_avg 
      crank_tooth_saved logical indicating whether the crank tooth stored in the 
      persistent data area is valid 
      crank_total ms total cranking time accumulator 
      crank_total_lim The maximum cumulative cranking time that may occur before 
      starting is disabled. The cumulative cranking timer is reset based on the 
      selection for "Crank limiter reset mode". 
      crank_trans_FBlim If the "Transmission in-gear override" is set to 
      'Starter Output Feedback', this is the threshold the low/high-side 
      feedback must meet for starter-lockout/auto-crank control to become 
      active. If the selected starter control output channel is a low-side 
      output, this is the lower limit. If the selected starter control output 
      channel is a high-side output, this is the upper limit. 
      crank_trans_lim When set to a value greater than 0, this setting provides 
      a mechanism to allow starting when the "Transmission in-gear override" is 
      actively preventing start. Once the signal on the "Start signal input" is 
      held active for this amount of time then the "Transmission in-gear 
      override" functionality will begin to be ignored and will continue to be 
      ignored for as long as the start signal remains active.

      When "Transmission in-gear override" is set to 'Park/Neut Switch and ETC7 
      Required', this feature can be disabled by ETC7. See "Transmission in-gear 
      override" for details. 
      crank_trans_lim_actv active/inactive indication for when starter-lockout 
      has been overridden by the "Transmission in-gear override limit" feature 
      (0=inactive, 1=active) 
      crank_trans_lim_tmr time that the start signal input has been continuously 
      active in ms 
      crank_trans_neut Disables starter engagement and auto-cranking if the 
      transmission is in-gear.

      When set to 'Park/Neut Switch and ETC7 Required', then SPN 2900 (ECI SPN 
      3086) in ETC7 (ECI PGN 65098) is required to be available and indicating 
      that cranking is enabled. If SPN is not available, in error, or indicating 
      that cranking is disabled, then start is inhibited and "Transmission 
      in-gear override limit" feature is disabled. If SPN is indicating that 
      cranking is enabled, then the "Trans/Park neutral safety switch" on the 
      Inputs worksheet determines if start is allowed.

      Note: PGN 61445 must be added to the supported PGN lists if the J1939 ETC2 
      option is selected. PGN 65098 must be added to the supported PGN lists if 
      ETC7 option is selected. 
      crank_trans_wait If the transmission in-gear override is enabled and a 
      non-zero value is entered here, the starter engagement after key-on will 
      be delayed by this amount of time. This option is mainly intended to 
      handle CAN-communicated delays for the J1939 ETC2 transmission in-gear 
      check on wake-up, though it is active and available for all transmission 
      in-gear override modes. 
      CRI1_boost_raw CRI bank 1 boost voltage 
      CRI1_HWfault_latch CRI bank 1 fault flag latch 
      CRI1_LS_i_raw CRI bank 1 low-side current feedback 
      CRI1_V_boost_filt CRI bank 1 current boost voltage

      CRI2_HWfault_latch CRI bank 2 fault flag latch

      CRI2_V_boost_filt CRI bank 2 current boost voltage

      CRIPcal_V 1D Interpolation Table: Rail pressure sensor voltage input

      operating mode

      CRI_bst_dP_scalar6 This value is used as a fixed throttle delta-P command

      worksheet is used. 
      CRI_bst_dP_slct0 Boost EMP throttle delta-P - Diesel Engine Operating Mode

      CRI_cad_Gpr The pulse timing for advanced purge

      CRI_DOC_Tcl_slct0 If enabled, the post 2 fueling quantity will be adjusted 
      to maintain the specified DOC outlet temperature target. 
      CRI_DOC_Tcl_slct1 DOC closed-loop T control (If enabled, the post 2 
      fueling quantity will be adjusted to maintain the specified DOC outlet

      CRI_EGR_dP_slct0 EGR minimum delta-P - Diesel Engine Operating Mode 0 
      CRI_EGR_dP_slct1 EGR minimum delta-P - Diesel Engine Operating Mode 1 
      CRI_EGR_dP_slct2 EGR minimum delta-P - Diesel Engine Operating Mode 2 
      CRI_EGR_dP_slct3 EGR minimum delta-P - Diesel Engine Operating Mode 3 
      CRI_EGR_dP_slct4 EGR minimum delta-P - Diesel Engine Operating Mode 4 
      CRI_EGR_dP_slct5 EGR minimum delta-P - Diesel Engine Operating Mode 5

      CRI_FPerr_high For CRI systems, this is the high fuel pressure tolerance 
      that is added to the current fuel pressure target for fault detection. 
      CRI_FPerr_low For CRI systems, this is the low fuel pressure tolerance 
      that is subtracted from the current fuel pressure target for fault 
      detection. Note that this value is positive. 
      CRI_grneng This selects the allowed/enabled modes for green-engine fuel 
      rail air purge initiation. 'Manual trigger only' allows and requires user 
      interaction to arm the trigger for purge initiation. 'Manual or Zero-Hour 
      trigger' allows and enables manual arming or automatically arms the system 
      in a zero-hour first-start scenario for purge initiation.

      NOTE: If only green-engine air purge is required, the other 'General' rail 
      purge mode switch should be set to 'Disabled'. These 2 modes (General and 
      Green-engine) are independent and may be enabled separately or at the same 
      time. 
      CRI_grneng_mantrig Trigger to arm initiation of green engine fuel rail air 
      purge operation once the engine begins to cranking. Note that this switch 
      can also automatically arm in 'ZeroHour' mode in a zero hour first start 
      scenario. 
      CRI_grneng_state Current state of the green engine fuel rail airpurge 
      function. 
      CRI_hardware_config Common-rail injection hardware configuration. 
      CRI_hold_decay Injector hold current decay 
      CRI_hold_recharge This switch selects whether or not the boost voltage 
      capacitors are recharged during the 'hold' phase of a pulse-width. If this 
      switch is set to 'Disabled', recharging only occurs on a bank after a 
      pulse ends. If it is set to 'Enabled', recharging begins after the 
      'CRI_peakhold_decay' time following the end of the peak phase. 
      cri_Iinj_samp Sampled CRI injection current value for testing CRT/BIP 
      detection circuit 
      CRI_IMVcad_final For pulsedIMV control, this is the final CAD equivalent 
      of the pulse. Note that it may be negative due to the margin extension of 
      the base control pulse. 
      CRI_IMVcad_max In CAD-Pulse IMV control mode, this is the maximum 
      mechanical CAD control duration (which is always positive) produced by the 
      sum of the PID and feedforward control terms. Note that it excludes the 
      zero-response time offset CAD equivalent value. 
      CRI_IMVcad_min In CAD-Pulse IMV control mode, this is the minimum 
      mechanical CAD control duration (which may be negative) produced by the 
      sum of the PID and feedforward control terms. Note that it excludes the 
      zero-response time offset CAD equivalent value. 
      CRI_IMVd_fHz IMV dither frequency 
      CRI_IMVd_imag IMV dither amplitude 
      CRI_IMVff_mode This is the mode selector for the function of the IMV 
      feedforward table. It selects how the table values are used. In continuous 
      mode, the only valid values are Disabled, Amps, and mA/mg. In pulsed mode 
      the only valid values are Disabled and us/mg. 
      CRI_IMVff_TLU IMV feedforward table lookup value 
      CRI_IMVi_cmd IMV current commnd - final 
      CRI_IMVi_FB For continuous IMV mode this is the average current over 1 
      dither period. For pulsed IMV mode this is the peak current. 
      CRI_IMVi_halfpeak For pulsedIMV mode only, this is the current sample 
      taken at 1/2 the risetime to peak current at the start of the IMV pulsed 
      waveform. This is the value used for pulsedIMV overcurrent diagnostics. 
      CRI_IMVi_max The maximum allowed current command to the IMV when operated 
      in continuous mode. This limit is applied even during manual control. 
      CRI_IMVi_min The minimum allowed current command to the IMV when operated 
      in continuous mode. This is an unsigned value that should never be < 0. 
      CRI_IMVi_raw For continuous IMV mode, this is the same as the normal 
      feedback current which is the average current over 1 dither period. For 
      pulsed IMV mode, this is the non lowpass filter compensated peak current. 
      CRI_IMVpw_CAD In CAD-Pulse IMV control mode, this is the desired 
      electrical duration of the trigger pulse for the start of the mechanical 
      duration. This value may be overridden by the min/max electrical on-time 
      values. 
      CRI_IMVpw_cmd For pulsedIMV control, this is the effective IMV control 
      pulse duration in ms based the control loop and feedforward computations. 
      It DOES NOT include any additional noneffective 'CRI_IMVp_baseline' which 
      occurs after the effective IMV inlet cutoff CAD. 
      CRI_IMVpw_max For pulsed-IMV control, this is the upper-limit of allowed 
      control on-time for effective pulse durations. 
      CRI_IMVpw_min For pulsed-IMV control, this is the lower-limit of allowed 
      control on-time for effective pulse durations. NOTE - this number should 
      generally be slightly negative to accommodate errors in 
      'CRI_IMVp_baseline'. 
      CRI_IMVpw_total For pulsedIMV control, this is the total IMV control pulse 
      duration in ms. This includes both 'effective' and 'noneffective' duration 
      contributions from 'CRI_IMVpw_cmd' and 'CRI_IMVp_baseline'. 
      CRI_IMVp_acc_max IMV raill pressure accumulator maximum 
      CRI_IMVp_acc_min IMV raill pressure accumulator minimum 
      CRI_IMVp_baseline This is a IMV pressure control offset value (in amps for 
      continuous control or ms for time/CAD pulsed control) that is added to the 
      PID and feedforward values to form the total control output term. It is 
      the typical zero-response current in continuous mode, and it is the 
      mechanical response time compensation for pulsed mode. 
      CRI_IMVp_Ddz Cubic rolloff dead-zone to be applied to the diesel rail 
      pressure edot value in the derivative (Kd) PID signal chain. 
      CRI_IMVp_ff This is the final computed feedforward control term in either 
      amps (for continuous mode) or ms (for pulsed mode) based on the table 
      lookup value and the feedforward selected mode 'CRI_IMVff_mode'. 
      CRI_IMVp_FSO_Ifrz During fuel shutoff, if the diesel rail pressure edot is 
      decaying (negative) at a rate less than this negative value, the IMV 
      integrator will not wind towards greater fuel pressure reduction. This 
      value should be a negative value - positive values do not make physical 
      sense. 
      CRI_IMVp_Kd IMV rail pressure Kd gain 
      CRI_IMVp_Ki IMV rail pressure Ki gain 
      CRI_IMVp_Kp IMV rail pressure Kp gain 
      CRI_IMVp_NCvalve Selects the type of IMV (inlet metering valve) on a CRI 
      system (diesel or GDI). Normally Open allows fuel to flow at 0 current, 
      Normally Closed is shut at 0 current. 
      CRI_IMV_ena IMV output enable switch 
      CRI_IMV_HW_period This is the hardware PWM output drive frequency for the 
      IMV driver. Driver heating may be a concern above 10 KHz.
      NOTE: key-switch power must be cycled for this value to take effect. 
      CRI_IMV_Iaccum IMV rail pressure control integrator 
      CRI_IMV_Iinit This is the initialization value for the IMV rail pressure 
      control integrator when starting up or transitioning to active PID control 
      mode. Depending on the continuous or pulsed IMV mode the units are either 
      amps,ms,CAD (CTLunits). 
      CRI_IMV_mH IMV inductance L 
      CRI_IMV_ohms IMV resistance R estimate 
      CRI_IMV_ohms_Ki IMV resistance R gain 
      CRI_IMV_ohms_max IMV resistance R maximum 
      CRI_IMV_ohms_min IMV resistance R minimum 
      CRI_IMV_ohms_nom IMV resistance R nominal 
      CRI_IMV_PID IMV rail pressure control PID term 
      CRI_IMV_pulsed Specifies continuous or pulsed (engine synchronous) control 
      output strategy for the IMV (inlet metering valve) in a CRI (diesel or 
      GDI) system. 
      CRI_IMV_Vdiode IMV recirculation diode drop 
      CRI_i_hold Injector hold current 
      CRI_i_hold_BIP Hold current for BIP detection pulse 
      CRI_i_HS_short Injector high-side short current 
      CRI_i_hys Injector peak/hold hysteresis 
      CRI_i_LS_short Injector low-side short current 
      CRI_i_peak Injector peak current 
      CRI_i_peak_BIP Peak current for BIP detection pulse 
      CRI_i_peak_init If this feature is supported on the CR injector driver, 
      this is the 'Initial' peak current trigger setpoint. This is a higher 
      instantaneous current that the injector is driven to prior to normal peak 
      current with chopping control. This current is typically higher than the 
      normal peak current and is typically used on GDI systems. 
      CRI_i_peak_init_BIP Initial peak current for BIP detection pulse 
      CRI_i_PH_offset Current trigger offset for peak-to-hold transition of the 
      CRI injector driver system.The nominal peak->hold trigger point is at the 
      middle of hold current switching waveform (i.e. average(hold, 
      hold-hysteresis)). This value shift that trigger up (+) and down (-) from 
      this nominal point. 
      CRI_i_recharge Boost recharging during hold phase. This switch selects 
      whether or not the boost voltage capacitors are recharged during the 
      'hold' phase of a pulse-width. 
      CRI_last_rise_time1 For CR injectors, this is the measured risetime from 
      injection start to the peak current target in us. 
      CRI_last_rise_time2 Common rail injector 2A peak current rise time 
      CRI_last_rise_time3 Common rail injector 1B peak current rise time 
      CRI_last_rise_time4 Common rail injector 2B peak current rise time 
      CRI_last_rise_time5 Common rail injector 1C peak current rise time 
      CRI_last_rise_time6 Common rail injector 2C peak current rise time 
      CRI_last_rise_time7 Common rail injector 1D peak current rise time 
      CRI_last_rise_time8 Common rail injector 2D peak current rise time 
      CRI_lift_pump_ena Low-pressure lift pump output enable switch 
      CRI_LS_PH_off Calibration variable to set behavior of low-side FET during 
      decay from peak to hold current levels 
      CRI_mainpo1_margin Main - Post 1 margin 
      CRI_mainpo2_margin Main - Post 2 margin
