      EGO1Z_H_Iacc EGO1 impedance based PI heater control integrator 
      EGO1Z_ohms EGO1 measured impedance in ohms. 
      EGO1Z_Rd EGOZ heater PI control loop target impedance. 
      EGO1Z_samp_fail Number of tries since last successful try to 
      EGO1_config EGO/UEGO configuration is predicated on the following 
      assumptions:
      1) Limited to 2 or fewer pre-catalyst sensors
      2) Limited to 2 or fewer post-catalyst sensors
      3) A post-catalyst sensor must have a matching pre-catalyst sensor 
defined.

      The ECM examines the sensors in order (1-4). The first pre-catalyst sensor 
      found will be associated with Bank 1. The second pre-catalyst sensor will 
      be associated with Bank 2 or will be used for averaging. The first 
      post-catalyst sensor will be associated with Bank 1. The second 
      post-catalyst sensor will be associated with Bank 2.

      Example:
      EGO1/UEGO1 is configured as post-catalyst.
      EGO2/UEGO2 is configured as post-catalyst.
      EGO3/UEGO3 is configured as pre-catalyst.
      EGO4/UEGO4 is configured as pre-catalyst.

      The bank association will be as follows:
      Bank 1 pre-cat: EGO3/UEGO3
      Bank1 post-cat: EGO1/UEGO1
      Bank2 pre-cat: EGO4/UEGO4
      Bank3 post-cat: EGO2/UEGO2 
      EGO1_phiFB EGO1 current phi 
      EGO1_phiFB_avg EGO1 average phi 
      EGO1_phiFB_dphidt EGO1 phi derivative 
      EGO1_phiFB_RMS EGO1 phi RMS 
      EGO1_raw EGO1 raw volts 
      EGO1_volts EGO1 measurement 
      EGO2flag System flag - XEGO2 
      EGO2H_DC EGO2 heater duty cycle 
      EGO2H_FB_volts EGO2 heater low-side feedback 
      EGO2H_LS_raw EGO2 heater low-side feedback (raw volts) 
      EGO2H_V_d EGO2 heater voltage target 
      EGO2Z_H_Iacc EGO2 impedance based PI heater control integrator 
      EGO2Z_ohms EGO2 measured impedance in ohms. 
      EGO2Z_Rd EGOZ heater PI control loop target impedance. 
      EGO2Z_samp_fail Number of tries since last successful try to 
      EGO2_config The ECM examines the sensors in order (14). The first 
      precatalyst sensor found will be associated with Bank 1. The second 
      precatalyst sensor will be associated with Bank 2 or will be used for 
      averaging. The first postcatalyst sensor will be associated with Bank 1. 
      The second postcatalyst sensor will be associated with Bank 2. 
      EGO2_phiFB EGO2 current phi 
      EGO2_phiFB_avg EGO2 average phi 
      EGO2_phiFB_dphidt EGO2 phi derivative 
      EGO2_phiFB_RMS EGO2 phi RMS 
      EGO2_raw EGO2 raw volts 
      EGO2_volts EGO2 measurement 
      EGO3flag System flag - XEGO3 
      EGO3H_DC EGO3 heater duty cycle 
      EGO3H_FB_volts EGO3 heater low-side feedback 
      EGO3H_LS_raw EGO3 heater low-side feedback (raw volts) 
      EGO3H_V_d EGO3 heater voltage target 
      EGO3Z_H_Iacc EGO3 impedance based PI heater control integrator 
      EGO3Z_ohms EGO3 measured impedance in ohms. 
      EGO3Z_Rd EGOZ heater PI control loop target impedance. 
      EGO3Z_samp_fail Number of tries since last successful try to 
      EGO3_config The ECM examines the sensors in order (14). The first 
      precatalyst sensor found will be associated with Bank 1. The second 
      precatalyst sensor will be associated with Bank 2 or will be used for 
      averaging. The first postcatalyst sensor will be associated with Bank 1. 
      The second postcatalyst sensor will be associated with Bank 2. 
      EGO3_phiFB EGO3 current phi 
      EGO3_phiFB_avg EGO3 average phi 
      EGO3_phiFB_dphidt EGO3 phi derivative 
      EGO3_phiFB_RMS EGO3 phi RMS 
      EGO3_raw EGO3 raw volts 
      EGO3_volts EGO3 measurement 
      EGO4flag System flag - XEGO4 
      EGO4H_DC EGO4 heater duty cycle 
      EGO4H_FB_volts EGO4 heater low-side feedback 
      EGO4H_LS_raw EGO4 heater low-side feedback (raw volts) 
      EGO4H_V_d EGO4 heater voltage target 
      EGO4Z_H_Iacc EGO4 impedance based PI heater control integrator 
      EGO4Z_ohms EGO4 measured impedance in ohms. 
      EGO4Z_Rd EGOZ heater PI control loop target impedance. 
      EGO4Z_samp_fail Number of tries since last successful try to 
      EGO4_config The ECM examines the sensors in order (14). The first 
      precatalyst sensor found will be associated with Bank 1. The second 
      precatalyst sensor will be associated with Bank 2 or will be used for 
      averaging. The first postcatalyst sensor will be associated with Bank 1. 
      The second postcatalyst sensor will be associated with Bank 2. 
      EGO4_phiFB EGO4 current phi 
      EGO4_phiFB_avg EGO4 average phi 
      EGO4_phiFB_dphidt EGO4 phi derivative 
      EGO4_phiFB_RMS EGO4 phi RMS 
      EGO4_raw EGO4 raw volts 
      EGO4_volts EGO4 measurement 
      EGOH1_off_loDC EGOH1 open / ground short diagnostic: PWM duty cycle lower 
      limit entry condition 
      EGOH1_off_loVf EGOH1 open / ground short diagnostic: low-side feedback 
      lower limit entry condition 
      EGOH1_on_hiDC EGOH1 short to power diagnostic: PWM duty cycle upper limit 
      entry condition 
      EGOH1_on_hiVf EGOH1 short to power diagnostic: low-side feedback upper 
      limit entry condition 
      EGOH1_PWM_manual EGOH1 PWM duty-cycle manual mode 
      EGOH2_off_loDC EGOH2 open / ground short diagnostic: PWM duty cycle lower 
      limit entry condition 
      EGOH2_off_loVf EGOH2 open / ground short diagnostic: low-side feedback 
      lower limit entry condition 
      EGOH2_on_hiDC EGOH2 short to power diagnostic: PWM duty cycle upper limit 
      entry condition 
      EGOH2_on_hiVf EGOH2 short to power diagnostic: low-side feedback upper 
      limit entry condition 
      EGOH2_PWM_manual EGOH2 PWM duty-cycle manual mode 
      EGOH3_off_loDC EGOH3 open / ground short diagnostic: PWM duty cycle lower 
      limit entry condition 
      EGOH3_off_loVf EGOH3 open / ground short diagnostic: low-side feedback 
      lower limit entry condition 
      EGOH3_on_hiDC EGOH3 short to power diagnostic: PWM duty cycle upper limit 
      entry condition 
      EGOH3_on_hiVf EGOH3 short to power diagnostic: low-side feedback upper 
      limit entry condition 
      EGOH3_PWM_manual EGOH3 PWM duty-cycle manual mode 
      EGOH4_off_loDC EGOH4 open / ground short diagnostic: PWM duty cycle lower 
      limit entry condition 
      EGOH4_off_loVf EGOH4 open / ground short diagnostic: low-side feedback 
      lower limit entry condition 
      EGOH4_on_hiDC EGOH4 short to power diagnostic: PWM duty cycle upper limit 
      entry condition 
      EGOH4_on_hiVf EGOH4 short to power diagnostic: low-side feedback upper 
      limit entry condition 
      EGOH4_PWM_manual EGOH4 PWM duty-cycle manual mode 
      EGOHpost_pre_wt_mult Multiplier for calculating the post-cat EGO heater 
      wait time. This value is multiplied by the total preheat time for the 
      pre-cat sensor, which includes delay time, preheat time, and dewpoint wait 
      time. The EGO Heater Control Target Impedance/Voltage Limit Schedule 
      begins when the wait time lapses. 
      EGOHpost_run_mode This switch determines the post-cat EGO heater control 
      mode. The normal mode is 'On when engine is running' and will always allow 
      active heater control to the impedance setpoint while the engine is 
      running.

      The second mode is the same, except that the heater power is halted if 
      post-cat EGO feedback is disabled in an engine operating condition by 
      specifying a 0.000 post-cat phi target.

      The third mode replicates the first mode, but also keeps the post-cat EGO 
      heater on if the pre-cat UEGO heater is on. The 'UEGO heater stays on at 
      engine stop when key-ON' timer will also hold the post-cat EGO heater on. 
      This mode is intended for hybrid applications where the engine halts 
      temporarily with the key-on. 
      EGOHpost_run_tmr Timer for using the EGO Heater Control Target 
      Impedance/Voltage Limit Schedule with a post-cat EGO sensor.. 
      EGOHpost_wait_tm Time to wait before starting the EGO Heater Control 
      Target Impedance/Voltage Limit Schedule. 
      EGOHpost_wait_tmr Elapsed wait time before starting the EGO Heater Control 
      Target Impedance/Voltage Limit Schedule. 
      EGOH_PWM1_DC EGOH1 PWM duty-cycle 
      EGOH_PWM2_DC EGOH2 PWM duty-cycle 
      EGOH_PWM3_DC EGOH3 PWM duty-cycle 
      EGOH_PWM4_DC EGOH4 PWM duty-cycle 
      EGOH_Vdef_postcat Default voltage used for postcat heater calculations if 
      impedance samples fail 
      EGOH_Vdef_precat Default voltage used for precat heater calculations if 
      impedance samples fail 
      EGOZ_enable Switch: Controls the EGO impedance sample system (Monitor only 
      or Heater Control) 
      EGOZ_heatoff_ena Turns off the EGO heaters during impedance sampling in 
      order to produce a more reliable and consistent result. 
      EGOZ_H_Iinit Whenever the key is off or the engine is stopped, the EGOZ 
      based heater control loop integrator will be reset to this value. Set this 
      to a low value for a soft heater startup, and set it to the default heater 
      voltage for a rapid startup. 
      EGOZ_H_Ki EGOZ heater PI control loop integrator gain. 
      EGOZ_H_Kp EGOZ heater PI control loop proportional gain. 
      EGOZ_H_Vmax EGOZ heater PI control loop maximum voltage command (and 
      integrator lower limit). 
      EGOZ_H_Vmin EGOZ heater PI control loop minimum voltage command (and 
      integrator lower limit). 
      EGOZ_poll_tout Time between EGOZ sample queueing per sensor. 
      EGOZ_presamp Time required to take an initial EGO voltage sample before 
      applying an impedance pulse. 
      EGOZ_presamp_SStol EGO impedance pre-sample point-to-point variance 
      tolerance at a sampling rate of approximately 15us per sample. 
      EGOZ_pulse_t Duration of an impedance sampling pulse (single direction). 
      EGOZ_pulse_thresh Pre-sample voltage threshold to determine whether the 
      impedance sampling pulse is high-pulling or low-pulling. 
      EGOZ_Rcold_def Cold default initialization value for the EGO impedance 
      values. 
      EGOZ_Rhot_postcat EGO impedance threshold below which the post-cat 
      sensor(s) are considered to be 'hot' or 'active'. 
      EGOZ_Rhot_precat EGO impedance threshold below which the pre-cat sensor(s) 
      are considered to be 'hot' or 'active'. 
      EGOZ_samp_fail_lim Number of tries to allow a sensor to obtain a valid 
      impedance sample before returning to a default heater control voltage. 
      EGOZ_sensor 0,1,2 = EGO1,2,3 
      EGOZ_settle_final Time to wait on an individual sensor to recover after an 
      impedance sampling cycle. 
      EGOZ_settle_ini Time after initial pre-sampling time waiting for op-amp to 
      settle on drive pulse state. 
      EGOZ_state 0=idle, 1=init, 1=done 
      EGO_phidt_n Window used to calculate rate of change of phi, used for CL 
      calculations 
      EGRad_adapt_Amin The max adaptive correction for any particular entry in 
      the area adaptive table is given by 

      max(min limit, learn +/- limit * nominal area)

      Examples:
      if adaptive learn +/- limit = 50%
      and adaptive learn min limit = 0.200 in^2

      For a nominal 0.1 in^2 entry, a 0.2 in^2 correction is allowed
      For a nominal 1.0 in^2 entry, a 0.5 in^2 correction is allowed

      The CdA adaptive limits (determined by this parameter and the +/- limit 
      multiplier) are shown in the nominal valve CdA plot. 
      EGRad_adapt_dz The max adaptive correction for any particular entry in the 
      area adaptive table is given by 
      EGRad_adapt_lim The max adaptive correction for any particular entry in 
      the area adaptive table is given by 

      max(min limit, learn +/- limit * nominal area)

      Examples:
      if adaptive learn +/- limit = 50%
      and adaptive learn min limit = 0.200 in^2

      For a nominal 0.1 in^2 entry, a 0.2 in^2 correction is allowed
      For a nominal 1.0 in^2 entry, a 0.5 in^2 correction is allowed

      The CdA adaptive limits (determined by this parameter and the +/- min area 
      limit) are shown in the nominal valve CdA plot. 
      EGRad_adapt_status EGR adaptive area status 
      EGRad_adapt_valid If the absolute value of the flow error is more than 
      this value, no further adaptive updates are performed until closed-loop 
      has been allowed to reduce the error below this amount. 
      EGRad_adapt_wait If CL or adaptive updates are disallowed for any reason 
      (other than the deadzone requirement), this wait time is imposed after CL 
      updates begin before adaptive updates resume. 
      EGRad_CdA_in2 EGR adaptive correction 
      EGRad_CLadapt_assist Parameter used to assist CL/adaptive correction 
      calibration 
      EGRad_CL_actlmt active EGR closed-loop final CL correction limit 
      EGRad_CL_Dz If the accumulated and averaged EGR% error over an engine 
      cycle is less than this amount, the CL accumulator will not be updated. 
      EGRad_CL_K This gain is applied to the average EGR% error accumulated 1 
      transport delay period, and used to update the CL EGR% command. 
      EGRad_CL_Kd Closed loop control derivative gain 
      EGRad_CL_Kp Closed loop control proportional gain 
      EGRad_CL_lim Obsoleted parameter 
      EGRad_CL_pct current EGR closed-loop correction % diluent in 
      floating-point 
      EGRad_CL_status indicates status of the EGR CL updates but remains latched 
      with disabling conditions 
      EGRad_CL_updates EGRad_CL_updates 
      EGRad_CL_valid_cnt Number of valid CL updates required before adaptive 
      updates engage. Enter '0' to disable this wait period. 
      EGRad_cmdact_err EGR command tracking error as command - actual in % 
      EGRad_cmdact_ss_dtau If a steadystate diluent error exists, the spark 
      timing is adjusted and is lowpass filtered using this (large) time 
      constant when the error is decreasing. 
      EGRad_cmdact_ss_err EGR command tracking error as command - actual in %, 
      steady-state estimate using low-pass filter on increasing error, instant 
      drop on decreasing error 
      EGRad_cmdact_ss_itau The EGR min/nom spark adjustment uses a 
      transport-delayed version of the EGR diluent command to decide the spark 
      timing, since the actual EGR feedback can be significantly delayed. If a 
      steady-state error exists, however, the spark timing should be adjusted to 
      account for the diluent error. To handle this situation, the EGR diluent 
      error is low-passed using a large time constant when the error is 
      increasing, and a smaller time constant when the error is decreasing. The 
      min/nom EGR spark command is adjusted using the low-passed error. 
      EGRad_dMAPdt_lmt Closed Loop and adaptive learn is disabled when MAPdt 
      exceeds this trigger value 
      EGRad_dmdotdt_lmt Obsoleted parameter 
      EGRad_edot_Dz Cubic rolloff dead-zone to be applied to the EGR edot value 
      used in the derivative (Kd) PID signal chain. 
      EGRad_edot_LP Post interpolation low-pass filter constant for EGR% 
      tracking error derivation calculation. 
      EGRad_edot_n EGR flow % error derivative calculation linear least-squares 
      window. More points yields a quieter and more accurate derivative, but 
      introduces more time lag. Fewer points has the opposite effect. This value 
      must be <= 25 ms and should be in 5ms intervals. 
      EGRad_EGRLP_min Obsoleted parameter 
      EGRad_EGRwrP_slew On tip-in from idle, TIP will momentarily drop below 
      remote UEGO pressure, used to measure the EGR flow rate in a low-pressure 
      EGR configuration. During this reverse flow condition, fresh air will flow 
      past the UEGO sensor, causing it to read at near 0 psi until some time 
      after forward flow is re-established. During this time when the remote 
      UEGO pressure is invalid, the measured EGR diluent percentage is pegged to 
      the transport delayed EGR command. Once forward flow is re-established and 
      the remote UEGO sensor stabilizes, the measured diluent percentage is 
      slewed back to the actual feedback window once closed loop is 
      re-activated. This parameter specifies the duration for this slew 
      operation.

      This slew time is only applied when "UEGO mounting configuration" is set 
      to 'Remote Pre-Intercooler' or 'Remote Post-Intercooler'. 
      EGRad_ena This option enables closed-loop and adaptive EGR valve area 
      updates. 
      EGRad_in2pct_max Interpolated from Max Adapt Sensitivity (in^2/100%), 
      given EGR Valve Normalized Position (%) command. 
      EGRad_in2pct_min minimum allowed EGR CdA sensitivity at the current EGR 
      valve command 
      EGRad_Kadapt This gain drives the speed of the adaptive area correction 
      updates. It is in units of % area change per area error % per second. 
      EGRad_KCL Obsoleted parameter 
      EGRad_MAF_min Adaptive updates will not occur until the MAF indicated flow 
      rate is above this limit. This option is ignored if the MAF is not the EGR 
      flow feedback source. 
      EGRad_mdot_min Adaptive updates will not occur until the commanded and 
      modeled EGR flow rates are above this limit. 
      EGRad_PRadapt_max Obsoleted parameter 
      EGRad_PRadapt_ratio ratio of PR adaptive vs. CdA adaptive: -1=OFF, 0.0=CdA 
      adaptive active, 1.0=PR adaptive active 
      EGRad_PRadapt_sw Specify the valve pressure ratio where the adaptive 
      updates should start transitioning from an area-based to a pressure 
      ratio-based approach. When the pressure ratio is between the start-end 
      limits, both CdA and PR adaptive are engaged, however, the gains are 
      limited to provide smooth transitions between the 2 adaptive modes. 
      EGRad_PRadapt_swend Specify the valve pressure ratio where the adaptive 
      updates should complete the transition from an area-based to a pressure 
      ratio-based approach. In general, this parameter should be the same as the 
      highlighted cells on the adaptive x-axes. When the pressure ratio is 
      between the start-end limits, both CdA and PR adaptive are engaged, 
      however, the gains are limited to provide smooth transitions between the 2 
      adaptive modes. 
      EGRad_PRCL_max Obsoleted parameter 
      EGRad_PR_adapt_crct active EGR adaptive pressure ratio correction 
      EGRad_PR_adapt_lim EGR adaptive pressure ratio learn ± limit 
      EGRad_PR_Kadapt EGR adaptive pressure ratio learn gain 
      EGRad_sens_max Obsoleted parameter 
      EGRad_sens_min Obsoleted parameter 
      EGRad_stable_wait If CL updates are disallowed for any reason (such as 
      those conditions defined by the parameters above), this wait time is 
      imposed after the condition is removed before CL and/or adaptive updates 
      resume. 
      EGRad_store_EE This switch determines whether the EGR adaptive valve area 
      learn tables are retained in battery supported memory or permanent memory. 
      In battery supported memory, the adaptive tables will be cleared if the 
      battery power is removed from the ECM. In permanent memory, a key-on reset 
      sequence must be performed to clear the tables. 
      EGRad_strt_wait Wait time following EGR flow start before any CL or 
      adaptive updates are performed. 
      EGRad_TPS_min Adaptive area updates should be disabled at low valve 
      positions since the 0%, 0 in^2 table entry will not be updated. For 
      example, if the valve flow characterization table has the following 
      entries:

      0.00% 0.000 in^2
      2.56% 0.019 in^2

      then adaptive updates should be shut down when the valve position goes 
      sufficiently below 2.56% in order to keep the adaptive entry term used to 
      adjust the 0.019 in^2 entry from updating when that cell has little of the 
      interpolated focus. 
      EGRad_tran_dMAP MAP is latched at the beginning of the CL accumulation 
      transport delay period. If MAP changes by more than this amount, the MAP 
      is re-latched following the stabilization wait period and the CL 
      accumulation period resets. 
      EGRad_tran_dmdpct The diluent command is latched at the beginning of the 
      CL accumulation transport delay period. If the command changes by more 
      than this amount, the command is re-latched following the stabilization 
      wait period and the CL accumulation period resets. 
      EGRad_UEGO_stable_wt If a reverse flow is detected in the low-pressure EGR 
      block, this wait time is imposed after the flow transitions to the forward 
      direction before closed-loop and/or adaptive updates resume. This delay 
      allows time for the remote-mounted UEGO, used to detect EGR flow rate, to 
      stabilize after the flow direction change. 

      This wait time is only applied when "UEGO mounting configuration" is set 
      to 'Remote Pre-Intercooler' or 'Remote Post-Intercooler'.

      The actual wait time enforced prior to resuming closed-loop and/or 
      adaptive updates is the larger of the "EGR CL stabilization wait" and "EGR 
      CL remote UEGO stabilization wait" values. 
      EGRclr_EFM_mdot Modeled EGR cooler eductor port mass flow for low-pressure 
      EGR systems. 
      EGRclr_EFM_mult For low-pressure EGR systems, this multiplier is applied 
      to the EGR cooler eductor port flow model output. 
      EGRdP EGR delta P w/ no offset typ across a fixed orifice or venturi or 
      across the EGR valve itself 
      EGRdP_config If an EGR delta-P sensor is enabled and the orifice location 
      on the EGRControl page is set to 'none', the delta-P sensor is assumed to 
      be across an EGR valve. Either an EGRLP or EGRHP sensor should be present 
      (but not both) and used with the delta-P sensor to determine EGR valve 
      flow. If an EGRdP sensor is enabled, neither an EGRLP or EGRHP sensor is 
      (or both are) present, and the EGR orifice location is set to 'none', an 
      invalid configuration is detected (and displayed in EDIS) and the EGRdP 
      sensor is ignored. 
      EGRdP_cyl_events Enter the number of cylinder events to use for EGRdP 
      measurement windowing. Lower values result in faster sensor response, 
      higher values minimize the engine-related pulsations. Set this value to 
      0.0 to disable cylinder event based windowing. Otherwise, this value must 
      be >= 1 if cylinder and the max window is limited to 200ms. NOTE: This 
      option requires hardware support and will is not supported on all input 
      channels. 
      EGRdP_dz This is the cutoff for the cubic deadzone on the delta-P sensor, 
      applied prior to low-pass filtering. If the difference between the 
      instantaneous dP and low-passed dP reading is below this value, the error 
      is reduced via a cubic deadzone before being applied to the low-passed dP. 

      EGRdP_Dz This is the cutoff for the cubic deadzone on the delta-P sensor, 
      applied prior to low-pass filtering. If the difference between the 
      instantaneous dP and low-passed dP reading is below this value, the error 
      is reduced via a cubic deadzone before being applied to the low-passed dP. 

      EGRdP_ena Exhaust gas recirculation delta pressure sensor input channel 
      EGRdP_HiExp_dP_min To execute the "EGRdP higher than expected" fault when 
      "EGRdP threshold source" is set to 'Table Based', the EGRdP sensor reading 
      must meet or exceed this value. 
      EGRdP_HiExp_mdot EGR flow threshold for EGRdP lower than expected fault. 
      The modeled EGR flow must be greater than this value and the EGRdP 
      pressure condition must be met for the fault to become active. 
      EGRdP_HiExp_p Minimum pressure threshold for EGRdP lower than expected 
      fault. The EGRdP pressure must be below this value and the EGR modeled 
      flow condition must be met for the fault to become active. 
      EGRdP_HiExp_source Single point or table-based selector for the "EGRdP 
      higher than expected" diagnostic EGRdp threshold. 
      EGRdP_HiExp_tbl_pct This value defines the percentage above the expected 
      EGRdP value from the "Air Mass Flow-Based Expected EGRdP" table that the 
      EGRdP sensor reading must exceed to latch the "EGRdP higher than expected" 
      fault when "EGRdP threshold source" is set to 'Table Based'. 

      For example, if this parameter is set to 25%, then the EGRdP threshold 
      used for fault processing is 125% of the expected EGRdP table value. 

      EGRdP_inst EGRdP sensor instantaneous measurement (psi) 
      EGRdP_LoExp_mdot EGR flow threshold for EGRdP higher than expected fault. 
      The modeled EGR flow must be less than this value and the EGRdP pressure 
      condition must be met for the fault to become active. 
      EGRdP_LoExp_p Maximum pressure threshold for EGRdP higher than expected 
      fault. The EGRdP pressure must be above this value and the EGR modeled 
      flow condition must be met for the fault to become active. 
      EGRdP_lo_LP_dBP Pressure margin below the barometric pressure used to 
      rationalize the EGR valve low pressure side reading for the "EGR valve dP 
      lower than expected - LP tube disconnected" diagnostic. 
      EGRdP_lo_LP_dP EGR valve delta pressure threshold for the "EGR valve dP 
      lower than expected - LP tube disconnected" diagnostic. 
      EGRdP_lo_LP_err Pressure difference between the target and actual EGR 
      valve delta pressures that must be exceeded to latch the "EGR valve dP 
      lower than expected - LP tube disconnected" diagnostic. 
      EGRdP_lo_LP_mdot Minimum EGR flow command fault condition for the "EGR 
      valve dP lower than expected - LP tube disconnected" diagnostic. 
      EGRdP_lo_rev_dP Maximum EGR valve delta pressure fault condition for the 
      "EGR valve dP lower than expected - tubes reversed" diagnostic. 
      EGRdP_lo_rev_err Pressure difference between the target and actual EGR 
      valve delta pressures that must be exceeded to latch the "EGR valve dP 
      lower than expected - tubes reversed" diagnostic. 
      EGRdP_lo_rev_mdot Minimum EGR flow command fault condition for the "EGR 
      valve dP lower than expected - tubes reversed" diagnostic. 
      EGRdP_max EGR delta P maximum value in the cylinder-event based ring 
      buffer window 
      EGRdP_maxv EGRdP analog input maximum voltage. Used for EGRdP high voltage 
      fault. 
      EGRdP_min EGR delta P minimum value in the cylinder-event based ring 
      buffer window 
      EGRdP_minv EGRdP analog input minimum voltage. Used for EGRdP low voltage 
      fault. 
      EGRdP_offset EGR delta P no flow offset 
      EGRdP_offset_clrdly Delay between end of key off clear cycle and start of 
      EGRdP offset sampling. Only used when EGRdP offset learn is enabled and 
      set to the Key-Off Clear Only mode. 
      EGRdP_offset_clrtime Specifies the maximum amount of time allowed for 
      EGRdP sensor offset learning at key-off. Set this value to 0 to disable 
      the time limit. 
      EGRdP_offset_dPmax This is the maximum EGR delta-P reading for no-flow 
      offset sampling. If the actual EGR delta-P reading is above this limit, 
      the sample is rejected and the offset stabilization wait must elapse 
      before offset sampling resumes. 
      EGRdP_offset_dPmin This is the minimum EGR delta-P reading for no-flow 
      offset sampling. If the actual EGR delta-P reading is below this limit, 
      the sample is rejected and the offset stabilization wait must elapse 
      before offset sampling resumes. 
      EGRdP_offset_dPpls This parameter can be used to disable EGRdP offset 
      sampling when the EGR valve is closed but pressure pulsations would case a 
      skew in the dP reading. The min/max pressures within a 50ms window are 
      compared. If the (difference / 2) is larger than this value, the sample is 
      rejected and the stabilization wait must elapse before sampling resumes. 
      EGRdP_offset_ECT Oil-filled EGR delta-P sensors may have more offset at 
      low temperatures because of the oil viscosity. Using a reasonable ECT 
      lower-limit for EGR delta-P offset sampling prevents offset mis-learning. 
      EGRdP_offset_flowwt Once all the other EGR delta-P sampling offset 
      conditions are satisfied, the system will wait this amount of time before 
      sampling begins. This wait time is ignored for the initial key-on wait 
      sequence, and is only applied when one of the other validation conditions 
      is violated. 
      EGRdP_offset_keywt EGRdP sensor offset sampling will be initialized by 
      default at key-on (i.e. the stabilization wait is bypassed in favor of 
      this key-on wait). This allows EGRdP sampling prior to engine running 
      while the dP sensor is immune to flow pulsations. 
      EGRdP_offset_learn If enabled, during no EGR flow conditions (when the 
      constraints below are satisfied), the raw EGRdP reading will be sampled 
      and used as an offset during normal EGR operation. If 'Start Inhibit Only' 
      is selected, delta-P offset sampling will only take place during the 
      key-on start inhibit period of the run cycle. If 'Key-Off Clear Only' is 
      selected, offset sampling will only occur following the key off clear 
      cycle, after a delay set by the "EGRdP offset key-off clear wait" time. 
      EGRdP_offset_state EGR delta-P sensor offset sampling state tracking 
      EGRdP_offset_strtwt If this value is non-zero, starting will be inhibited 
      to allow for a pre-start pressure offset pegging. 
      EGRdP_offset_tau This is the low-pass filter time constant used to sample 
      the EGR delta-P offset value. It should be relatively high to adequately 
      average out noise at high engine speeds, but low enough to provide offset 
      updates during normal operation. 
      EGRdP_offset_vlvmax EGR delta-P no-flow offset sampling will not begin 
      until the EGR valve command and actual positions are within this window of 
      the minimum EGR position / valve command. For example, if this value is 
      1.0% and the EGR position / valve command minimum is 5.0% (e.g. smart 
      valve), the delta-P offset sequence will begin once the commanded and 
      actual EGR valve positions are below 6.0%. 
      EGRdP_Paux_cal EGRdP sensor auxiliary pressure calibration table 
      assignment 
      EGRdP_tau This is the low-pass time constant applied to the EGR delta-P 
      low-pass/cubic deadzone filter. It is applied after the offset is added to 
      the raw delta-P sensor reading. 
      EGRdP_trust_latch_tm Time that EGRdP must remain within the dead zone 
      before it can be trusted. Minimum time is 1 second. 
      EGRdP_trust_pct EGRdP trustworthiness 
      EGRdP_trust_zero_dz Dead zone for trusting the EGRdP sensor. EGRdP will be 
      set to 0 until both EGRdP and EGRHP are trusted. Set to 0 to disable EGRdP 
      rationalization. 
      EGRdP_wdw_dz_lp EGRdP, averaged over the calibrated number of cylinder 
      events, deadzoned, and low-passed 
      EGRfb_LL_dP EGR feedback based load-limit: dP 
      EGRfb_LL_MAF EGR feedback based load-limit: MAF 
      EGRfb_LL_openloop This should generally be <= the smallest of the 
      feedback-based load limit calibration values. This is applied to any 
      min/nom imposed load-limit (since open-loop EGR operation is prohibited, 
      load is limited to % EGR entries in the min table). 
      EGRfb_LL_UEGO EGR feedback based load-limit: UEGO 
      EGRfb_minnom_dP EGR feedback based min/nom operation: dP 
      EGRfb_minnom_MAF EGR feedback based min/nom operation: MAF 
      EGRfb_minnom_UEGO EGR feedback based min/nom operation: UEGO 
      EGRHPLP_cyl_events Enter the number of cylinder events to use for 
      EGRHP/EGRLP measurement windowing. Lower values result in faster sensor 
      response, higher values minimize the engine-related EGRHP/EGRLP 
      pulsations. This value must be >= 1, and the max window is limited to 
      200ms. Set this value to 0.0 to disable cylinder event based windowing. 
      EGRHPLP_Dz This parameter is used with the cubic deadzone -- the cubic 
      deadzone routine returns either a cubic deadzone limited change in 
      pressure OR the low-passed pressure (whichever is closest to the raw 
      value). 
      EGRHPLP_tau Low-pass filter time constant in ms for the windowed 
      high-speed EGRHP and EGRLP pressures. 
      EGRHP_def Default EGRHP value. This value should generally be a few psi 
      greater than EGRLP default. 
      EGRHP_ena Exhaust gas recirculation (high pressure side) input channel 
      EGRHP_float EGR valve inlet pressure (high) in psia - rationalized 
      EGRHP_inst EGRHP instantaneous 
      EGRHP_location EGRHP location. The standard 'Valve Inlet' implies the 
      sensor is mounted directly at the inlet to the EGR valve. If this 
      selection is set to 'Pre-venturi+valve' and the venturi location on the 
      EGR page is set to pre-valve, then the actual valve inlet pressure is 
      EGRHP = sensed value + EGRdP 
      EGRHP_maxv EGRHP analog input maximum voltage. Used for EGRHP high voltage 
      fault. 
      EGRHP_mdl_float EGRHP modeled 
      EGRHP_minv EGRHP analog input minimum voltage. Used for EGRHP low voltage 
      fault. 
      EGRHP_OOR_lim_neg Minimum pressure threshold for EGRHP out of range fault. 
      EGRHP must be less than (TIP - EGR Cooler Drop) by at least this much for 
      the fault to become active. 
      EGRHP_OOR_lim_pos Maximum pressure threshold for EGRHP out of range fault. 
      EGRHP must be greater than (TIP - EGR Cooler Drop) by at least this much 
      for the fault to become active. 
      EGRHP_OOR_maxMAP Maximum MAP condition for EGRHP out of range fault. MAP 
      load must be below this value for the fault to be active. 
      EGRHP_OOR_maxRPM Maximum RPM condition for EGRHP out of range fault. RPM 
      must be below this value for the fault to be active. 
      EGRHP_OOR_minMAP Minimum MAP condition for EGRHP out of range fault. MAP 
      load must be above this value for the fault to be active. 
      EGRHP_OOR_minRPM Minimum RPM condition for EGRHP out of range fault. RPM 
      must be above this value for the fault to be active. 
      EGRHP_OOR_vlv_min Minimum EGR valve position for EGRHP out of range fault. 
      EGR valve position must be greater than this value for the fault to be 
      active. 
      EGRHP_Paux_cal EGRHP sensor auxiliary pressure calibration table 
      assignment 
      EGRHP_trust_latch_tm Time that EGRHP model error must remain within the 
      dead zone before it can be trusted. Minimum latch time is 1 second. 
      EGRHP_trust_mdl_dz EGRHP model error dead zone for trusting the EGRHP 
      sensor. EGRHP will be modeled based on EMP until both EGRdP and EGRHP are 
      trusted. Set to 0 to disable EGRHP rationalization. 
      EGRHP_trust_mdl_err EGRHP model error 
      EGRHP_trust_pct EGRHP trustworthiness 
      EGRHP_trust_unlatcht Unlatch time for EGRHP trustworthiness. Minimum 
      unlatch time is 1 second. 
      EGRHP_wdw EGRHP, averaged over the calibrated number of cylinder events 
      EGRHP_wdw_dz_lp EGRHP, averaged over the calibrated number of cylinder 
      events, deadzoned, and low-passed 
      EGRLP_dedt IRV closed-loop EGRLP tracking error derivative. 
      EGRLP_dedt_dz EGRLP error derivative deadzone. 
      EGRLP_def Default EGRLP value. This should generally be a few psi less 
      than EGRHP. 
      EGRLP_ena Exhaust gas recirculation (low pressure side) input channel 
      EGRLP_float EGR valve inlet pressure (low) in psia - rationalized 
      EGRLP_inst EGRLP instantaneous 
      EGRLP_Paux_cal EGRLP sensor auxiliary pressure calibration table 
      assignment 
      EGRLP_wdw EGRLP_wdw 
      EGRO_postlk_EGRdP EGR delta-P threshold for the EGR post-orifice leak 
      detected diagnostic 
      EGRO_postlk_FSO_max Maximum throttle open fuel shutoff active duration 
      threshold for the "EGR post-orifice leak detected" diagnostic. 
      EGRO_postlk_FSO_min Minimum throttle open fuel shutoff active duration 
      threshold for the "EGR post-orifice leak detected" diagnostic. 
      EGRO_postlk_rpmdt RPMdt threshold for the EGR post-orifice leak detected 
      diagnostic 
      EGRO_postlk_RPMmax Maximum RPM threshold for the "EGR post-orifice leak 
      detected" diagnostic. 
      EGRO_postlk_source Single point or table-based selector for the "EGR 
      post-orifice leak detected" diagnostic EGRdp threshold. 
      EGRO_postlk_tbl_pct Margin percentage above the EGR expected pressure 
      change table EGRdP values that will cause the "EGR post-orifice leak 
      detected" diagnostic to latch. 
      EGRO_postlk_vlvdP_hi Maximum EGR valve dP threshold for the "EGR 
      post-orifice leak detected" diagnostic. 
      EGRO_postlk_vlvdP_lo Minimum EGR valve dP threshold for the "EGR 
      post-orifice leak detected" diagnostic. 
      EGRO_vlv_dP EGR dP sensor assembly-to-EGR valve pressure drop 
      EGRO_vlv_dP_C EGR dP sensor assembly-to-EGR valve delta P scaling 
      EGRO_vlv_dP_nom EGR dP sensor assembly-to-EGR valve nominal pressure drop 
      EGRT Exhaust Gas Recirculation (cooler outlet/mixing) temperature 
      EGRT_def Default EGRT value 
      EGRT_ena Exhaust gas recirculation temperature sensor input channel 
      EGRT_hi_ECTmax EGRT temperature high diagnostic: ECT upper limit entry 
      condition 
      EGRT_hi_ECTmin EGRT temperature high diagnostic: ECT lower limit entry 
      condition 
      EGRT_hi_mdot EGR flow minimum threshold fault condition for the "EGRT 
      temperature high" diagnostic. 
      EGRT_hi_mdot_wt "EGRT temperature high" fault condition that specifies the 
      minimum amount of time the EGR flow must exceed its minimum threshold. 
      EGRT_hi_Tmax EGRT temperature high diagnostic: EGRT lower limit entry 
      condition 
      EGRT_maxv EGRT high voltage diagnostic: voltage upper limit threshold 
      EGRT_maxv_ECTmin EGRT high voltage diagnostic: ECT lower limit entry 
      condition 
      EGRT_minv EGRT low voltage diagnostic: voltage lower limit threshold 
      EGRT_Taux_cal EGRT auxiliary temperature calibration table selection 
      EGRT_vdr EGRT input channel pullup resistor resistance value 
      EGRwrP_def Default EGR UEGO pressure, used for pressure compensation when 
      the sensor is not available (e.g. not present or confirmed to be in a 
      fault state). 
      EGRwrP_ena Designates auxiliary temperature sensor input for measuring 
      Air/EGR mixture pressure at EGR UEGO sensor location 
      EGRwrP_float EGR UEGO sensor pressure in psia 
      EGRwrP_Paux_cal EGR UEGO pressure sensor auxiliary pressure calibration 
      table selection 
      EGRwrP_tau Low pass time constant applied to EGR UEGO pressure sensor 
      signal 
      EGRwrT_ena This is the Exhaust Gas Recirculation wide-range Temperature 
      sensor. Typically used in conjunction with the EGR UEGO. Use the "TAUX 
      low-pass filter" calibration parameter to set the tau for input filtering. 

      EGRwrT_float EGR Temperature in degrees R as float 
      EGRwrT_Taux_cal EGR UEGO temperature sensor auxiliary temperature 
      calibration table selection 
      EGRwrT_vdr EGR UEGO temperature input channel pullup resistor resistance 
      value 
      EGRwr_drifthalt_ms Obsoleted parameter 
      EGRwr_drift_status EGR drift compensation status (Off: UEGO Inactive, Off: 
      Key-Cycle Timeout, Off: MAP High, Not Allowed+Active, Off: FSO TPS Open 
      Req, Reserved – 5, Reserved – 6, Reserved – 7, Reserved – 8, Reserved – 9, 
      Allowed+Inactive, Allowed+Active) 
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPdft If MAP <= BP - this value, drift sampling will be 
      allowed to engage.
      The following illustrates a typical setup for the EGR UEGO pressure 
      calibration parameters:

      BP = 14.4 psia
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPint = 1.5 psi
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPmix = .5 psi
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPdft = 1.0 psi

      A) MAP >=15.9 psia (BP + EGRwr_flowctl_dPint)
      . flow control valve will connect to compressor inlet
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed
      . drift sampling not allowed

      B) 15.9 psia > MAP >= 14.9 psia (BP + EGRwr_flowctl_dPmix)
      . flow control valve left in previous state (hysteresis region)
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed (actual feedback will be a linear 
      combination of UEGO and venturi + dP if a 3-way valve is not available and 
      the UEGO is not intake-mounted). drift sampling not allowed 

      C) 14.9 psia > MAP >= 13.4 psia (BP - EGRwr_flowctl_dPdft). flow control 
      valve will connect to fuel mixer
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed (if flow control valve is present)
      . drift sampling not allowed 

      D) 13.4 psia > MAP (BP - EGRwr_flowctl_dPdft)
      . flow control valve will connect to fuel mixer
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed (if flow control valve is present)
      . drift sampling allowed 
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPint If MAP >= BP + this value, then the EGR UEGO flow 
      control valve will disengage and vent the EGR/air mixture flowing past the 
      UEGO sensor back to the compressor inlet. The following illustrates a 
      typical setup for the EGR UEGO pressure calibration parameters:

      BP = 14.4 psia
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPint = 1.5 psi
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPmix = .5 psi
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPdft = 1.0 psi

      A) MAP >=15.9 psia (BP + EGRwr_flowctl_dPint)
      . flow control valve will connect to compressor inlet
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed
      . drift sampling not allowed

      B) 15.9 psia > MAP >= 14.9 psia (BP + EGRwr_flowctl_dPmix)
      . flow control valve left in previous state (hysteresis region)
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed (actual feedback will be a linear 
      combination of UEGO and venturi + dP if a 3-way valve is not available and 
      the UEGO is not intake-mounted)
      . drift sampling not allowed 

      C) 14.9 psia > MAP >= 13.4 psia (BP - EGRwr_flowctl_dPdft)
      . flow control valve will connect to fuel mixer
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed (if flow control valve is present)
      . drift sampling not allowed 

      D) 13.4 psia > MAP (BP - EGRwr_flowctl_dPdft)
      . flow control valve will connect to fuel mixer
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed (if flow control valve is present)
      . drift sampling allowed 
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPmix If MAP <= BP + this value, then the EGR UEGO flow 
      control valve will engage and recirculate the EGR/air mixture flowing past 
      the UEGO sensor to the fuel mixer inlet.

      The following illustrates a typical setup for the EGR UEGO pressure 
      calibration parameters:

      BP = 14.4 psia
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPint = 1.5 psi
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPmix = .5 psi
      EGRwr_flowctl_dPdft = 1.0 psi

      A) MAP >=15.9 psia (BP + EGRwr_flowctl_dPint)
      . flow control valve will connect to compressor inlet
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed
      . drift sampling not allowed

      B) 15.9 psia > MAP >= 14.9 psia (BP + EGRwr_flowctl_dPmix)
      . flow control valve left in previous state (hysteresis region)
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed (actual feedback will be a linear 
      combination of UEGO and venturi + dP if a 3-way valve is not available and 
      the UEGO is not intake-mounted)
      . drift sampling not allowed 

      C) 14.9 psia > MAP >= 13.4 psia (BP - EGRwr_flowctl_dPdft)
      . flow control valve will connect to fuel mixer
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed (if flow control valve is present)
      . drift sampling not allowed 

      D) 13.4 psia > MAP (BP - EGRwr_flowctl_dPdft)
      . flow control valve will connect to fuel mixer
      . EGR UEGO measurement allowed (if flow control valve is present)
      . drift sampling allowed

      valve will disengage and vent the EGR/air mixture flowing past the UEGO 
      sensor back to the compressor inlet. The following illustrates a typical 
      setup for the EGR UEGO pressure calibration parameters: 
      EGRwr_mount_type To enable EGR measurement via a UEGO sensor:
      1. Configure UEGO1 or UEGO2 to 'Intake Air+EGR'
      2. Select the UEGO pressure sensor input on the 'Inputs' sheet
      3. Select the appropriate mounting configuration here 
      EGRwr_pstvlv_V Obsoleted parameter 
      EGRwr_UEGO_fbpct % of current feedback signal from EGR UEGO 
      EGRwr_UEGO_slew Enter a non-zero value to slew in the UEGO feedback. This 
      is most useful for delta-P sensor to UEGO feedback transitions, where 
      there can be an error between the EGR% provided by the 2 methods. 
      EGR_act_flow_tau Obsoleted parameter 
      EGR_CdA_Dz This parameter specifies a cubic-rolloff deadzone for 
      instantaneous changes in EGR valve position. Changes in valve command >= 
      this value are instantaneously implemented, and changes < this value are 
      slewed-in over the low-pass time constant specified below. 
      EGR_CdA_tau Low pass time constant for filtering instantaneous EGR valve 
      position change command signal 
      EGR_channel Assign EGR valve control to ECM HBridge, PWM channel or 
      CANbased control 
      EGR_clr_Cr_nom EGR Cooler nominal heat capacity ratio 
      EGR_clr_dP Pressure loss across the EGR cooler 
      EGR_clr_dP_C EGR cooler flow rate delta P scaling 
      EGR_clr_dP_nom EGR cooler nominal pressure drop 
      EGR_clr_eta2_ECTmax EGR cooler efficiency low 2 diagnostic: ECT upper 
      limit entry condition 
      EGR_clr_eta2_ECTmin EGR cooler efficiency low 2 diagnostic: ECT lower 
      limit entry condition 
      EGR_clr_eta2_Tmax EGR cooler efficiency low 2 diagnostic: EGRT lower limit 
      entry condition 
      EGR_clr_eta_dTmax EGR cooler efficiency low 1 diagnostic: EGRT - ECT delta 
      temperature max limit entry condition. The EGRT sensor must be capable of 
      reading temperatures up to the upper ECT limit + this value. 
      EGR_clr_eta_ECTmax EGR cooler efficiency low 1 diagnostic: ECT upper limit 
      entry condition 
      EGR_clr_eta_ECTmin EGR cooler efficiency low 1 diagnostic: ECT lower limit 
      entry condition 
      EGR_clr_eta_mdot EGR flow minimum threshold fault condition for the "EGR 
      cooler efficiency low 1" and "EGR cooler efficiency low 2" diagnostics. 
      EGR_clr_eta_mdotmin Obsoleted parameter 
      EGR_clr_eta_mdot_wt "EGR cooler efficiency low 1" and "EGR cooler 
      efficiency low 2" fault condition that specifies the minimum amount of 
      time the EGR flow must exceed its minimum threshold. 
      EGR_clr_eta_nom EGR Cooler nominal efficiency

      EGR_cmd_dmdotdt_wdw Obsoleted parameter 
      EGR_cmd_tau Obsoleted parameter 
      EGR_cool_delay EGR Transport Delay: EGR cold delay time (ms) 
      EGR_cool_xa EGR Transport Delay: EGR cold delay air component (%) 
      EGR_cool_xd EGR Transport Delay: EGR cold delay diluent component (%) 
      EGR_cool_xf EGR Transport Delay: EGR cold delay fuel component (%) 
      EGR_ctl_status EGR ouput control status (Disabled, Inactive: run time, 
      Inactive: ECT low, Inactive: ECT high, Inactive: IAT low, Inactive: IAT 
      high, Active) 
      EGR_deice_AAT_max Maximum AAT for purging condensation from the EGR loop. 
      EGR_deice_idle_tm Primary idle time before purging condensation from the 
      EGR loop. This parameter is used after engine start or between purges. If 
      0, EGR de-icing is disabled. 
      EGR_deice_pct_cmd Percent diluent command for purging condensation from 
      the EGR loop. This value must be greater than the diluent command 'on' 
      limit. When a "Force Idle" fault is active, the diluent command 'on' limit 
      is used instead. 
      EGR_deice_post_tm Time delay between stopping EGR flow and returning to 
      idle. 
      EGR_deice_pre_tm Time delay between reaching the target engine speed and 
      starting EGR flow. 
      EGR_deice_purge_IAT Target IAT for purging condensation from the EGR loop. 

      EGR_deice_purge_tm Time to flow EGR after reaching the target IAT, to 
      purge condensation from the EGR loop. 
      EGR_deice_retidle_tm Secondary idle time before purging condensation from 
      the EGR loop. If non-zero, this parameter is used after any form of 
      vehicle operation. If zero, the primary idle time is used instead. 
      EGR_deice_rpm Engine speed for purging condensation from the EGR loop. 
      EGR_deice_rpm_rate Engine speed ramp rate for purging condensation from 
      the EGR loop. 
      EGR_deice_state EGR de-icing status 
      EGR_deice_tmr Elapsed time since conditions allow purging condensation 
      from the EGR loop, or elapsed time while purging condensation from the EGR 
      loop. 
      EGR_deice_wait_tm Current time to wait before purging condensation from 
      the EGR loop. This value is either the primary or secondary idle time, 
      times the multiplier interpolated based on current ambient air 
      temperature. 
      EGR_dmdot_cmd EGR_dmdot_cmd 
      EGR_dmdot_cmd_dz Cubic deadzone applied to the diluent command derivative 
      estimate. Note the final derivative estimate is post a cubic deadzone and 
      then subsequent low-pass filter. 
      EGR_dmdot_cmd_n Time window used for the derivative estimation, must be in 
      increments of 5ms and < 300 ms. 
      EGR_dmdot_cmd_tau Low-pass filter applied after the derivative estimate is 
      dead-zoned.

      EGR_initpct_0md_slew Increasing slew rate for the percent diluent command 
      reduction after the maximum zero EGR flow time has lapsed. 
      EGR_initpct_0md_tm Maximum time with zero EGR flow before increasing the 
      percent diluent command reduction. 
      EGR_initpct_accmd Cumulative off-idle EGR valve flow for calculating the 
      percent reduction in commanded diluent flow percentage. 
      EGR_initpct_accmdmax Maximum accumulated off-idle EGR valve flow for using 
      the percent reduction in commanded diluent flow percentage. 
      EGR_initpct_reduct This feature reduces EGR flow at startup and after 
      excessive idling to prevent misfire while any exiting condensation is 
      removed.

      This parameter specifies the initial percent reduction in the commanded 
      diluent flow percentage. The actual percent reduction decreases to 0, 
      proportional to the accumulated EGR valve flow relative to the specified 
      maximum accumulated EGR valve flow. 
      EGR_LoExp2_mdot EGR flow lower than expected 2 diagnostic: EGR commanded 
      flow lower limit entry condition

      EGR_max_DC Maximum EGR valve position 
      EGR_mdot_fill_Dz max MAP_load allowed at EGR load-limit diluent command 
      EGR_mindil_cmdtbl Select the table to use for the minimum diluent mass 
      fraction. If this is set to 'None', the minimum diluent command is assumed 
      to be zero (used for transients). 
      EGR_mindil_SH Min diluent command reference humidity 
      EGR_mindil_SHref Enter the actual humidity when the minimum total diluent 
      mass fraction and spark advance tables were calibrated.

      For low-pressure applications, the tables are assumed to have been 
      calibrated at the default EGRHP and default EGRT. 
      EGR_mindil_spktbl Select the spark command table that corresponds to the 
      minimum diluent mass fraction table. If disabled, normal spark timing will 
      be used. 
      EGR_minnom_bst_BP Current EGR minnom value requested by the altitude 
      compensation system. 
      EGR_minnom_derate Min/Nom derate request 
      EGR_minnom_ECT Min/Nom ECT request 
      EGR_minnom_FB Min/Nom FB type request 
      EGR_minnom_frac EGR min/nom fraction: final multiplier following slew-rate 
      limiting: >1.0=extrapolate above nom, 1.0=use nominal, 0.0=use min, 
      <0.0=extrapolate below min, -1=EGR off 
      EGR_minnom_FSO During FSO, the EGR min/nom command is forced to this 
      value. The EGR command is hard-coded to 0 during FSO, however, upon 
      exiting FSO, initializing the min/nom EGR command to a value < 1.0 
      (assuming the min-to-nom slew is not immediate) provides for reduced EGR 
      commands and retarded spark timing to help with transient performance and 
      catalyst lightoff. 
      EGR_minnom_nslew This parameter slews the time it takes to transition from 
      nominal to the min command table, and from the min to off. 
      EGR_minnom_pslew This parameter slews the time it takes to transition from 
      off to the min command table, and from the min to nominal tables. 
      EGR_minnom_raw raw multiplier used for computing the EGR diluent command: 
      >1.0=extrapolate above nom, 1.0=use nominal, 0.0=use min, <0.0=extrapolate 
      below min, -1=EGR off 
      EGR_minnom_runwt EGR run-wait time based off/min/nom selection 
      EGR_minnom_senstrst Current EGR minimum/nominal request limit for sensor 
      trustworthiness 
      EGR_min_DC Minimum EGR valve position 
      EGR_nomdil_SH Nominal diluent command reference humidity 
      EGR_nomdil_SHref Enter the actual humidity when the diluent mass fraction 
      table was calibrated.

      For low-pressure applications, the tables are assumed to have been 
      calibrated at the default EGRHP and default EGRT.

      EGR_oct_ena EGR octane adaptation control (Enabled or Disabled) 
      EGR_oct_lim A proportional power derate is applied for octane ratings less 
      than this value. 
      EGR_oct_lim_mode Selects the derate table used for the proportional power 
      derate for octane ratings below the threshold. As the octane rating 
      decreases from the threshold to 0%, the power derate scales proportionally 
      from 100% down to the limit.
