      ICam_Kp Icam Proportional Gain. Used when ECam_control_cal = Intake / Cam1 

      ICam_maxerr Intake cam / distributor position diagnostic: Intake cam 
      position error 
      ICam_PWM_DC Intake cam control PWM duty cycle 
      ICam_PWM_mode Intake cam PWM mode (Automatic, Manual Timing, Manual DC) 
      ICam_PWM_taud Intake cam PWM output period 
      ICam_ref_nom "ICam nominal pulse alignment": Sets the CAD location of the 
      cam stable edge nominal reference pulse. See "ICam nominal pulse offset" 
      description for more details. 
      ICam_ref_offset Specifies the absolute CAD offset for the stable edge 
      closest to TDC (reference pulse). 
      ICam_ref_timing Intake cam nominal valve opening 
      ICam_samp_BTDC Intake cam edge sample 
      ICam_timing_a Intake cam open actual 
      ICam_timing_ctrl CAM1/Icam timing control FLAG. Set to Disabled and/or can 
      be set to the D/A port 
      ICam_timing_d Intake cam open target 
      ICAVD_mis Misfire detected diagnostic: misfire count for the cylinder that 
      exceeds this calibrated percentage of maximum will set the fault. 
      ICAVD_miscat Emissions/catalyst damaging misfire diagnostic: misfire count 
      for the cylinder that exceeds this calibrated percentage of maximum will 
      set the fault. 
      ICAV_adpt1 Misfire Statistics - Adaptive Correction (cylinder 1) 
      ICAV_adpt10 Misfire Statistics - Adaptive Correction (cylinder 10) 
      ICAV_adpt2 Misfire Statistics - Adaptive Correction (cylinder 2) 
      ICAV_adpt3 Misfire Statistics - Adaptive Correction (cylinder 3) 
      ICAV_adpt4 Misfire Statistics - Adaptive Correction (cylinder 4) 
      ICAV_adpt5 Misfire Statistics - Adaptive Correction (cylinder 5) 
      ICAV_adpt6 Misfire Statistics - Adaptive Correction (cylinder 6) 
      ICAV_adpt7 Misfire Statistics - Adaptive Correction (cylinder 7) 
      ICAV_adpt8 Misfire Statistics - Adaptive Correction (cylinder 8) 
      ICAV_adpt9 Misfire Statistics - Adaptive Correction (cylinder 9) 
      ICAV_adpthst_load If enabled, the adaptive progress histogram will be 
      restored at power-on and adaptive progress will continuous from its 
      previous state. If disabled, the adaptive learn sequence must restart 
      before misfire detection will be active. Note that the adaptive tables are 
      always restored, regardless of the setting selected for this option. 
      ICAV_adptT Obsoleted parameter 
      ICAV_adpt_cyl Misfire Statistics - Adaptive Correction 
      ICAV_adpt_dead Adaptation is temporarily shutdown when continuous 
      indicator <= (deadzone %) * continuous threshold. Reasonable deadzone 
      values prevent adaptive parameter drift during steady-state operation 
      while allowing the adaptive tables to converge enough to prevent false 
      misfire diagnostics. Typical values are 10-25%. 
      ICAV_adpt_flt Indicates whether a faulted misfire diagnostic is disabling 
      adaptive updates. 
      ICAV_adpt_flt_ena If enabled, misfire adaptive updates are disabled if any 
      of the misfire diagnostics are in a faulted state. The relevant misfire 
      diagnostics are Misfire detected (cylinders 1-10) and Emissions/catalyst 
      damaging misfire (cylinders 1-10). 
      ICAV_adpt_hires Enables high-resolution mode for adaptive parameter 
      updates. This mode limits adaptive updates to off-axis terms (i.e. cells 
      far away from the current cell), and performs high-resolution adaptive 
      updates during extended steady-state operation. This mode will increase 
      the time required before misfire diagnostics are fully enabled. 
      ICAV_adpt_K Adaptive gain to use for learning steady-state accelerations 
      that are unrelated to misfire (e.g. inconsistent tooth spacing, crankshaft 
      vibrations, bent propellers, etc.). This gain is used in the safe region 
      when the adaptive progress is below the threshold. 
      ICAV_adpt_Khi Adaptive gain to use for learning steady-state accelerations 
      that are unrelated to misfire (e.g. inconsistent tooth spacing, crankshaft 
      vibrations, bent propellers, etc.). If the adaptive progress is above the 
      progress threshold, the adaptive gain shifts from the high to low gain as 
      the continuous indicator grows from the deadzone to the continuous 
      threshold. 
      ICAV_adpt_Klo Adaptive gain to use for learning steady-state accelerations 
      that are unrelated to misfire (e.g. inconsistent tooth spacing, crankshaft 
      vibrations, bent propellers, etc.). If the adaptive progress is above the 
      progress threshold, the adaptive gain shifts from the high to low gain as 
      the continuous indicator grows from the deadzone to the continuous 
      threshold. 
      ICAV_adpt_limit Added a calibratable adaptive table entry limit. Previous 
      implementations automatically saturated at -0.7% and +0.7% speed 
      adaptation. High-output engines will typically require more adaptive 
      correction to handle cylinder-to-cylinder variations. 
      ICAV_adpt_rolloff Rolloff to use when updating adaptive table elements. 
      Adaptive table lookups use a linear combination of 4 table entries. During 
      the adaptive update, each entry is inversely weighted by its distance from 
      the current operating point:

      if weight >= rolloff, weight = weight
      if weight < rolloff, weight = weight^2

      Reasonable values of 0.25-0.35 prevent adaptive estimation drift during 
      steady-state operation by limiting the adaptive updates applied to distant 
      table entries. 
      ICAV_adpt_wt Disables adaptation following a detected misfire. 
      ICAV_cal_assist Misfire calibration assist request (inactive, adaptive 
      learn, thresholds) 
      ICAV_cat_prot Enables and selects the derate table used for misfire 
      catalyst protection. If enabled and any of the misfire or spark coil 
      diagnostics associated with one cylinder have a resolved status of 
      "Confirmed and active", the following actions will be taken:
      - Load limiting will be applied using the derate table selected by this 
      dropdown.
      - EGR minnom command will be forced to -1. EGR load limiting which would 
      normally be active is this case is disabled. The table selected above must 
      be used to control load limit instead.
      - Phi and spark tables will change to the fuel selected by the "Misfire 
      cat protection fuel type" dropdown.

      Note: the "Misfire detected" faults are only checked if "Misfire cat 
      protection - level 1 faults" is set to 'Included'. 
      ICAV_cat_prot_2cyl This value determines what misfire catalyst protection 
      action is taken if any of the misfire or spark coil diagnostics associated 
      with at least 2 cylinders have a resolved status of "confirmed and 
      active". If this value is set to 'Single cylinder option', then the 
      actions associated with single-cylinder misfire catalyst protection are 
      enforced (see the comment for "Misfire cat protection - single cylinder"). 
      If this value is set to 'Engine Shutdown', then a forced shutdown will 
      occur.

      For either option, "Misfire cat protection - single cylinder" must be 
      enabled (i.e. set to one of the load-limit table options). 

      Note: the "Misfire detected" faults are only checked if "Misfire cat 
      protection - level 1 faults" is set to 'Included'. 
      ICAV_cat_prot_act Indicates whether misfire catalyst protection is active. 

      ICAV_cat_prot_fuel Selects the fuel type used for phi and spark tables 
      when misfire catalyst protection is active. 
      ICAV_cat_prot_level1 Parameter determines if the "Misfire detected" faults 
      are apart of the list of faults that trigger misfire catalyst protection. 
      When set to 'Included', then "Misfire detected" faults are checked by both 
      "Misfire cat protection - single cylinder" and "Misfire cat protection - 
      multi-cylinder" features. When set to 'Excluded', then "Misfire detected" 
      faults are not checked. Note: the "Misfire detected" fault reactions set 
      by the fault switches on the Diagnostics worksheet are always honored. 
      ICAV_chst_cnts 2D Interpolation Table - inputs are Airflow (mg/L-disp) and 
      RPM, output is Continuous Misfires count 
      ICAV_chst_prog 1D Histogram Table - Histogram divisions are Adapt Prog 
      (cycles), histogram data is Continuous Misfires count 
      ICAV_chst_tmult 1D Histogram Table - Histogram divisions are Normalized 
      Indicator, histogram data collected is Continuous Misfires count 
      ICAV_cid_fail Misfire continuous ID fail count 
      ICAV_cid_num Number of cylinders to consider in continuous misfire 
      cylinder identification algorithm. If set to 1, the maximum decelerating 
      cylinder is selected and paired continuous identification is disabled. 
      Typically values are (Ncyl/2-1) or (Ncyl/2). 
      ICAV_cid_succ Misfire continuous ID success count 
      ICAV_cid_thres Cylinders with decelerations above this threshold (in 
      percent of the max deceleration) are included in the firing-order based 
      continuous misfire identification algorithm. The maximum number of 
      cylinders considered is specified by ICAV_cid_num. 
      ICAV_cts_norm ICAV normalized continuous misfire indicator = (indicator / 
      threshold) 
      ICAV_cts_tau Time constant for continuous indicator low-pass filtering. 
      ICAV_cyc_cts ICAV continuous misfire indicator 
      ICAV_cyc_diag "ICAV misfire pct cycle history" - Defines the number of 
      cumulative cycles used in the percent misfire computation. 
      ICAV_dctsnrm ICAV continuous misfire indicator derivative 
      ICAV_dctsnrmi_max ICAV maximum derivative continuous indicator at idle 
      ICAV_dctsnrm_max If the normalized continuous indicator is increasing at a 
      rate faster than this limit, adaptive progress is disabled for a limited 
      (see value below) number of cycles to avoid adapting over a pending 
      misfire. 
      ICAV_dctsnrm_wt If the normalized continuous indicator is increasing at a 
      rate faster than the above limit, adaptive progress is disabled for this 
      number of cycles to avoid adapting over a pending misfire. 
      ICAV_det_trig ICAV misfire detected trigger 
      ICAV_dgear_wt Temporarily disables misfire detection when a pending/active 
      gear change is detected (usually transmitted over the J1939 network). 
      ICAV_dhist ICAV adaptive progress derivative 
      ICAV_dhist_max Temporarily disables misfire detection if the derivative of 
      the adaptive progress (filtered using the time constant below) exceeds 
      this limit. Enter '0' to disable this feature. 
      ICAV_dhist_tau ICAV adaptive progress derivative filter 
      ICAV_diag_wt ICAV VE/knock detect disable 
      ICAV_ECT_ena Disables and resets misfire detection when the engine coolant 
      temperature is below this threshold. 
      ICAV_ena Enables/disables ICAVbased misfire detection. 
      ICAV_expadpt1 Misfilre cylinder 1 adaptive. 
      ICAV_expadpt10 Misfilre cylinder 10 adaptive. 
      ICAV_expadpt2 Misfilre cylinder 2 adaptive. 
      ICAV_expadpt3 Misfilre cylinder 3 adaptive. 
      ICAV_expadpt4 Misfilre cylinder 4 adaptive. 
      ICAV_expadpt5 Misfilre cylinder 5 adaptive. 
      ICAV_expadpt6 Misfilre cylinder 6 adaptive. 
      ICAV_expadpt7 Misfilre cylinder 7 adaptive. 
      ICAV_expadpt8 Misfilre cylinder 8 adaptive. 
      ICAV_expadpt9 Misfilre cylinder 9 adaptive. 
      ICAV_expadptT Time constant for knock FSO control. See TKNK_FSO_exit_mdot. 

      ICAV_Flag ICAV misfire system flag 
      ICAV_flt_trig Misfire fault trigger threshold 
      ICAV_hires_mult Multiplier to use when performing off-axis high-resolution 
      mode updates. A value of 1.00 limits off-axis adaptive terms to their max 
      possible value * their current interpolation weighting. Values greater 
      than 1.0 allow the off-axis terms to grow towards their maximum values as 
      long as their weighting in the current operating condition is non-zero. 
      ICAV_hist Misfire adaptive progress histogram 
      ICAV_idle_hyst Hysteresis to apply to the 'activate engine speed' when 
      disabling idle mode misfire detection. When a transition to idle mode 
      occurs, misfire detection is initially disabled for a fixed time (see 
      'initial misfire detection disable' below). Once misfire detection is 
      re-enabled, normal misfire detection resumes, albeit with reduced adaptive 
      gains. Idle mode is exited when rpm > 'active engine speed' + 'deactivate 
      engine speed hysteresis'. 
      ICAV_idle_Kmult Multiplier to apply to adaptive gains while in idle mode. 
      When a transition to idle mode occurs, misfire detection is initially 
      disabled for a fixed time (see 'initial misfire detection disable' below). 
      Once misfire detection is re-enabled, normal misfire detection resumes, 
      albeit with reduced adaptive gains. Idle mode is exited when rpm > 'active 
      engine speed' + 'deactivate engine speed hysteresis'. 
      ICAV_idle_rpm Engine speed below which idle mode will be activated. When a 
      transition to idle mode occurs, misfire detection is initially disabled 
      for a fixed time (see 'initial misfire detection disable' below). Once 
      misfire detection is re-enabled, normal misfire detection resumes, albeit 
      with reduced adaptive gains. Idle mode is exited when rpm > 'active engine 
      speed' + 'deactivate engine speed hysteresis'. 
      ICAV_idle_wt Amount of time to disable misfire detection when idle mode is 
      initially activated. When a transition to idle mode occurs, misfire 
      detection is initially disabled for a fixed time (see 'initial misfire 
      detection disable' below). Once misfire detection is re-enabled, normal 
      misfire detection resumes, albeit with reduced adaptive gains. Idle mode 
      is exited when rpm > 'active engine speed' + 'deactivate engine speed 
      hysteresis'. 
      ICAV_ind_cts Misfire Statistics - Continuous Deceleration counts by 
      cylinder 
      ICAV_ind_rdm Misfire Statistics - Random Deceleration counts by cylinder 
      ICAV_KNK_max ICAV knock misfire detect disable 
      ICAV_LED_adapt ICAV misfire system EDIS LED - adapting 
      ICAV_LED_diag ICAV misfire system EDIS LED - diagnosing 
      ICAV_LED_gear ICAV misfire system EDIS LED - gear change 
      ICAV_LED_idle ICAV misfire system EDIS LED - idle mode 
      ICAV_LED_init ICAV misfire system EDIS LED - initialized 
      ICAV_LED_miss ICAV misfire system EDIS LED - misfiring 
      ICAV_LED_safe ICAV misfire system EDIS LED - safe 
      ICAV_LED_trans ICAV misfire system EDIS LED - transient 
      ICAV_maL_max Misfire detection load limit - max. Misfire detection will be 
      temporarily disabled if the mass air flow exceeds this upper limit. 
      ICAV_maL_min Misfire detection load limit - min. Misfire detection will be 
      temporarily disabled if the mass air flow exceeds this lower limit. 
      ICAV_MAPdt_mult Multiplier to use on MAPdt misfire disabling threshold 
      when a misfire is detected. The multiplier remains in use for the number 
      of cycles specified in the persist value below. 
      ICAV_MAPdt_off Misfire MAPdt trigger 
      ICAV_maxcts_maL ICAV max norm continuous indicator load 
      ICAV_maxcts_nrm ICAV max norm continuous indicator 
      ICAV_maxcts_rpm ICAV max norm continuous indicator speed 
      ICAV_max_rdm ICAV random indicator maximum 
      ICAV_miscyl_rst Time to illuminate cylinder-specific LEDs when a misfire 
      is detected. 
      ICAV_miscyl_tmr Individual Cylinder Misfire Detected indicator (based on 
      either firing order or block order) 
      ICAV_misdet_mult Multiplier to apply to emissions/catalyst damaging fault 
      trigger table for general misfire fault triggering. Note the generic 
      'misfire detected' fault compares the table fault trigger to (bank 1 + 2 
      misfire rate) * multiplier. 
      ICAV_mis_cyls Misfire Statistics - Total Misfire counts by cylinder 
      ICAV_nomis_keyc ICAV misfire free key cycles 
      ICAV_nomis_lmt Resets the individual cylinder misfire counts (used for 
      diagnostics only) after a specified number of misfire-free key cycles. Set 
      this value to zero to disable individual cylinder misfire count resetting. 

      ICAV_nrm_bk1 Normalized misfire bank1 
      ICAV_nrm_bk2 Normalized misfire bank2 
      ICAV_nrm_LP2 Normalized Misfire counts (by cylinder) 
      ICAV_nrm_total Normalized misfire 
      ICAV_OILT_src This selection sets whether the oil temperature is 
      calculated from the model or read from the OILT sensor and will disable 
      misfire detection when this temperature is outside a range specified by 
      the maximum and minimum oil temperature tables. When set to 'Sensor' the 
      temperature is read from either the OILT sensor or the OILTL sensor, with 
      the OILT sensor taking precedence. 
      ICAV_pct_bk1 ICAV misfire percent bank1 
      ICAV_pct_bk2 ICAV misfire percent bank2 
      ICAV_pct_LP2 Percent misfire counts (by cylinder) 
      ICAV_pct_tau ICAV tau 
      ICAV_pct_total ICAV misfire percent 
      ICAV_pct_Ttau ICAV misfire pct filter constant 
      ICAV_PTO_ena If enabled, misfire detection is disabled when Power Take-Off 
      (PTO) is active. The engine speed and MAP load maximum limits for PTO 
      misfire detection disable are specified in the "PTO: misfire detection 
      disable max engine speed" and "PTO: misfire detection disable max MAP 
      load" parameters, respectively. 
      ICAV_PTO_MAPload_max Specifies the maximum MAP load misfire detection is 
      disabled when Power Take-Off (PTO) is active. 
      ICAV_PTO_rpm_max Specifies the maximum engine speed misfire detection is 
      disabled when Power Take-Off (PTO) is active. 
      ICAV_rdmtrans_wt Number of cycles to disable random misfire detection 
      after detecting a transient condition and restoring continuous misfire 
      detection. Note that unlike the continuous misfire detection, the 
      decelerations used to diagnose random misfire are not filtered, and are 
      more susceptible to speed/load transients. 
      ICAV_rdm_norm ICAV random normalized indicator 
      ICAV_rdm_rst Re-enables random misfire detection once the random misfire 
      indicator has dropped below the threshold * hysteresis (percent). 
      ICAV_rdm_wt Disables random misfire diagnostics for the specified number 
      of cycles after a misfire is detected. 
      ICAV_reset Misfire reset (Inactive, Reset misfire count, Reset adaptation, 
      Reset all) 
      ICAV_rhst_cnts 2D Interpolation Table - inputs are Airflow (mg/L-disp) and 
      RPM, output is Random Misfires count 
      ICAV_rhst_prog 1D Histogram Table - Histogram divisions are Adapt Prog 
      (cycles), histogram data collected is Random Misfires count 
      ICAV_rhst_tmult 1D Histogram Table - Histogram divisions are Normalized 
      Indicator, histogram data collected is Random Misfires count 
      ICAV_rmis_transwt Disables transient detection for a specified number of 
      cycles after a random misfire occurs. Enter '0' to disable this feature. 
      ICAV_rpmdt_mult Multiplier to use on MAPdt misfire disabling threshold 
      when a misfire is detected. The multiplier remains in use for the number 
      of cycles specified in the persist value below. 
      ICAV_rpmdt_off Disables misfire diagnostics during speed transients. 
      ICAV_rpm_dt ICAV RPMdt 
      ICAV_rpm_max ICAV upper speed limit 
      ICAV_rpm_min ICAV lower speed limit 
      ICAV_safe ICAV adaptive safe 
      ICAV_safe_cnt ICAV adaptive safe percent 
      ICAV_safe_latch ICAV adaptive safe % latch 
      ICAV_start_wait Waiting period upon engine restart before entering 
      ICAV-based misfire detection. 
      ICAV_status ICAV status 
      ICAV_sync_cnt ICAV misfire sync count 
      ICAV_thres_cts ICAV continuous indicator threshold 
      ICAV_thres_hist Number of cycles at a particular operating condition 
      before adaptation is considered complete and diagnostics are enabled. 
      ICAV_thres_mult Multiplier to apply to the continuous and random misfire 
      thresholds while the adaptive progress is less than the adaptive progress 
      threshold. A nonzero multiplier minimizes false-positive misfire 
      detections on initial startups, but reduces the ability to detect true 
      misfires. 
      ICAV_thres_rdm ICAV random indicator threshold 
      ICAV_thres_safe ICAV adaptive safe threshold 
      ICAV_transient_wt Temporarily disables misfire diagnostics following a 
      speed or load transient. 
      ICAV_transx_wt Persistence for MAPdt/rpmdt disabling threshold multiplier 
      once a misfire is detected. 
      ICAV_VECWT_max VE cylinder wall temperature + misfire detect disable 
      ICAV_VECWT_min VE cylinder wall temperature - misfire detect disable 
      ICAV_wdw_mult ICAV acceleration window multipliers 
      ICAV_wind_safe Safe region duty-cycle wind-up time. The safe region 
      duty-cycle winds up to 100% while operating in the safe region. When a 
      transition from a safe to an unsafe region occurs, adaptation is left 
      enabled while the duty-cycle winds down to 0%. 
      ICAV_wind_unsafe Unsafe region duty-cycle wind-down time. The safe region 
      duty-cycle winds up to 100% while operating in the safe region. When a 
      transition from a safe to an unsafe region occurs, adaptation is left 
      enabled while the duty-cycle winds down to 0%. 
      ICCOT Intercooler coolant outlet temperature. 
      ICCOT_ena Intercooler coolant outlet temperature channel. 
      ICCOT_hi_RPMmin Minimum engine speed fault condition for the "ICCOT 
      temperature high" diagnostic 
      ICCOT_hi_Tmax Intercooler coolant outlet temperature threshold fault 
      condition for the "ICCOT temperature high" diagnostic 
      ICCOT_hi_wait Minimum engine run time fault condition for the "ICCOT 
      temperature high" diagnostic 
      ICCOT_proj_lp Low-passed projected intercooler coolant outlet temperature. 

      ICCOT_proj_tau Low-pass time constant for the projected intercooler 
      coolant outlet temperature. 
      ICCOT_resp_tau Intercooler coolant outlet temperature sensor response 
      time, which is used to estimate the instantaneous temperature at the 
      sensor. 
      ICCOT_Taux_cal Intercooler coolant outlet temperature calibration table. 
      ICCOT_vdr Intercooler coolant outlet temperature pullup resistor value. 
      IC_pin_pulse_arm Cam1 fault pin-unlock logic 
      IC_pin_pulse_state This mode tracks the state machine states during intake 
      cam impending fault pin unlocking activity. 
      IC_pin_pulse_try Cam1 fault pin-unlock activity 
      IdleFPP_ena Switch to allow initial idle speed modification based on FPP 
      percent command. 
      IdleFPP_loadadd If a droop min governor is used, a linear interpolated 
      fraction of this value over the FPP range will be added to the nominal 
      load. 
      IdleFPP_max Upper end of FPP command percent range for idle speed 
      modification. FPP values above this will value will cause use of this 
      maximum idle speed target. 
      IdleFPP_min Lower end of FPP command percent range for idle speed 
      modification. FPP values below this will value will cause use of an 
      unmodified idle speed target. 
      IdleFPP_rpmdelta Specifies the speed range adder for idle speed 
      modification based on interpolation between the lower and upper FPP 
      command percent values. 
      IdleFPP_rpmmax Specifies the maximum allowed commanded idle speed after 
      adding the rpm delta to the current base idle speed. If this value is 
      below the base idle speed, the base idle speed is used.

      idle_SD_ena If enabled, the engine will automatically shutdown after the 
      "Idle shutdown time" if the engine remains on idle and roadspeed is zero.

      idle_SD_sw_chan This switch overrides (disables) the automatic idle 
      shutdown. 
      idle_SD_tout Amount of time in idle and stationary before automatic engine 
      shutdown is initiated. 
      idle_SD_wait_tout Minimum amount of time between the engine entering idle 
      shutdown, and the release of idle shutdown. Entering idle shutdown will 
      stop fuel to the engine. Releasing idle shutdown will resume fuel to the 
      engine. The back-on time specifies the delay that will be imposed between 
      turning off fuel (shutdown initiated) and restoring of fuel (release of 
      the shutdown).

      The back-on time is essentially a fuel transport delay to allow clearing 
      of fuel before spark ignition is resumed. 
      IGN_DIS_chan Selects the digital input channel used for the Ignition 
      Disable (IGN_DIS) switch. 
      IGN_DIS_chan_cfg If an Aux DIG is selected for the input, this value 
      determines the logic state(s) where the engine is allowed to run. An 
      active state for this input indicates that a shutdown is NOT requested. 
      The Default active values are:

      Aux DIG1 = Gnd
      Aux DIG2 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG3 = Gnd
      Aux DIG4 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG5 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG6 = +V/Gnd

      Aux DIG19 = Gnd
      Gov1 = Gnd
      Gov2 = Gnd

      IGN_DIS_Sw_state Indicates the SPOCK IGN_DIS switch state. 
      IGN_LED Indicates the SPOCK IGN_DIS switch state. 
      Imax_gov_acc Max speed governor integral accumulator 
      Imax_gov_save Saved copy of Imax_gov_acc used for reinitializing 
      Imax_gov_start Max Governor initial integrator value 
      Imin_gov_acc Min speed governor integral accumulator 
      Imin_gov_save Saved copy of Imin_gov_acc used for reinitializing 
      Imin_gov_start Min Governor initial integrator value 
      imu_accel_x IMU Accelerometer X-axis linear acceleration value in g. 
      imu_accel_x_max Specifies the value at which the accelerometer X-axis 
      value should be considered out-of-range high. The “Accelerometer 
      full-scale range” calibration setting should be considered when adjusting 
      this value. 
      imu_accel_x_min Specifies the value at which the accelerometer X-axis 
      value should be considered out-of-range low. The “Accelerometer full-scale 
      range” calibration setting should be considered when adjusting this value. 

      imu_accel_x_raw IMU Accelerometer X-axis linear acceleration raw value 
      (OUTX_L_XL, OUTX_H_XL). 
      imu_accel_y IMU Accelerometer Y-axis linear acceleration value in g. 
      imu_accel_y_max Specifies the value at which the accelerometer Y-axis 
      value should be considered out-of-range high. The “Accelerometer 
      full-scale range” calibration setting should be considered when adjusting 
      this value. 
      imu_accel_y_min Specifies the value at which the accelerometer Y-axis 
      value should be considered out-of-range low. The “Accelerometer full-scale 
      range” calibration setting should be considered when adjusting this value. 

      imu_accel_y_raw IMU Accelerometer Y-axis linear acceleration raw value 
      (OUTY_L_XL, OUTY_H_XL). 
      imu_accel_z IMU Accelerometer Z-axis linear acceleration value in g. 
      imu_accel_z_max Specifies the value at which the accelerometer Z-axis 
      value should be considered out-of-range high. The “Accelerometer 
      full-scale range” calibration setting should be considered when adjusting 
      this value. 
      imu_accel_z_min Specifies the value at which the accelerometer Z-axis 
      value should be considered out-of-range low. The “Accelerometer full-scale 
      range” calibration setting should be considered when adjusting this value. 

      imu_accel_z_raw IMU Accelerometer Z-axis linear acceleration raw value 
      (OUTZ_L_XL, OUTZ_H_XL). 
      imu_gyro_x IMU Gyroscope X-axis (Pitch) angular rate value in dps. 
      imu_gyro_x_max Specifies the value at which the gyroscope X-axis value 
      should be considered out-of-range high. The “Gyroscope full-scale range” 
      calibration setting should be considered when adjusting this value. 
      imu_gyro_x_min Specifies the value at which the gyroscope X-axis value 
      should be considered out-of-range low. The “Gyroscope full-scale range” 
      calibration setting should be considered when adjusting this value. 
      imu_gyro_x_raw IMU Gyroscope X-axis (Pitch) angular rate raw value 
      (OUTX_L_G, OUTX_H_G). 
      imu_gyro_y IMU Gyroscope Y-axis (Roll) angular rate value in dps. 
      imu_gyro_y_max Specifies the value at which the gyroscope Y-axis value 
      should be considered out-of-range high. The “Gyroscope full-scale range” 
      calibration setting should be considered when adjusting this value. 
      imu_gyro_y_min Specifies the value at which the gyroscope Y-axis value 
      should be considered out-of-range low. The “Gyroscope full-scale range” 
      calibration setting should be considered when adjusting this value. 
      imu_gyro_y_raw IMU Gyroscope Y-axis (Roll) angular rate raw value 
      (OUTY_L_G, OUTY_H_G). 
      imu_gyro_z IMU Gyroscope Z-axis (Yaw) angular rate value in dps. 
      imu_gyro_z_max Specifies the value at which the gyroscope Z-axis value 
      should be considered out-of-range high. The “Gyroscope full-scale range” 
      calibration setting should be considered when adjusting this value. 
      imu_gyro_z_min Specifies the value at which the gyroscope Z-axis value 
      should be considered out-of-range low. The “Gyroscope full-scale range” 
      calibration setting should be considered when adjusting this value. 
      imu_gyro_z_raw IMU Gyroscope Z-axis (Yaw) angular rate raw value 
      (OUTZ_L_G, OUTZ_H_G). 
      imu_support Indicates if an inertial measurement unit (IMU) sensor is 
      supported on the platform 
      imu_temp IMU Temperature (OUT_TEMP_L, OUT_TEMP). 
      imu_temp_max Specifies the value at which the temperature received from 
      the inertial measurement unit will be considered excessively high. The 
      LSM6DS3 IMU has an operating temperature range of -40 to 85 degrees 
      Celsius. 
      imu_temp_min Specifies the value at which the temperature received from 
      the inertial measurement unit will be considered excessively low. The 
      LSM6DS3 IMU has an operating temperature range of -40 to 85 degrees 
      Celsius. 
      imu_temp_min_wait Specifies the time to wait after key-on before executing 
      the diagnostic. When operating in very cold environments this allows time 
      for the inertial measurement unit to heat up and thus avoid false 
      positives diagnostic conclusions. 
      IMVD_Ifb_hi This is the current threshold above which an IMV short-circuit 
      or low-side short-to-power diagnostic will set. 
      IMVD_Ifb_lo This is the current threshold below which an IMV open-circuit 
      or low-side short-to-ground diagnostic will set. 
      IMVD_lo_Icmd For Continuous-Current (i.e. proportional valve type) IMV 
      open-circuit or low-side short-to-ground diagnostics, this is the minimum 
      current command required to allow detection. 
      IMVD_lo_PWcmd For Pulsed-IMV open-circuit or low-side short-to-ground 
      diagnostics, this is the minimum pulse-width required to allow detection. 
      IMVpck_CADfixed During post-sync cranking, the pulsed-IMV control will 
      transition to crank-synchronous fixed-CAD-pulse bang-bang control instead 
      of fixed-time-interval bang-bang control. This is the duration of the IMV 
      pulses in that mode. 
      IMVpck_CAD_cycmin During pre-sync cranking fixed-time-interval IMV pulse 
      mode, the engine will remain in this mode even if sync is attained for 
      this minimum number of engine cycles or until the target rail pressure is 
      achieved. Set to zero to immediately transition to fixed-CAD-interval mode 
      at sync. 
      IMVpck_Pctlhyst_pct Pulsed-IMV cranking mode 'bang-bang' pressure control 
      hysteresis value. IMV fixed-time pulses will fire until the target rail 
      pressure is achieved, and then they will stop firing until the rail 
      pressure falls to the target minus this hysteresis value. 
      IMVpck_presync_tau Pulsed-IMV cranking mode fixed-time pulse firing 
      interval prior to the engine attaining full cam-sync. 
      IMVpck_pstsync_ph Pulsed-IMV cranking mode post-sync pulse firing engine 
      position phasing. 
      IMVpck_PWfixed Pulsed-IMV cranking mode fixed-time pulse-width that is 
      used for 'bang-bang' control during cranking. 
      IMVpck_taufix PulsedIMV cranking mode fixed time interval firing 
      modeeither active or inactive depending on the sync state. 
      IMVpulsetest_mode For pulsedIMV control, this test mode allows firing of 
      the IMV pulses in astopped engine condition at a 50ms intervalbut note 
      that relay power must be engaged manually if required. 
      IMVpulsetest_pw For pulsedIMV control, this is the duration of the pulse 
      test mode pulse in an engine stopped condition (see CRI_IMVpulse_test for 
      more details). 
      IMVpulse_Icushion For pulsed-IMV control, this is the average current 
      target for the 'cushion' phase of the pulse waveform following the 
      completion of the 'on-time' pulse. 
      IMVpulse_Ihold For pulsed-IMV control, this is the 'hold' current 
      following the 'peak' and 'reduce' phases of the pulse waveform. 
      IMVpulse_Ipeak For pulsed-IMV control, this is the peak current achieved 
      at then end of the 'peak' phase of the pulse waveform. 
      IMVpulse_Ireduce For pulsed-IMV control, this is the average current 
      during the 'reduce' phase between the 'peak' and 'hold' phases of the 
      pulse waveform. 
      IMVpulse_Tcushion For pulsed-IMV control, this is the time duration of the 
      'cushion' phase following the 'pause' or 'off' phase of the pulse 
      waveform. 
      IMVpulse_Tdecay For pulsed-IMV control, this is the time duration of the 
      'decay' phase following the 'cushion' phase of the pulse waveform during 
      which the solenoid is in a free-wheel mode before final cushioning 
      termination. 
      IMVpulse_Tmx_rpmeq For Pulsed-IMV control during cranking and dry-rail 
      detection, this rpm value will be used to compute a time-equivalent max 
      IMV pulse duration at 90% duty-cycle between IMV intake events to override 
      the absolute time value IMVpulse_Ttotal_max. Set to 0 to disable this 
      feature or for backward compatibility. 
      IMVpulse_Tpause For pulsed-IMV control, this is the time duration of the 
      'pause' or 'off' phase between the end of the 'on-time' or 'hold' phase 
      and the 'cushion' phase of the pulse waveform. 
      IMVpulse_Tpeak_max For pulsed-IMV control, this is the maximum time that 
      will be allowed for the peak phase of the current pulse regardless of 
      battery voltage. 
      IMVpulse_Treduce For pulsed-IMV control, this is the time duration of the 
      'reduce' phase between the 'peak' and 'hold' phases of the pulse waveform. 

      IMVpulse_Ttotal_max For pulsed-IMV control, this is the maximum time that 
      will be allowed for the total effective on-time phase of the current pulse 
      regardless of battery voltage or any other command override. This total 
      time excludes the time required for any additional pause, cushion, or 
      decay phases. 
      IMV_pulse_phase The pulsed-IMV mode end-of-pulse phasing relative to TDCC 
      #1 cylinder. 
      IMV_pulse_spacing The pulse spacing for pulse-IMV mode control. This is 
      usually synchronous to the number of lobes on the high pressure pump. 
      IMV_varcam_mode If the pump/pulsed-IMV are driven by a variable camshaft, 
      this mode allows the firing angle of the IMV to be continuously adjusted 
      based on the current camshaft position. If the pump/pulsed-IMV are driven 
      by a fixed camshaft or some other crankshaft-phase-locked device, this 
      mode should be disabled by selecting the 'Fixed' option. 
      IMV_varcam_nom If a variable-cam driven pulsed-IMV is specified, then this 
      timing value represents the 'nominal' or 'cranking' cam timing for which 
      there is zero adjustment to the IMV firing angle. If the actual timing 
      during running advances past this value, the IMV pulse will advance by the 
      same difference. 
      INDUCEblk_off An Inducement warning may cause a continuous output 
      activation or a blinking/pulsing output. The on/off times specify this 
      behavior. For a continuously on output in an active state, set the 
      off-time to zero and the on-time to any value. 
      INDUCEblk_on An Inducement warning may cause a continuous output 
      activation or a blinking/pulsing output. The on/off times specify this 
      behavior. For a continuously on output in an active state, set the 
      off-time to zero and the on-time to any value. 
      INDUCEout_mirror Current on/off state of the Inducement warning output 
      pin. 
      INDUCE_bulbchk This is the time that the Inducement warning output will 
      remain on following an initial key-on/engine-stopped event to allow the 
      operator to observe that the output (bulb) is functioning. 
      INDUCE_bulbon Determines whether the Inducement warning output will be 
      continuously on or blinked/pulsed during the key-on bulb check period. 
      INDUCE_lamp This switch selects the J1939 network output lamp for 
      inducement faults. 
      Inj10_bank Injector 10 location (Not Present, Bank 1, Bank 2) 
      inj10_info_bo Injector 10 block order 
      inj10_info_class Injector 10 class 
      inj10_info_fo Injector 10 firing order 
      inj10_info_hw Injector 10 hardware channel

      INJD_max_riseT For CR injector open-circuit diagnostics, this is the 
      maximum current rise time allowed to the peak current target during the 
      boost phase. 
      INJD_min_riseT For CR injector short-circuit diagnostics, this is the 
      minimum current rise time allowed to the peak current target during the 
      boost phase. 
      INJD_off_lo Injector Loop Open or Low-Side Short to Ground diagnostic: 
      Non-CR Injector off-state low-side voltage entry condition 
      INJD_off_minVbat Injector Loop Open or Low-Side Short to Ground 
      diagnostic: minimum battery voltage entry condition 
      INJD_on_hi Injector Coil Shorted diagnostic: Non-CR Injector off-state 
      low-side voltage entry condition 
      INJD_on_maxVbat Injector Coil Shorted diagnostic: maximum battery voltage 
      entry condition 
      INJD_ph_maxR_minV For peak and hold injection this is the minimum battery 
      voltage required for accurate peak current rise time analysis. At lower 
      voltages the injector may not be able to achieve the peak current target. 
      INJD_Vboost_HItol For CR injection drive, this is the maximum (actual - 
      target) voltage tolerance applied to detect high boost voltage for 
      diagnostics (note - positive value). 
      INJD_Vboost_LOtol For CR injection drive, this is the maximum (target - 
      actual) voltage tolerance applied to detect low boost voltage for 
      diagnostics (note - positive value). 
      InjTT_dcy_t Crank injection timing transition decay 
      InjTT_x_dcy Crank injection timing transition decay fraction 
      inj_active_class Active injector class 
      inj_active_order Active injector order 
      inj_count The total number of physical injector drivers utilized on the 
      ECM. 
      inj_count_postrun Post-running injection count 
      inj_count_prerun Pre-running injection count

      parameter. 
      inj_gaseous_tipout Gaseous injection downstream volume compensation 
      parameter. 
      inj_gaseous_VmL Gaseous injection downstream volume compensation 
      parameter. 
      inj_kill Injector kill 
      inj_kill_mode Injector kill mode 
      inj_kill_tout This is the maximum continuous amount of time that a single 
      injector can remain killed during an injector kill test. After the 
      timeout, this test will be reset to off. Setting this value to greater 
      than 60.0 seconds (i.e. 61.0 seconds) effectively disables this timeout. 
      inj_mode Injection mode indication, inj_mode = -1 Full Sequential, =0, 
      Initial pending, = +1, Initial Fired 
      inj_off_min Minimum injector off-time - primary. This is the minimum time 
      required following an injection before the controller will attempt to add 
      another injection. This time insures that the prior injection is 
      mechanically completed so that an accurate accounting of the injected fuel 
      can be made. 
      inj_off_min_I2 Minimum injector off-time - secondary. This is the minimum 
      time required following an injection before the controller will attempt to 
      add another injection. This time insures that the prior injection is 
      mechanically completed so that an accurate accounting of the injected fuel 
      can be made. 
      inj_roll_active Logical indicating that injection roll is active which is 
      used with a mismatched # of injectors/cylinders which is used with 
      Throttle Body Injection 
      inj_sweep_CL_delay This is the time between individual injector tests to 
      allow CL BM to return to normal operating conditions. The maximum allowed 
      time is 65 seconds. 
      inj_sweep_delta This is the minimum CL BM change required for an 
      individual injector to pass the injector sweep test when that injector is 
      killed. 
      inj_sweep_ena This shows if the injector sweep test is currently running. 
      The test will not run if any of the following conditions are true: 
      -Engine is not injected
      -Injector individual kill timeout > 60 seconds
      -CL is not running
      -Engine is not running 
      inj_sweep_results Injector sweep test results 
      inj_sweep_state Displays the current status of the injector sweep test. If 
      the test is "Active", this will inform the user what part of the test is 
      currently active, i.e. the ECM is waiting for CL to reach steady state 
      after an injector is tested. If the test is "Disabled", this will inform 
      the user if a test has run since the ECM has been power cycled and whether 
      that test resulted in success or error. 
      inj_sweep_tmr This displays the time elapsed for each time-dependent state 
      in the injector sweep test. When in the "Test Injector n" state, this will 
      display the time elapsed since the injector was killed and will not exceed 
      the value set in "Injector individual kill timeout". When in the 
      "Restoring CL Baseline" state, testing will not begin on the next injector 
      until the time specified in "Injector sweep CL reset delay" has elapsed. 
      inj_sweep_tout This is the maximum continuous amount of time that each 
      injector can remain killed during the individual injector kill part of 
      this test. This time should be sufficient to allow for the CL BM to 
      respond to the killed injector.
      This time cannot exceed 60 seconds. 
      inj_sync_trans_ena This option determines how injection events are handled 
      when transitioning from crank-to-cam synced. It should generally be 
      enabled on new applications and set to 'legacy handling' on old 
      applications.

      1) If legacy handling is used, certain cylinders may experience an extra 
      or missing injection event during the crank-to-cam synchronization 
      transition. Many application parameters affect if individual cylinders 
      will miss or receive an extra injection event: number of cylinders, 
      crank-cam configuration, position of the cam synchronization event, and 
      cranking injection timing. Note that if the initial crank position guess 
      is correct, all injection events are correct. If the initial crank 
      position guess is incorrect and gets corrected when the cam synchronizes, 
      certain cylinders may experience an extra or missing injection event. The 
      behavior is consistent and repeatable, however, so leaving this set to 
      'legacy handling' is the recommended mode for old applications.

      a. For waste-spark and distributed ignition applications, injections are 
      typically started while only crank-synced. On the transition to 
      cam-synced, certain cylinders may receive an extra injection event while 
      other cylinders may go a cycle without fuel.

      b. For coil-on-plug applications, all injectors will typically fire when 
      cam synchronization occurs. If a cylinder fires just after or near the 
      closing of the intake valve and the fuel does not enter the cylinder 
      immediately, that cylinder may receive an extra injection event. A 
      double-event is more likely to occur on 8 cylinder applications and less 
      likely on 4 cylinder applications.

      2) If enabled, all prior and future injection events are individually 
      analyzed when cam synchronization occurs. If a prior event finishes at 
      least 45 CAD BBDCI, it is considered to have entered on the 
      previous/current intake event. If a prior event finishes after 45 CAD 
      BBDCI, it is considered late and will enter in the next engine cycle so 
      the event on the next cycle is skipped in order to avoid double 
      injections. Similarly, if an event is late but can complete before 45 CAD 
      BBDCI, it is immediately fired. If the event is late and cannot complete 
      before 45 CAD BBDCI, the injection event is skipped. 

      NOTE: For GM distributed applications, 30 CAD BBDCI is used instead of 45 
      CAD BBDCI. 
      inj_timing Injection timing 
      inj_timing_crk This is the initial injection timing used during cranking 
      that may also be used during linear decay during after start. 
      inj_timing_dz This parameter specifies a cubic-rolloff deadzone for 
      instantaneous changes in injection timing. Changes in injection timing >= 
      this value are instantaneously implemented, and changes < this value are 
      slewed-in over the low-pass time constant specified below. 
      inj_timing_dz_I2 This parameter specifies a cubic-rolloff deadzone for 
      instantaneous changes in injection timing. Changes in injection timing >= 
      this value are instantaneously implemented, and changes < this value are 
      slewed-in over the low-pass time constant specified below. 
      inj_timing_dz_tau Primary Injection timing dead zone tau. See 
      inj_timing_dz 
      inj_timing_dz_tau_I2 Secondary Injection timing dead zone tau. See 
      inj_timing_dz_I2 
      inj_timing_norm This is the normal injection timing used during running 
      without lowpass or deadzone effects. 
      inj_type Fuel injector type 
      intby_poserr_err Position error percentage threshold for the "Unable to 
      reach intercooler/EGR cooler split valve target position" diagnostic. 
      intby_poserr_minVbat Minimum battery voltage threshold for the "Unable to 
      reach intercooler/EGR cooler split valve target position" diagnostic. 
      intby_poserr_wait Minimum duration the position error must persistently 
      occur for the "Unable to reach intercooler/EGR cooler split valve target 
      position" diagnostic.

      IOAI_alternator Selects the input used for alternator monitoring. If an 
      Aux PUD input or the default input is selected, it is assumed to be a 
      0-28.3V input. If an input with a different voltage range is selected, the 
      reported alternator voltage will be incorrect. When an Aux DIG input is 
      selected, normal scaling is used.

      channel for communicating the reverse hydraulic pressure signal to the ECM

      parking brake position sensor. See park_brake_rawfilt and 
      park_brake_sw_stat for measured feedback values.

      channel for the seat occupancy sensor.

      IparkA_dly HBA Actuator park current delay: Time that H-bridge current 
      must exceed the park limit before command limiting becomes active. 
      Similarly this amount of time must pass for it to deactivate. 
      IparkA_ena HBA Actuator parking current control enable: This feature will 
      attenuate the max H-bridge command after the 'park current limit' has been 
      exceeded for the time defined in 'park delay'. The electrical model is 
      used to estimate the current.
      -- Single Point: Uses 'Actuator I park limit' as parking current limit for 
      entire range of position feedback.
      -- 1-D Lookup Table: Uses the 4-point 'Table-based I park limit' to set a 
      limit current that is dependent on position sensor feedback. 
      IparkA_Ilim HBA park current limit when 'Single-Point' mode is selected. 
      IparkA_Ki HBA ramp rate used when transitioning into or out of park 
      current limiting. Ramps the attenuation that will be applied to the 
      H-bridge maximum command. 
      IparkA_max_att HBA park current max attenuation 
      IparkB_dly HBB Actuator park current delay: Time that H-bridge current 
      must exceed the park limit before command limiting becomes active. 
      Similarly this amount of time must pass for it to deactivate. 
      IparkB_ena HBB Actuator parking current control enable: This feature will 
      attenuate the max H-bridge command after the 'park current limit' has been 
      exceeded for the time defined in 'park delay'. The electrical model is 
      used to estimate the current.
      -- Single Point: Uses 'Actuator I park limit' as parking current limit for 
      entire range of position feedback.
      -- 1-D Lookup Table: Uses the 4-point 'Table-based I park limit' to set a 
      limit current that is dependent on position sensor feedback. 
      IparkB_Ilim HBB park current limit when 'Single-Point' mode is selected. 
      IparkB_Ki HBB ramp rate used when transitioning into or out of park 
      current limiting. Ramps the attenuation that will be applied to the 
      H-bridge maximum command. 
      IparkB_max_att HBB park current max attenuation 
      Ipark_dly DBW Actuator park current delay: Time that H-bridge current must 
      exceed the park limit before command limiting becomes active. Similarly 
      this amount of time must pass for it to deactivate. 
      Ipark_ena DBW Actuator parking current control enable: This feature will 
      attenuate the max H-bridge command after the 'park current limit' has been 
      exceeded for the time defined in 'park delay'. The electrical model is 
      used to estimate the current.
      -- Single Point: Uses 'Actuator I park limit' as parking current limit for 
      entire range of position feedback.
      -- 1-D Lookup Table: Uses the 4-point 'Table-based I park limit' to set a 
      limit current that is dependent on position sensor feedback. 
      Ipark_Ilim DBW park current limit when 'Single-Point' mode is selected. 
      Ipark_Ki DBW ramp rate used when transitioning into or out of park current 
      limiting. Ramps the attenuation that will be applied to the H-bridge 
      maximum command. 
      Ipark_max_att DBW park current max attenuation 
      IPAS_engaged Indicates when the idle pull away speed is engaged. 
      IPAS_mode Sets engagement and disengagement conditions for using an 
      elevated idle speed to improve vehicle pull away performance.

      If set to "Vehicle speed only", the elevated idle speed will be used if 
      roadspeed exceeds the engagement speed, and the normal idle speed will be 
      used if roadspeed drops below the maximum disengagement speed.

      If set to "Vehicle speed + parking brake", the elevated idle speed will be 
      used if vehicle speed conditions are met, or if the transmission is in 
      gear and the parking brake is inactive.

      If set to "Vehicle speed + parking brake + foot brake", the elevated idle 
      speed will be used if vehicle speed conditions are met, or if the 
      transmission is in gear, the parking brake is inactive, and the foot brake 
      is inactive. 
      IPAS_rpm Minimum governor speed to use when idle pull away speed 
      conditions are met. 
      IPAS_speed_off The idle speed returns to the normal idle speed after 
      roadspeed is below this value. 
      IPAS_speed_on The elevated idle speed will be used after roadspeed exceeds 
      this value. 
      IRV_AFILT_dP Air filter pressure drop at IRV flow rate. 
      IRV_CL_Amax IRV closed-loop min authority. 
      IRV_CL_Amin IRV closed-loop proportional gain. 
      IRV_CL_crct IRV valve closed-loop correction. 
      IRV_CL_Iaccum IRV closed-loop integral accumulator. 
      IRV_CL_Kd IRV closed-loop derivative gain. 
      IRV_CL_Ki IRV closed-loop integral gain. 
      IRV_CL_Kp IRV closed-loop max authority. 
      IRV_dP_cmd IRV commanded delta-P to achieve the target EGRLP. 
      IRV_EGRLPd IRV EGRLP pressure target. 
      IRV_EGRLP_error IRV EGRLP pressure error = 
      IRV_Pin IRV inlet pressure (estimated). 
      IRV_PR_cmd IRV pressure ratio command post-limiting, calculated from the 
      IRV delta-P command and the inlet pressure. 
      IRV_PR_max Maximum pressure ratio for the IRV feedforward term 
      computation. Generally, setting this to 0.98 yields acceptable results. 
      IRV_vlv_act IRV actual position. 
      IRV_vlv_cmd IRV commanded position. 
      IRV_vlv_max Maximum IRV position command, typically set to 100% to allow 
      the IRV to be fully open when EGR is off or sufficient EGR delta-P exists. 

      IRV_vlv_min Minimum IRV position command, typically set to a value greater 
      than 0 since the IRV should never be fully closed. 
      ISO15765_2_Err_Cnt Count of packets that triggered an error within layer 2 
      TP 
      ISO15765_2_Err_Code Bit mask of error codes triggered within layer 2 TP 
      ISO15765_4_Err_Cnt Count of packets that triggered an error within OBD 
      ISO15765_4_Err_Code Bit mask of error codes triggered within OBD 
      ISO15765_emissup Enables support for transmission of PID 0x5F - "Emission 
      requirements to which vehicle is designed" over the ISO 15031 and/or the 
      ISO 14229 protocol.

      For the ISO 15031 / SAE J1979 protocol this value is transmitted in 
      response to a Service 0x01 "Request current powertrain diagnostic data" 
      request for PID ID 0x5F - " Emission requirements to which vehicle is 
      designed".

      For the ISO 14229 (UDS) protocol this value is transmitted in response to 
      a Service 0x22 – "ReadDataByIdentifier" request for DID 0xF45F – "Emission 
      requirements to which vehicle is designed". 
      ISO15765_ena Obsoleted parameter 
      ISO15765_ipt_comp Enables support for transmission of InfoType 0x0B - 
      "In-use Performance Tracking for compression ignition engines" over the 
      ISO 15031 and/or the ISO 14229 protocol.

      For the ISO 15031 / SAE J1979 protocol this value is transmitted in 
      response to a Service 0x09 - "Request Vehicle Information" request for PID 
      ID 0x0B - "In-use Performance Tracking for compression ignition engines".

      For the ISO 14229 (UDS) protocol this value is transmitted in response to 
      a Service 0x22 - "ReadDataByIdentifier" request for DID 0xF80B - "In-use 
      Performance Tracking for compression ignition engines". 
      ISO15765_ipt_spark Enables support for transmission of InfoType 0x08 - 
      "In-use Performance Tracking for spark ignition engines" over the ISO 
      15031 and/or the ISO 14229 protocol.

      For the ISO 15031 / SAE J1979 protocol this value is transmitted in 
      response to a Service 0x09 - "Request Vehicle Information" request for PID 
      ID 0x08 - "In-use Performance Tracking for spark ignition engines".

      For the ISO 14229 (UDS) protocol this value is transmitted in response to 
      a Service 0x22 - "ReadDataByIdentifier" request for DID 0xF808 - "In-use 
      Performance Tracking for spark ignition engines". 
      ISO15765_lambda_max Parameter configures the maximum air-to-fuel 
      equivalence ratio (lambda) in PID 0x4F (data byte A). When parameter is 
      set to 'Custom (4.000)', then data byte A will report 0x04. The scaling 
      for PIDs 0x34 to 0x3B and 0x44 will be 4.000/65535 (0.0000610 per bit). 
      When parameter is set to 'Default (1.999)', then data byte A will report 
      0x00. The scaling for PIDs 0x34 to 0x3B and 0x44 will be the default which 
      is 1.999/65535 (0.0000305 per bit). 
      ISO15765_obdsup Enables support for transmission of PID 0x1C - "OBD 
      requirements to which vehicle or engine is certified" over the ISO 15031 
      and/or the ISO 14229 protocol.

      For the ISO 15031 / SAE J1979 protocol this value is transmitted in 
      response to a Service 0x01 "Request current powertrain diagnostic data" 
      request for PID ID 0x1C - "OBD requirements to which vehicle or engine is 
      certified".

      For the ISO 14229 (UDS) protocol this value is transmitted in response to 
      a Service 0x22 – "ReadDataByIdentifier" request for DID 0xF41C – "OBD 
      requirements to which vehicle or engine is certified".

      J1939EC_broad2_ena If this switch is set to 'Enabled', the J1939 Engine 
      Configuration (EC1) PGN will be broadcast at either 5 or 2 second 
      intervals (set in the 'J1939 EC1 broadcast rate' dropdown). This is a 
      large (34 byte) multi-packet message.

      Inherent support is provided for Tx broadcast of this message - DO NOT 
      enter the PGN into the 'Broadcast Tx PGN List'. DO enter the PGN (65251) 
      into the 'Supported Tx PGN List' to enable the broadcast.

      Similarly, this dropdown handles the corresponding J1939 Retarder 
      Configuration (RC) PGN (65249) -- follow the EC1 rules above for handling 
      cal setup of the RC packet. 
      J1939EC_broad3_ena If this switch is set to 'Enabled', the J1939 Engine 
      Configuration (EC1) PGN will be broadcast at either 5 or 2 second 
      intervals (set in the 'J1939 EC1 broadcast rate' dropdown). This is a 
      large (34 byte) multi-packet message.

      Inherent support is provided for Tx broadcast of this message - DO NOT 
      enter the PGN into the 'Broadcast Tx PGN List'. DO enter the PGN (65251) 
      into the 'Supported Tx PGN List' to enable the broadcast.

      Similarly, this dropdown handles the corresponding J1939 Retarder 
      Configuration (RC) PGN (65249) -- follow the EC1 rules above for handling 
      cal setup of the RC packet. 
      J1939EC_broad_ena If this switch is set to 'Enabled', the J1939 Engine 
      Configuration(EC1) PGN will be broadcast at either 5 or 2 second intervals 
      (set in the 'J1939 EC1 broadcast rate' dropdown).
      This is a large (34 byte) multi-packet message.Inherent support is 
      provided for Tx broadcast of this message - DO NOT enter the PGN into the 
      'Broadcast Tx PGN List'.
      DO enter the PGN (65251) into the 'Supported Tx PGN List' to enable the 
      broadcast.Similarly, this dropdown handles the corresponding J1939 
      Retarder Configuration (RC) PGN (65249) - follow the EC1 rules above for 
      handling cal setup of the RC packet. 
      J1939EC_tx_rate Determines the broadcast rate for the Engine Configuration 
      (EC) and/or Retarder Configuration (RC) PGNs if they have been enabled for 
      broadcast by the "J1939 EC1/RC broadcast" setting. The "J1939 EC1/RC 
      broadcast" option is per CAN channel and the broadcast rate applies to all 
      CAN channels. 
      J1939RC_ER_pt3_rpmd Specifies the engine speed for point 3, SPN 549, of 
      the J1939 retarder torque curve in the RC PG sent from source address 15 
      (Engine Retarder). 
      J1939RC_ER_pt4_rpmd Specifies the engine speed for point 4, SPN 550, of 
      the J1939 retarder torque curve in the RC PG sent from source address 15 
      (Engine Retarder). 
      J1939RC_ER_rpm Engine speeds for the five-point retarder torque curve in 
      the J1939 RC PG sent from source address 15 (Engine Retarder). 
      J1939RC_ER_trq Torque percentages for the five-point retarder torque curve 
      in the J1939 RC PG sent from source address 15 (Engine Retarder). 
      J1939RC_EXR_pt3_rpmd Specifies the engine speed for point 3, SPN 549, of 
      the J1939 retarder torque curve in the RC PG sent from source address 41 
      (Exhaust Retarder). 
      J1939RC_EXR_pt4_rpmd Specifies the engine speed for point 4, SPN 550, of 
      the J1939 retarder torque curve in the RC PG sent from source address 41 
      (Exhaust Retarder). 
      J1939RC_EXR_rpm Engine speeds for the five-point retarder torque curve in 
      the J1939 RC PG sent from source address 41 (Exhaust Retarder). 
      J1939RC_EXR_trq Torque percentages for the five-point retarder torque 
      curve in the J1939 RC PG sent from source address 41 (Exhaust Retarder). 
      J1939_ABS_active LED to indicate when J1939 indicates ABS is active 
      J1939_addr2Fail J1939-2 address conflict fail limit 
      J1939_addr2_conflict J1939 address conflict counter - CAN2 
      J1939_addr2_frcena This switch selects how the J1939 address is computed 
      for the CAN link. 'Engine Number Based' uses the 
      master/slave1/slave2/slave3 engine number configuration to set the address 
      to 0/1/138/139. 'Forced Constant Value' uses the numerical value below 
      without regard for any changes in engine number. 
      J1939_addr2_frcval When the CAN2 address selection mode is set to 'Forced 
      Constant Value' this is the value that is used for the address. This value 
      is ignored otherwise. 
      J1939_addr2_latch current J1939 address - CAN2 
      J1939_addr3Fail J1939-3 address conflict fail limit 
      J1939_addr3_conflict J1939 address conflict counter - CAN3 
      J1939_addr3_frcena This switch selects how the J1939 address is computed 
      for the CAN link. 'Engine Number Based' uses the 
      master/slave1/slave2/slave3 engine number configuration to set the address 
      to 0/1/138/139. 'Forced Constant Value' uses the numerical value below 
      without regard for any changes in engine number. 
      J1939_addr3_frcval When the CAN2 address selection mode is set to 'Forced 
      Constant Value' this is the value that is used for the address. This value 
      is ignored otherwise.

      J1939_addr_conflict J1939 address conflict counter - CAN1

      master/slave1/slave2/slave3 engine number configuration to set the address 
      to 0/1/138/139. 'Forced Constant Value' uses the numerical value below

      Constant Value' this is the value that is used for the address. This value 
      is ignored otherwise.

      J1939_AWP_rpma Actual motor speed as reported by the smart auxiliary water 
      pump over CAN 
      J1939_DM19_calid Specifies the CAN1 calibration ID to transmit in J1939 
      DM19 or ISO 15031-5 / SAE J1979 Service 0x09 responses. Note that only the 
      first 16 bytes are transmitted if the customer software part number option 
      is selected -- longer part numbers are truncated. Unused bytes are set to 
      0. 
      J1939_DM19_calid2 Specifies the CAN2 calibration ID to transmit in J1939 
      DM19 or ISO 15031-5 / SAE J1979 Service 0x09 responses. Note that only the 
      first 16 bytes are transmitted if the customer software part number option 
      is selected -- longer part numbers are truncated. Unused bytes are set to 
      0. 
      J1939_DM19_calid3 Specifies the CAN3 calibration ID to transmit in J1939 
      DM19 or ISO 15031-5 / SAE J1979 Service 0x09 responses. Note that only the 
      first 16 bytes are transmitted if the customer software part number option 
      is selected -- longer part numbers are truncated. Unused bytes are set to 
      0. 
      J1939_DM19_cksum Roadspeed network max speed byte. 
      J1939_DM4_manuf Select the manufacturer-proprietary information to append 
      to a J1939 DM4 freeze frame response. The default option will append 1 
      byte for the engine starts since last occurrence (saturating at 250), and 
      1 byte specifying the fault snapshot index. The fault engine hour option 
      will append a 4-byte value with the engine hours at first occurrence 
      (scaled 0.05hr/bit with 0 offset), and a 4-byte value with the engine 
      hours at the most recent occurrence (scaled 0.05hr/bit with 0 offset). 
      J1939_DM5_OBDc Specify the OBD compliance standard that applies. 
      J1939_DM5_OBDc2 J1939 DM5 OBD compliance - CAN2 
      J1939_DM5_OBDc3 J1939 DM5 OBD compliance - CAN3 
      J1939_EBC1_SD_tout Minimum amount of time between setting EBC1 Engine 
      Auxiliary Shutdown Switch (SPN 970) and the clearing of the Engine 
      Auxiliary Shutdown Switch. Setting the Engine Auxiliary Shutdown Switch 
      will stop fuel to the engine and then subsequent clearing of the Engine 
      Auxiliary Shutdown Switch will resume fuel to the engine. The back on time 
      specifies the amount of delay that will be imposed between turning off 
      fuel (shutdown request) and restoring of fuel (clearing of the shutdown 
      request). The delay is essentially a fuel transport delay to allow 
      clearing of fuel before spark ignition is resumed. 
      J1939_EC1_droop For Engine Configuration Map-Mode 1 operation, allow the 
      point 6 value to be independent of the point 2 value.

      This only applies to calculating point 6 for droop mode. In isochronous 
      mode, point 2 and point 6 are always the same value.

      This setting also controls the torque percentages reported for ISO 15031-5 
      PID 0x64 / ISO 14229 DID 0xF464 - "Engine Percent Torque Data". 
      J1939_EC1_pt7_rpm Parameter is the value of SPN 533 in EC1 which is the 
      maximum momentary override speed (Point 7). Value is only applicable when 
      "J1939 EC1 point 7 override speed source" is set to 'Calibration'. 
      J1939_EC1_pt7_src Parameter configures the source of SPN 533 in EC1 which 
      is the maximum momentary override speed (Point 7). When parameter is set 
      to 'Point 6 (Legacy)', then Point 7 is set equal to Point 6. When 
      parameter is set to 'Calibration', then Point 7 is set equal to the value 
      of "J1939 EC1 point 7 override speed". 
      J1939_EC1_pt7_time Parameter is the value of SPN 534 in EC1 which is the 
      maximum time limit allowed to override the engine's high idle speed. Set 
      to 0.0 seconds to indicate that high-idle override is not allowed. The 
      maximum valid time is 25.0 seconds. If parameter is greater than 25.0 
      seconds, then time limit is disabled (broadcasted value will be 0xFF). 
      J1939_EC1_rpm_src Parameter configures the J1939 EC1 engine speed values 
      for points 3, 4, and 5 (SPN 529-531). When set to 'Evenly Distributed 
      (Legacy)', the speed values are evenly distributed between point 1 and 
      point 2. When set to 'Table-Based', the "J1939 EC1 Speed Points" table on 
      the 'Estimators' worksheet is used.

      Engine speed and torque values may be derated. See "J1939 EC1 variable 
      rate reporting" on the 'Comms' worksheet for configuring dynamic points. 
      J1939_EEC1_low_idle Parameter determines when the Engine Torque Mode (SPN 
      899) in EEC1 is set to low idle governor (0b0000). When parameter is 'Min 
      Gov Engaged (Legacy)', then the minimum governor must be engaged 
      (gov_type_engaged = 4). When parameter is 'Min Gov or FPP at Idle', then 
      either the minimum governor must be engaged or the FPP is at idle. This 
      option handles scenarios where no governor is engaged (gov_type_engaged = 
      0) and the accelerator pedal is at idle. The engine speed has not fallen 
      low enough to engage the minimum governor. 
      J1939_EEC1_SPN_ena Obsoleted parameter 
      J1939_EEC1_torq_lmt Determines how the Engine Torque Mode (SPN 899) 
      parameter transmitted in the Electronic Engine Control 1 (EEC1) PGN is 
      encoded when received TSC1 requests are actively limiting the engine 
      torque. When enabled, the EEC1 PGN will transmit the engine torque mode 
      associated with the TSC1 torque limit request when the desired engine load 
      is below the requested limit. Otherwise, SPN 899 is encoded with the 
      actual torque mode generating, limiting, or controlling the engine load 
      when below the TSC1 torque limit (e.g. accelerator pedal/operator 
      selection, high speed governor, etc.). 
      J1939_ena Enabling switch for CAN1 communications 
      J1939_ena2 Controls the second CAN channel. 
      J1939_ena3 Enabling switch for CAN3 communications 
      J1939_ETC_loss This is the time after an engine run condition is detected 
      that a failure to receive a electronic (network) throttle position command 
      message will cause this fault to begin setting validation. 
      J1939_ETC_loss2 ETC (electronic throttle command) message loss during 
      engaged gear situation 
      J1939_exr_torque_tbl If set to "Percentage", then exhaust brake torque is 
      computed as a percentage of the "Retarder Torque" column. The percentage 
      is specified by the "Exhaust brake percent of retarder torque" parameter.

      If set to "Separate Table", then engine/drivetrain braking torque is 
      interpolated from the "Engine Retarder Torque" column, and the exhaust 
      braking torque is interpolated from the "Exhaust Retarder Torque" column. 
      J1939_FPPdual_idle This parameter determines how the "Accelerator Pedal 1 
      Low Idle Switch" (SPN 558) parameter in the J1939 EEC2 PGN is encoded when 
      a dual pot FPP is enabled and an IVS switch is not available.

      If set to 'Not Allowed', SPN 588 is encoded with 11b = Not Available.

      If set to 'FPP command idle', the FPP command at-idle indication is used 
      to set SPN 558 to either 00b = Accelerator pedal 1 not in low idle 
      condition or 01b = Accelerator pedal 1 in low idle condition.

      For the 'Report FPP during TSC1' option, SPN 558 in EEC2 will use the FPP 
      pedal position idle threshold for the dual pot FPP during TSC1 override of 
      the FPP command. This switch will allow reporting of the pedal FPP idle 
      indication in SPN 558 while TSC1 override of the FPP command is active.

      The 'FPP position idle' option always uses the FPP pedal position idle 
      threshold to determine how to encode SPN 558. 
      J1939_fuel_rate_acc Current low-pass filtered J1939 engine gas mass flow 
      rate 
      J1939_fuel_rate_FT1 Specifies the encoding of the J1939 EI PGN Engine Gas 
      Mass Flow Rate 1 parameter. If the selection does not match the active 
      fuel type, then the SPN is encoded with 0 kg/h. 
      J1939_fuel_rate_FT2 Specifies the encoding of the J1939 GFI3 PGN Engine 
      Fuel System 2 Gas Mass Flow Rate parameter. If the active fuel type is not 
      gaseous (LPG/NG) or the selection does not match the active fuel type, 
      then the SPN is encoded with 0 kg/h. 
      J1939_fuel_rate_mode This selection determines which fuel rate is 
      broadcast in PGN 65266, "Liquid Fuel Economy" for SPN 183, "Engine Fuel 
      Rate." This selection also determines which fuel rate is reported for ISO 
      15031-5 PID 0x5E / ISO 14229 DID 0xF45E - "Engine Fuel Rate" and ISO 
      15031-5 PID 0x9D / ISO 14229 DID 0xF49D - "Fuel Rate" 
      J1939_fuel_rate_mult Modifier on the J1939_Fuel_Rate to help improve the 
      accuracy of broadcast fuel consumption 
      J1939_fuel_rate_tau Specifies the time constant used for the J1939 engine 
      gas mass flow rate low-pass filter. 
      J1939_GFC_ena Enables two Gaseous Fuel Consumption (GFC) low-pass filters 
      which provide the data reported in proprietary J1939 PGN 65001 and 65002. 
      Filter 1 provides the data for PGN 65001 and Filter 2 provides the data 
      for PGN 65002.

      The two low-pass filters use the currently active fuel's Actual Specific 
      Gravity to allow reporting of the GFC mass as a volume.

      The GFC mass and volume are reported as consumption per hour and as 
      consumption per 100 km if a roadspeed input is available. 
      J1939_GFC_m_100km1 Gaseous fuel consumption per 100km per low pass filter 
      1 
      J1939_GFC_m_100km2 Gaseous fuel consumption per 100km per low pass filter 
      2 
      J1939_GFC_m_hr1 Gaseous fuel consumption mass per low pass filter 1 
      J1939_GFC_m_hr2 Gaseous fuel consumption mass per low pass filter 2 
      J1939_GFC_tau1 Filter 1 low pass time constant 
      J1939_GFC_tau2 Filter 2 low pass time constant 
      J1939_key_state Current consolidated key state that may be resolved from 1 
      or more separate J1939 SPNs 
      J1939_lamps_AmbWarn J1939 amber warning lamp status 
      J1939_lamps_MIL J1939 MIL status 
      J1939_lamps_Protect J1939 Protect status
