      LoadLim_Taux2_src This switch determines which temperature source is used 
      for auxiliary-temperature 2 based load-limiting. If this feature is not 
      requested, set this switch to 'Not Used' or set all table entries to 100%. 
      Note that the general 'Load-Limiting' enable switch must be set to 
      'Enabled' for this table to be activated. All other load-limiting tables 
      are also activated,so the lowest numerical value takes precedence. 
      LoadLim_Taux2_T Current value of selected auxiliary temperature 2 source. 
      LoadLim_Taux_src This switch determines which temperature source is used 
      for auxiliary-temperature 1 based load-limiting. If this feature is not 
      requested, set this switch to 'Not Used' or set all table entries to 100%. 
      Note that the general 'Load-Limiting' enable switch must be set to 
      'Enabled' for this table to be activated. All other load-limiting tables 
      are also activated,so the lowest numerical value takes precedence.

      For EGRT-based load-limiting, use the "Auxiliary-Temperature 2 Load Limit" 
      table. 
      LoadLim_Taux_T Current value of selected auxiliary temperature 1 source. 
      LoadLim_T_active Indicates the active speed based load limit table 
      load_cmd_pct Final (normalized) command load [0, 1] 
      load_est_type Switch: Determines the number iterations when computing the 
      desired MAP*VE product term (algorithm is iterative). This parameter was 
      more critical on the 3G Hardware due to the computational load requirement 
      on the microprocessor to execute The volumetric efficiency table can be 
      used or not, and depending on the complexity of the VE shape, more or less 
      iterations can be used. 
      local_cal_sync_CS_32 Localized calibration sync checksum 
      LOCKOFF2_pin This switch selects what output pin will control the 
      secondary gaseous fuel lockoff. This will mirror the normal lockoff 
      output. This setting should be disabled when not in use.

      Output channels that include a recirculation path should not be used with 
      a lockoff solenoid. 
      LOCKOFF3_pin When "Tri-Fuel mode" is enabled, this switch selects what 
      output pin will be used to control the second gaseous fuel primary lockoff 
      solenoid. This will be the fuel type NOT selected in the "Tri-Fuel mode 
      LOCKOFF output" setting.

      Output channels that include a recirculation path should not be used with 
      a lockoff solenoid. 
      LOCKOFF4_pin When "Tri-Fuel mode" is enabled, this switch selects what 
      output pin will control the second gaseous fuel secondary lockoff 
      solenoid. This will be the fuel type NOT selected in the "Tri-Fuel mode 
      LOCKOFF output" setting.

      Select 'Secondary lockoff pin' to use the same output pin as configured 
      for the "Secondary Gaseous lockoff enable pin" parameter. Because both 
      secondary lockoff solenoids on each gaseous fuel line are receiving the 
      same output signal with this setting, both solenoids will be held open 
      while the engine is running and gaseous fuel is flowing through one of the 
      lines. This setting does not affect lockoff control of the primary lockoff 
      solenoids in tri-fuel mode.

      This setting should be disabled when not in use. 

      Output channels that include a recirculation path should not be used with 
      a lockoff solenoid.

      LOCKOFF_flowwt This value determines how long a delay will be imposed 
      after the gaseous fuel lockoff is opened before fuel flow will be 
      commanded from the fuel metering devices. These may be either gaseous 
      injectors or an EPR device. A value of zero disables this feature.

      When the current fuel device is a CFV, a minimum value of 50ms will be 
      used for this delay if the entered value is lower. This substitution is 
      internal to the code – the (lower) entered value will still be shown in 
      the cell and will be used in the event of a fuel system change. 
      LOCKOFF_flt_err_rpt Determines when error (2) is reported instead of the 
      open/closed (1/0) state of the gaseous lockoff valve in the J1939 PGN 
      65433 SPN 65271. 

      If one of the following faults is historic latched:
      - Fuel run-out longer than expected
      - Fuel leak (regulator to mixer)

      Then this parameter determines when error is reported instead of the 
      open/closed state. There are 2 options:

      1) Historic latched and “Never Forget” is enabled for the fault
      2) Historic latched

      Error will always be reported when the fault is active latched. 
      LOCKOFF_hold_DC Specify the (possibly) reduced duty-cycle to use following 
      the lockoff hold wait period. The duty-cycle entered here is subject to 
      the following battery voltage correction:DC actual = DC calibration * 
      V_def / Vbatwhere V_def is the default battery voltage from the 
      'Estimators' tab. On I-EPR applications, only the primary lockoff utilizes 
      this feature. 
      LOCKOFF_hold_wait Specify the period of time to use 100% duty-cycle when 
      the lockoff initially opens. After this period of time, the (possibly) 
      reduced duty-cycle below is used to reduce heat dissipation. This value 
      must be <= 60.0 seconds. On I-EPR applications, only the primary lockoff 
      utilizes this feature. 
      LOCKOFF_hw_cfg Indicates if a LOCKOFF output pin is available in hardware 
      lockoff_keyoff_ena Closes the lock-off when "Key-off/on abs trigger" or 
      "Key-off rel trigger" conditions are met, without waiting for validation 
      times "Key-off abs validate" or "Key-off rel validate". 
      LOCKOFF_keyonwt This value determines how long a delay will be imposed 
      after key-on before the gaseous fuel lockoff is opened. A value of zero 
      disables this feature. 
      lockoff_key_wait This is the timeout value for a key-on engine-stopped 
      condition past which the gaseous fuel lockoff will be turned off. This 
      value must be <= to the key-on stopped wait general power timeout to be 
      meaningful since the power timeout will override the fuel supply disable 
      timeout if it is shorter. 
      LOCKOFF_LS_raw Lockoff output feedback (raw volts) 
      LOCKOFF_pin This switch selects what output pin will control the gaseous 
      fuel lockoff. The 'Standard' option means that the typical "named" pin on 
      the ECM will control this function. The 'Disabled' option means that no 
      output pin will be manipulated in response to a request to control this 
      device.

      Output channels that include a recirculation path should not be used with 
      a lockoff solenoid. 
      LOCKOFF_PWM_DC Lockoff PWM duty-cycle 
      LOCKOFF_PWM_manual Lockoff PWM manual control selection 
      LOCKOFF_wakeup Time required for the LP/NG lockoff solenoid to open. 
      LOD_flk_abort_Vbat Battery voltage drop threshold monitored during a fuel 
      leak (regulator to mixer) pressure test to detect starter engagement. If 
      this voltage drop is exceeded and the battery voltage derivative exceeds 
      its threshold, the fuel leak test is aborted. 
      LOD_flk_abort_Vbatdt Battery voltage derivative threshold in volts/sec 
      monitored during a fuel leak (regulator to mixer) pressure test to detect 
      starter engagement. If this value is exceeded and the battery voltage drop 
      exceeds its threshold, the fuel leak test is aborted. 
      LOD_flk_cyc_force Number of engine run cycles that must occur between fuel 
      leak test runs before test will be forced to run even if the minimum 
      number of warmed up cycles has not been reached. 
      LOD_flk_eng_cyc Number of engine run cycles between runs of the fuel leak 
      test. Only engine cycles where the coolant temperature remains above the 
      lockoff diagnostics ECT threshold for the specified time will be counted. 
      LOD_flk_eng_cycles Total engine cycles since last run of fuel leak test. 
      LOD_flk_Pdec Pressure drop during the fuel leak test that will trigger a 
      fault. 
      LOD_flk_P_initial Fuel leak initial sampled EPR feedback pressure. 
      LOD_flk_retry_lim Maximum number of times the fuel leak test may be 
      retried after failure. 
      LOD_flk_sd_tout Sets the timeout in seconds allowed for the engine to stop 
      during a fuel leak test. If the engine does not reach 0 rpm within this 
      amount of time after shutdown, it will be forced to stop by closing the 
      lockoff, and the test will be aborted. 
      LOD_flk_spk_inh_cyc Number of crank cycles to inhibit spark for on next 
      engine start after completion of fuel leak test, if engine is still warm. 
      LOD_flk_spk_inh_ECT Engine coolant temp threshold required to cause spark 
      inhibit on next engine start after fuel leak test. 
      LOD_flk_state Fuel leak test status 
      LOD_flk_test_run Indicates whether fuel leak test was run at last engine 
      shutdown. 
      LOD_flk_test_tmr Fuel leak test timer. 
      LOD_flk_tm Time limit to monitor for pressure drop during the fuel leak 
      test. 
      LOD_flk_warm_cycles Warmed-up engine cycles since last run of fuel leak 
      test. 
      LOD_flk_WARN_force This switch controls the soft or hard warning output if 
      there is a historic fault stored for this lockoff diagnostic. If this 
      switch is set to other than 'Disabled', then that particular warning 
      output channel will be forced to an ON state continuously until the 
      historic fault is cleared by either a technician or the start-cycle 
      auto-clearing mechanism. 
      LOD_FROmax Time past key-off/lockoff-off when a fault will set during fuel 
      runout mode. 
      LOD_FRO_vehspd_max Maximum vehicle speed for evaluating the "Fuel run-out 
      longer than expected" diagnostic. The fuel run-out timer resets when the 
      vehicle speed exceeds this value. If set to 0, the maximum vehicle speed 
      condition is disabled. 
      LOD_min_ECT Minimum engine coolant temp that engine must exceed for the 
      specified time before lockoff leak diagnostics can run. 
      LOD_min_ECT_tm Time that engine coolant temp must exceed specified 
      threshold before lockoff leak diagnostics can run. 
      LOD_min_ECT_tmr Time above minimum ECT on current engine cycle. 
      LOD_slk_cyc_force Number of engine run cycles that must occur between 
      lockoff slow leak test runs before test will be forced to run even if the 
      minimum number of warmed up cycles has not been reached. 
      LOD_slk_eng_cyc Number of engine run cycles between runs of the lockoff 
      slow leak test. 
      LOD_slk_eng_cycles Total engine cycles since last run of lockoff slow leak 
      test. 
      LOD_slk_Pinc Pressure rise during the lockoff slow leak test that will 
      trigger a fault. 
      LOD_slk_P_initial Lockoff slow leak initial sampled EPR feedback pressure. 

      LOD_slk_state Lockoff slow leak test status. 
      LOD_slk_test_tmr Lockoff slow leak test timer. 
      LOD_slk_tm Time limit to monitor for pressure rise during the lockoff slow 
      leak test. 
      LOD_slk_warm_cycles Warmed-up engine cycles since last run of lockoff slow 
      leak test. 
      LOD_throt_lim Sets the maximum throttle position allowed while the fuel 
      leak diagnostic is running. 
      LOD_WARN_force This switch controls the soft or hard warning output if 
      there is a historic fault stored for this lockoff diagnostic. If this 
      switch is set to other than 'Disabled', then that particular warning 
      output channel will be forced to an ON state continuously until the 
      historic fault is cleared by either a technician or the start-cycle 
      auto-clearing mechanism. 
      LowCLTemp_MAP Failed to reach closed loop temperature diagnostic: MAP 
      lower limit entry condition 
      LowCLTemp_rpm Failed to reach closed loop temperature diagnostic: RPM 
      lower limit entry condition 
      LowDiagTemp_MAP Failed to reach diagnostics temperature: MAP lower limit 
      entry condition 
      LowDiagTemp_rpm Failed to reach diagnostics temperature: RPM lower limit 
      entry condition 
      LowOperTemp_ECT Operating temperature reached conditions for ECT/CHT 
      diagnostics: ECT lower limit entry condition 
      LowOperTemp_MAP Operating temperature reached conditions for ECT/CHT 
      diagnostics: MAP lower limit entry condition 
      LowOperTemp_rpm Operating temperature reached conditions for ECT/CHT 
      diagnostics: RPM lower limit entry condition 
      LOWREVLIMblk_off A warning may cause a continuous output activation or a 
      blinking/pulsing output. The on/off times specify this behavior. For a 
      continuous-on output in an active state, simply set the off-time to zero 
      and the on-time to any value. 
      LOWREVLIMblk_on A warning may cause a continuous output activation or a 
      blinking/pulsing output. The on/off times specify this behavior. For a 
      continuous-on output in an active state, simply set the off-time to zero 
      and the on-time to any value. 
      LOWREVLIM_active Logical indicating on-going low rev limit activity 
      LOWREVLIM_fuel_rpm Current fuel low rev limit (with slew control) 
      LOWREVLIM_gov_rpm Current governor low rev limit (with slew control) 
      LOWREVLIM_lamp Output lamp associated with lowrevlim faults. 
      LOWREVLIM_maxgv_set Specifies the governor settings to use for the max 
      governor while a low rev limit is active. If set to "Use Max Gov isoc 
      settings", the max governor control mode is set to isochronous while a low 
      rev limit is active. 
      LOWREVLIM_slew_down This value controls how fast a fault triggered reduced 
      rev limit will slew down to its final value when it first becomes engaged 
      (this is a positive value). 
      LOWREVLIM_slew_up This value controls how fast a fault triggered reduced 
      rev limit slews away (out) when it disengages if engagement only during an 
      active fault condition is specified. 
      LOWREVLIM_use Logical used to indicate that in the global code that the 
      LOWREVLIM_fuel_rpm/gov_rpm values are valid and in force 
      LPG_NG_lockout Minimum LPG run time required after NG to LPG transition 
      before allowing switch back to NG. 
      LPG_NG_ovlp Time that both Lockoff valves will both be ON while 
      transitioning from LPG to NG. 
      LP_EGO EGO low-pass filter time constant 
      LP_fast Fast standard low-pass filter time constant for items such as IVS, 
      ... 
      LP_nominal Nominal standard low-pass filter time constant for items such 
      as FPP1, FPP2, ... 
      LP_slow Slow standard low-pass filter time constant for items such as ECT, 
      MAT, ... 
      LP_UEGO External UEGO Low Pass Filter time constant 
      LSD_diag_buzz Buzzer electrical status (Ground short, Open load, Power 
      short, OK) 
      LSD_diag_FPrly Fuel pump relay electrical status (Ground short, Open load, 
      Power short, OK) 
      LSD_diag_MIL MIL electrical status (Ground short, Open load, Power short, 
      OK) 
      LSD_diag_relay Power relay electrical status (Ground short, Open load, 
      Power short, OK) 
      LSD_diag_start Start relay electrical status 
      LSD_diag_tach Tach output electrical status (Ground short, Open load, 
      Power short, OK) 
      LSM6DS3_accel_aabw This setting specifies the IMU accelerometer anti-alias 
      filter bandwidth. When set to 'Automatic', the appropriate frequency is 
      selected based on the output data rate.

      LSM6DS3_accel_cdf This setting specifies the IMU accelerometer composite 
      digital filter configuration. The default setting is “Disabled”. 
      LSM6DS3_accel_fs This setting specifies the IMU accelerometer full scale 
      range. The default setting is +/- 8 g. 
      LSM6DS3_accel_odr This setting specifies the IMU accelerometer output data 
      rate. The default setting is 208 Hz. 
      LSM6DS3_gyro_fs This setting specifies the IMU gyroscope full scale range. 
      The default setting is +/- 245 dps. 
      LSM6DS3_gyro_hpf This setting specifies the IMU gyroscope digital high 
      pass filter configuration. The default setting is “Disabled”. 
      LSM6DS3_gyro_odr This setting specifies the IMU gyroscope output data 
      rate. The default setting is 208 Hz. 
      LSM6DS3_gyro_orient This setting adjusts the orientation of the gyroscope 
      axis. The default setting is “Pitch=X, Roll=Y, Yaw=Z”. 
      LSM6DS3_gyro_sign_x This setting specifies if the sign for the gyroscope 
      pitch axis uses a default positive sign of if it should be flipped. The 
      default setting is “Positive sign”. 
      LSM6DS3_gyro_sign_y This setting specifies if the sign for the gyroscope 
      roll axis uses a default positive sign of if it should be flipped. The 
      default setting is “Positive sign”. 
      LSM6DS3_gyro_sign_z This setting specifies if the sign for the gyroscope 
      yaw axis uses a default positive sign of if it should be flipped. The 
      default setting is “Positive sign”. 
      M2TC_dly_shift_1G2 Once a 1st to 2nd upshift has been requested, this is 
      the time to wait before the actual shift solenoid is engaged. 
      M2TC_dly_Tcut_1G2 Once a 1st to 2nd upshift has been requested, this is 
      the time to wait before initiating torque-cut on the engine. 
      M2TC_dur_Tcut_1G2 Once a 1st to 2nd upshift torque-cut has been initiated, 
      this is the hold time for the torque-cut (both spark and load limit). 
      M2TC_LL_restore Following the active torque-cut duration, any load limit 
      value present will be ramped back to 100% (unlimited) at this rate. 
      M2TC_LoadLim_init During active torque-cut, this throttle based load limit 
      value will be used. 
      M2TC_output_ena For 2-speed transmission control, this selects the shift 
      solenoid output channel. It is assumed that open=1st, and energized=2nd 
      gear. 
      M2TC_prr Current engine speed percent 
      M2TC_prrlim_G1 This is the engine max governed rpm limit that will be used 
      while the transmission is in 1st gear in automatic mode. This governed 
      speed is typically higher than the 2nd gear rpm limit.

      NOTE: In manual mode, the 2nd gear max governor limit is always used even 
      though the transmission may be in 1st gear. 
      M2TC_prrlim_G2 This is the engine max governed rpm limit that will be used 
      while the transmission is in 2nd gear in automatic mode. This is typically 
      a lower speed than the 1st gear governor limit.

      NOTE: In manual mode, the 2nd gear max governor limit is always used even 
      though the transmission may be in 1st gear. 
      M2TC_prrlim_nhyst After the occurrence of a 1st gear to 2nd gear engine 
      governor limit change, this hysteresis value will be subtracted from the 
      1st gear governor rpm limit to establish a switching point for reinstating 
      the 1st gear governor limit after downshifting back to 1st gear. 
      M2TC_prrshift_1G2 This is the speed at which an instant 1st to 2nd upshift 
      will occur. 
      M2TC_prrshift_2G1 This is the maximum speed allowed for a 2nd to 1st 
      downshift to occur. Neutral engagement is also required. 
      M2TC_retard_init During active torque-cut, this spark retard value will be 
      used. It is a positive retard value. 
      M2TC_ret_decay Following the active torque-cut duration, any spark retard 
      value present will be decayed back to zero at this rate. 
      M2TC_rpmlim This is the active max governor limit commanded by the 
      transmission control logic. 
      M2TC_timeshift_1G2 This is the amount of time to wait before initiating a 
      1st to 2nd upshift when the engine is above the 2nd gear governor speed. 
      MAF_cyl_events Enter the number of cylinder events to use for MAF 
      frequency measurement. Lower values result in faster sensor response, 
      higher values minimize the engine-related MAF pulsations. The max window 
      is limited to 200ms. Set this value to 0.0 to disable cylinder event based 
      windowing. 
      MAF_ena MAF sensor support is only for calibration purposes and is not 
      currently used in any of the ECM air flow computations. Note that not all 
      pulse/roadspeed inputs are capable of MAF measurement. The ECM PC display 
      shows if this feature is available on a particular ECM platform. 
      MAF_flow_gsec LPF Mass air flow sensor measurement 
      MAF_flow_tau Obsoleted parameter 
      MAF_flow_tau_ms Low-pass filter time constant in ms for the mass air flow 
      measurement. 
      MAF_PWM_edge MAF edge capture (rising edge/falling edge) 
      MAF_PWM_periods Obsoleted parameter 
      MAG_BIAS_raw crank/cam mag pickup bias voltage feedback 
      manual_air_cmd Manual air target 
      manual_air_mode Manual air mode 
      Manual_BM Manual block multiplier / fuel correction 
      manual_EGR_cmd1 Manual EGR command 1 
      manual_EGR_cmd2 Manual EGR command 2 
      manual_EGR_mode Manual EGR mode 
      manual_EGR_slct Manual EGR mode select 
      manual_EGR_tau Manual EGR command time constant 
      manual_EGR_toggle Manual EGR mode toggle between commands 
      manual_ext_pwr Entry value: Switch to force manual external aux power on 
      during key-on/engine stopped (0=normal, 1=relay only, 2=all externals 
      manual_TC_cmd Manual TC command in floating-point, function varies 
      depending on 'manual_TC_mode' selection 
      manual_TC_mode user selection of a manual TC control mode 
      MAP Intake Manifold Pressure 
      MAPc MAP Scaling factor (from voltage to pressure) - (determined from 
      MAPcal, MAPcal_P) 
      MAPcal_P 1D interpolation table MAP calibrated pressure output values 
      MAPcal_V 1D interpolation table raw MAP voltage input values 
      MAPdt Time derivative of MAP (non-deadzone version) 
      MAPdtMAP_dz 1D Interpolation Table - MAPdt MAP Based Trigger. Input is 
      steady-state MAP (psia), output is MAPdt MAP-Based Trigger (psi/sec) 
      MAPdtMAP_MAP 1D Interpolation Table - MAPdt MAP Based Trigger. 
      Steady-state MAP (psia) input values 
      MAPdt_CLoff CL disable dMAPdt trigger 
      MAPdt_crk_dz MAPdt dead-zone value during cranking. 
      MAPdt_dz Dead zone limited value of dMAP/dt (units of pressure/time) 
      MAPdt_dz_acttrg Active MAPdt trigger value 
      MAPdt_dz_shape MAPdt trigger shape 
      MAPdt_dz_src MAPdt normal trigger source 
      MAPdt_est Estimated MAPdt based on throttle model. This value is utilized 
      if MAP_Invalid flag is set to TRUE 
      MAPdt_global_filt Parameter configures the filtering and calculation 
      method for the time derivative of MAP. When set to 'Default', the 
      derivative is calculated by interpolating MAP samples within the "MAPdt 
      interpolation window". When set to 'Cylinder Windowed', the derivative is 
      calculated from MAP_windowed. Refer to "MAP/TIP Cylinder Window 
      Calculation" section on the Inputs worksheet for configuring MAP 
      cylinder-event windowing. 

      Note: the "MAPdt low-pass filter" is applied to both calculation methods. 
      MAPdt_ICTmax MAPdt maximum ICT - During MAPdt based intake manifold 
      filling calculations, the lesser of the current ICT and the maximum ICT 
      entered here will be used as the air temperature for the filling dynamics. 

      MAPdt_MAPss MAP steady-state 
      MAPdt_MAPss_tau LPF time constant used for filtering value of the 
      (computed)steady state value of MAP 
      MAPdt_n MAPdt calculation MAP interpolation window. More points yields a 
      quieter and more accurate derivative, but introduces more time lag. Fewer 
      points has the opposite effect. Only applicable when "MAPdt global filter 
      method" is set to 'Default'. 
      MAPdt_nrm_dz MAPdt dead-zone value during normal operation. 
      MAPdt_windowed High speed cylinder event windowed MAPdt value 
      MAPdt_xLP Post interpolation/cylinder-windowing low-pass filter constant 
      for MAPdt. 
      MAPe Effective intake manifold pressure during intake (transient 
      compensated) 
      MAPKV_MAPss MAP KV steady-state 
      MAPKV_MAPss_tau MAP KV steady-state low-pass tau 
      MAPKV_ofst MAP KV steady-state offset 
      MAPo MAP Offset (from voltage to pressure) - (determined from MAPcal, 
      MAPcal_P) 
      MAPraw_LP High-speed anti-aliasing low-pass time constant for the raw MAP 
      input voltage. 
      MAPrsc_max_phi MAP rescaling maximum MAP for phi lookups 
      MAPrsc_max_trim MAP rescaling maximum MAP for trim lookups 
      MAPrsc_min_phi Rescaled version of minimum MAP used for phi lookups 
      MAPrsc_min_trim MAP rescaling minimum MAP for trim lookups 
      MAPrsc_phi MAP rescaling factor used in MAP lookups (adjusted for BP) 
      MAPrsc_trim MAP value rescaled as a function of barometric pressure (BP) 
      MAP_addtl_flt_react Enables additional fault reactions for specified MAP 
      faults. When any of the setting's specified faults are enabled and 
      faulted, the fuel calculation mode is automatically switched from 
      'Throttle-Model Based' to 'Speed-Density + dMAP/dt'. This is only 
      applicable to "Throttle-body injection fuel mode" and "CFV fuel 
      calculation mode".

      One or more of the faults below can be specified:
      "MAP higher than expected" fault
      "MAP pegging reference out-of-range" fault

      The "MAP high pressure" and "MAP low voltage" faults already switch the 
      fuel calculation mode when enabled and faulted.

      Note: This setting's fault reactions are in addition to any other 
      reactions, such as the fault switches on the 'Diagnostics' worksheet. 
      MAP_CADproject Number of CAD (in degrees) to project MAP value 
      MAP_def default MAP value 
      MAP_est Estimated value of MAP based on throttle model 
      MAP_est_step_size Parameter sets the integration time step size used when 
      calculating the throttle-model estimated MAP (MAP_est). The estimated 
      derivative of MAP (MAPdt_est) is numerically integrated using the 
      specified time step size. The default is 5 ms. A smaller time step can be 
      used to improve stability of the numerical integration. Below are the 
      enumerated step size values:
      0 = 5 ms (default)
      1 = 2.5 ms
      2 = 1.67 ms
      3 = 1.25 ms 
      MAP_favg_n MAP window filter size for fast fuel computations 
      MAP_fl_scaling TIP-based full load rescaling 
      MAP_fullload Full load MAP value at the current engine speed 
      MAP_fullload_BPlim For naturally aspirated applications, this parameter 
      determines how altitude compensation is applied to the engine-speed based 
      MAP full-load value from the "Engine No-Load/Full-Load Calibration" table. 
      If disabled, the MAP full-load table value, which is configured for 
      standard barometric pressure, is rescaled for the current barometric 
      pressure. 

      If enabled, the MAP full-load table value is only rescaled if it is above 
      the current barometric pressure. Adjustment is limited so that the minimum 
      rescaled MAP full-load value is the current barometric pressure. 
      MAP_global_filt This switch selects what type of general global filter 
      scheme is used for the MAP signal in most modes of operation. The 
      'Default' setting uses a combination of low-pass filtering and 
      time-averaging. The 'Cylinder Windowed' mode uses a sliding engine 
      synchronous window averaging technique. Refer to "MAP/TIP Cylinder Window 
      Calculation" section for configuration. Note that 'Throttle-Model Base 
      Throttle-Body Fueling' always uses cylinder windowing regardless of this 
      switch setting. 
      MAP_HiExp MAP higher than expected diagnostic: MAP-MAP estimate minimum 
      delta threshold 
      MAP_high_air MAP at high airflow point (psia at high airflow) 
      MAP_load MAP load 
      MAP_max MAP high pressure diagnostic: MAP upper limit threshold 
      MAP_maxRPM MAP high pressure diagnostic: RPM lower limit entry condition 
      MAP_maxTPS MAP high pressure diagnostic: TPS upper limit entry condition 
      MAP_max_unlch MAP must drop below this value before the "MAP high 
      pressure" fault unlatches. When this parameter is set to 256 psia or 
      higher, ECM fault reactions (other than those controlled by fault 
      switches) will occur when the fault is active or latched. 
      MAP_MinKVflt Sets minimum MAP to run CD Spark < 5KV diagnostic fault. 
      MAP_minv MAP low voltage diagnostic: MAP voltage lower limit threshold 
      MAP_minvRPM MAP low voltage diagnostic: RPM lower limit entry condition 
      MAP_minvTPS MAP low voltage diagnostic: TPS lower limit entry condition 
      MAP_minv_unlch MAP voltage (MAP_raw) must rise above this value before the 
      "MAP low voltage" fault unlatches. When this parameter is set to 0V, ECM 
      fault reactions (other than those controlled by fault switches) will occur 
      when the fault is active or latched. 
      MAP_misfire_OK MAP below which CD spark based misfire detection is 
      disabled. 
      MAP_MPI_max MPI Transient Compensation: MAP Max 
      MAP_MPI_min MPI Transient Compensation: MAP Min 
      MAP_noload No load MAP value at the current engine speed 
      MAP_raw Full scale A/D MAP 
      MAP_savg_n MAP window filter size for slow time-constant system use such 
      as cylinder wall heating, ... 
      MAP_slow Slow filtered Intake Manifold Pressure 
      MAP_TIP_win_calc Parameter configures the calculation method for MAP and 
      TIP cylinder-event windowing. When set to 'Single Window', a window of 
      size "MAP/TIP cylinder window size primary" is used for calculating 
      MAP_windowed and TIP_windowed.

      When set to 'Dual Windows', two windows are used for calculating 
      MAP_windowed and TIP_windowed. The two windows consist of a primary window 
      of size "MAP/TIP cylinder window size primary" and a secondary window of 
      size "MAP/TIP cylinder window size secondary". The average of each window 
      contributes to the final windowed pressure value. The "MAP/TIP Dual 
      Windows" table determines the secondary window's contribution based on the 
      engine speed. For example, if the secondary contribution is 20% based on 
      the table, then the final windowed pressure value will be the summation of 
      80% of the primary window's average and 20% of the secondary window's 
      average. Dual windows are typically used to gradually switch between the 
      primary window's average at low engine speeds and the secondary window's 
      average at high engine speeds. 
      MAP_TIP_win_cyls This is the cylinder-window width of the engine 
      synchronous sliding window filter averaging technique used in some MAP and 
      TIP signal chains. For example - on a 8-cylinder engine - a value of 2.0 
      will average the MAP and TIP over a constant 180 CAD window. Note that 
      this value is always used for 'Throttle-Model Based Throttle-Body 
      Fueling'. 
      MAP_TIP_win_cyls2 This is the cylinder-window width for a secondary 
      MAP/TIP sliding window filter. Only applicable when "MAP/TIP cylinder 
      window calculation" is set to 'Dual Windows'. 
      MAP_windowed High speed cylinder event windowed MAP value 
      MAT Intake manifold runner temperature 
      MATs standard MAT value 
      MAT_def default MAT value 
      MAT_est_EGR Obsoleted parameter 
      MAT_est_ena MAT estimation enable switch. Set this switch='MAT=IAT' to use 
      the normal IAT analog input to calculate the MAT. Set this switch='IAT-CHT 
      based estimate' to use an IAT-CHT based estimate for the MAT. 
      MAT_est_tau MAT_tau is the low-pass filter time constant for the estimated 
      MAT value. The MAT will reach 63% of the estimated steady-state value 
      within MAT_tau seconds. 
      MAT_est_xmax Maximum percentage of IAT contribution to MAT 
      MAT_est_xmin Minimum percentage of IAT contribution to MAT 
      maxdgv_I_max Max Droop Governor: Integrator Max 
      maxdgv_I_min Max Droop Governor: Integrator Min 
      maxgvspk_TSC_FA_Gov3 This switch controls the source of the SPARK governor 
      gain settings used during TSC1 remote speed control requests 
      (Full-Authority). 
      maxgvspk_TSC_Gov3 This switch controls which SPARK governor gain settings 
      are used during remote speed limiting. Gov3 is always used during remote 
      speed command (setpoint) control, and the Max governor is always used 
      during remote speed limit control. However, the Max governor can be forced 
      to use Gov3 spark governor settings during speed limiting using this 
      switch. 
      maxgv_auth_max Max Governor: Max authority value 
      maxgv_auth_min Max Governor: Min authority value 
      maxgv_gain_slct Max Gov Gain selection (Fuel Based, Standard Gains, or 
      Alternate Gains) 
      maxgv_nomload Max Droop Governor: Nominal load 
      maxgv_odz Max Governor output deadzone value 
      maxgv_odz_tau Max Governor output deadzone time constant 
      maxgv_odz_wall Max Governor output deadzone wall 
      maxgv_spk_dzo Max Spark Governor overshoot deadzone 
      maxgv_spk_dzu Max Spark Governor undershoot deadzone 
      maxgv_spk_Kpo Max Spark Governor overshoot gain 
      maxgv_spk_Kpu Max Spark Governor undershoot gain 
      maxgv_spk_mxadv Max Spark Governor max advance 
      maxgv_spk_mxret Max Spark Governor max retard 
      maxgv_TPSLP Max Governor TPS Low pass time constant 
      maxgv_TSC_FA_Gov3 This switch controls the source of the THROTTLE governor 
      gain settings used during TSC1 remote speed control requests 
      (Full-Authority). 
      maxgv_TSC_Gov3 This switch controls which THROTTLE governor gain settings 
      are used during remote speed limiting. Gov3 is always used during remote 
      speed command (setpoint) control, and the Max governor is always used 
      during remote speed limit control. However, the Max governor can be forced 
      to use Gov3 throttle governor settings during speed limiting using this 
      switch. 
      maxigv_appdlt Max Isochronous Governor: Approach rpm delta 
      maxigv_apprdt Max Isochronous Governor: Approach drpm/dt 
      maxigv_Iinit Max Isochronous Governor: Integrator re-initializer gain 
      (value) 
      maxigv_Iinit_ena Max Isochronous Governor: Integrator re-initializer 
      feature 
      maxigv_I_max Max Isochronous Governor: Integrator Max 
      maxigv_I_min Max Isochronous Governor: Integrator Min 
      MaxSetPt2_ena This switch controls the user max speed setpoint control 
      system. The AUX PUx selections allow Off=OPEN, RPM or Roadspeed 
      control=GROUND options. The AUX DIGx selections allow Off=OPEN, RPM 
      control=GROUND, Roadspeed control=+V options. The PU2 options with DIG2 
      qualification use the state of DIG2 at key-on and ignore it thereafter. 
      Engagement via PU2 is ignored on a Slave engine if the multi-engine sync 
      enable is set to 'PU2 on Slave'. 
      MaxSetPt_actvlt This switch determines what (if any) output is used to 
      drive a light to indicate a locked/controlling system. 
      MaxSetPt_appdn_kph This is the vehicle speed window below the max vehicle 
      speed setpoint where blinking/pulsing the control indication light/output 
      can take place AFTER speed control initial engagement. Set this value to 
      zero to disable this function. The output indication will simply go from 
      full-on to full-off once the speed control releases if this function is 
      disabled. This parameter only applies if the system is in primary vehicle 
      speed mode. 
      MaxSetPt_appdn_rpm This is the rpm window below the max engine speed 
      setpoint where blinking/pulsing the control indication light/output can 
      take place AFTER speed control initial engagement. Set this value to zero 
      to disable this function. The output indication will simply go from 
      full-on to full-off once the speed control releases if this function is 
      disabled. This parameter only applies if the system is in primary engine 
      speed mode. 
      MaxSetPt_apprdt If the engine speed is above the target speed when the 
      system is initially engaged, the speed will be slewed down toward the 
      final setpoint at this rate (entered as a positive value). Set this value 
      to 9999 rpm/sec to disable this feature. 
      MaxSetPt_appup_kph This is the vehicle speed window below the max speed 
      setpoint where blinking/pulsing the control indication light/output can 
      take place PRIOR to speed control initial engagement. Set this value to 
      zero to disable this function. The output indication will simply go from 
      full-off to full-on once the speed control takes over if this function is 
      disabled. This parameter only applies if the system is in primary vehicle 
      speed mode. 
      MaxSetPt_appup_rpm This is the rpm window below the max engine speed 
      setpoint where blinking/pulsing the control indication light/output can 
      take place PRIOR to speed control initial engagement. Set this value to 
      zero to disable this function. The output indication will simply go from 
      full-off to full-on once the speed control takes over if this function is 
      disabled. This parameter only applies if the system is in primary engine 
      speed mode. 
      MaxSetPt_ena This switch controls the user max speed setpoint control 
      system. The AUX PUx selections allow Off=OPEN, RPM or Roadspeed 
      control=GROUND options. The AUX DIGx selections allow Off=OPEN, RPM 
      control=GROUND, Roadspeed control=+V options. The PU2 options with DIG2 
      qualification use the state of DIG2 at key-on and ignore it thereafter.
      Engagement via PU2 is ignored on a Slave engine if the multi-engine sync 
      enable is set to 'PU2 on Slave'. 
      MaxSetPt_engaged Max Gov User Setpoint System active 
      MaxSetPt_Gov3 This switch determines whether the standard max governor 
      parameters or the alternate Gov3 parameters are used when the user 
      setpoint max engine speed system is engaged. 
      MaxSetPt_keyon This switch controls how the max set point system behaves 
      after a key-cycle. It can either be engaged or dis-engaged following a 
      key-on event by default, or it can retain the state prior to key-off. 
      MaxSetPt_light Follows the active light/output state for the max engine 
      speed limit system. 
      MaxSetPt_rpm rpm target value currently commanded by User Max Gov Setpoint 
      System 
      MaxSetPt_RS Roadspeed control max speed limit when in RPMbased control 
      mode. 
      MaxSetPt_rtn_ena If enabled, once the max set speed system disengages, the 
      FPP must be reduced to the current operating condition before FPP control 
      becomes active. This switch should almost always be set to 'Enabled.' 
      MaxSetPt_switch Max Gov User Setpoint OFF/Engine Speed/Vehicle Speed 
      switch 
      max_gov_highidle_rpm High idle speed, calculated based on the 'Governor 
      max authority', 'Load-limited Max Gov', and current Kp gain. 
      max_gov_override This speed overrides any higher max governor speeds 
      programmed by the user. 
      max_gov_rpm Max Governor speed setting. This value cannot be changed on 
      Main page 
      mda_trans_tau Transient air flow low-pass time constant

      mdot_EGR_cmd mdot_EGR_cmd 
      mdot_EGR_dP EGR measured flow - dP 
      mdot_EGR_float EGR flow - total 
      mdot_EGR_inc_max Maximum allowed increase in commanded EGR valve flow 
      mdot_EGR_MAF EGR measured flow - MAF 
      mdot_EGR_min EGR minimum table requested flow 
      mdot_EGR_nom EGR nominal table requested flow 
      mdot_EGR_OFF If the EGR command is non-zero (i.e. the EGR command has 
      previously exceeded the 'on' limit above), the EGR command will be set to 
      0 when the EGR flow rate command drops below this limit. Set to 0 to 
      disable hysteresis based on the flow rate command. 
      mdot_EGR_ON If the EGR command is 0, the EGR flow rate command must exceed 
      this limit before non-zero EGR commands are installed. Set to 0 to disable 
      hysteresis based on the flow rate command. 
      mdot_EGR_ON_cold If the EGR command is 0 and IAT is below the IAT 
      threshold, the EGR flow rate command must exceed this limit before 
      non-zero EGR commands are installed. Set to 0 to disable the 
      cold-temperature flow command 'on' limit. 
      mdot_EGR_req Requested EGR valve flow 
      mdot_EGR_UEGO EGR measured flow - UEGO 
      mdot_EGR_VdP EGR post-volume dm/dt 
      mdot_EGR_zero_tmr Elapsed time with zero EGR flow.

      on speed density 
      mdot_eng_TPSf Reference mdot total (air+fuel+diluent) at the engine based 
      on throttle model

      mdot_trans_TPS_dzpct This cubic deadzone is applied to the transient 
      portion (i.e. intake manifold filling portion) of the air flow as compared
