      OBSOLETE_964 Obsoleted parameter 
      OBSOLETE_9804 Obsoleted parameter 
      OBSOLETE_9805 Obsoleted parameter 
      OBSOLETE_9806 Obsoleted parameter 
      OBSOLETE_9807 Obsoleted parameter 
      OBSOLETE_9808 Obsoleted parameter 
      OBSOLETE_9809 Obsoleted parameter 
      OBSOLETE_981 Obsoleted parameter 
      OBSOLETE_9810 Obsoleted parameter 
      OBSOLETE_9811 Obsoleted parameter 
      OBSOLETE_9812 Obsoleted parameter 
      OCT_adapt The current fuel octane indication. 0% indicates lowoctane (base 
      spark table), and 100% indicates hi octane (alternate spark table). 
      OCT_adapt_ena Selects enable/disable of the adaptive octane function. 
      Inherently selects the 'high' octane table when enabled - the base table 
      for the current fuel becomes the 'low' octane table. 
      OCT_adapt_fault_mode Specifies how adaptive octane should react while a 
      MAP, ECT, or IAT fault is active or latched.

      When "Set to 0%" is selected (the default), the octane rating will be set 
      to 0%. This is the recommended setting for gasoline engines.

      When "Use last value" is selected, the octane rating will not update. This 
      is the recommended setting for gaseous fuel types. 
      OCT_adapt_reset Resets the octane rating and increasing slew rate to 
      power-up default values. 
      OCT_dec_knkpctinc_dz Minimum increasing change in knock retard to trigger 
      an octane rating decrease, as a percentage of the knock retard gain.

      If set to 100%, the derivative-based decrease is disabled. 
      OCT_dec_tm Octane rating decrease window duration for responding to a 
      knock retard increase. 
      OCT_ECT_ena Octane estimation will be locked-out for ECT temperatures 
      below this value. 
      OCT_gsln_alt_tbl Alternate spark table which will be adapted towards when 
      adaptive octane is active and running on gasoline fuel 
      OCT_gsln_ena Type of octane to adapt to when running on gasoline fuel. 
      OCT_inc_tmr Current octane increase wait timer value to be compared with 
      the wait time value below. 
      OCT_inc_wait If an increase in octane is indicated and ready, this is the 
      amount of time that must elapse from the last knock event (activity) of a 
      magnitude greater than 'OCT_inc_wait_pct' below before octane will adapt 
      in the increasing direction. Set to zero to disable this feature. 
      OCT_inc_wait_pct This is the instantaneous knock activity threshold below 
      which the octane increase timer will begin incrementing. See the 
      description of the wait time above for more information. 
      OCT_init On power-up from loss of battery, the ECM will load this value as 
      the initial octane rating. 0% indicates initial low-octane (base spark 
      table), and 100% indicates initial hi-octane (alternate spark table). 
      OCT_init_mode This switch controls the way that the octane rating is 
      initialized on key-up. 'Use last value' uses the value from when the 
      engine last shut down. 'Reset to default' always resets to the cold 
      power-up default. 
      OCT_init_table This value selects either a scalar based initialization 
      strategy (using the cold power-up default octane rating) or a table based 
      initialization strategy (using the adaptive octane table below). 
      OCT_learning Logical indicating conditions are valid for updating the 
      octane rating. 
      OCT_LP_alt_tbl Alternate spark table which will be adapted towards when 
      adaptive octane is active and running on LP fuel. 
      OCT_LP_ena Type of octane to adapt to when running on LP fuel. 
      OCT_MAPss This is the lowpass filtered version of the MAP used to generate 
      a 'steady state' MAP estimate. This 'steady state' value is compared to 
      the instantaneous MAP to determine if the engine is within a steady state 
      window for octane adaptive estimation validation. 
      OCT_MAPss_win The octane adaptation low-pass (steady-state) MAP must match 
      the instantaneous MAP within a +/- window of this size to validate octane 
      adaptation. 
      OCT_max_MAP Octane estimation will be locked-out for MAP or MAP load 
      pressures above this value. 
      OCT_max_RPM Octane estimation will be locked-out for RPM speeds above this 
      value. 
      OCT_mem_type This switch selects either a single-point adaptive octane 
      value, or a table-based adaptive strategy. 
      OCT_min_MAP Octane estimation will be locked-out for MAP or MAP load 
      pressures below this value. 
      OCT_min_RPM Octane estimation will be locked-out for RPM speeds below this 
      value. 
      OCT_NG_alt_tbl Alternate spark table which will be adapted towards when 
      adaptive octane is active and running on NG fuel. 
      OCT_NG_ena Type of octane to adapt to when running on NG fuel. 
      OCT_phi_ena Selects enable/disable of octane based phi interpolation 
      strategy. Inherently selects the 'high' octane phi table when enabled. The 
      base table for the current fuel becomes the 'low' octane phi table. If 
      this feature is enabled, it should generally be set to the same high 
      octane fuel type table as the normal adaptive octane enable switch to 
      avoid confusion. 
      OCT_phi_gsln_alt_tbl Alternate fuel table which will be adapted towards 
      when adaptive octane based phi is enabled and running on gasoline fuel. 
      OCT_phi_gsln_ena Enables or disables octane based phi adaption when 
      running on gasoline fuel. 
      OCT_phi_LP_alt_tbl Alternate fuel table which will be adapted towards when 
      adaptive octane based phi is enabled and running on LP fuel. 
      OCT_phi_LP_ena Enables or disables octane based phi adaption when running 
      on LP fuel. 
      OCT_phi_NG_alt_tbl Alternate fuel table which will be adapted towards when 
      adaptive octane based phi is enabled and running on NG fuel. 
      OCT_phi_NG_ena Enables or disables octane based phi adaption when running 
      on NG fuel. 
      OCT_ret_decrease Knock retard values above this will cause the octane 
      rating to decrease at a rate proportional to the current knock retard, 
      once validation conditions are satisfied.

      If set to a value above the maximum knock retard, the proportional 
      decrease is disabled. 
      OCT_ret_increase Knock retard values below this will cause the octane 
      rating to increase once validation conditions are satisfied. 
      OCT_RPMss This is the lowpass filtered version of the RPM used to generate 
      a 'steadystate' RPM estimate. This 'steadystate' value is compared to the 
      instantaneous RPM to determine if the engine is within a steadystate 
      window for octane adaptive estimation validation. 
      OCT_RPMss_win The octane adaptation low-pass (steady-state) RPM must match 
      the instantaneous RPM within a +/- window of this size to validate octane 
      adaptation. 
      OCT_run_wait Octane estimation will be locked-out for this amount of time 
      after engine start to allow engine stabilization. 
      OCT_slew_dec Minimum slew rate for the proportional octane rating 
decrease.

      When the adaptive octane memory type is set to "Table Based", the rate 
      should be at least 0.31%/sec. 
      OCT_slew_dec_cur When conditions are validated for octane rating decrease, 
      the octane value will slew at this rate continuously while valid 
      conditions remain. The slew rate is proportional to the knock retard as it 
      increases from the minimum for an octane rating decrease to the maximum 
      allowed retard. 
      OCT_slew_dec_Kd Minimum slew rate for octane rating decrease based on the 
      maximum increase in knock retard during the octane rating decrease window.

      When the adaptive octane memory type is set to "Table Based", the rate 
      should be at least 0.31%/sec. 
      OCT_slew_dec_Kd_max Maximum slew rate for octane rating decrease based on 
      the maximum increase in knock retard during the octane rating decrease 
      window.

      When the adaptive octane memory type is set to "Table Based", the rate 
      should be at least 0.31%/sec. 
      OCT_slew_dec_max Maximum slew rate for the proportional octane rating 
      decrease.

      When the adaptive octane memory type is set to "Table Based", the rate 
      should be at least 0.31%/sec. 
      OCT_slew_inc After key-on, when conditions are validated for octane rating 
      increase, the octane value will slew at this rate continuously while valid 
      conditions remain. When the "Adaptive octane memory type" is set to 'Table 
      Based', the rate should be at least 0.31%/sec. 
      OCT_slew_inc_cur When conditions are validated for octane rating increase, 
      the octane value will slew at this rate continuously while valid 
      conditions remain. This value changes from the key-on increasing octane 
      slew rate to the steady-state increasing octane slew rate after the knock 
      retard reaches the maximum value for an octane rating increase. 
      OCT_slew_inc_mode Indicates the increasing slew rate used by adaptive 
      octane. 
      OCT_slew_inc_ss Increasing octane slew rate to use after the knock retard 
      reaches the maximum value for an octane rating increase. This steady-state 
      rate will be used until the next key-on reset. 
      OCT_ss_tau This is the time-constant of a low-pass filter applied to the 
      MAP and RPM to generate a 'steady-state' MAP and RPM estimate. These 
      'steady-state' values are compared to the instantaneous values to 
      determine if the engine is within a steady-state window for octane 
      adaptive estimation validation. 
      OCT_tbl_store_EE If the Key-on octane rating reset mode is 'Use last 
      value', this switch determines whether the adaptive octane table is 
      retained in battery supported memory or permanent memory.

      In battery supported memory, the adaptive octane table will be cleared if 
      the battery power is removed from the ECM.

      In permanent memory, a key-on reset sequence must be performed to clear 
      the table. 
      OCT_update_tmr This timer begins incrementing when the engine is in a 
      steadystate MAP and RPM region. When it limits at the adaptive validation 
      wait time, octane learning begins. This timer holds at this limit while 
      steadystate conditions hold. 
      OCT_update_wait The engine must be in a steady-state MAP and RPM region 
      for this amount of time before octane adaptation will start. 
      OILL_def_lowlev Default low oil level 
      OILL_def_normlev Default normal oil level 
      OILL_input Oil level discrete input channel 
      OILL_sense Oil level discrete input sense 
      OilP2_loP Fault condition parameter 
      OilP2_loP2 This value should be greater than or equal to the low RPM oil 
      pressure limit. 
      OILPc Oil pressure sensor constant 
      OilPcal_P 1D Interpolation Table: Oil Pressure Sensor Calibration 
      (psia/psig) 
      OilPcal_V 1D interpolation table oil pressure sensor voltage input values 
      OilPgd_chan OilP gauge driver output channel 
      OilPgd_ctl_type This switch controls the gauge driver output type 
      configured in hardware on the ECM. 'Duty-cycle PWM' mode indicates that a 
      simple low-side switch is the output, and 'Resistance Simulation' 
      indicates that the output is configured for this special type of control. 
      OilPgd_DC This is the PWM dutycyle either used directly in PWM dutycycle 
      mode, or the internal PWM dutycycle used to simulate resistance in 
      resistance simulation mode. 
      OilPgd_Id This is the commanded current through the gauge driver circuit. 
      OilPgd_pctref OilP gauge reference percent of scale 
      OilPgd_per Value is only applicable for output channels 'Aux PWM1' through 
      'Aux PWM4'. 'Aux PWM5' has a hardcoded period of 0.5 ms. 
      OilPgd_Ra This is the current actual resistance being generated by the 
      gauge driver circuit as measured by the internal voltage and current 
      feedback systems. 
      OilPgd_Rd This is the current target resistance for the gauge driver 
      circuit. It may include multihelm compensation relative to the tablelookup 
      value. 
      OilPgd_Rdtbl This is the target resistance extracted from the calibration 
      table. 
      OilPgd_Rpu This is the current estimate of the pullup resistance inside 
      the OilP gauge. This value may change with gauge position and/or 
      excitation voltage. 
      OilPgd_Rpu_def This is the default (initial) estimate of the gauge 
      driver's estimate of the pullup resistance inside the gauge itself. This 
      value does not have be accurate - it only affects the initial gauge 
      movement after key-on. 
      OilPgd_Rpu_tau This time-constant determines the effective closed-loop 
      resistance control update rate for the 'Resistance Simulation' mode of 
      operation. It does not apply otherwise. It should generally be set to 
      approximately 100ms, but may be increase or decreased to achieve the 
      desired gauge response time and stability. 
      OilPgd_Vexc_ratio This is the internal resistor divider ratio of the gauge 
      with respect to the supply voltage and ground. If no divider ratio is 
      present internal to the gauge, set this value to 1.0. 
      OilPgd_Vexc_reg This is the voltage regulator level for the internal gauge 
      excitation voltage. If no regulation exists, just set this value above 
      normal operating voltage (such as 36 volts). 
      OilPgd_V_FB This is the current measured voltage at the gauge driver input 
      pin on the ECM connector. It is used in the computation of the simulated 
      sender resistance. 
      OILPo Oil pressure sensor offset 
      OilP_abs_gage Oil pressure sensor calibration: absolute/gauge pressure 
      select 
      OilP_comm_tout Timeout value for the "oil pressure communication lost 
      (SENT)" fault becoming active. Must be >= 100ms. 
      OILP_def_lowigp Default low-OK oil pressure 
      OILP_def_lowp Default low oil pressure 
      OILP_def_normp Default normal oil pressure 
      OILP_gauge_DHena Use this switch to allow the simulated sender driver to 
      drive two (dual-helm) gauges in parallel. Dual-helm mode may either be 
      permanently enabled or it can be indicated using a hardware input channel. 
      A grounded input on any of the pulled-up input selectable choices 
      indicates dual-helm mode. 
      OILP_gauge_DHstat dual-helm oil pressure gauge driver mode indicator 
      OILP_gauge_dz This value defines a +/- cubic deadzone for multi-engine 
      gauge synchronization. Differences between the average of all multi-engine 
      gauges are reduced by a cubic factor relative to this deadzone, but 
      differences >= this deadzone are displayed at exactly the original value. 
      OILP_gauge_sync This switch will synchronize multiple oil pressure gauges 
      on a multi-engine configuration within a cubic deadband as defined below. 
      OILP_gauge_value synced/unsynced OILP gauge driver value in psig 
      OilP_hiP Fault condition parameter 
      OilP_hiP_RPM Oil pressure high (sender) diagnostic: RPM lower limit entry 
      condition 
      OilP_loP Fault condition parameter 
      OilP_loP2 Fault condition parameter 
      OilP_loRPM Fault condition parameter 
      OilP_loRPM2 Fault condition parameter 
      OilP_maxV Oil pressure sensor maximum voltage 
      OilP_minV Oil pressure sensor minimum voltage 
      OILP_press Oil pressure (pressure version) 
      OILP_raw OILP sensor raw volts 
      OILP_RPM RPM lower limit for all oil pressure low faults 
      OILP_state Oil pressure state 
      OILP_stat_ena Enables the monitoring of the oil pressure (OILP_press) to 
      record the min pressure and the engine hour meter of the last pressure <= 
      the trigger pressure. 
      OILP_stat_low_rpm Engine speed must be >= this value to allow updates to 
      the oil pressure low hour meter and oil pressure min. 

      This value may be set to 0 to disable this requirement. 
      OILP_stat_lo_HM The hour meter at which the oil pressure met or dropped 
      below the OILP_stat_lo_trig value. 
      OILP_stat_lo_trig If the oil pressure drops to or is less than this 
      trigger limit the oil pressure hour meter will be updated. The oil 
      pressure hour meter update may only trigger once per engine cycle. 
      OILP_stat_lo_wait Specifies the time to wait after engine start before 
      allowing updates to the oil pressure low hour meter and oil pressure min. 

      This value may be set to 0 to disable this requirement. 
      OILP_stat_min The minimum oil pressure seen since last reset. 
      OILP_stat_reset_key Specifies the unique key (1-65535) required to clear 
      the oil pressure statistics. 
      OILP_stat_reset_usr Oil pressure statistics may be reset be setting this 
      variable to the OILP_stat_reset_key value. 
      OILP_stopped_wait Stopped wait time for the oil pressure switch voltage 
      diagnostics, following an engine-running state. This setting is ignored 
      after the initial key-on that wakes the ECM from the sleep state. 
      OILP_test Oil pressure configuration 
      OILP_trig Oil pressure switch threshold voltage 
      OilP_type Oil Pressure switch/sender selection switch 
      OilP_VlvStk OPC oil valve stuck check difference 
      OilP_volt Oil pressure (voltage) 
      OILP_wait "Run time wait for all oil pressure low faults": this value 
      applies when 'Run time wait threshold source' is set to 'Single Point'. 
      OILP_wait_source Single point or table-based selector for the oil pressure 
      low diagnostics run time wait threshold. 
      OilQ_active Oil quality monitoring active switch 
      OilQ_alertreps When an oil quality auto-learn sequence is complete, the 
      audible alert (as defined on the 'Diagnostics' page) will perform the 
      'Audible Alert for Non-Audible Warning' alert sequence. The alert sequence 
      is composed of the initial pulse defined on the 'Diagnostics' page and 
      this number of repeated on/off pulses. 
      OilQ_chan Select the appropriate oil quality sensor input channel. Note 
      that all inputs are assumed to be configured as pull-downs. Also note that 
      the diagnostic fault voltage limits on the 'Diagnostics' page do not apply 
      when the input is being used as an oil quality sensor input, since the 
      limits are learned during normal/valid operation. 
      OilQ_ena If 'Enabled' is selected, an oil quality sensor is assumed to be 
      present and oil quality monitoring begins immediately. If 'Auto-sense' is 
      selected, a valid voltage (between the high/low limits defined below) must 
      be received for the 'Oil quality input validation' time before oil quality 
      monitoring will begin. Once an oil quality sensor has been auto-detected, 
      oil quality sensing will remain active unless it is manually 
      disabled/reset by a user. 
      OilQ_rpm_lmt Oil quality detection will be disabled when the engine speed 
      exceeds this limit. 
      OilQ_state Oil quality status 
      OilQ_trimchan If a trim sensor is present, oil quality monitoring can be 
      temporarily disabled during high trim angles when the oil quality sensor 
      may be primarily exposed to air. 
      OilQ_trimpct Drive trims above this value will cause a temporary disabling 
      of oil quality monitoring. 
      OilQ_trimpctlearn Time required to validate a sensor present when the 
      input configuration is set to 'Auto-sense'. This value is also used to 
      validate the sensor open and sensor closed readings in the nominal voltage 
      learn sequence. 
      OilQ_tvalid Time required to validate a sensor present when the input 
      configuration is set to 'Auto-sense'. This value is also used to validate 
      the sensor open and sensor closed readings in the nominal voltage learn 
      sequence. 
      OilQ_Vhi Upper limit for sensor input voltage during an auto-sense detect 
      sequence. 
      OilQ_Vlo Upper limit for sensor input voltage during an auto-sense detect 
      sequence. 
      OilQ_Vndelta Max delta from nominal voltage in (-) direction required for 
      a passing oil quality sensor reading. 
      OilQ_Vnom Oil quality nominal voltage 
      OilQ_Vpdelta Max delta from nominal voltage in (+) direction required for 
      a passing oil quality sensor reading.

      ovlp_Aeff This is the average effective area of the cam overlap over the 
      cam overlap CAD of rotation. It includes any discharge coefficient (Cd). 
      Typically, this value can be computed using the following formula if the 
      intake/exhaust valve lift values are known: 

      Aavg = (Ain*Aexh)/(Ain+Aexh)*(1+Asmall/Alarge*.6), where 

      Ain = intake valve area, 
      Aexh = exhaust valve area, 
      Asmall = min(Ain, Aexh), 
      Alarge = max(Ain, Aexh) 

      Then, the effective area = 

      Cd * integral(Aavg dCAD) / delta-CAD 

      This value is used to compute a VE altitude correction term for high 
      overlap engines. Set this value to zero to disable this feature. 
      ovlp_cyc_frac This is the effective rotation duration in crank degrees 
      that the effective area above acts over during overlap. 
      ovlp_EGT_def This is an estimated/average/default exhaust gas temperature 
      estimate for the combustion gases at the end of the exhaust stroke. This 
      is typically very hot even at idle (1200 deg F). 
      ovlp_m_port This is the result of the estimated overlap exhaust gas 
      induction calculation per cylinder relative to the standard or reference 
      value when the engine was calibrated. 
      OvSpd_volt overspeed input voltage in volts 
      park_brake_rawfilt Parking brake position analog feedback voltage. Value 
      is only valid if "Parking brake position input" is set to an analog input 
      such as 'Aux PU1'. See park_brake_sw_stat for parking brake digital switch 
      input status. 
      park_brake_sw_stat Parking brake switch status. If "Parking brake position 
      input" is set to 'Disabled', then parameter is set to the received CCVS 
      message parking brake switch status (PGN 65465). If "Parking brake 
      position input" is set to an Aux DIG input, then parameter is updated 
      accordingly. However, if "Parking brake position input" is set to an 
      analog input such as 'Aux PU1', then parameter is not applicable. See 
      park_brake_rawfilt for analog voltage feedback.

      Phi_cmd_dly Commanded equivalence ratio taking into account engine 
      transport delay 
      Phi_FSO_active Fuel shutoff (FSO) phi offset 
      Phi_FSO_cs_state Cold start operation state. Possible indications:
      - "Disabled": cold start emissions mode is disabled in the calibration
      - "Wait for start": engine is stopped, or has been running for less than 3 
      seconds
      - "Inactive": after engine start, ECT was above the threshold for cold 
      start operation
      - "Active": after engine start, ECT was below the threshold for cold start 
      operation
      - "Timed out": the engine was running longer than the maximum calibrated 
      time for cold start operation
      - "Complete": CBT exceeded the maximum temperature in the "Post-FSO Phi 
      Catalyst Enrichment" table, and post-FSO enrichment is operating normally 
      Phi_FSO_max_ms See the 'FSO phi catalyst enrichment' comment for details 
      on this parameter. 
      Phi_FSO_offset If non-zero and an active post-cat EGO sensor is available, 
      the phi command will be modified upon exiting fuel shutoff for more rapid 
      catalyst lightoff. The enrichment will end when any of the following are 
      true:
      - "FSO phi catalyst max engagement" time is exceeded.
      - A post-cat sensor lean-to-rich switch is achieved: the post-cat 
      voltage(s) must be greater than "FSO phi catalyst post-EGO switch" AND the 
      last FSO duration must have been longer than "FSO phi catalyst post-EGO 
      switch FSO duration" seconds.
      - For a single-bank application, the relative oxygen level is below the 
      desired relative oxygen level plus the approach delta, "FSO phi catalyst 
      ROL approach delta". 
      Phi_FSO_pst_mode Selects the post-FSO catalyst enrichment mode. The 
      following behaviors are enabled when set to "Enhanced" or "Enhanced + 
CBT":
      - Enables fast closed-loop acquire mode during post-FSO enrichment
      - Uses estimated ROL after one transport delay in conditions determining 
      when to exit post-FSO enrichment
      - Enables use of an optional, alternate TWC diagnostic pre-cat phi target 
      after ROL drops below the post-FSO enrichment threshold and before 
      post-cat phi reaches the diagnostic completion threshold.

      "Enhanced + CBT" mode behaves the same as "Enhanced" mode with the 
      addition to allow the FSO enrichment to be disabled/enabled by the CBT 
      model during a cold start. This also allows use of a multi-point table of 
      FSO enrichment values based on CBT. This will only be active if Cold Start 
      Mode is active. 
      Phi_FSO_pst_ROLapdlt ROL approach delta for exiting post-FSO catalyst 
      enrichment. 
      Phi_FSO_pst_ROL_thld ROL threshold for exiting post-FSO catalyst 
      enrichment. 
      Phi_FSO_pst_sw See the 'FSO phi catalyst enrichment' comment for details 
      on this parameter. 
      Phi_FSO_pst_sw_len The minimum fuel shutoff duration required to allow 
      post-cat voltage to terminate catalyst enrichment after a fuel shutoff 
      event. Set to 0 seconds to disable requirement. See "FSO phi catalyst 
      enrichment" for more details. 
      Phi_global_offset Manual global phi offset 
      Phi_lowslew_ena This features slews into lean phi commands at a given rate 
      limit. This allows stable fuel control near the lean limit. 
      Phi_lowslew_lim This defines the phi command below which lean-slewing will 
      be implemented. Phi commands above this value are tracked instantaneously. 

      Phi_lowslew_rate This defines the maximum lean-going phi command rate of 
      change for phi commands below the phi limit. 
      Phi_post_act Post Catalyst Phi Feedback Selection from engine operating 
      map (0 = inactive, 1 = active) 
      Phi_post_cs_CBT This is the CBT threshold which the CBT model must surpass 
      during a cold start that will allow the switch back to post-cat control 
      mode. This is only active if cold start mode is active. 
      Phi_post_cs_state Cold start operation state. Possible indications:
      - "Disabled": cold start emissions mode is disabled in the calibration
      - "Wait for start": engine is stopped, or has been running for less than 3 
      seconds
      - "Inactive": after engine start, ECT was above the threshold for cold 
      start operation
      - "Active": after engine start, ECT was below the threshold for cold start 
      operation
      - "Timed out": the engine was running longer than the maximum calibrated 
      time for cold start operation
      - "Complete": CBT exceeded the "Cold start continuous phi CBT threshold", 
      and post-cat control will no longer be disabled by cold start operation 
      Phi_post_d Post Catalyst Target Phi

      Phi_UEGO_raw UEGO phi (uncorrected) - sensor 1 
      pid_0x01_mil ISO 15031 / SAE J1979 MIL state 
      PID_CAT_B1S1_src Enables support for transmission of PID 0x3C – “Catalyst 
      Temperature Bank 1, Sensor 1” over the ISO 15031 and/or the ISO 14229 
      protocol.

      The following options are available:
      - Legacy – This selection is provided for backwards compatibility. When 
      selected, PID 0x3C will be supported if the “Catalyst 1/inlet “ (CAT1_ena) 
      setting is not set to “Disabled”. When supported, the Catalyst 1/inlet 
      temperature (CAT_Tin) will be transmitted. This is the default selection.
      - Disabled – PID 0x3C will not be supported.
      - Bed temperature (model) – PID 0x3C will be supported and the modeled 
      Catalyst Bed Temperature (CBT) will be transmitted.
      - Inlet temperature – PID 0x3C will be supported and the Catalyst 1/inlet 
      temperature (CAT_Tin) will be transmitted.
      - Outlet temperature – PID 0x3C will be supported and the Catalyst 
      2/outlet temperature (CAT_Tout) will be transmitted.

      For the ISO 15031 / SAE J1979 protocol this value is transmitted in 
      response to a Service 0x01 "Request current powertrain diagnostic data" 
      request for PID ID 0x3C - " Catalyst Temperature Bank 1, Sensor 1".

      For the ISO 14229 (UDS) protocol this value is transmitted in response to 
      a Service 0x22 – "ReadDataByIdentifier" request for DID 0xF43C – " 
      Catalyst Temperature Bank 1, Sensor 1". 
      PID_CAT_B1S2_src Enables support for transmission of PID 0x3E – “Catalyst 
      Temperature Bank 1, Sensor 2” over the ISO 15031 and/or the ISO 14229 
      protocol.

      The following options are available:
      - Legacy – This selection is provided for backwards compatibility. When 
      selected, PID 0x3E will be supported if the “Catalyst 2/outlet “ 
      (CAT2_ena) setting is not set to “Disabled”. When supported, the Catalyst 
      2/inlet temperature (CAT_Tout) will be transmitted. This is the default 
      selection.
      - Disabled – PID 0x3E will not be supported.
      - Bed temperature (model) – PID 0x3E will be supported and the modeled 
      Catalyst Bed Temperature (CBT) will be transmitted.
      - Inlet temperature – PID 0x3E will be supported and the Catalyst 1/inlet 
      temperature (CAT_Tin) will be transmitted.
      - Outlet temperature – PID 0x3E will be supported and the Catalyst 
      2/outlet temperature (CAT_Tout) will be transmitted.

      For the ISO 15031 / SAE J1979 protocol this value is transmitted in 
      response to a Service 0x01 "Request current powertrain diagnostic data" 
      request for PID ID 0x3C - " Catalyst Temperature Bank 1, Sensor 1".

      For the ISO 14229 (UDS) protocol this value is transmitted in response to 
      a Service 0x22 – "ReadDataByIdentifier" request for DID 0xF43C – " 
      Catalyst Temperature Bank 1, Sensor 1".

      PN_CFV_eng_cal_mod CFV part number based calibration reference code 
      (entered or provided by EControls) 
      PN_MFA_eng_cal_mod MFA part number based calibration reference code

      PN_MFG_eng_cal_mod MFG part number based calibration reference code

      PN_MJ_eng_cal_mod Engine calibration EPR calibration model 
      postcat_phi_retard The number of crank angle degrees the spark timing is 
      retarded for low-pressure EGR systems when the post-catalyst phi is below 
      the "Post-cat phi spark retard engage" threshold and EGR is flowing. 
      postphi_ret_CAD Specifies the amount of spark retard to apply when 
      low-pressure EGR is flowing and the post-catalyst phi is below the 
      "Post-cat phi spark retard engage" threshold.

      EGR flow rates of 30% or higher will modify spark timing using this full 
      value. Below 30%, the spark retard value will linearly decrease with the 
      EGR flow rate.

      Enter a positive value for this parameter to indicate the number of crank 
      angle degrees to retard the spark. A value of 0 disables this feature. 
      postphi_ret_diseng When post-catalyst phi based spark retard is active for 
      an engine equipped with a low-pressure EGR system, the phi must rise above 
      this threshold to discontinue modifying spark when the EGR is flowing. 
      postphi_ret_engage For an engine equipped with a low-pressure EGR system, 
      this parameter specifies the threshold to apply post-catalyst phi spark 
      retard when the EGR is flowing. Spark timing is modified when the 
      post-catalyst phi is below this threshold and will continue until the phi 
      rises above the "Post-cat phi spark retard disengage threshold". 
      postphi_ret_FSO_wt Specifies the number of post-catalyst EGO transport 
      delays that must occur before applying post-cat phi spark retard after 
      fuel shutoff exits and the subsequent phi catalyst enrichment ends. 
      power_mode Current power status 
      PPEG_BP_ECT_ena Pressure Offset Pegging: ECT enabling (BP). Certain 
      sensors will exhibit a temperature-dependent drift. Use this to disable 
      sampling during cold operation. 
      PPEG_BP_EEstore Pressure Offset Pegging: Behavior at power-on (BP). At 
      power-on, the previous offset can be restored from EEPROM or the offset 
      can be zeroed. If restored from EEPROM is selected, the pressure offset 
      filter will be initialized with the previous value (allowing for long-term 
      low-pass behavior of the offset pressure). 
      PPEG_BP_enable Pressure Offset Pegging: Enable switch and reference 
      pressure selection (BP). 
      PPEG_BP_fault BP pegging offset out-of-range diagnostic: BP offset sample 
      (absolute value) threshold 
      PPEG_BP_keyon_wt Pressure Offset Pegging: Key-on wait (BP). This value 
      should be set to allow enough time for voltages to stabilize at key-on. 
      PPEG_BP_keyX_wt Pressure Offset Pegging: Key-off clear wait (BP). If 
      non-zero, during the key-off clear period, pressure offset pegging will be 
      allowed. If non-zero and the start inhibit period is set to 0 and either 
      the max port flow or engine speed are set to 0, then the key-off clear 
      period will be the only period where sampling can occur. 
      PPEG_BP_mdot_max Pressure Offset Pegging: Max total port flow (BP). If the 
      maximum mass flow and/or the maximum engine speed are set to 0, pressure 
      offset pegging will only occur during the sampling period following 
      key-on. Otherwise, start may be inhibited during the sampling period (if 
      start inhibit period is non-zero) but pressure offset pegging will 
      continue after the sampling period whenever the engine speed and port mass 
      flow rates are below the specified limits. 
      PPEG_BP_Nmax Pressure Offset Pegging: Max engine speed (BP). If the 
      maximum mass flow and/or the maximum engine speed are set to 0, pressure 
      offset pegging will only occur during the sampling period following 
      key-on. Otherwise, start may be inhibited during the sampling period (if 
      start inhibit period is non-zero) but pressure offset pegging will 
      continue after the sampling period whenever the engine speed and port mass 
      flow rates are below the specified limits. 
      PPEG_BP_offset Pressure Offset Pegging: psi offset to be applied to BP, 
      from pressure pegging at start/low-flow 
      PPEG_BP_ofst_max Pressure Offset Pegging: Max allowed offset (BP). The 
      pressure offset will be limited to +/- this value. 
      PPEG_BP_Pref_max Pressure Offset Pegging: Maximum reference pressure (BP). 
      If the reference pressure is above this limit, pressure offset pegging 
      will be temporarily disabled. Pegging will resume after the reference 
      pressure is between the min/max limits and the invalid condition wait 
      period has elapsed. 
      PPEG_BP_Pref_min Pressure Offset Pegging: Minimum reference pressure (BP). 
      If the reference pressure is below this limit, pressure offset pegging 
      will be temporarily disabled. Pegging will resume after the reference 
      pressure is between the min/max limits and the invalid condition wait 
      period has elapsed. 
      PPEG_BP_start_wt Pressure Offset Pegging: Start inhibit period (BP). If 
      this value is non-zero, starting will be inhibited to allow for a 
      pre-start pressure offset pegging. If this value is 0, starting will not 
      be inhibited and the RPM/mass flow limits below must be used to make sure 
      the conditions are reasonable for a valid pressure comparison. 
      PPEG_BP_state Pressure Offset Pegging state (BP) 
      PPEG_BP_tau Pressure Offset Pegging: Offset low-pass time constant (BP). 
      Low pass filter time constant used to filter the reference - actual 
      pressure reading. 
      PPEG_BP_valid_wt Pressure Offset Pegging: Invalid conditions wait (BP). If 
      the flow rate, engine speed, or reference pressure readings are outside 
      the specified limits, this value determines the delay before offset 
      pegging once the limits are satisfied. The valid period should generally 
      be longer than the key-on wait period. 
      PPEG_CVP1_ECT_ena Certain sensors will exhibit a temperature-dependent 
      drift. Use this to disable sampling during cold operation for the CVP1 
      sensor. 
      PPEG_CVP1_EEstore At power-on, the previous offset for the CVP1 sensor can 
      be restored from EEPROM or the offset can be zeroed. If restored from 
      EEPROM is selected, the pressure offset filter will be initialized with 
      the previous value (allowing for long-term low-pass behavior of the offset 
      pressure). 
      PPEG_CVP1_enable Enables pressure offset pegging for the CVP1 sensor using 
      BP as the reference for an absolute sensor type and 0 psi for a 
      differential sensor type. 
      PPEG_CVP1_fault This CVP1 pegging offset out-of-range diagnostic limit is 
      applied to the instantaneous samples and not the final offset, since the 
      final offset might be limited to a value less than this diagnostic limit. 
      PPEG_CVP1_keyon_wt This value should be set to allow enough time for 
      voltages to stabilize at key-on for the CVP1 sensor. 
      PPEG_CVP1_keyX_wt If non-zero, during the key-off clear period, CVP1 
      pressure offset pegging will be allowed. If non-zero and the start inhibit 
      period is set to 0 and either the max port flow or engine speed are set to 
      0, then the key-off clear period will be the only period where sampling 
      can occur. 
      PPEG_CVP1_mdot_max If the maximum mass flow and/or the maximum engine 
      speed are set to 0, CVP1 pressure offset pegging will only occur during 
      the sampling period following key-on. Otherwise, start may be inhibited 
      during the sampling period (if start inhibit period is non-zero) but 
      pressure offset pegging will continue after the sampling period whenever 
      the engine speed and port mass flow rates are below the specified limits. 
      PPEG_CVP1_Nmax If the maximum mass flow and/or the maximum engine speed 
      are set to 0, CVP1 pressure offset pegging will only occur during the 
      sampling period following key-on. Otherwise, start may be inhibited during 
      the sampling period (if start inhibit period is non-zero) but pressure 
      offset pegging will continue after the sampling period whenever the engine 
      speed and port mass flow rates are below the specified limits. 
      PPEG_CVP1_offset This parameter stores the current CVP1 pressure offset 
      value. 
      PPEG_CVP1_ofst_max The CVP1 pressure offset will be limited to +/- this 
      value. 
      PPEG_CVP1_Pref_max If the reference pressure is above this limit, CVP1 
      pressure offset pegging will be temporarily disabled. Pegging will resume 
      after the reference pressure is between the min/max limits and the invalid 
      condition wait period has elapsed. 
      PPEG_CVP1_Pref_min If the reference pressure is below this limit, CVP1 
      pressure offset pegging will be temporarily disabled. Pegging will resume 
      after the reference pressure is between the min/max limits and the invalid 
      condition wait period has elapsed. 
      PPEG_CVP1_start_wt If this value is non-zero, starting will be inhibited 
      to allow for a pre-start CVP1 pressure offset pegging. If this value is 0, 
      starting will not be inhibited and the RPM/mass flow limits below must be 
      used to make sure the conditions are reasonable for a valid pressure 
      comparison. 
      PPEG_CVP1_state This parameter stores the current CVP1 pressure offset 
      state. 
      PPEG_CVP1_tau Low pass filter time constant used to filter the reference - 
      actual pressure reading for the CVP1 sensor. 
      PPEG_CVP1_valid_wt If the flow rate, engine speed, or reference pressure 
      readings are outside the specified limits, this value determines the delay 
      before CVP1 offset pegging once the limits are satisfied. The valid period 
      should generally be longer than the key-on wait period. 
      PPEG_CVP2_ECT_ena Certain sensors will exhibit a temperature-dependent 
      drift. Use this to disable sampling during cold operation for the CVP2 
      sensor.

      PPEG_CVP2_offset This parameter stores the current CVP2 pressure offset 
      value. 
      PPEG_CVP2_ofst_max The CVP1 pressure offset will be limited to +/- this 
      value. 
      PPEG_CVP2_Pref_max If the reference pressure is above this limit, CVP2 
      pressure offset pegging will be temporarily disabled. Pegging will resume

      PPEG_CVP2_Pref_min If the reference pressure is below this limit, CVP2 
      pressure offset pegging will be temporarily disabled. Pegging will resume 
      after the reference pressure is between the min/max limits and the invalid

      PPEG_CVP2_start_wt If this value is non-zero, starting will be inhibited 
      to allow for a pre-start CVP2 pressure offset pegging. If this value is 0, 
      starting will not be inhibited and the RPM/mass flow limits below must be 
      used to make sure the conditions are reasonable for a valid pressure 
      comparison. 
      PPEG_CVP2_state This parameter stores the current CVP2 pressure offset 
      state. 
      PPEG_CVP2_tau Low pass filter time constant used to filter the reference - 
      actual pressure reading for the CVP2 sensor. 
      PPEG_CVP2_valid_wt If the flow rate, engine speed, or reference pressure 
      readings are outside the specified limits, this value determines the delay 
      before CVP2 offset pegging once the limits are satisfied. The valid period 
      should generally be longer than the key-on wait period. 
      PPEG_EBP_ECT_ena Pressure Offset Pegging: ECT enabling (EBP). Certain 
      sensors will exhibit a temperature-dependent drift. Use this to disable 
      sampling during cold operation. 
      PPEG_EBP_EEstore Pressure Offset Pegging: Behavior at power-on (EBP). At 
      power-on, the previous offset can be restored from EEPROM or the offset 
      can be zeroed. If restored from EEPROM is selected, the pressure offset 
      filter will be initialized with the previous value (allowing for long-term 
      low-pass behavior of the offset pressure). 
      PPEG_EBP_enable Pressure Offset Pegging: Enable switch and reference 
      pressure selection (EBP). 
      PPEG_EBP_fault EBP pegging offset out-of-range diagnostic: EBP offset 
      sample (absolute value) threshold 
      PPEG_EBP_keyon_wt Pressure Offset Pegging: Key-on wait (EBP). This value 
      should be set to allow enough time for voltages to stabilize at key-on. 
      PPEG_EBP_keyX_wt Pressure Offset Pegging: Key-off clear wait (EBP). If 
      non-zero, during the key-off clear period, pressure offset pegging will be 
      allowed. If non-zero and the start inhibit period is set to 0 and either 
      the max port flow or engine speed are set to 0, then the key-off clear 
      period will be the only period where sampling can occur. 
      PPEG_EBP_mdot_max Pressure Offset Pegging: Max total port flow (EBP). If 
      the maximum mass flow and/or the maximum engine speed are set to 0, 
      pressure offset pegging will only occur during the sampling period 
      following key-on. Otherwise, start may be inhibited during the sampling 
      period (if start inhibit period is non-zero) but pressure offset pegging 
      will continue after the sampling period whenever the engine speed and port 
      mass flow rates are below the specified limits. 
      PPEG_EBP_Nmax Pressure Offset Pegging: Max engine speed (EBP). If the 
      maximum mass flow and/or the maximum engine speed are set to 0, pressure 
      offset pegging will only occur during the sampling period following 
      key-on. Otherwise, start may be inhibited during the sampling period (if 
      start inhibit period is non-zero) but pressure offset pegging will 
      continue after the sampling period whenever the engine speed and port mass 
      flow rates are below the specified limits. 
      PPEG_EBP_offset Pressure Offset Pegging: psi offset to be applied to EBP, 
      from pressure pegging at start/low-flow 
      PPEG_EBP_ofst_max Pressure Offset Pegging: Max allowed offset (EBP). The 
      pressure offset will be limited to +/- this value. 
      PPEG_EBP_Pref_max Pressure Offset Pegging: Maximum reference pressure 
      (EBP). If the reference pressure is above this limit, pressure offset 
      pegging will be temporarily disabled. Pegging will resume after the 
      reference pressure is between the min/max limits and the invalid condition 
      wait period has elapsed. 
      PPEG_EBP_Pref_min Pressure Offset Pegging: Minimum reference pressure 
      (EBP). If the reference pressure is below this limit, pressure offset 
      pegging will be temporarily disabled. Pegging will resume after the 
      reference pressure is between the min/max limits and the invalid condition 
      wait period has elapsed. 
      PPEG_EBP_start_wt Pressure Offset Pegging: Start inhibit period (EBP). If 
      this value is non-zero, starting will be inhibited to allow for a 
      pre-start pressure offset pegging. If this value is 0, starting will not 
      be inhibited and the RPM/mass flow limits below must be used to make sure 
      the conditions are reasonable for a valid pressure comparison. 
      PPEG_EBP_state Pressure Offset Pegging state (EBP) 
      PPEG_EBP_tau Pressure Offset Pegging: Offset low-pass time constant (EBP). 
      Low pass filter time constant used to filter the reference - actual 
      pressure reading. 
      PPEG_EBP_valid_wt Pressure Offset Pegging: Invalid conditions wait (EBP). 
      If the flow rate, engine speed, or reference pressure readings are outside

      PPEG_EGRdP_fault Pressure offset threshold for EGRdP pegging offset 
      out-of-range fault. If a measured sample of the EGRdP offset pressure is 
      greater than this value (positive or negative), the fault will begin to 
      latch. 
      PPEG_EGRHP_ECT_ena Pressure Offset Pegging: ECT enabling (EGRHP). Certain 
      sensors will exhibit a temperature-dependent drift. Use this to disable 
      sampling during cold operation.

      can be zeroed. If restored from EEPROM is selected, the pressure offset 
      filter will be initialized with the previous value (allowing for long-term 
      low-pass behavior of the offset pressure).

      pressure selection (EGRHP). 
      PPEG_EGRHP_fault EGRHP pegging offset out-of-range diagnostic: EGRHP 
      offset sample (absolute value) threshold

      PPEG_MAP_fault MAP pegging offset out-of-range diagnostic: All pressures 
      pegged to MAP with offset faults enabled are out of range and agree within 
      this value. NOTE: This limit is applied to the instantaneous samples and 
      not the final offset, since the final offset might be limited to a value 
      less than this diagnostic limit.

      pegging once the limits are satisfied. The valid period should generally 
      be longer than the key-on wait period. 
      PR_air_critical Critical pressure ratio. In a flow nozzle -- the pressure 
      ratio which will accelerate the flow to a velocity equal to the local 
      velocity of sound in Air. The maximum gas flow through a nozzle is 
      determined by the critical pressure. 
      PR_pseudo MAP/TIP lower bounded by PR_air_critical 
      PR_uncrct TOP/TIP lower bounded by PR_air_critical, w/o adaptive 
      correction applied in the case of dual-mode adaptive 
      PTOd_btn_rls_tout If set to a non-zero value, the PTO is disabled if all 
      buttons do not return to a released state before the specified time 
      elapses. 
      PTOd_dec_sw Power take-off (PTO) decrement 
      PTOd_disable Configures the discrete PTO controller disable switch input. 
      Can optionally be paired with a momentary PTO discrete control enable 
      switch. If a PTO discrete control disable switch is configured, the 
      momentary control enable state will no longer toggle between ON and OFF 
      states. The control enable state will only toggle ON. The PTO discrete 
      control disable switch is a momentary switch.

      When configured as one of the J1939 CCVS1 SPNs, the input is received from 
      either ECI PGN 65465 or 65467.

      When configured as J1939 PTO SPN 980, the input is received from ECI PGN 
      42315. Option 'J1939 PTO - SPN 980=01' will have an active indication when 
      SPN has a value of 1. Option 'J1939 PTO - SPN 980=00' is inverted and will 
      have an active indication when SPN has a value of 0. 
      PTOd_disable_2inputs If enabled, the PTO is disabled if two or more 
      enable, disable, set/inc, or resume/dec active input signals or fault 
      conditions are received simultaneously. The "PTO discrete set/resume 
      engine speed" setting is not used.

      If disabled, simultaneously pressing the set/inc and resume/dec buttons 
      will set the engine speed to the "PTO discrete set/resume engine speed" or 
      the last speed target stored to non-volatile memory. 
      PTOd_disable_cfg If an Aux DIG is selected for the control disable input, 
      this value determines the active logic state(s). Default values are 
      defined when Aux DIG1 through Aux DIG10 are selected for the control 
      disable input
      Aux DIG1 = Select
      Aux DIG2 = Select
      Aux DIG3 = Select
      Aux DIG4 = Select
      Aux DIG5 = Select
      Aux DIG6 = Select
      Aux DIG7 = Select
      Aux DIG8 = Select
      Aux DIG9 = Select
      Aux DIG10 = Select 
      PTOd_dis_sw_stat Discrete PTO disable switch input status (0=Inactive, 
      1=Active, 2=Error/Fault, 3=Not Configured). 
      PTOd_ena Logical: PTO Discrete Controller enabled 
      PTOd_enable_mode If set to "Enable input" (the default):
      - The PTO is initially disabled.
      - Pressing the enable button will enable the PTO. The pending engine speed 
      is set to the last speed target stored to non-volatile memory, the "PTO 
      discrete initial engine speed", or the "PTO slow/min engine speed". 
      Pressing the enable button has no immediate effect on the engine speed.
      - Pressing the disable button will disable the PTO.
      - The first tap of the "set/inc" button after enabled sets the engine 
      speed to the last speed target stored to non-volatile memory or the "PTO 
      set/inc engine speed", and engages the PTO.
      - The first tap of the "resume/dec" button after enabled sets the engine 
      speed to the "PTO resume/dec engine speed", and engages the PTO.
      - The PTO will disengage when the multi-function input control function 
      changes.

      If set to "Always enabled":
      - The PTO is always enabled.
      - Pressing the enable button will engage the PTO. When the vehicle is 
      stopped (less than 0.5 kph) and the foot pedal position is at idle, then 
      the PTO is engaged and the engine speed is set to the last speed target 
      stored to non-volatile memory, the "PTO discrete initial engine speed", or 
      the "PTO slow/min engine speed". Otherwise, if the current engine speed is 
      between the "PTO slow/min engine speed" and the "PTO fast/max engine 
      speed", then the PTO is engaged and the current engine speed will be 
      maintained.
      - Pressing the disable button will disengage the PTO.
      - The first tap of the "set/inc" or "resume/dec" button after enabled has 
      no special behavior.
      - The PTO will be disabled when the multi-function input control function 
      changes.

      If set to "J1939 PTO":
      - The PTO is initially disabled.
      - When disabled, pressing the Accelerate, Decelerate, or Resume button 
      will enable and engage the PTO. When the vehicle is stopped (less than 0.5 
      kph) and the foot pedal position is at idle, then the PTO is engaged and 
      the engine speed is set to the last speed target stored to non-volatile 
      memory, the "PTO discrete initial engine speed", or the "PTO slow/min 
      engine speed". Otherwise, if the current engine speed is between the "PTO 
      slow/min engine speed" and the "PTO fast/max engine speed", then the PTO 
      is engaged and the current engine speed will be maintained.
      - Pressing the Set button will disengage the PTO, but will not reset the 
      PTO set point speed.
      - The first tap of the "set/inc" or "resume/dec" button after enabled has 
      no special behavior.
      - The PTO will be disabled when the multi-function input control function 
      changes.

      Additional behaviors when set to "Always enabled":
      - The PTO will disengage when the actual engine speed is outside of the 
      PTO operating range.
      - A disable input must be configured.
      - The PTO will be disabled if the disable input is faulty.

      Additional behaviors when set to "J1939 PTO":
      - When disengaged, pressing the Resume button will re-engage the PTO. When 
      the vehicle is stopped (less than 0.5 kph) and the foot pedal position is 
      at idle, then the PTO is engaged and the engine speed is set to the PTO 
      speed target at the time the PTO was disengaged. Otherwise, if the current 
      engine speed is between the "PTO slow/min engine speed" and the "PTO 
      fast/max engine speed", then the PTO is engaged and the current engine 
      speed will be maintained. The Resume button has no function while engaged.
      - The PTO will disengage in similar conditions as roadspeed cruise 
      control, such as clutch depressed, foot brake depressed, invalid 
      transmission status, etc. In other configurations, these conditions 
      disable the PTO. 
      PTOd_enable_moment PTO discrete control enable switch type (toggle vs. 
      momentary switch) 
      PTOd_ena_sw_stat Discrete PTO enable switch input status (0=Inactive, 
      1=Active, 2=Error/Fault, 3=Not Configured). 
      PTOd_inc_sw Power take-off (PTO) increment 
      PTOd_resdec_cfg If an Aux DIG is selected for the input, this value 
      determines the active logic state(s). The Default values are:
      Aux DIG1 = Gnd
      Aux DIG2 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG3 = Gnd
      Aux DIG4 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG5 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG6 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG7 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG8 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG9 = Gnd
      Aux DIG10 = Gnd
      Aux DIG11 = Gnd
      Aux DIG12 = Gnd
      Aux DIG13 = Gnd
      Aux DIG14 = Gnd
      Aux DIG15 = Gnd
      Aux DIG16 = Gnd
      Aux DIG17 = Gnd
      Aux DIG18 = Gnd
      Aux DIG19 = Gnd
      Gov1 = Gnd
      Gov2 = Gnd 
      PTOd_resdec_chan Configures the discrete PTO resume/decrement input. When 
      configured as one of the J1939 CCVS1 SPNs, the input is received from 
      either ECI PGN 65465 or 65467. 
      PTOd_resdec_ramp Discrete PTO RESUME/DECC ramp down rate (PTO + ramp rate 
      to use after the initial wait time) 
      PTOd_resdec_rpm Engine speed target for the initial res/- button press. 
      PTOd_resdec_sw_stat Discrete PTO resume/decrement switch input status 
      (0=Inactive, 1=Active, 2=Error/Fault, 3=Not Configured). 
      PTOd_resdec_tap PTO rpm decrease for each momentary button press shorter 
      than the ramp up wait time. 
      PTOd_resdec_wait The initial res/- button press will change the PTO target 
      to the engine speed above. After waiting this amount of time, the engine 
      speed will ramp down at the ramp rate specified below. 
      PTOd_res_sw Power take-off (PTO) resume 
      PTOd_rpm_accum Discrete PTO governor target speed (working variable) 
      PTOd_rpm_init Initial PTO engine speed to use when the PTO is engaged in 
      the "Always enabled" or "J1939 PTO" configurations, or when engaged by 
      holding set/+ or res/- longer than the ramp wait time. When "PTO discrete 
      set/inc engine speed retention" is set to "Permanently retained", this 
      value is only used when a previous PTO discrete engine speed has not been 
      stored to non-volatile memory. If set to zero, the "PTO slow/min engine 
      speed" is used instead. 
      PTOd_setinc_cfg If an Aux DIG is selected for the input, this value 
      determines the active logic state(s). The Default values are:
      Aux DIG1 = Gnd
      Aux DIG2 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG3 = Gnd
      Aux DIG4 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG5 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG6 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG7 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG8 = +V/Gnd
      Aux DIG9 = Gnd
      Aux DIG10 = Gnd
      Aux DIG11 = Gnd
      Aux DIG12 = Gnd
      Aux DIG13 = Gnd
      Aux DIG14 = Gnd
      Aux DIG15 = Gnd
      Aux DIG16 = Gnd
      Aux DIG17 = Gnd
      Aux DIG18 = Gnd
      Aux DIG19 = Gnd
      Gov1 = Gnd
      Gov2 = Gnd 
      PTOd_setinc_chan Configures the discrete PTO set/increment input. When 
      configured as one of the J1939 CCVS1 SPNs, the input is received from 
      either ECI PGN 65465 or 65467. 
      PTOd_setinc_ramp PTO + ramp rate to use after the initial wait time above. 

      PTOd_setinc_rpm Engine speed target for the initial set/+ button press. 
      See 'PTO discrete set/inc engine speed retention' above. 
      PTOd_setinc_store_EE Selects how the engine speed target is determined for 
      initial PTO engagement. The default initial PTO speed is calculated as 
      follows:
      - If this parameter is set to "Permanently retained", and non-volatile 
      memory contains a set point, then uses the value retained in non-volatile 
      memory;
      - otherwise, uses "PTO discrete initial engine speed" if non-zero, which 
      will be clamped between "PTO slow/min engine speed" and "PTO fast/max 
      engine speed";
      - otherwise, uses "PTO slow/min engine speed".

      For the "J1939 PTO" configuration:
      - The initial engagement speed target is always the default initial PTO 
      speed.

      For other configurations:
      - If this parameter is set to "Reset when disengaged", a set/+ button 
      press sets the speed target to the value specified in the 'PTO discrete 
      set/inc engine speed' calibration variable.
      - If this parameter is set to "Permanently retained":
      * The very first set/+ button press sets the speed target to the value 
      specified in the 'PTO discrete set/inc engine speed' calibration variable.
      * Any subsequent set/+ button press sets the speed target to the value 
      retained in non-volatile memory.

      For all configurations:
      - Holding set/+ or res/- to engage the PTO will start the speed target 
      ramp from the default initial PTO speed.
      - If this parameter is set to "Permanently retained", the latest speed 
      target is retained in non-volatile memory. 
      PTOd_setinc_sw_stat Discrete PTO set/increment switch input status 
      (0=Inactive, 1=Active, 2=Error/Fault, 3=Not Configured). 
      PTOd_setinc_tap PTO rpm increase for each momentary button press shorter 
      than the ramp up wait time. 
      PTOd_setinc_wait The initial set/+ button press will change the PTO target 
      to the engine speed above. After waiting this amount of time, the engine 
      speed will ramp up at the ramp rate specified below. 
      PTOd_setres_rpm Enter the engine speed to use as the PTO target if the 
      set/+ and resume/- buttons are simultaneously pressed. The PTO system will 
      interlock a simultaneous button state and require both buttons return to 
      the off state before taking further action. This setting is not used if 
      set to zero or if "PTO discrete control disabled by simultaneous inputs" 
      is enabled. 
      PTOd_setres_wait Enter an additional debounce time for the set/+ and 
      resume/- inputs. A nonzero time here allows the system time to validate a 
      simultaneous set/+ and resume/- button press without regard to which 
      button is pressed first. However, if nonzero, the PTO system will wait the 
      specified time before accepting either input as ON. 
      PTOd_set_sw Power take-off (PTO) set 
      PTOd_sw Configures the discrete PTO controller enable switch input.

      When configured as one of the J1939 CCVS1 SPNs, the input is received from 
      either ECI PGN 65465 or 65467.

      When configured as J1939 PTO SPN 980, the input is received from ECI PGN 
      42315. Option 'J1939 PTO - SPN 980=01' will have an active indication when 
      SPN has a value of 1. Option 'J1939 PTO - SPN 980=00' is inverted and will 
      have an active indication when SPN has a value of 0. 
      PTOd_sw_cfg If an Aux DIG is selected for the control activation, this 
      value determines the active logic state(s). Default values are defined 
      when Aux DIG1 through Aux DIG10 are selected for the control activation.
      Aux DIG1 = Select
      Aux DIG2 = Select
      Aux DIG3 = Select
      Aux DIG4 = Select
      Aux DIG5 = Select
      Aux DIG6 = Select
      Aux DIG7 = Select
      Aux DIG8 = Select
      Aux DIG9 = Select
      Aux DIG10 = Select

      PTOp_ena_sw_stat Proportional PTO enable switch input status (0=Inactive, 
      1=Active, 2=Error/Fault, 3=Not Configured). 
      PTOp_rpm_inst PTO Proportional Controller rpm target speed 
      PTO_brake_override If enabled, PTO will be disabled if the brake is 
      depressed. 
      PTO_clutch_override If enabled, PTO will be disabled if the clutch is 
      depressed. 
      PTO_ebrake_override If enabled, PTO mode will be temporarily disabled if 
      either of the driveline brakes are engaged. Regardless of this setting, 
      the drive brakes (engine, exhaust, and/or transmission retarder) are 
      prohibited from engaging while PTO is active and the PTO set speed > min 
      governor speed + fuel shutoff idle wait. This option determines the PTO 
      behavior when the PTO set speed is below these limits and the drive brakes 
      activate. 
      PTO_ena Power take-off (PTO) proportional control enabled indication 
      PTO_gov_type The discrete 1/2/3 governor settings prohibit user override. 
      The last setting allows FPP override on discrete governor 3. 
      PTO_max_load_pct PTO maximum load percent 
      PTO_rpmd Power take-off (PTO) engine speed target 
      PTO_rpmfast The upper limit for the PTO engine speed control. 
      PTO_rpmslow The lower limit for the PTO engine speed control. 
      PTO_rpm_dz Dead zone for disengaging PTO engine speed control. 
      PTO_spdinput Enables and selects input for Power Take Off proportional 
      control. 
      PTO_sw Configures the proportional PTO controller enable switch input. If 
      the brake, clutch, or drivebrake disengage the PTO, the proportional 
      enable switch must be toggled to allow re-engagement of proportional PTO 
      mode. 
      PTO_sw_cfg If an Aux DIG is selected for the control activation, this 
      value determines the active logic state(s). Default values are defined 
      when Aux DIG1 through Aux DIG10 are selected for the control activation:
      Aux DIG1 = Select
      Aux DIG2 = Select
      Aux DIG3 = Select
      Aux DIG4 = Select
      Aux DIG5 = Select
      Aux DIG6 = Select
      Aux DIG7 = Select
      Aux DIG8 = Select
      Aux DIG9 = Select
      Aux DIG10 = Select 
      PTO_sw_validation If a switch-off validation is required, the PTO switch 
      must transition from off to on following an engine stopped, key-off, 
      cruise-active, roadspeed loss, brake/clutch/drive-brake override, vehicle 
      interlock invalid, or roadspeed too high condition. 
      PTO_vehspd_limit The PTO feature will be disabled if the vehicle speed 
      exceeds this limit. Set this to 0.0 to only allow PTO engagement while the 
      vehicle is stopped. If this value is set to 0.0 and a "Roadspeed loss" 
      fault exists, PTO will be disabled until the roadspeed can be evaluated. 
      PTO_vehspd_min The PTO feature will be disabled if the vehicle speed is 
      below this threshold. Set this to a value greater than 0.5 kph to only 
      allow PTO engagement while the vehicle is moving. 
      PTO_Vfast The upper limit for the PTO engine speed control input. 
      PTO_Vslow The lower limit for the PTO engine speed control input. 
      PTPs Standard Pre-Turbine Pressure

      pulse_Hz_capture Pulse-in Hz capture available

      over all cylinders

      PWM6_short_loDC PWM6 short to power diagnostic: Alternate entry condition 
      - PWM current feedback upper limit. This mode is only intended for ECM's 
      with PWM current feedback and should not be used otherwise. 
      PWM6_short_mA PWM6 short to power diagnostic: Alternate entry condition - 
      PWM duty cycle low limit. This mode is only intended for ECM's with PWM 
      current feedback and should not be used otherwise. 
      PWM7_off_loDC PWM7 open / ground short diagnostic: PWM duty cycle lower 
      limit entry condition 
      PWM7_off_loVf PWM7 open / ground short diagnostic: PWM low-side feedback 
      voltage lower limit entry condition 
      PWM7_on_hiDC PWM7 short to power diagnostic:PWM duty cycle upper limit 
      entry condition 
      PWM7_on_hiVf PWM7 short to power diagnostic: PWM low-side feedback upper 
      limit entry condition. 
      PWM8_off_loDC PWM8 open / ground short diagnostic: PWM duty cycle lower 
      limit entry condition 
      PWM8_off_loVf PWM8 open / ground short diagnostic: PWM low-side feedback 
      voltage lower limit entry condition 
      PWM8_on_hiDC PWM8 short to power diagnostic:PWM duty cycle upper limit 
      entry condition 
      PWM8_on_hiVf PWM8 short to power diagnostic: PWM low-side feedback upper 
      limit entry condition. 
      PWM9_off_loDC PWM9 open / ground short diagnostic: PWM duty cycle lower 
      limit entry condition 
      PWM9_off_loVf PWM9 open / ground short diagnostic: PWM low-side feedback 
      voltage lower limit entry condition 
      PWM9_on_hiDC PWM9 short to power diagnostic:PWM duty cycle upper limit 
      entry condition 
      PWM9_on_hiVf PWM9 short to power diagnostic: PWM low-side feedback upper 
      limit entry condition. 
      PWMLO_off_hi_volt Lockoff open diagnostic: High-side feedback upper limit 
      threshold 
      PWMLO_off_loDC Lockoff open / ground short diagnostic: PWM duty-cycle 
      lower limit threshold 
      PWMLO_off_loVf Lockoff open / ground short diagnostic: PWM low-side 
      feedback lower limit threshold 
      PWMLO_on_hiDC Lockoff short to power diagnostic: PWM duty-cycle upper 
      limit threshold 
      PWMLO_on_hiVf Lockoff short to power diagnostic: PWM low-side feedback 
      upper limit threshold 
      PWMLO_on_loVf Lockoff ground short diagnostic: High-side feedback lower 
      limit threshold 
      PWMLO_pwr_src Specifies whether lockoff valve power is controlled by the 
      key switch or the RELAY output. 
      PWM_flt_DCtrans_wt PWM duty-cycle transition fault ignore wait entry 
      condition for all AUX PWM diagnostics. On transitions between duty-cycle 
      fault checking conditions (high-to-low duty cycle or low-to-high 
      duty-cycle transitions), this time must elapse before the PWM fault 
      checking begins. This allows wider limits to be used on the PWM fault 
      checks without artificially latching a fault due to repeated duty-cycle 
      transitions. 
      PWM_I_FB_dly_us Hydraulic Fwd/Rev Current Measurement: Current Measurement 
      Delay. Time to wait following a completed PWM cycle before completing 
      current measurements. 
      PWM_I_peak_back_max_us Hydraulic Fwd/Rev Current Measurement: Peak current 
      search window. This is the size of the window at the end of the PWM 
      on-cycle used to search for the peak current. 
      PWPCF Pulse Width Pressure Correction Factor 
      PWPCF_deltaPW PWPCF based pulse-width offset for all cylinders in timer 
      ticks 
      PWPCF_I2 Pressure Correction (PCF) - secondary. Pulse width correction 
      factor as a function of supply pressure 
      PWPCF_mode Pressure Correction mode - primary. Specifies the pressure 
      correction factor to use when calculating a pulse width correction factor 
      as a function of supply pressure. 
      PWPCF_mode_I2 Pressure Correction mode - secondary. Specifies the pressure 
      correction factor to use when calculating a pulse width correction factor 
      as a function of supply pressure. 
      pwr_correction Power Correction factor 
      pwr_crct_mode Power correction type 
      PW_avg Instantaneous Pulse Width average over all cylinders 
      PW_emg_data Mass of fuel per injection for the given on-time. These values 
      may not exceed 1900 mg/inj. 
      PW_ems_data Extended injector on-time in ms for the given mass per 
      injection for very large (cold start) injections. These values may not 
      exceed 950 ms. 
      PW_mg_data (Primary Injector Pulse Width) Mass of fuel per injection for 
      the given on-time. 
      PW_mg_data_I2 (Secondary Injector Pulse Width) Mass of fuel per injection 
      for the given on-time. 
      PW_min_extra This is the minimum zero-based pulse-width (proportion to 
      mg/inj) that the controller will add after the primary injection pulse for 
      a particular cylinder event. The actual minimum injection pulse will be 
      equal to this value plus the current injector offset time. 
      PW_min_extra_I2 Fuel Injector Transient Setup: Extra injection minimum PW 
      (secondary) 
      PW_ms_data (Primary Injector Pulse Width) Injector on-time in ms for the 
      given mass per injection. 
      PW_ms_data_I2 (Secondary Injector Pulse Width) Injector on-time in ms for 
      the given mass per injection. 
      PW_offset_global Global Pulse Width for all cylinders 
      PW_zero Fuel Injector Transient Setup: PW zero equivalent (primary) 
      PW_zero_I2 Fuel Injector Transient Setup: PW zero equivalent (secondary) 
      radby_poserr_err Position error percentage threshold for the "Unable to 
      reach radiator bypass valve target position" diagnostic. 
      radby_poserr_minVbat Minimum battery voltage threshold for the "Unable to 
      reach radiator bypass valve target position" diagnostic. 
      radby_poserr_wait Minimum duration the position error must persistently 
      occur for the "Unable to reach radiator bypass valve target position" 
      diagnostic. 
      RangeHst_cnt Range counter/timer accumulator value 
      RangeHst_cntr_upd Specifies the sample rate for all event counters. At 
      each sample time, an event counter is incremented if the run-time 
      parameter value falls within the calibrated range and its value was not 
      within range during the previous sample. 
      RangeHst_ECIPP_ndx ECM internal parameter index of the selected 
      counter/timer variable 
      RangeHst_max Range counter/timer maximum value
