      SCC2_Vd Hydraulic Reverse Solenoid Control: Re-circulation diode voltage 
      SCD_active_ms Start command detection: Command detection active timer 
      SCD_off_FB_volts If start command detection is active and the starter 
      output feedback voltage is below this limit, the starter command will be 
      set to 'off'. 
      SCD_PWM_dc Specify the starter relay duty-cycle command to use while 
      command detection is active. Note for the first 10ms the starter relay 
      engages, the command is always 100%. 
      SCD_relay_on_wt Once the reduced duty-cycle PWM starter relay output 
      activates (note for the first 10ms the starter relay engages, the command 
      is always 100%), this much time must pass before the starter command 
      detection engages. This parameter compensates for feedback settling and 
      filtering delays. 
      SCD_Vbat_min If Vbat is below this limit, user start command detection is 
      disabled. 
      SCRT Selective catalytic reduction (SCR) temperature 
      SCRT_ena Designates aux temperature sensor input for measuring Selective 
      catalytic reduction (SCRT) 
      SCRT_Taux_cal Selective catalytic reduction (SCR) temperature sensor 
      calibration table selection 
      SCRT_vdr Selective catalytic reduction (SCR) temperature input channel 
      pullup resistor configuration 
      SDblk_off A warning may cause a continuous output activation or a 
      blinking/pulsing output. The on/off times specify this behavior. For a 
      continuous-on output in an active state, simply set the off-time to zero 
      and the on-time to any value. 
      SDblk_on A warning may cause a continuous output activation or a 
      blinking/pulsing output. The on/off times specify this behavior. For a 
      continuous-on output in an active state, simply set the off-time to zero 
      and the on-time to any value. 
      SD_active indicates a shutdown or ramp-to-shutdown is currently active 
      SD_inhibit Indicates whether fault shutdown inhibit is active. 
      SD_lamp Output lamp associated with shutdown faults. 
      SD_out_ena Determines the channel used to output the engine shutdown 
      signal 
      SD_ramp_ena If this switch is 'Enabled' and a fault shutdown request is 
      generated, the rev limit is slewed to idle (min governor setpoint) at the 
      rev limit engagement slew down rate. Once the idle setpoint is reached, 
      the engine will continue to idle for the 'idle wait' time before the 
      engine is shut down. Note that this feature does not apply to TPS-related 
      faults, which will always generate immediate shutdowns. 
      SD_ramp_tmr Ramp to shutdown completed, at idle timer 
      SD_ramp_twait This value controls how long the engine will idle before 
      shutting down if the reduced rev limit fault shutdown feature is enabled. 
      SD_trigger_FMI Shutdown fault FMI 
      SD_trigger_SA Shutdown fault CAN Source Address 
      SD_trigger_SPN Shutdown fault SPN 
      secspd_actinv This diagnostic mode detects attempted activity by the user 
      on a secondary speed control system such as tap up/down, FPP2 based speed 
      control, etc... without valid conditions present for this type of control. 

      secspd_ena Secondary speed control mode selection via an independent input 
      determined by secspd_sw 
      secspd_FPP2act When the 'secondary speed control invalid activity' 
      diagnostic is 'Enabled', this value determines the detection sensitivity 
      of movement of the FPP2 input when FPP2 based speed control is an option. 
      A +/- change of more than this voltage level on FPP2 relative to the last 
      position of FPP2 when FPP2 speed control was actually valid and engaged 
      will trigger a fault. The comparison value for the last position is also 
      continuously low-passed to remove any drift effect. 
      secspd_FPP2trk FPP2 invalid activity reference level 
      secspd_FPP2trk_tau When the 'secondary speed control invalid activity' 
      diagnostic is 'Enabled', a low-pass filtered version of FPP2 is maintained 
      as a reference value for activity comparison. This reference value tracks 
      the actual FPP2 voltage without delay when FPP2 based control is valid and 
      engaged, but follows with this time constant once it is disengaged. This 
      eliminates drift over time for invalid activity comparisons. 
      secspd_sw This switch controls engagement of the secondary speed control 
      modes. See the discrete speed governor validation configuration comment 
      above for details on how this input is used for validating discrete-speed 
      governing. This input is also used for secondary foot pedal control. If 
      this switch is set to anything other than default: 

      1) If the BRAKE input is valid and FPP2 mode is set to speed control, this 
      input switches the active FPP mode between speed control and disabled.
      2) If this switch is set to default, the second foot pedal is controlled 
      only by the BRAKE input. 
      SecThreshold Secondary Spark Feedback Threshold 
      SENT1_crc_computed SENT1 Data Input Channel Configuration: SENT1 cyclic 
      redundancy check (CRC) computed 
      SENT1_crc_received SENT1 Data Input Channel Configuration: SENT1 cyclic 
      redundancy check (CRC) received 
      SENT1_crc_type This switch selects which CRC algorithm is used to verify 
      the contents of the SENT channel 1 frame. Early SENT sensors used the 
      J2716-FEB28 Legacy algorithm. More recent sensors use the J2716-JAN21 
      Recommended algorithm. 
      SENT1_data1 SENT1 data1 (integer) value 
      SENT1_Data1_c This is the slope of the linear transformation used on SENT1 
      Data1 such that Destination Value = Data1 * SENT1_Data1_c + SENT1_Data1_o.

      NOTE: the FP/FT sensor uses internal scaling and does not use the slope or 
      offset. 
      SENT1_Data1_def This is the default integer data to be used for 
      initialization and fault conditions for the SENT1 Data1 parameter. Normal 
      data is an integer from 0 to 4095 but this value may be a positive integer 
      up to 65535. 
      SENT1_Data1_o See SENT1_Data1_c for details. 
      SENT1_data2 SENT1 data2 (integer) value 
      SENT1_Data2_c This is the slope of the linear transformation used on SENT1 
      Data2 such that Destination Value = Data2 * SENT1_Data2_c + SENT1_Data2_o.

      NOTE: the FP/FT sensor uses internal scaling and does not use the slope or 
      offset. 
      SENT1_Data2_def This is the default integer data to be used for 
      initialization and fault conditions for the SENT1 Data2 parameter. Normal 
      data is an integer from 0 to 4095 but this value may be a positive integer 
      up to 65535. 
      SENT1_Data2_o See SENT1_Data2_c for details. 
      SENT1_diag_info SENT1 internal diagnostic flag 
      SENT1_ena This switch selects the SENT1 digital input channel mode. Note 
      that if this channel is enabled, a mating switch elsewhere in the system 
      must also be configured to accept the incoming data (such as TPS1_source, 
      TPS2_source, ...) 
      SENT1_error_cnt SENT1 error counter 
      SENT1_no_signal_cnt SENT1 no-signal counter 
      SENT1_serial_crc_no Count of packets where computed CRC did not match 
      message CRC 
      SENT1_serial_crc_ok Count of packets where computed CRC matched message 
      CRC 
      SENT1_serial_data 12bit data received in Enhanced Serial Protocol bits 
      SENT1_serial_def This is the default integer data to be used for 
      initialization and fault conditions for the SENT1 Enhanced Serial Protocol 
      extracted parameter. Normal data is an integer from 0 to 4095 but this 
      value may be a positive integer up to 65535. 
      SENT1_serial_msg_id 8bit Message ID received in Enhanced Serial Protocol 
      bits 
      SENT1_serial_resync Number of times Enhanced Serial Protocol did not line 
      up and a resync was required 
      SENT1_status SENT1 status byte 
      SENT1_sync_time SENT1 sync time 
      SENT1_timeout_cnt SENT1 timeout counter 
      SENT2_crc_computed SENT2 Data Input Channel Configuration: SENT2 cyclic 
      redundancy check (CRC) computed 
      SENT2_crc_received SENT2 Data Input Channel Configuration: SENT2 cyclic 
      redundancy check (CRC) received 
      SENT2_crc_type This switch selects which CRC algorithm is used to verify 
      the contents of the SENT channel 2 frame. Early SENT sensors used the 
      J2716-FEB2008 Legacy algorithm. More recent sensors use the J2716-JAN2010 
      Recommended algorithm. 
      SENT2_data1 SENT2 data1 (integer) value 
      SENT2_Data1_c This is the slope of the linear transformation used on SENT2 
      Data1 such that Destination Value = Data1 * SENT2_Data1_c + SENT2_Data1_o.

      NOTE: the FP/FT sensor uses internal scaling and does not use the slope or 
      offset. 
      SENT2_Data1_def This is the default integer data to be used for 
      initialization and fault conditions for the SENT2 Data1 parameter. Normal 
      data is an integer from 0 to 4095 but this value may be a positive integer 
      up to 65535. 
      SENT2_Data1_o See SENT2_Data1_c for details. 
      SENT2_data2 SENT2 data2 (integer) value 
      SENT2_Data2_c This is the slope of the linear transformation used on SENT2 
      Data2 such that Destination Value = Data2 * SENT2_Data2_c + SENT2_Data2_o.

      NOTE: the FP/FT sensor uses internal scaling and does not use the slope or 
      offset. 
      SENT2_Data2_def This is the default integer data to be used for 
      initialization and fault conditions for the SENT2 Data2 parameter. Normal 
      data is an integer from 0 to 4095 but this value may be a positive integer 
      up to 65535. 
      SENT2_Data2_o See SENT2_Data2_c for details. 
      SENT2_diag_info SENT2 internal diagnostic flag

      that if this channel is enabled, a mating switch elsewhere in the system 
      must also be configured to accept the incoming data (such as TPS1_source, 
      TPS2_source, ...)

      sf_blink_output Blink output channel (Disabled, MIL, hard warning, soft 
      warning). This setting specifies the logical output channel to blink when 
      stored faults are present. The actual physical output pin is determined 
      based on the “Warning/MIL Output Configuration” settings. 
      SGf Actual Specific Gravity of the fuel. This can be an approximation 
      based on a local average. 
      SGfs Standard Specific Gravity of the fuel used for the fuel flow 
      calibration 
      SGfs_LP Standard Specific Gravity of the fuel used for the fuel flow 
      calibration 
      SGfs_NG Standard Specific Gravity of the fuel used for the fuel flow 
      calibration 
      SGf_act Current fuel specific gravity. 
      SGf_LP Actual Specific Gravity of the fuel. This can be an approximation 
      based on a local average. 
      SGf_NG Actual Specific Gravity of the fuel. This can be an approximation 
      based on a local average. 
      SG_throttle Current mixture specific gravity at the throttle. 
      SH Current specific humidity (from environmental sensor) 
      ShftIntSS_FdFa Shift Interrupt shift state - Forward (desired) from 
      Forward (actual) 
      ShftIntSS_FdNa Shift Interrupt shift state - Forward (desired) from 
      Neutral (actual) 
      ShftIntSS_FdRa Shift Interrupt shift state - Forward (desired) from 
      Reverse (actual) 
      ShftIntSS_NdFa Shift Interrupt shift state - Neutral (desired) from 
      Forward (actual) 
      ShftIntSS_NdNa Shift Interrupt shift state - Neutral (desired) from 
      Neutral (actual) 
      ShftIntSS_NdRa Shift Interrupt shift state - Neutral (desired) from 
      Reverse (actual) 
      ShftIntSS_RdFa Shift Interrupt shift state - Reverse (desired) from 
      Forward (actual) 
      ShftIntSS_RdNa Shift Interrupt shift state - Reverse (desired) from 
      Neutral (actual) 
      ShftIntSS_RdRa Shift Interrupt shift state - Reverse (desired) from 
      Reverse (actual) 
      ShftInt_actv_tmr Shift interrupt active timer 
      ShftInt_ena This switch selects the hardware input pin that controls 
      activation of the shift interrupt function. Active is assumed to be a 
      switch to ground. For the network option, a negative torque limit from a 
      J1939 TSC1 command will initiate this function. 
      ShftInt_FPPmax Shift interrupt will not be engaged above this FPP limit. 
      ShftInt_idle This is the idle target for the air valve control (DBW or 
      IAC) during active shift interrupt in 'switch-type' mode. 
      ShftInt_ignoret If the shift interrupt hardware input channel stays active 
      continuously for more than this timeout value, the input will be ignored 
      until it has gone inactive for at least this same amount of time. Set this 
      value to zero to disable this function. 
      ShftInt_Kspkret This is the spark retard gain value during active shift 
      interrupt in 'switch-type' mode. It is applied beyond any specified rpm 
      deadzone relative to the shift interrupt idle target, and is limited by 
      the maximum shift interrupt retard value. 
      ShftInt_revlim This is the fuel rev limit value during active shift 
      interrupt in 'switch-type' mode. It should in general be greater than or 
      equal to the idle target value. 
      ShftInt_revlim_drpm This is the proportional fuel rev limit band during 
      active shift interrupt in 'switch-type' mode. Between the 'fuel rev limit' 
      value and 'fuel rev limit' + 'delta-rpm' all cylinders will begin being 
      cut proportionally until they are all eliminated. Set this value to zero 
      to an instantaneous fuel cut at the 'fuel rev limit' value. 
      ShftInt_state Shift Interrupt State 
      SHIFT_active_wt Shift mechanical engagement delay timer. Set to nonzero 
      values when shift is requested. It beings decrementing when the shift 
      feedback voltage indicates gear engagement 
      SHIFT_ctl_cmd Marine shift control command 
      SHIFT_ctl_fault Marine shift control fault indicator 
      SHIFT_ctl_max Marine shift control maximum percentage 
      SHIFT_ctl_min Marine shift control minimum percentage 
      SHIFT_dt_LP Post interpolation low-pass filter constant for shift feedback 
      derivation calculation in fraction/ms. 
      SHIFT_dt_n Shift feedback derivative calculation linear least-squares 
      window. More points yields a quieter and more accurate derivative, but 
      introduces more time lag. Fewer points has the opposite effect. 
      SHIFT_ena Enables/disables ECM-based marine transmission shift control 
      using the dedicated SHIFT H-bridge for FNR solenoid or FNR stern drive 
      actuator options. The FNR solenoid option uses the SHIFT H-bridge as 2 
      high-side half-bridges with the '+' output for the forward solenoid and 
      the '-' output for the reverse solenoid.

      The desired gear setting should be sent via the ECI proprietary packet PGN 
      61189/61190 or from a VP EVC system for any of the options, or from a 
      marine throttle & gear handle for the FNR solenoid option only. 
      SHIFT_engage_delay Once the shift actuator feedback indicates that the 
      desired gear position has been achieved, this parameter indicates the 
      amount of time needed for the mechanical drive to fully engage. After 
      receiving a shift indication, the ECM will wait this amount of time before 
      re-engaging the throttle and any other actions taken during the shift 
      sequence.

      NOTE: The maximum engine speed and mechanical engagement delay values are 
      used anytime an ECI hand controller is present, even if shift actuator 
      control is disabled. This is for compatibility with systems that use the 
      ECI hand controller to control the shift solenoids. In this scenario, the 
      hand control packet gives the ECM a desired gear. The ECM will zero the 
      foot pedal command, and when the engine speed is below the max engine 
      shift speed, a countdown timer will begin to allow for the mechanical 
      engagement of the drive. The shift is assumed complete when the mechanical 
      delay timer expires, and actual gear = desired gear at this time (actual 
      gear is translated back to the ECI hand controller via an ETC2 message). 
      SHIFT_FB_OOR Marine shift feedback absent or out-of-range diagnostic: 
      shift position feedback upper limit threshold 
      SHIFT_FB_OORlo Marine shift feedback absent or out-of-range diagnostic: 
      shift position feedback lower limit threshold 
      SHIFT_FB_raw Marine shift feedback raw volts 
      SHIFT_fwd_delta Marine shift gear engage window - forward 
      SHIFT_fwd_raw Marine shift gear target voltage - forward 
      SHIFT_Ihard_lim Enter the maximum supported current draw on the ECM for 
      shift actuator support. The actuator nominal resistance and back-emf gain 
      are used to actively limit the current draw and avoid overcurrent and 
      over-temperature situations. This value should be large enough to shift 
      under all battery voltages and operating temperatures, yet low enough to 
      avoid engaging the on-board hardware overcurrent protection circuitry, 
      which currently engages at 20A. 
      SHIFT_intcirc_fail Shift actuator or drive circuit failure: The internal 
      circuitry protection will engage at >= 20A in an 
      overcurrent/short-to-ground situation and shut down the actuator drive 
      circuit for 100ms. This calibratable parameter specifies how many times 
      this sequence can occur within 1 key cycle before this fault will begin to 
      latch. 
      SHIFT_int_acc Marine shift shift integral accumulator 
      SHIFT_int_dt_frz The feedback error accumulator freeze rate. This value 
      should be relatively low for slow actuators to avoid large overshoots at 
      the endpoints of the control. Increase this value for faster convergence 
      to the desired setpoint, and decrease this value to help eliminate 
      overshoot at the forward/reverse endpoints of the actuator movement. 
      SHIFT_int_max The maximum integrator value. Note the negated value is used 
      for movements in the opposite direction. Smaller values prevent overshoot, 
      larger values yield faster response and better tracking. 
      SHIFT_Ipark_att Marine shift parking current attenuation 
      SHIFT_Ipark_dly Enter the delay before the parking current control will 
      engage. Allow ample time for shifts to complete under normal operating 
      conditions. 
      SHIFT_Ipark_ena Enables park current limiting control. During fault or 
      failure-to-achieve desired gear situations, the parking current control 
      reduces the actuator loading by limiting the PWM DC%. This feature should 
      not engage during normal operation and can be safely enabled to handle 
      fault situations. 
      SHIFT_Ipark_Ki Enter the current ramp rate to use for transitions into and 
      out of park current limiting control. 
      SHIFT_Ipark_lim Enter the maximum current limit for a prolonged 
      failure-to-achieve desired gear or stalled motor situation. This value 
      should be high enough to engage the drive under almost all normal 
      situations. It should also be low enough to limit actuator damage during 
      stalled motor situations. 
      SHIFT_Ipark_max_att Park current control limits the maximum PWM DC% sent 
      to the shift actuator. Enter the maximum allowed DC% reduction. If the DC% 
      reduction required to maintain the parking current exceeds this value, the 
      DC% will be increased (or decreased) to this value. When this happens, the 
      parking current may exceed the desired limit. 
      SHIFT_I_est Marine shift estimated current 
      SHIFT_I_est_abs Marine shift absolute estimated current 
      SHIFT_I_FB_raw Marine shift feedback current raw volts 
      SHIFT_I_meas Marine shift measured current 
      SHIFT_Ki PID Ki gain for the shift actuator feedback error, translating a 
      raw A/D feedback error accumulation into a % duty-cycle. 
      SHIFT_Kp PID Kp gain for the shift actuator feedback error, translating a 
      raw A/D feedback error into a % duty-cycle. 
      SHIFT_K_emf This constant is used along with velocity to estimate the 
      back-emf and actuator current. The estimated actuator current is used to 
      limit the commanded duty-cycle and avoid the internal hardware overcurrent 
      limits. 
      SHIFT_LoadLim_pct During active torque cut, this is the actual 
      instantaneous throttle based load limit value. 
      SHIFT_neut_delta Marine shift gear engage window - neutral 
      SHIFT_neut_raw Marine shift gear target voltage - neutral 
      SHIFT_Nlock_btn byte reflecting the status of the neutral interlock 
      transmission from an ECI hand controller (00=off/error/NA, 01=on) 
      SHIFT_open_fail Shift actuator or drive circuit failure diagnostic: 
      estimated-measured current upper limit entry condition 
      SHIFT_retard During active torque cut, this is the actual instantaneous 
      spark retard value. 
      SHIFT_rev_delta Marine shift gear engage window - reverse 
      SHIFT_rev_raw Marine shift gear target voltage - reverse 
      SHIFT_R_ohms Estimate of the nominal resistance of the motor or solenoid. 
      Note this should be measured under a stall condition. 
      SHIFT_short_fail Shift actuator or drive circuit failure diagnostic: 
      measured-estimated current upper limit entry condition 
      SHIFT_target_dead Marine shift gear feedback target deadband - Enter the 
      target raw voltage deadband for the desired gear engagement. 
      SHIFT_Vcomp_max This is the maximum voltage for the voltage compensation 
      correction. Voltages >= this voltage will not result in a further 
      reduction in the shift actuator control drive beyond min/max. Set max=min 
      to eliminate voltage compensation. 
      SHIFT_Vcomp_min This is the standard/minimum voltage for the voltage 
      compensation correction. Voltages <= this voltage will not result in a 
      change in the shift actuator drive. 
      shutoff_chk fuel/spark shutoff command from master ECM 
      SH_airEGR_mix Air and EGR mixture specific humidity. 
      SH_def Specific Humidity 
      SH_phi_ena Enable/disable lean phi humidity correction for misfire 
      prevention. 
      SH_phi_xmul Phi humidity offset at 0.65 phi 
      SH_UEGO_ena Enable/disable UEGO phi correction based on specific humidity 
      measurement. 
      SH_UEGO_nom Nominal (zero correction) specific humidity for UEGO sensor 
      output correction. 
      simulation_key Engine simulation mode key 
      sim_engine_mode Engine simulation mode 
      sim_entry_cond_valid Specifies the valid/invalid state of entry conditions 
      for simulated faults 
      sim_fault_calls Enables simulation of calls to fault_update and allows 
      disabling of calls from normal code base 
      sim_fault_context Specifies the loop from which to simulate calls to 
      fault_update 
      sim_fault_latch Fault simulation action 
      sim_fault_mode Fault simulation mode 
      sim_fault_ndx Fault Simulation - simulated fault index 
      sim_fault_prohibit Non-simulation indexes 
      sim_fsys_action Fault system level simulation actions 
      sim_fsys_adjust Fault simulation adjustment in +/- hours. Applies to fault 
      system simulation "Adj" actions. 
      sim_fsys_set Fault simulation updated parameter value. Applies to fault 
      system simulation "Set" actions. 
      sim_fsys_state Fault system level simulation state 
      SIS_FF_load This % load value will be added to the current min governor 
      load command whenever the actual/desired gear match and are other than 
      neutral. This feature only works for network system enabled actual/desired 
      shift interrupt mode. 
      SIS_idle This is the idle target for the air valve control (DBW or IAC) 
      during active shift interrupt. 
      SIS_Kspkret Shift interrupt spark retard gain 
      SIS_revlim This is the fuel rev limit value during activeshift interrupt. 
      It should in general be greater than or equal to the idle target value. 
      SIS_revlim_drpm This is the proportional fuel rev limit band. Between the 
      'fuel rev limit' value and 'fuel rev limit' + 'deltarpm' all cylinders 
      will begin being cut proportionally until they are all eliminated. Set 
      this value to zero to an instantaneous fuel cut at the 'fuel rev limit' 
      value. 
      SIS_spkret_dz This is the rpm delta deadzone above the shift interrupt 
      idle target rpm for initiating spark retard. It is a positive number. 
      SIS_spkret_max This is the maximum spark retard contribution that the 
      shift interrupt spark governor will be allowed to make. It is a positive 
      number representing spark retard. However, the final modifier will be 
      limited to the system wide minimum spark advance (usually -10 CAD BTDC). 
      SIS_spk_mod Shift Interrupt spark governor modification 
      SI_INJ_channels Injector (SI) hardware channels 
      slnk_invalid_fsh_adr Records the approximate address of the instruction 
      that caused the most recent invalid flash access exception from within 
      Simulink user code. 
      slnk_invalid_fsh_cnt Records the number of invalid flash accesses from 
      within Simulink user code. 
      slnk_invalid_RAM_adr Records the approximate address of the instruction 
      that caused the most recent invalid RAM access exception from within 
      Simulink user code. 
      slnk_invalid_RAM_cnt Records the number of invalid RAM accesses from 
      within Simulink user code. 
      slnk_invalid_reg_adr Records the approximate address of the instruction 
      that caused the most recent invalid register access exception from within 
      Simulink user code. 
      slnk_invalid_reg_cnt Records the number of invalid register accesses from 
      within Simulink user code. 
      slnk_nvm_reprog_clr If enabled the Simulink data stored in non-volatile 
      memory will be cleared after a reprogramming event. 
      slnk_nvm_wr_period If enabled any unwritten updates to the Simulink data 
      stored in non-volatile memory will be written out periodically. A value of 
      0 will disable this feature.

      !!!WARNING!!! This is a highly sensitive setting. Miscalibration may lead 
      to EEPROM failure. Care should be taken when using smaller periods as this 
      could lead to decreased life expectancy of EEPROM storage. 
      SLOCK_hw_config SLOCK hardware config 
      slowPWMin_DC The currently measured dutycycle of the slow PWM input 
      waveform. 
      slowPWMin_ena This switch selects which analog channel will be used (if 
      any) for measuring a low-bandwidth PWM signal period and duty-cycle. This 
      signal has a typical discretization of between 1ms and 2ms depending on 
      the primary/secondary analog input characteristics of the chosen channel 
      on the particular ECM. 
      slowPWMin_period The currently measured period of the slow PWM input 
      waveform. 
      slowPWMin_per_edge This switch determines how the incoming PWM waveform is 
      computed. For example, if rising edges are stable in time and falling 
      edges move to generate different duty-cycles, then select 
      'Rising-To-Rising Edge'. If only a frequency measurement is required, 
      select the edge with the sharpest transition (if one edge is sharper than 
      the other). 
      slowPWMin_tout This is the maximum time that will be allowed on the input 
      in a constant high or low state before invalidating the signal as lost or 
      disconnected. 
      slowPWMin_valid Logical indicating the PWM waveform is active and meets 
      period AND duty cycle specs (used for validate the roadspeed input) 
      SMK_lmt_persist_min This is the amount of time the smoke limiting active 
      LED will be lit in the PC display once smoke limiting is triggered. 
      SMK_mode Smoke control mode 
      SoftStartPchan # of PWM cycles to delay turning on Pchan FET on tank 
      charge after spark using 25kHz PWM 
      SoftStartPWM # of PWM cycles to enforce Soft Start PWM Max DC while 
      PWM'ing the low side FET on tank charge after spark 
      SoftStartPWMmaxDC Soft Start PWM Max DC enforced for Soft Start PWM count 
      cycles while PWM'ing the low side FET on tank charge after spark 
      SparkKV Spark KV - Firing Order 
      SparkKVMF Misfire spark KV 
      SparkKVMFD1 Delta KV between normal fire and misfire spark 
      SparkKVMFD2 Delta KV between late fire and misfire spark 
      SparkKVMFD3 Delta KV between skip fire and late fire misfire spark 
      SparkKVRF Refire spark KV 
      SparkKV_BO Spark KV low-pass filtered - Block Order 
      SparkKV_deltaHi Threshold for Avg KV High comparison 
      SparkKV_deltaLo Threshold for Avg KV Low comparison 
      SparkKV_filt Spark KV low-pass filtered - Firing Order 
      SparkKV_filt_avg Spark KV low-pass filtered average 
      spark_hardware_inuse Spark hardware in-use 
      spark_shutoff_chk Coil and Injector Diagnostics: logical 0/1 representing 
      the spark shutoff status 
      spark_type Spark system type (coils, distributor, wasted spark) 
      spk10_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 10 
      spk11_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 11 
      spk12_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 12 
      spk1_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 1 
      spk2_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 2 
      spk3_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 3 
      spk4_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 4 
      spk5_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 5 
      spk6_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 6 
      spk7_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 7 
      spk8_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 8 
      spk9_info_hw Spark Hardware Channel - 9 
      SpkDelayCal This is a signed offset used to tweak the secondary feedback 
      timing measurement for known cct/coil offsets 
      SPKD_crank_enabled Spark coil diagnostics - diagnose faults while cranking 
      enable switch 
      SPKD_dwabs_hi Primary Coil Shorted diagnostic - total dwell upper limit 
      threshold 
      SPKD_dwabs_lo Primary Loop Open or Low-Side Short to Ground diagnostic - 
      total dwell upper limit threshold 
      SPKD_dwmaxv_hi Common spark coil diagnostic conditions: Battery voltage 
      upper limit entry condition 
      SPKD_dwminv_lo Common spark coil diagnostic conditions: Battery voltage 
      lower limit entry condition 
      SPKD_dw_hi Primary Coil Shorted diagnostic - dwell adjustment upper limit 
      threshold 
      SPKD_dw_lo Primary Loop Open or Low-Side Short to Ground diagnostic - 
      dwell adjustment upper limit threshold 
      SPKD_extmod_Vmin Common spark coil diagnostic conditions: External spark 
      module voltage lower limit entry condition 
      SPKD_open_loA Primary Loop Open or Low-Side Short to Ground diagnostic - 
      final current lower limit threshold 
      SPKD_short_hiA Primary Loop Open or Low-Side Short to Ground diagnostic - 
      crank dwell lower limit threshold 
      SPKD_short_trig Fault condition 
      spkgv_mod Spark governor advance modifier in CAD 
      SPKI_samp_raw spark current or diagnostic module feedback value 
      spkmon_min_dissipate Enter the required coil dissipation time between 2 
      consecutive current samples on a shared current sense line (see the 
      current monitoring selections to the right). A value of 0 disables this 
      additional wait time and only requires consecutive spark events not 
      overlap. 
      spko_cyl_dzfilt If enabled, the spark advance dead-zone and dead-zone tau 
      are used to slew in changes in cylinder-specific spark timing. See the 
      'Spark advance dead-zone' comments above for more details. 
      spko_cyl_mode Select the cylinder-specific spark advance offset mode. 
      spkret_decay_time This value is used to calculate the decay rate for the 
      spark retard modifier determined by the 'MAP-based Spark Retard' table. If 
      'Engine start spark retard' is set to "Enabled", the spark retard modifier 
      will be decayed back to 0 when the ECT-based hold time expires after 
      engine start. If 'FSO spark retard mode' is set to "Table Based", the 
      spark retard modifier applied after an FSO ON->OFF transition (fuel has 
      been turned back on) will be decayed back to 0 when the FSO time-based 
      hold time expires. 
      spkret_EGT Specifies the EGT temperature that must be exceeded before the 
      applied spark retard modifier is decayed back to 0 at engine start. This 
      parameter only applies when the ‘Engine start spark retard’ parameter is 
      set to “Enabled – ECT and EGT”. 
      spkret_hold_mult If the EGT sensor is not present or in a faulted state 
      when the ‘Engine start spark retard’ parameter is set to “Enabled – ECT 
      and EGT”, the ‘EGT spark retard decay threshold’ parameter is ignored and 
      only the ECT->Hold Time table is used to determine the spark retard 
      modifier hold duration at engine start. This multiplier is applied to the 
      table-based hold duration. Enter a value between 0 and 1. 
      spkret_hold_tmr The amount of time in seconds remaining for the active 
      engine start/fuel shutoff spark retard modifier, as shown in the 
      'Start/FSO Retard' parameter. 
      spk_adv Total final spark advance in CAD BTDC 
      spk_adv_altOCT The currently extracted base spark advance for highoctane 
      fuel from the selected highoctane table. 
      spk_adv_base Base spark advance 
      spk_adv_crk Crank spark timing value 
      spk_adv_dz "Spark advance dead-zone": This parameter specifies a 
      cubic-rolloff deadzone for instantaneous changes in spark timing. Changes 
      in spark timing >= this value are instantaneously implemented. Changes in 
      spark timing < this value are slewed-in over the low-pass time constant, 
      spk_adv_dz_tau. 
      spk_adv_dz_tau Spark advance dead zone time constant 
      spk_adv_OCTcomp The current octane compensated base spark advance for the 
      engine using linear interpolation between the lowoctane base spark advance 
      for the current fuel and the highoctane base spark advance from the 
      selected alternate table. The current octane rating determines the 
      weighting between these two values. 
      SPK_channels Spark hardware channels 
      SPK_coil_fail_hiV External Spark Module Coil Failure diagnostic: spark 
      module diagnostic feedback lower limit voltage 
      SPK_coil_fail_loV External Spark Module Coil Failure diagnostic: spark 
      module diagnostic feedback upper limit voltage 
      SPK_coil_fail_wt External Spark Module Coil Failure diagnostic: Engine run 
      time entry condition 
      SPK_hardware_config Spark hardware configuration 
      SPK_IGBT_T Spark coil IGBT junction temperature 
      SPK_IGBT_T_raw Spark coil IGBT thermistor raw volts 
      SPK_IGBT_T_Timer Countdown timer for spark kill of an individual spark 
      coil when a coil or spark failure is detected. Valid values are:

      0 - No spark shutdown.

      1..254 - Num secs to shutdown spark. Fault unlatch timer starts after 
      spark kill timer reaches 0 and spark kill has been stopped.

      255 - Shutdown spark for key cycle. 
      SPK_int_fail_hiV External Spark Module Failure diagnostic: spark module 
      diagnostic feedback lower limit voltage 
      SPK_int_fail_loV External Spark Module Failure diagnostic: spark module 
      diagnostic feedback upper limit voltage 
      SPK_int_fail_wt External Spark Module Failure diagnostic: Engine run time 
      entry condition 
      spk_kill Spark kill command 
      spk_kill_CBT This is the maximum catalyst bed temperature allowed during a 
      spark kill test. Setting this value to zero permits any catalyst bed 
      temperature. 
      spk_kill_cyl This value displays the cylinder currently selected for spark 
      kill. 
      spk_kill_MAP This is the maximum manifold pressure allowed during a spark 
      kill test. Setting this value to zero permits any manifold pressure. 
      spk_kill_mfmode Enable/disable misfire detection spark during spark kill 
      spk_kill_mode This switch selects the spark kill mode. In single 
      continuous mode, the selected cylinder will misfire each cycle. In paired 
      continuous mode, the selected cylinder and the cylinder on the same 
      mechanical rotation segment but on the opposing revolution will misfire. 
      In evenly spaced random cylinder mode, spark kill will engage on on evenly 
      spaced spark events. In this mode, the initial spark kill is determined by 
      the 'Spark Kill Command' selection, while the 'Spark Kill Pct' variable 
      determines the spacing. 
      spk_kill_pct This value is only used when the spark kill mode is set to 
      evenly spaced cylinder. It determines how often a spark kill event is 
      induced. The percentage is calculated as the number of misfires vs. total 
      number of cylinder events. 
      spk_kill_rpm This is the maximum engine speed allowed during a spark kill 
      test. Setting this value to zero permits any engine speed. 
      spk_kill_tout This is the maximum continuous amount of time that a single 
      spark coil can remain killed during a spark kill test. After the timeout, 
      this test will be reset to off. Setting this value to greater than 60.0 
      seconds (i.e. 61.0 seconds) effectively disables this timeout. 
      spk_max_ECT ECT/CHT spark max limit in CAD BTDC 
      spk_max_global Global ignition advance max - Absolute maximum limit 
      applied to final spark advance command. 
      spk_min_dissipate Minimum spark dissipation time (ms) - min wait time for 
      proper coil energy dissipation (used for distributor systems since there 
      are typically only one coil in the system) 
      spk_min_global Global ignition advance min - Absolute minimum limit 
      applied to final spark advance command. 
      spk_off_BP BP spark offset in CAD 
      spk_off_ECT CHT spark advance offset 
      spk_off_ECTvL CHT-MAP spark advance offset 
      spk_off_global Exit value: Global spark offset in CAD 
      spk_off_MATvL MAT-MAP spark advance offset 
      spk_ofst_maxadv Maximum allowed advance of any manual spark offset value 
      used during engineering development. Examples include the global advance 
      offset and the individual cylinder advance offset values. 
      spk_ret_CWT CWT spark retard in CAD 
      spk_rpmlo_crank_ena Controls the 'Spark low-rpm crank limit' feature (see 
      below) for different fuel types.

      Disabled - Disables 'Spark low-rpm crank limit' feature for all fuel 
types.
      This has the same effect as setting 'Spark low-rpm crank limit' = 0.
      Gasoline Only - Enables the 'Spark low-rpm crank limit' value for gasoline 
      only.
      LP Only - Enables the 'Spark low-rpm crank limit' value for LP fuel type 
      only.
      NG Only - Enables the 'Spark low-rpm crank limit' value for NG fuel type 
      only.
      Gaseous Only - Enables the 'Spark low-rpm crank limit' value for gaseous 
      fuel types (LP + NG) only.
      Always enabled - Enables the 'Spark low-rpm crank limit' value for all 
      fuel types. 
      spk_rpmlo_crank_lmt Disables spark at engine speeds below this limit 
      during an aborted/failed crank attempt. Set this parameter to zero to 
      disable this feature. On port-injected engines, the fuel is simultaneously 
      disabled. On gaseous EPR-based applications, fuel delivery continues to 
      avoid potential lean-backfire situations on spin down.

      NOTE: If the cranking rpm 'Crank_rpm' is set below this rpm, it will cause 
      no-start cranking events in some configurations. 
      spk_rpmlo_stall_lmt Disables spark at engine speeds below this limit 
      during an engine stall situation. Set this parameter to zero to disable 
      this feature. On port-injected engines, the fuel is simultaneously 
      disabled. On gaseous EPR-based applications, fuel delivery continues to 
      avoid potential lean-backfire situations on spin down. 
      SPL_BM Parameter is the current average fuel correction for fast 
      single-point fuel learning. Fuel correction is sampled every 50ms and 
      filtered with a tau equal to one-seventh the value of the "Single-point 
      evaluation time". 
      SPL_BM_saved The previously saved average fuel correction for fast 
      single-point fuel learning. Fuel correction is from a previous engine 
      cycle that completed sampling in accordance with the "Single-point 
      evaluation time". 
      SPL_eval_tmr Parameter is the current evaluation timer value for fast 
      single-point fuel learning. 
      SPL_mon_state Parameter displays the current state for fast single-point 
      fuel learning.
      0 = 'Disabled' - feature disabled or active fuel type is not NG
      1 = 'Engine off' - engine not running
      2 = 'Waiting for warm up' - engine warming up
      3 = 'Waiting for stabilization' - waiting for operating conditions to 
      stabilize within SPL window
      4 = 'Sampling in progress' - stabilized, sampling and averaging fuel 
      correction
      5 = 'Sampling complete' - sampling complete, waiting for engine to shut 
      down before modifying NG AL table
      6 = 'Update in progress' - sampling complete, slewing to new NG AL table 
      while engine is running
      7 = 'Update complete' - NG AL table update is complete (update occurred 
      while engine was running) 
      SPL_NG_BM_delta Parameter specifies the change in fuel correction required 
      to trigger a single-point learn when "Single-point learn" is set to 
      'Enabled - Delta Fuel Correction'. The fuel correction only includes 
      adaptive and closed-loop block multipliers. If sampling completes in 
      accordance with the "Single-point evaluation time", then the sampled 
      average fuel correction will be evaluated in accordance with the 
      "Single-point learn update method". The average fuel correction is 
      compared against the stored average fuel correction from a previous engine 
      cycle. A fast single-point learn will occur when the following criteria 
      are satisfied:
      1). A copy of the adaptive learn table was saved on a previous engine 
      cycle.
      2). The absolute delta between the current fuel correction and previous 
      fuel correction is greater than this parameter.
      If criteria are met, then the adaptive learn table is overwritten with the 
      previously saved table and the difference between the current fuel 
      correction and previous fuel correction is added to every entry in the 
      adaptive learn table. 
      SPL_NG_BM_high Parameter specifies the threshold for an abnormally high 
      fuel correction and is only applicable when "Single-point learn" is set to 
      'Enabled - Absolute, Unidirectional' or 'Enabled - Absolute, 
      Bidirectional'. The fuel correction only includes adaptive and closed-loop 
      block multipliers. If sampling completes in accordance with the 
      "Single-point evaluation time", then the sampled average fuel correction 
      will be evaluated in accordance with the "Single-point learn update 
      method". If the average fuel correction is greater than this parameter, 
      then the fuel correction is considered abnormally high.

      A fast learn will occur when the following criteria are satisfied:
      1). Fuel correction is deemed abnormally high
      2). Fuel correction was previously deemed nominal
      3). A copy of the nominal adaptive learn table was previously saved
      If criteria are met, then the adaptive learn table is overwritten with the 
      nominal copy and the difference between the abnormally high fuel 
      correction and nominal fuel correction is added to every entry in the 
      adaptive learn table. 
      SPL_NG_BM_nominal Parameter specifies the threshold for a nominal fuel 
      correction and is only applicable when "Single-point learn" is set to 
      'Enabled - Absolute, Unidirectional' or 'Enabled - Absolute, 
      Bidirectional'. The fuel correction only includes adaptive and closed-loop 
      block multipliers. If sampling completes in accordance with the 
      "Single-point evaluation time", then the sampled average fuel correction 
      will be evaluated in accordance with the "Single-point learn update 
      method". If the average fuel correction is less than this parameter, then 
      the fuel correction is considered nominal.

      If the previous engine cycle and current engine cycle had nominal fuel 
      correction, then a copy of the adaptive learn table is stored for future 
      use. The copy of the table is only a copy and is not actively used or 
      updated while the engine is running. The copy is only updated at the end 
      of an engine cycle if the previously stated criteria are true.

      A fast learn will occur when the following criteria are satisfied:
      1). Fuel correction is deemed nominal
      2). Fuel correction was previously deemed abnormally high
      3). A copy of the nominal adaptive learn table was previously saved
      If criteria are met after engine shuts down, then the adaptive learn table 
      is overwritten with the nominal copy. If "Single-point learn" is set to 
      'Enabled - Absolute, Unidirectional', then no offset is added to the 
      nominal copy. If "Single-point learn" is set to 'Enabled - Absolute, 
      Bidirectional', then the difference between the measured fuel correction 
      and previously saved nominal fuel correction is added to every entry in 
      the adaptive learn table. 
      SPL_NG_ECT_min Parameter specifies the minimum engine coolant temperature 
      before single-point fuel learning can initiate. Only applicable when 
      "Single-point learn" is enabled. 
      SPL_NG_ena Parameter configures fast single-point NG fuel learning. If the 
      active fuel is not NG, then feature is disabled. When parameter is 
      enabled, fuel correction is sampled and averaged when the engine is 
      operating in a specified speed/MAP-load window and adaptive updates are 
      active. The averaged fuel correction only includes adaptive and 
      closed-loop block multipliers.

      When set to 'Enabled - Delta Fuel Correction': The average fuel correction 
      is compared against the stored average fuel correction from a previous 
      engine cycle. A copy of the adaptive learn table is always saved for 
      future use after sampling is complete.

      In 'Delta' mode, a fast single-point learn will occur when the following 
      criteria are satisfied:
      1). A copy of the adaptive learn table was saved on a previous engine 
cycle
      2). The absolute delta between the current fuel correction and previous 
      fuel correction is greater than the "Single-point fuel correction delta"
      If criteria are met, then the adaptive learn table is overwritten with the 
      previously saved table and the difference between the current fuel 
      correction and previous fuel correction is added to every entry in the 
      adaptive learn table.

      When set to 'Enabled - Absolute, Unidirectional' or 'Enabled - Absolute, 
      Bidirectional': The averaged fuel correction is compared against 
      nominal/high thresholds. If the previous engine cycle and current engine 
      cycle had nominal fuel correction, then a copy of the adaptive learn table 
      is stored for future use. 

      In 'Absolute' mode, a fast single-point learn will occur when the 
      following criteria are satisfied:
      1). Fuel correction is deemed abnormally high
      2). Fuel correction was previously deemed nominal
      3). A copy of the nominal adaptive learn table was previously saved
      If criteria are met, then the adaptive learn table is overwritten with the 
      nominal copy and the difference between the abnormally high fuel 
      correction and nominal fuel correction is added to every entry in the 
      adaptive learn table.

      A similar fast learn will occur when the following criteria are satisfied:
      1). Fuel correction is deemed nominal
      2). Fuel correction was previously deemed abnormally high
      3). A copy of the nominal adaptive learn table was previously saved
      If criteria are met, then the adaptive learn table is overwritten with the 
      nominal copy. If parameter is set to 'Enabled - Absolute, Unidirectional', 
      then no offset is added to the nominal copy. If parameter is set to 
      'Enabled - Absolute, Bidirectional', then the difference between the 
      measured fuel correction and previously saved nominal fuel correction is 
      added to every entry in the adaptive learn table. 
      SPL_NG_eval_time Parameter specifies the cumulative time that fuel 
      correction is sampled and averaged while within the single-point fuel 
      learning window. Only applicable when "Single-point learn" is enabled. 
      SPL_NG_MAPload_max Parameter specifies the maximum MAP-load for the 
      single-point fuel learning speed/MAP-load window. Only applicable when 
      "Single-point learn" is enabled. 
      SPL_NG_MAPload_min Parameter specifies the minimum MAP-load for the 
      single-point fuel learning speed/MAP-load window. Only applicable when 
      "Single-point learn" is enabled. 
      SPL_NG_rpm_max Parameter specifies the maximum engine speed for the 
      single-point fuel learning speed/MAP-load window. Only applicable when 
      "Single-point learn" is enabled. 
      SPL_NG_rpm_min Parameter specifies the minimum engine speed for the 
      single-point fuel learning speed/MAP-load window. Only applicable when 
      "Single-point learn" is enabled. 
      SPL_NG_run_min Parameter specifies the minimum engine run time before 
      single-point fuel learning can initiate. Only applicable when 
      "Single-point learn" is enabled. 
      SPL_NG_stable_time Parameter specifies the minimum time that the engine 
      must operate within the speed/MAP-load window before single-point fuel 
      learning can sample fuel correction. After engine conditions are 
      stabilized within the window, fuel correction is sampled and averaged for 
      the "Single-point evaluation time". If engine operating conditions fall 
      outside of the speed/MAP-load window, then sampling is halted and engine 
      conditions must stabilize again before sampling can resume. Only 
      applicable when "Single-point learn" is enabled. 
      SPL_NG_update_mode Parameter determines when a single-point fuel learn is 
      executed. When set to 'After engine stops', then a single-point fuel learn 
      will occur after sampling is complete and engine stops. When set to 
      'Immediate', then a single-point fuel learn will occur immediately after 
      sampling is complete. Any adjustments to the adaptive learn table will be 
      slewed using the "Single-point learn update rate". 
      SPL_NG_update_rate Parameter specifies the slew rate for updates to the 
      adaptive learn table during a single-point learn while the engine is 
      running. Parameter is only applicable when "Single-point learn update 
      method" is set to 'Immediate'. Each point in the adaptive table is slewed 
      independently to their desired learned value. If engine stops before 
      slewing is complete, then the adaptive table will immediately be updated 
      with the final table values. 
      SPN_1039_ena Obsoleted parameter 
      SPN_1040_ena Obsoleted parameter 
      SPN_1082_ena Obsoleted parameter 
      SPN_1437_latch_tm Latch time for the SPN 1437 Road Speed Limit Status to 
      change to Active. 
      SPN_1437_mode Selects when SPN 1437 is marked as "Active". 
      SPN_1437_unlatch_tm Unlatch time for the SPN 1437 Road Speed Limit Status 
      to change to Inactive. 
      SPN_3237_ena Obsoleted parameter 
      SPN_3344_ena Parameter determines if SPN 3344 is reported in EC1 as well 
      as if the engine torque curve reports static or dynamic speed/torque 
      points in EC1.
      When set to 'Disabled - Static Points', SPN 3344 is not present and a 
      static (legacy) set of speed/torque curve points is reported.
      When set to 'Enabled - Static Points', SPN 3344 is present and a static 
      (legacy) set of speed/torque curve points is reported.
      When set to 'Enabled - Dynamic Points', SPN 3344 is present and a dynamic 
      set of speed/torque curve points with active derates applied is reported.
      When set to 'Disabled - Dynamic Points', SPN 3344 is not present and a 
      dynamic set of speed/torque curve points with active derates applied is 
      reported.
      When set to 'Disabled - Dynamic, No TSC1', SPN 3344 is not present and a 
      dynamic set of speed/torque curve points with active derates applied is 
      reported. However, active TSC1 speed and torque limits are removed.
      When set to 'Enabled - Dynamic, No TSC1', SPN 3344 is present and a 
      dynamic set of speed/torque curve points with active derates applied is 
      reported. However, active TSC1 speed and torque limits are removed.
      When set to 'Disabled - Dynamic, Improved', SPN 3344 is not present and a 
      dynamic set of speed/torque curve points with active derates applied is 
      reported. The accuracy of torque values is improved by calculating the 
      derate for each point versus using the current derate which is only valid 
      at the current engine speed.
      When set to 'Enabled - Dynamic, Improved', SPN 3344 is present and a 
      dynamic set of speed/torque curve points with active derates applied is 
      reported. The accuracy of torque values is improved by calculating the 
      derate for each point versus using the current derate which is only valid 
      at the current engine speed. 

      NOTE: SPN 3344 always reports a 10ms TSC1 rate. This setting also controls 
      the torque percentages reported for ISO 15031-5 PID 0x64 / ISO 14229 DID 
      0xF464 - "Engine Percent Torque Data".

      For dynamic points, the application of active derates to torque points is 
      configurable through the "J1939 torque / engine load conversion" parameter 
      on the Estimators worksheet. Derates are in units of engine load 
      percentage and need to be converted to a net torque percentage. 
      SPN_69_ena Obsoleted parameter 
      SPN_899_ena Obsoleted parameter 
      SPN_94_ena Obsoleted parameter 
      SPN_976_ena Obsoleted parameter 
      SPOCK_ECM1_LED Indicates receipt/timeout of LESK_ECM1 PGN 
      spock_spk_halt Indicates 4G ECM is requesting spark halt 
      spock_SVN_revision SVN revision of SPOCK measurement synced to 4G ECM 
      spock_sync_ena Enables calibration and measurement sync between SPOCK and 
      4G ECM 
      spock_XLS_revision XLS revision of SPOCK measurement synced to 4G ECM 
      sPWMi_DC_hi An analysis is done on the duty-cycle of the incoming PWM 
      signal. This parameter specifies the highest valid duty-cycle. Set to 100% 
      to accept all duty-cycles. 
      sPWMi_DC_lo An analysis is done on the duty-cycle of the incoming PWM 
      signal. This parameter specifies the lowest valid duty-cycle. Set to 0% to 
      accept all duty-cycles. 
      sPWMi_per_hi An analysis is done on the period (1/frequency) of the 
      incoming PWM signal. This parameter specifies the highest valid period. 
      Set to 2*timeout to accept all non-timed-out periods. 
      sPWMi_per_lo An analysis is done on the period (1/frequency) of the 
      incoming PWM signal. This parameter specifies the lowest valid period. Set 
      to 0 to accept all non-timed-out periods. 
      SRVC_fixed_interval This is the default fixed service interval used when 
      "Service notification mode" is set to "Fixed Interval (hours)". The 
      service interval must be >= 1.0 hours (for this fixed value and for the 
      table entries below). 
      SRVC_fixed_int_km_L1 This is the service interval used for the 'Service 
      Interval Expired - Level 1' diagnostic when "Service notification mode" is 
      set to "Fixed Interval (kms)". The service interval is in increments of 5 
      km and must be >= 5 km. 
      SRVC_fixed_int_km_L2 This is the service interval used for the 'Service 
      Interval Expired - Level 2' diagnostic when "Service notification mode" is 
      set to "Fixed Interval (kms)". The service interval is in increments of 5 
      km and must be greater than or equal to the level 1 service interval. 
      SRVC_km_rem Distance which can be traveled before the 'Service Interval 
      Expired - Level 1' diagnostic becomes active. When the value is negative, 
      the level 1 service interval has passed. 
      SRVC_mode Enables the service notification feature.

      If "Fixed Interval (hours)" is selected, the 'Service Interval Expired - 
      Level 1' fault will set after the number of operating hours specified 
      below.

      If "Speed/Load Based" is selected, the service interval is weighted by the 
      number of hours specified at the current operating condition. For example, 
      spending 5 hours at an operating condition with a 5 hour service interval 
      will result in the service interval remaining dropping from 100% to 90%.

      If "Fixed Interval (kms)" is selected, the 'Service Interval Expired - 
      Level 1' fault and the 'Service Interval Expired - Level 2' fault will set 
      after the respective distances have passed. 
      SRVC_pct_accum Service interval used 
      SRVC_update_key Service update key 
      SRVC_update_status Service update status 
      SSBSI_FdNa_idle Shift-status based shift-int gov idle FdNa 
      SSBSI_FdNa_Kspkret Shift-status based shift-int spark ret gain FdNa 
      SSBSI_FdNa_revlim Shift-status based shift-int rev lim FdNa 
      SSBSI_FdNa_rldrpm Shift-status based shift-int rev lim drpm FdNa 
      SSBSI_FdRa_idle Shift-status based shift-int gov idle FdRa 
      SSBSI_FdRa_Kspkret Shift-status based shift-int spark ret gain FdRa 
      SSBSI_FdRa_revlim Shift-status based shift-int rev lim FdRa 
      SSBSI_FdRa_rldrpm Shift-status based shift-int rev lim drpm FdRa 
      SSBSI_NdFa_idle Shift-status based shift-int gov idle NdFa 
      SSBSI_NdFa_Kspkret Shift-status based shift-int spark ret gain NdFa 
      SSBSI_NdFa_revlim Shift-status based shift-int rev lim NdFa 
      SSBSI_NdFa_rldrpm Shift-status based shift-int rev lim drpm NdFa 
      SSBSI_NdRa_idle Shift-status based shift-int gov idle NdRa 
      SSBSI_NdRa_Kspkret Shift-status based shift-int spark ret gain NdRa 
      SSBSI_NdRa_revlim Shift-status based shift-int rev lim NdRa 
      SSBSI_NdRa_rldrpm Shift-status based shift-int rev lim drpm NdRa 
      SSBSI_RdFa_idle Shift-status based shift-int gov idle RdFa 
      SSBSI_RdFa_Kspkret Shift-status based shift-int spark ret gain RdFa 
      SSBSI_RdFa_revlim Shift-status based shift-int rev lim RdFa 
      SSBSI_RdFa_rldrpm Shift-status based shift-int rev lim drpm RdFa 
      SSBSI_RdNa_idle Shift-status based shift-int gov idle RdNa 
      SSBSI_RdNa_Kspkret Shift-status based shift-int spark ret gain RdNa 
      SSBSI_RdNa_revlim Shift-status based shift-int rev lim RdNa 
      SSBSI_RdNa_rldrpm Shift-status based shift-int rev lim drpm RdNa 
      STARTER_FB_raw starter output low-side voltage diagnostic input 
      start_autocrk_wt Additional debounce time to validate a start signal 
      before starter engagement. Note this is in addition to the normal debounce 
      time used on auxiliary inputs. 
      START_CMD_hiV When "Start signal input" is set to "Standard", this value 
      specifies the START_CMD input high state voltage trigger level. When 
      "Start signal input" is set to any other option, this value is not used. 
      START_CMD_loV When "Start signal input" is set to "Standard", this value 
      specifies the START_CMD input low state voltage trigger level. When "Start 
      signal input" is set to any other option, this value is not used. 
      START_CMD_raw START_CMD input raw voltage 
      START_CMD_volt START_CMD input header voltage 
      start_lock_output This is the low-side output channel used for the 
      starter-lockout/auto-crank starter relay control described above. 
      start_longtooth number of invalid too-large tooth spacing encountered 
      during starting 
      start_lostsync number of sync-loss events during starting 
      START_off_hi_volt Start relay coil open diagnostic: high-side feedback 
      upper limit threshold 
      START_off_loVf Start relay coil open diagnostic: low-side feedback lower 
      limit threshold 
      START_on_hiVf Start relay coil short to power diagnostic: Output feedback 
      upper limit threshold 
      START_on_loVf Start relay control ground short diagnostic: High-side 
      feedback lower limit threshold 
      start_postsync Number of teeth following sync before run speed is achieve 
      start_presync Exit value: Number of teeth counted before sync is attained 
      start_pwr_off Start command power available 
      start_rpm_avg Average start speed 
      start_tmr Start time 
      stop_latch_wait Amount of time the engine must be stopped before the 
      auto-crank feature re-engages. The engine must have been previously 
      latched in the "run" state for this feature to be active. 
      strt_add cold start fuel adder in fraction 
      strt_ECT_lmt The minimum engine coolant temperature required to exit the 
      warm-up phase. If coolant temperature is faulted, then coolant temperature 
      check is bypassed. Only applicable when "Starting initial speed mode" is 
      set to 'ECT Table-Based + Warm Up'. 
      strt_fuel_off Any cranking fuel is attenuated to zero as the engine speed 
      initially accelerates from 'Run Speed' to this speed linearly. Once the 
      engine reaches this speed, all cranking fuel is eliminated. 
      strt_idle_dcy initial starting idle speed (flare) decay rate in rpm/ms 
      strt_idle_hld initial starting idle speed (flare) hold time in [16.0] ms 
      strt_idle_ini initial starting idle speed (flare) in rpm 
      strt_idle_mode This switch determines the mode of operation for the 
      initial starting idle speed parameters.

      The legacy 'Single-Point / Zero-Hold' mode is a single-point initial speed 
      with no hold time and a single-point ramp-rate.

      The 'ECT Table-Based' mode is an ECT-based schedule for the initial speed, 
      hold time, and ramp rate.

      The 'ECT Table-Based + Warm Up' mode is also an ECT-based schedule for the 
      initial speed, hold time, and ramp rate. However, additional warm-up 
      criteria must be satisfied before ramping. The oil temperature must be 
      greater than the "Warm-up phase min oil temp" and engine coolant 
      temperature greater than the "Warm-up phase min ECT". If a warm-up 
      override start request is received, the hold time and warm-up criteria 
      will be bypassed completely. Furthermore, the ramp rate will be multiplied 
      by the "Warm-up override ramp-rate multiplier" to reach the target 
      governor speed faster.

      A warm-up override start request is defined as the reception of ECI PGN 
      42351 with a crank request (bits 3-4 in SPN 65393) and a warm-up override 
      request (bits 7-8 in SPN 65393). 
      strt_idle_state The start initial speed state 
      strt_ign_rpm The "Cranking Ignition Timing" table is used up to this speed 
      on starts. Note that a run-mode transition according to the 'Run RPM' 
      takes precedence over this value for switching to run-mode spark timing. 
      In addition, any "Crank Timing Decay" value looked-up versus CHT will 
      cause a linear decay from the crank timing value toward normal spark 
      timing. 
      strt_inj_mode_I1 For primary injection operation, set this switch to 
      'Single-Point' to utilize the single value injection timing below during 
      crank only (legacy). Set this switch to 'CHT Table Based' to utilize the 
      after-start table injection timing and decay calibration - this 
      table-based value will take full effect during cranking and decay during 
      after-start. 
      strt_inj_mode_I2 For secondary injection operation, set this switch to 
      'Single-Point' to utilize the single value injection timing below during 
      crank only (legacy). Set this switch to 'CHT Table Based' to utilize the 
      after-start table injection timing and decay calibration - this 
      table-based value will take full effect during cranking and decay during 
      after-start. 
      strt_inj_rpm The cranking injection timing value is used up to this speed 
      on starts. 
      strt_inj_tmng Injection timing used during cranking when in primary 
      injection mode until the "Crank injection timing rpm limit" is reached. 
      CAD BBDCI refers to CAD before BDC intake (end of intake). 
      strt_inj_tmng_I2 Injection timing used during cranking when in secondary 
      injection mode until the "Crank injection timing rpm limit" is reached. 
      CAD BBDCI refers to CAD before BDC intake (end of intake). 
      strt_max_FPP Values < 100% limit the maximum throttle position during 
      crank. This value is ignored during fuel clear requests. 
      strt_min_FPP Start minimum FPP 
      strt_min_idle Parameter is only applicable when "Starting initial speed 
      mode" is set to 'Single-Point / Zero-Hold'. 
      strt_min_idle_dcy Parameter is only applicable when "Starting initial 
      speed mode" is set to 'Single-Point / Zero-Hold'. Parameter is only 
      applied when ramping down to a target speed. Ramping up to a higher speed 
      has no slewing. 
      strt_mult cold start fuel multiplier in fraction 
      strt_no_warmup Indicator that a warm-up override start request was 
      received and warm-up phase will be bypassed. 
      strt_no_warmup_mult When a warm-up override start request is received, the 
      calculated ramp rate from the ECT table is multiplied by this parameter to 
      effectively increase the ramp rate. Parameter is only applicable when 
      "Starting initial speed mode" is configured as 'ECT Table-Based + Warm 
      Up'. Value must be greater than or equal to 1.

      A warm-up override start request is defined as the reception of ECI PGN 
      42351 with a crank request (bits 3-4 in SPN 65393) and a warm-up override 
      request (bits 7-8 in SPN 65393). 
      strt_OILT_lmt The minimum oil temperature required to exit the warm-up 
      phase. If oil temperature is disabled or faulted, then oil temperature 
      check is bypassed. Only applicable when "Starting initial speed mode" is 
      set to 'ECT Table-Based + Warm Up'. 
      strt_spkret_ena If enabled, a spark retard modifier is applied at engine 
      start based on the 'MAP-based Spark Retard' table. The spark retard 
      modifier is updated based on changing MAP load values and applied for the 
      duration of time specified by the 'Engine Start Spark Retard Hold' table. 
      Once the hold time expires, the spark retard modifier is decayed back to 0 
      at a rate calculated from the 'Spark retard decay time' parameter. 
      STR_CalBaseName Calibration file base name 
      STR_Calibration_File Calibration file name 
      STR_cal_grp_name1 Calibration Group: Name the groups 
      STR_cal_grp_name2 Calibration Group: Name the groups 
      STR_cal_grp_name3 Calibration Group: Name the groups 
      STR_cal_grp_name4 Calibration Group: Name the groups 
      STR_cal_grp_name5 Calibration Group: Name the groups 
      STR_cal_grp_name6 Calibration Group: Name the groups 
      STR_cal_grp_name7 Calibration Group: Name the groups 
      STR_cal_grp_name8 Calibration Group: Name the groups 
      STR_cal_pwd Calibration Password which may be required during EDIS 
      authentication. 
      STR_cal_pwd_hint Calibration Password Hint retrieved from the ECM by EDIS 
      to select the correct Calibration Password. EDIS displays this value to 
      the user to aid them in entering the correct Calibration Password.

      STR_DID_0xF180 The ISO 14229 (UDS) protocol value transmitted in response 
      to a Service 0x22 ReadDataByIdentifier request for DID 0xF180, 
      BootSoftwareIdentificationDataIdentifier. The size of the response is 13 
      bytes. The first byte is the number of modules, which is 0x01. The 
      remaining 12 bytes are this parameter formatted as a null padded ISO 
      8859-1 ASCII string. 
      STR_DID_0xF196 The ISO 14229 (UDS) protocol value transmitted in response 
      to a Service 0x22 – “ReadDataByIdentifier” request for DID 0xF196 – 
      exhaustRegulationOrTypeApprovalNumberDataIdentifer.

      A null padded ISO 8859-1 ASCII format string of length 10 will be 
      returned.

      ECU/module with the data retrieved from the device.

      InfoType ID 0x0A – “ECUNAME”.

      a Service 0x22 – “ReadDataByIdentifier” request for DID 0xF80A – 
      “ECUNAME”.
