      STR_Update_Comment Update Comment 
      STR_V1gd_comment Volt1 gauge driver calibration comment 
      STR_VECmt VE Table Comment 
      STR_Vehicle Vehicle description(s) 
      STR_WWHOBD_GTR_ver WWHOBD GTR number reported over UDS 
      svn_compile_date SVN compile date 
      svn_compile_date_str SVN compile date string 
      svn_compile_status SVN compile status 
      svn_mixed SVN mixed revisions 
      svn_modified SVN modified 
      svn_remote_compiled SVN remote compiled 
      svn_revision SVN revision 
      SVN_revision_hst Software version history SVN revisions 
      swap_crank_cam If this option is enabled, the crank signal should be wired 
      to the cam1 input pins on the header, and the cam sensor should be wired 
      to the crank input on the header. All calibration values are still applied 
      normally (i.e. setup the crank input calibration for the actual crank 
      sensor, and setup the cam1 calibration for the cam sensor). 
      SWARNblk_off A soft warning may cause a continuous output activation or a 
      blinking/pulsing output. The on/off times specify this behavior. For a 
      continuously on output in an active state, simply set the offtime to zero 
      and the ontime to any value. 
      SWARNblk_on A soft warning may cause a continuous output activation or a 
      blinking/pulsing output. The on/off times specify this behavior. For a 
      continuously on output in an active state, simply set the off time to zero 
      and the on time to any value. 
      SWARNblk_open_off Soft warning open-output transfer Blink/Pulse off-time 
      (ms) 
      SWARNblk_open_on Soft warning open-output transfer Blink/Pulse on-time 
      (ms) 
      SWARNchan_open This switch controls which output pin will be actuated when 
      a soft warning is triggered and the normal soft-warning output is detected 
      to be open. If the MIL, soft, and hard warning channels are set or 
      transferred to the same output, MIL functionality receives the highest 
      priority and soft warning functionality receives the lowest priority. 
      SWARNfcn Soft warning function status (Disconnected, Idle off, MIL, Hard 
      warning, Soft warning, Audible alert) 
      SWARNout_mirror Soft warning output pin 
      SWARN_bulbchk This is the time that the soft warning output will remain on 
      following an initial keyon/engine stopped event to allow the operator to 
      observe that the output (bulb) is functioning. 
      SWARN_bulbon Soft Warning Output Bulp-Check Config - Determines whether 
      the warning output will be continuously on or blinked/pulsed during the 
      key-on bulb check period. 
      SWARN_chan This switch controls which output pin will be actuated when a 
      soft warning is triggered. A selection of 'None' will not control an 
      output pin, but will continue to communicate a soft warning over the 
      various communications links. In particular, the J1939 'Warn' lamp 
      indication will be on during an active soft warning condition. If the soft 
      and hard warning channels are set to the same output, hard warning 
      functionality (blinking or continuous) takes precedence during an active 
      hard warning. 
      SWARN_lamp Output lamp associated with softwarning faults. 
      Sww_CHT 2D interpolation table CHT (X-axis) input values 
      Sww_mult 2D Interpolation Table: Engine Speed Attenuation Factor (input 
      rpm/CHT, output Cww factor) 
      Sww_rpm 2D interpolation table rpm (y-axis) input values 
      sw_debounce General digital input debounce - Time to validate the state of 
      a general digital input such as the fuel select, aux inputs 
      sw_hiTri Digital input high (+V) trigger voltage. These inputs include 
      Gov1/2, AUX_DIG1/2/3 and other tri-state digital inputs. These inputs have 
      a 0-35.16V input range, and are nominally pulled to a 2.54V equivalent 
      value. 
      sw_hiV Generic digital input high state voltage trigger level when input 
      is configured for 0-5V range. 
      sw_loTri Digital input low (grounded) trigger voltage. These inputs 
      include Gov1/2, AUX_DIG1/2/3 and other tri-state digital inputs. These 
      inputs have a 0-35.16V input range, and are nominally pulled to a 2.54V 
      equivalent value. 
      sw_loV Generic digital input low state voltage trigger level when input is 
      configured for 0-5V range. 
      sw_lowbat Battery (supply) voltage below which changes in state of a 
      digital input will be ignored due to unreliable pullup/pulldown voltages. 
      SW_reset_src Indicates the source of the last software reset. 
      sync_allow Required number of teeth before sync process is allowed 
      sync_state Synchronization state of the engine (>0=presync, 0=stopped, 
      -1=crank sync, -2=cam sync) 
      T2MJ_nom_PN 2D Interpolation Table: Given air mass inducted per liter 
      displacement (or MAP load) and engine speed, output is nominal pressure 
      for NG applications 
      T2MJ_nom_PP 2D Interpolation Table: Given air mass inducted per liter 
      displacement (or MAP load) and engine speed, output is nominal pressure 
      for LPG applications 
      T2trim_nom_DCNG 2D Interpolation Table: NG Nominal PWM Valve Setpoint. 
      Used when trim_load_src = MAP 
      T2trim_nom_DCP 2D Interpolation Table: LPG Nominal PWM Valve Setpoint. 
      Used when trim_load_src = MAP. 
      T2trim_nom_maLNG Air mass per volume displacement input values for 2D 
      Nominal Phi tables (NG) 
      T2trim_nom_maLP Air mass per volume displacement input values for 2D 
      Nominal Ph tables (LPG) 
      T2trim_nom_MAPNG MAP input values for 2D Nominal Phi tables (NG) 
      T2trim_nom_MAPP MAP input values for 2D Nominal Ph tables (LPG) 
      T2trim_nom_phiNG 2D Interpolation Table: NG Nominal Phi at nominal 
      carburetor conditions (inputs are rpm and MAP). Used when trim_load_src = 
      MAP 
      T2trim_nom_phiP 2D Interpolation Table: LPG Nominal Phi at nominal 
      carburetor conditions (inputs are rpm and MAP). Used when trim_load_src = 
      MAP 
      T2trim_nom_rpmNG RPM input values for 2D Nominal Phi tables (NG) 
      T2trim_nom_rpmP RPM input values for 2D Nominal Ph tables (LPG) 
      TACH_FB_raw Tachometer raw volts 
      tach_mode Tachometer output mode 
      TACH_off_loVf Tach output ground short diagnostic: Low-side feedback lower 
      limit threshold 
      TACH_on_hiVf Tach output short to power diagnostic: Low-side feedback 
      upper limit threshold 
      tach_override_dis Select whether crank-cam module override is allowed. If 
      allowed, specific crank-cam modules can drive the tach output directly and 
      the user-specified parameters below will be ignored. 
      tach_pprev Tachometer output custom pulse frequency 
      TACH_PWM_DC Tachometer manual duty cycle 
      TACH_PWM_manual Tachometer manual mode enable 
      TACLT_max_Lmin Auxiliary coolant pump characterization, assuming an 
      engine-speed dependent flow rate. 
      TACLT_max_rpm Auxiliary coolant pump characterization, assuming an 
      engine-speed dependent flow rate. 
      TACLT_vlv_EGR_flow EGR cooler coolant flow characterization for the 
      intercooler/EGR cooler split valve. The flow rate is expressed as % of 
      maximum pump flow at the current engine speed. For each valve position, 
      the sum of the intercooler and EGR cooler flow rates can be less than 100% 
      to account for flow restrictions. 
      TACLT_vlv_flow Auxiliary coolant radiator flow characterization for the 
      radiator bypass 3-way valve. The flow rate is expressed as % of available 
      flow at current intercooler/EGR cooler split valve position and specifies 
      the amount of flow through the radiator. 
      TACLT_vlv_int_flow Intercooler coolant flow characterization for the 
      intercooler/EGR cooler split valve. The flow rate is expressed as % of 
      maximum pump flow at the current engine speed. For each valve position, 
      the sum of the intercooler and EGR cooler flow rates can be less than 100% 
      to account for flow restrictions. 
      TACLT_vlv_pos Auxiliary 3-way cooling valve positions. 
      TAMTSA_dec_minnom EGR min/nom fraction target during the decreasing TSC1 
      torque limit at the beginning of an AMT upshift. To disable a specific 
      gear, set the target to 1.00. Only applicable when "AMT shift assist EGR 
      min/nom" is set to 'Enabled'. 
      TAMTSA_dec_TPSd_tau Filter tau for TPS command filtering during the 
      decreasing TSC1 torque limit at the beginning of an AMT upshift. To 
      disable filtering for a specific gear, set corresponding "TPSd Filter Max 
      Time" value to 0ms. Only applicable when "AMT shift assist TPSd filtering" 
      is set to 'Decreasing Only' or 'Both'. 
      TAMTSA_dec_TPSd_tm Maximum duration of TPS command filtering during the 
      decreasing TSC1 torque limit at the beginning of an AMT upshift. To 
      disable filtering for a specific gear, set value to 0ms. Only applicable 
      when "AMT shift assist TPSd filtering" is set to 'Decreasing Only' or 
      'Both'. 
      TAMTSA_inc_TPSd_tau Filter tau for TPS command filtering during the 
      increasing TSC1 torque limit at the end of an AMT upshift. To disable 
      filtering for a specific gear, set corresponding "TPSd Filter Max Time" 
      value to 0ms. Only applicable when "AMT shift assist TPSd filtering" is 
      set to 'Increasing Only' or 'Both'. 
      TAMTSA_inc_TPSd_tm Maximum duration of TPS command filtering during the 
      increasing TSC1 torque limit at the end of an AMT upshift. To disable 
      filtering for a specific gear, set value to 0ms. Only applicable when "AMT 
      shift assist TPSd filtering" is set to 'Increasing Only' or 'Both'. 
      TAMTSA_inc_WGPd Maximum wastegate pressure allowed during the increasing 
      TSC1 torque limit at the end of an AMT upshift. Limit is applied to 
      bst_WGPdi which is the wastegate actuator desired pressure from the TIP 
      control loop. Set value to 256.0 psig to disable limiting for a specific 
      gear. Only applicable when "AMT shift assist WGPd limiting" is set to 
      'Enabled'. 
      TAMTSA_LL_gear AMT shift assistance load limiting table - transmission 
      gear axis 
      TAMTSA_LL_hold AMT shift assistance load limiting table - hold time axis 
      TAMTSA_LL_load AMT shift assistance load limiting table - load limit axis 
      TAMTSA_LL_rpm AMT shift assistance load limiting table - engine speed axis 

      TAMTSA_LL_slew AMT shift assistance load limiting table - slew rate axis 
      TANK1_DIS_raw Tank 1 Disable feedback voltage 
      TANK2_DIS_raw Tank 2 Disable feedback voltage 
      TankMaxDC_12V Max allowable DC for tank PWM at 12V 
      TankMaxDC_28V Max allowable DC for tank PWM at 24V 
      TankMinDC_12V Min allowable DC for tank PWM at 12V 
      TankMinDC_28V Min allowable DC for tank PWM at 24V 
      TankSetpoint This parameter determines the target voltage for closed loop 
      control of TANK_1_V, the CD spark tank voltage. 
      TankSetpointMF This parameter determines the target voltage for closed 
      loop control of TANK_1_V for misfire spark events. 
      TankSetptMF_actual Tank voltage setpoint for misfire spark as adjusted 
      based on Tank min/max V 
      TankSetptMF_limit Misfire detection is disabled if AutoKV setpoint > this 
      value 
      TANK_1_V Tank 1 capacitor voltage 
      TANK_1_VMF Tank 1 voltage just prior to misfire spark 
      TANK_1_VRF Tank 1 voltage just prior to refire spark 
      TANK_1_V_maxv Tank max voltage - fault and AutoKV 
      TANK_1_V_minv Tank min voltage - fault and AutoKV 
      TANK_1_V_raw Tank 1 raw feedback voltage 
      TANK_2_V Tank 2 capacitor voltage 
      TANK_2_VMF Tank 2 voltage just prior to misfire spark 
      TANK_2_VRF Tank 2 voltage just prior to refire spark 
      TANK_2_V_raw Tank 2 raw feedback voltage 
      TANK_ADCnts_Des Tank voltage desired 
      TANK_ADCnts_DesMF Tank voltage desired - misfire spark 
      TANK_ADCnts_final Tank voltage final target 
      TANK_Kp Reports the final computed TANK voltage closed-loop control 
      proportional term 
      TANK_PumpMult_180V This parameter determines the multiplier applied to the 
      proportional gain. The multiplier is based on the primary spark TANK 
      voltage setpoint which may be dynamically modified at runtime via AutoKV. 
      The most recent primary spark TANK voltage setpoint is interpolated 
      between the 180V and 280V multipliers, and this multiplier is then applied 
      to the proportional gain which is selected based on Vbat. 
      TANK_PumpMult_280V This parameter determines the multiplier applied to the 
      proportional gain. The multiplier is based on the primary spark TANK 
      voltage setpoint which may be dynamically modified at runtime via AutoKV. 
      The most recent primary spark TANK voltage setpoint is interpolated 
      between the 180V and 280V multipliers, and this multiplier is then applied 
      to the proportional gain which is selected based on Vbat. 
      TANK_Pump_Kp Not defined 
      TANK_Pump_Kp12V Not defined 
      Tappd_lwrA_mult Multiplier table for Boosted application 
      Tappd_lwrA_rpm 1D Interpolation Table: This table defines a set of 
      RPM-based “Lower approach delta” and “Lower approach slew up rate” values.

      Tappd_lwr_delta When TIP is lower than the desired boost TIP target minus 
      the “Lower approach delta” minus the “Lower approach slew margin” the 
      desired boost TIP target will be temporarily set to the delta point.

      Tappd_lwr_slew When TIP achieves or rises above the lower approach slew 
      margin point the boost TIP desired approach value (bst_TIPdapp) will be 
      slewed to the actual boost TIP desired value (bst_TIPd). This setting 
      defines the rate at which bst_TIPdapp is slewed up to bst_TIPd.

      Tappd_mult_BP Lower Approach Delta Altitude Compensation Table - BP axis 
      in psia. 
      Tappd_mult_pct Lower Approach Delta Altitude Compensation Table - Lower 
      approach multiplier axis in percent. Set to 100% to disable altitude 
      compensation. 
      TASspkgv_att_adv 2D Interpolation Table: Spark governor advance 
      attenuation. Inputs are MAP load (psia) and Speed (rpm); output is Advance 
      Attenuation multiplier. 
      TASspkgv_att_MAP 2D Interpolation Tables: Spark governor advance 
      attenuation and Spark governor retard attenuation. MAP load (psia) input 
      axis values 
      TASspkgv_att_ret 2D Interpolation Table: Spark governor retard 
      attenuation. Inputs are MAP load (psia) and Speed (rpm); output is Retard 
      Attenuation multiplier. 
      TASspkgv_att_rpm 2D Interpolation Tables: Spark governor advance 
      attenuation and Spark governor retard attenuation. Speed (rpm) input axis 
      values

      TAUX_dT1_ndx1 This is the ordinal number of the first Auxiliary 
      Temperature to use in the delta (difference) calculation. 1 = Aux 
      Temperature 1, 2 - Aux Temperature 2, etc. See 'Inputs' tab for Auxiliary 
      Temperatures. 
      TAUX_dT1_ndx2 This is the ordinal number of the second Auxiliary 
      Temperature to use in the delta (difference) calculation. 1 = Aux 
      Temperature 1, 2 - Aux Temperature 2, etc. See 'Inputs' tab for Auxiliary 
      Temperatures. 
      TAUX_dT2_delta Auxiliary Temperature delta-T 2 
      TAUX_dT2_max AUX Temperature delta T 2 high diagnostic: delta-T 1 upper 
      limit threshold 
      TAUX_dT2_min AUX Temperature delta T 2 low diagnostic: delta-T 1 lower 
      limit threshold 
      TAUX_dT2_ndx1 Ordinal number of the first Auxiliary Temperature to use in 
      the dT2 delta (difference) calculation. 1 = Aux Temperature 1, 2 - Aux 
      Temperature 2, etc. 
      TAUX_dT2_ndx2 Ordinal number of the second Auxiliary Temperature to use in 
      the dT2 delta (difference) calculation. 1 = Aux Temperature 1, 2 - Aux 
      Temperature 2, etc. 
      TAUX_LP_tau Auxiliary temperature low-pass filter time constant 
      TBI_fuel_calc This switch is used to define the fueling calculation 
      strategy used for throttle body fuel introduction applications.
      When specific MAP faults are enabled and faulted, the fueling calculation 
      strategy is automatically switched from 'Throttle Model Based' to 
      'Speed-density + dMAP'. Refer to "Fuel mode MAP fault reaction" on the 
      'DiagConfig' worksheet for more details. 
      TBI_tran_DCstrt_max At high injector duty-cycles, the transient fueling 
      compensation will not provide much benefit. This parameter keeps the 
      transient fueling compensation disengaged if the injector duty-cycle is 
      high. 
      TBI_tran_ena Transient throttle-body fueling enable: This feature is 
      intended to provide transient fueling compensation for synchronous 
      throttle-body injection applications. It is primarily used on natural gas 
      injection block systems. 
      TBI_tran_engage_cnt TBI transient fuel engage count 
      TBI_tran_extrap_in Obsoleted parameter 
      TBI_tran_extrap_out Obsoleted parameter 
      TBI_tran_injmin_DC Minimum TBI injector duty cycle 
      TBI_tran_injon_DC Total TBI injector duty cycle 
      TBI_tran_injon_num Total number of throttle body injectors active 
      TBI_tran_inj_minon At low flow rates, the 5ms period used for computing 
      TBI transient fueling will be increased in order to maintain this minimum 
      injector on-time. This injector on-time references the actual injector 
      minimum, and not the average PW before TBI transient fueling engages. 
      TBI_tran_inj_turnoff For transient throttle-body fueling compensation, the 
      injector off time is assumed constant. The injector turn-on time is 
      assumed to be the sum of the injector turn-off time and the calibrated 
      injector offset, since the injector offset is turn-on time - turn off 
      time. Note that for current-controlled injection systems, the turn-off 
      time will actually increase with increasing system while the turn-on time 
      will decrease with increasing system voltage. 
      TBI_tran_MAPdt_off Obsoleted parameter 
      TBI_tran_MAPdt_on Obsoleted parameter 
      TBI_tran_min_MAP Transient throttle-body injection will not engage if MAP 
      is below this limit. If MAP drops below this limit while TBI transient 
      injection is disabled, it will disengage. 
      TBI_tran_min_rpm This prevents engagement during spin-down and avoids 
      issues associated with very long time intervals between injection events. 
      TBI_tran_off_validms Obsoleted parameter 
      TBI_tran_off_validwt Obsoleted parameter 
      TBI_tran_off_wt_ms Once the disengagement conditions have been satisfied, 
      the transient fueling compensation will remain engaged for at least this 
      amount of time. 
      TBI_tran_PWpct_neg If the high-passed fuel PW goes below this value 
      (high-pass = raw value - low-passed value, where the raw-value is 
      pre-filtered), then TBI transient fueling is engaged. 
      TBI_tran_PWpct_off Once engaged, if the high-passed PW goes below this 
      value for the disengagement validation wait period, TBI transient fueling 
      will be disengaged. 
      TBI_tran_PWpct_pos If the high-passed fuel PW exceeds this value 
      (high-pass = raw value - low-passed value, where the raw-value is 
      pre-filtered), then TBI transient fueling is engaged. 
      TBI_tran_PW_dev Pulse-width steady state deviation 
      TBI_tran_PW_HPtau The average pulse-width PW_avg is pre-filtered, and then 
      used in a high-pass filter to determine if TBI transient fueling should be 
      engaged. This value is the high-pass filter time constant. 
      TBI_tran_PW_LPtau The average pulse-width PW_avg is pre-filtered, and then 
      used in a high-pass filter to determine if TBI transient fueling should be 
      engaged. This value is the pre-filter time constant. 
      TBI_tran_PW_prefilt Low-passed fueling pulse-width 
      TBI_tran_runtime_wt This wait period is intended to avoid engagement 
      during startup transient conditions. 
      TBI_tran_state Transient throttle-body status 
      TBI_tran_tcyl_min If the time between cylinder events is less than this 
      value, the throttle-body transient fueling compensation will not engage, 
      and if it is engaged, it will automatically disengage. Note the 
      compensation takes place at 5ms intervals, so attempting to run 
      throttle-body transient injection compensation at small intervals will 
      have a small effect on performance. This time can be set < 5.0 ms, 
      however, since the transient fueling compensation does exit synchronous 
      injection mode and allow simultaneous firing of all injectors (i.e. on a 
      6-cylinder engine with 5ms between cylinder events, it will take 30ms to 
      turn on all injectors during a hard tip-in without transient fueling 
      compensation engaged). 
      TBstTIP_Lo_MAP MAP column values for the "Boost Pressure Control Expected 
      TIP" table. 
      TBstTIP_Lo_TIPd TIP target column values for the "Boost Pressure Control 
      Expected TIP" table. 
      Tbst_FSO_Ptarg TIP target column values for the "TIP Target During FSO 
      Throttle-Open" table. Note that this table is used even while in delta-P 
      target mode. Set the first row TIP target to '0' to disable this feature. 
      Tbst_FSO_Ptarg_brk TIP target when throttle-open FSO is active and either 
      driveline braking or exhaust braking is active. 
      Tbst_FSO_rpm Engine speeds for the "TIP Target During FSO Throttle-Open" 
      table.

      Tbst_MATdr_mult 1D Interpolation Table: Mat Derate Temperature Correction 
      Multiplier 
      Tbst_Ptarg_ldcmd 2D interpolation table load command (%) (X-axis) input

      (percent). Output is TIP target and/or delta-P target 
      Tbst_Ptarg_rpm 2D interpolation table rpm (y-axis) input values 
      Tbst_WGAcmd_FF 2D Interpolation Table. Inputs are rpm and load command 
      (percent). Output is Waste Gate Actuator Feedforward Command percent. 
      Tbst_WGPnl_in 1D Interpolation Table: Non-Linear WGP Target Mapping (This 
      function is used to linearize wastegate response). Wastegate pressure 
      (psig) input values. 
      Tbst_WGPnl_out 1D Interpolation Table: Non-Linear WGP Target Mapping (This 
      function is used to linearize wastegate response). Linearized wastegate 
      pressure (psig) output values. 
      TB_fuelV This is the total volume of pure fuel in the flow path from the 
      throttle-body fuel metering valve orifice (inside the CFV for example) to 
      the throttle-body fuel mixing device ports. 
      TCAC_RS_speed Current vehicle speed for charge air cooler (CAC) 
      calculations 
      TCAC_Vdot_cold Cold air flow rate for charge air cooler (CAC) calculations 

      TCalID_table Target calibration identification table of parameters 
      Tcambmp_auto During an impending cam fault auto-unlocking procedure, this 
      switch enables 'phase 3' of the strategy called the 'bump' procedure. This 
      phase sends a single (usually) high-current long-duration pulse to the cam 
      actuator to attempt to 'unstick' it and return normal operation. If 
      enabled, this phase is initiated at 75% of the fault counter latch time 
      following the phase 1 starting-current pulse and the phase 2 'rattle' 
      pulses. 
      Tcambmp_dur This is the total pulse time for the 'Cam-Bump' maintenance 
      procedure. If this procedure is initiated by a technician, a current pulse 
      of the specified duration and current will be sent to the variable-cam 
      actuator of the engine (if so equipped) in order to attempt to release a 
      'stuck' cam phaser. This test can only be run once per key-cycle and is 
      subject to the rpm limit below. NOTE: To prevent this test from ever 
      running, set the duration to zero. 
      Tcambmp_I This is the current level to be used during the 'Cam-Bump' 
      procedure pulse as described in more detail above. 
      Tcambmp_keyon This switch forces a 'cam-bump' current of 'Tcambmp_I' amps 
      for a duration of 'Tcambmp_dur' ms during a key-on/engine-stopped 
      condition before the engine begins to rotate. If the engine rotates this 
      pulse is immediately terminated. 
      Tcambmp_rpm_max The engine speed must be less than this value in order to 
      run the 'Cam-Bump' procedure described above. 
      TCam_strt_ECT 1D interpolation table ECT input values 
      TCam_strt_tex 1D Interpolation Table: Given ECT as input, provides 
      additional ECT based timeout added to the base timeout to create a total 
      timeout for cam engine starting current. 
      TCATdP_max 1D Interpolation Table: Given Exhaust Flow Rate (liters/sec) as 
      input, provides minimum pressure (P) threshold (psi) for the "Catalyst 
      exhaust P lower than expected" diagnostic fault.

      TCATdP_min 1D Interpolation Table: Given Exhaust Flow Rate (liters/sec) as 
      input, provides maximum pressure (P) threshold (psi) for the "Catalyst 
      exhaust P higher than expected" diagnostic fault.

      TCATdP_vdot 1D Interpolation Table: Exhaust Flow Rate (liters/sec) input 
      axis values. 
      TCDdur_180V CD Spark Duration - 180V 
      TCDdur_230V CD Spark Duration - 230V 
      TCDdur_290V CD Spark Duration - 290V 
      TCDdur_Vbat CD Spark Duration - Vbat 
      TCD_MFexpected Misfire Expected KV 
      TCD_MFexpected_MAP Misfire Expected KV - MAP axis 
      TCD_MFexpected_RPM Misfire Expected KV - RPM axis 
      Tchk2_ECT_add 1D Interpolation Table. Given input of CHTcrank, output is 
      Secondary Choke Fuel Adder (%). When fuel is gaseous (LPG or NG) and 
      after-start enrichment is permitted by "After-start fuel enrichment mode", 
      the table's interpolated value is added only while running. 
      Tchk_ECT_add 1D Interpolation Table. Given input of CHTcrank, Output is 
      Primary Choke Fuel Adder (%). When fuel is gasoline, table's interpolated 
      value is added while cranking and running. When fuel is gaseous (LPG or 
      NG) and after-start enrichment is permitted by "After-start fuel 
      enrichment mode", the table's interpolated value is added only while 
      running (not cranking). 
      Tchk_ECT_decay 1D Interpolation Table. Given input of CHTcrank, Output is 
      Choke Decay Time. Applies to both primary and secondary after-start fuel 
      enrichment calculations. 
      Tchk_ECT_ECT 1D interpolation table CHT/ECT input values 
      Tchk_ECT_hold 1D Interpolation Table. Given input of CHTcrank, Output is 
      Choke Hold Time. Applies to both primary and secondary after-start fuel 
      enrichment calculations. 
      TCHT_CHT 1D Interpolation Table: Cylinder Head Temperature (CHT) 
      calibration table - CHT values used for reverse lookup, given sensor 
      resistance measurement (Ohms) 
      TCHT_ohms 1D Interpolation Table: Cylinder Head Temperature (CHT) 
      calibration table - CHT resistance (Ohms) values, used for reverse lookup 
      to calibrated CHT values.

      TCRI_ontime 2D Interpolation Table - Injector On-Time map. Given Fuel 
      Volume (mm3/stroke) and EITHER Rail Pressure (bar) OR Speed (rpm), returns 
      Injector On-Time (µs). NOTE: Rail Pressure input is used if a rail 
      pressure sensor signal is available. Otherwise, engine RPM is used. 
      TCRI_ontime_mm3 2D Interpolation Table - Injector On-Time map. Fuel Volume 
      (mm3/stroke) input axis values. 
      TCRI_ontime_prail 2D Interpolation Table - Injector On-Time map. Rail 
      Pressure (bar) input axis values. 
      TCRI_pulseoff_alt1 2D Table - Given Fuel Load (mg/cyl) and RPM input, 
      returns Forced Injection Disable (standard) command. 
      TCRI_pulseoff_std 2D Table - Given Fuel Load (mg/cyl) and RPM input, 
      returns Forced Injection Disable (Alternate) command. NOTE: Interpolation 
      is not performed on this table. The "closest" entry is used, and a 
      hysteresis is applied to stabilize the system. 
      TCRI_P_alt1 2D Interpolation Table - Fuel Pressure and Injector 
      Calibrations. Given Fuel Load (mg/cyl) and RPM inputs, returns Alternate 
      Fuel Pressure (bar) 
      TCRI_P_cld 2D Interpolation Table - Pressure Base Offsets. Given Fuel Load 
      (mg/cyl) and RPM inputs, returns Fuel Pressure Base Offset (bar) 
      TCRI_P_std 2D Interpolation Table - Fuel Pressure and Injector 
      Calibrations. Given Fuel Load (mg/cyl) and RPM inputs, returns Standard 
      Fuel Pressure (bar) 
      TCRI_Qload_alt1 2D Interpolation Table: rpm and fuel load input, Fuel Load 
      output (Alt1 table) 
      TCRI_Qload_alt2 2D Interpolation Table: rpm and fuel load input, Fuel Load 
      output (Alt2 table) 
      TCRI_Qload_std 2D Interpolation Table: rpm and fuel load input, Fuel Load 
      output (Standard table) 
      TCRI_Qmain_cld 2D Interpolation Table: Given Fuel Load (mg/cyl) and RPM 
      inputs, returns Main Injection Quantity Base Offset (mg/stroke) 
      TCRI_Qmin 2D Interpolation Table: Given Rail Pressure (bar) and RPM 
      inputs, returns Minimum Injection Quantity (mg/stroke) 
      TCRI_Qmin_xPrail 2D Interpolation Table: Rail Pressure (bar) input axis 
      values 
      TCRI_Qmin_yrpm 2D Interpolation Table: RPM input axis values 
      TCRI_Qpilot1_alt1 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Pilot1 Injection Map

      Quantity - Alternate (mg/stroke) 
      TCRI_Qpilot1_cld 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Pilot1 Cold Start

      TCRI_Qpilot1_std 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Pilot1 Injection Map 
      (Standard). Given Fuel Load (mg/cyl) and RPM input, returns Pilot 1

      TCRI_Qpilot2_alt1 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Pilot2 Injection Map

      TCRI_Qpilot2_std 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Pilot2 Injection Map

      TCRI_Qpost1_alt1 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Post1 Injection Map

      TCRI_Qpost1_std 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Post1 Injection Map 
      (Standard). Given Fuel Load (mg/cyl) and RPM input, returns Post 1

      TCRI_Qpost2_alt1 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Post2 Injection Map

      TCRI_Qpost2_cld 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Post2 Cold Start Injection

      Start Offset (mg/stroke) 
      TCRI_Qpost2_std 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Post2 Injection Map 
      (Standard). Given Fuel Load (mg/cyl) and RPM input, returns Post 2 
      Quantity - Standard (mg/stroke) 
      TCRI_QPT_xair 2D Interpolation Table - Air Mass and Smoke Limiting

      TCRI_QPT_xfpp 2D interpolation table fuel load (X-axis) input values

      TCRI_QPT_yrpm 2D Interpolation Table - Air Mass and Smoke Limiting 
      Calibration: RPM axis input values 
      TCRI_rho_diesel 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Fuel Density Map: Given

      - Alternate1 (CAD BTDCC) 
      TCRI_Tmain_alt2 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Main Injection Timing Map

      - Alternate2 (CAD BTDCC) 
      TCRI_Tmain_cld 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Main Cold Start Timing

      TCRI_Tpilot1_std 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Pilot1 Injection Timing

      Standard (CAD BTDCC) 
      TCrkTT_ECT_decay 1D Interpolation Table: Crank Timing Decay (seconds) for 
      after start liquid fuel enrichment 
      TCSB_ena This switch enable the closed-stop braking function to eliminate 
      high-velocity impacts in the closed position. 
      TCSB_Kd This value is multiplied by the difference between the actual 
      dPS/dt and the limit values defined by the min/max PS PSdt parameters and 
      the current PS (from min to min+delta). For example, if the current dPS/dt 
      = -200 %/s, the actuator is about to impact the closed-stop, and the min 
      PS PSdt parameter is -100 %/s, then for a Kd value of 1.0 %/%*sec, the 
      contribution to the braking force will be +100%. 
      TCSB_max_TPSdt dPS/dt value at the max PS (full-closed plus closed-stop PS 
      delta) position above which no braking action will occur. This must be a 
      value strictly < 0 and should be more negative than the min PS PSdt value. 

      TCSB_min_TPSdt dPS/dt value at the min PS (full-closed) position above 
      which no braking action will occur. This must be a value strictly < 0. 
      TCSB_TPSdelta Delta voltage from the current min PS value to initiate 
      closed-stop braking. PS values above this delta will not cause any braking 
      action under any condition. 
      TCTMA_dppredT Gaseous Fuels: 1D Interpolation Table to computing 
      CTM_dppredT (dphit/dT pre-cat target gain) from mass flow rate of air 
      through the engine 
      TCTMA_FSO_cold_tau Table corresponds to an ambient air temperature of "CTM 
      FSO table Cold AAT" and a steady-state bed temperature of "CTM FSO table 
      steady-state CBT - Cold AAT". Only applicable when "CTM FSO mode" is set 
      to 'Table-Based'. 
      TCTMA_FSO_hot_tau Table corresponds to an ambient air temperature of "CTM 
      FSO table Hot AAT" and a steady-state bed temperature of "CTM FSO table 
      steady-state CBT - Hot AAT". Only applicable when "CTM FSO mode" is set to 
      'Table-Based'. 
      TCTMA_mdot_a Gaseous Fuels: 1D Interpolation Table - Engine Air Mass Flow 
      (g/sec) input axis values. 
      TCTMA_tau Gaseous Fuels: 1D Interpolation Table - Given Engine Air Mass 
      Flow (g/sec) input, returns Catalyst Bed Temp Tau(time constant) (seconds) 

      TCTMA_Temp Gaseous Fuels: 1D Interpolation Table - Given Engine Air Mass 
      Flow (g/sec) input, returns Steady-State Catalyst Bed Temperature (deg F) 
      TCTM_dppredT Gasoline: 1D Interpolation Table to computing CTM_dppredT 
      (dphit/dT pre-cat target gain) from mass flow rate of air through the 
      engine 
      TCTM_mdot_a 1D interpolation table air mass flow rate input values 
      TCTM_tau Gasoline: 1D Interpolation Table for determining model based time 
      constant from mass flow rate of air through the engine 
      TCTM_Temp Gasoline: 1D Interpolation Table for estimating CTM Temperature 
      from mass flow rate of air through the engine 
      TCVdP_AAT AAT column values for the "Crankcase Ventilation Pressure 
      Diagnostics Run Time Wait" table. 
      TCVdP_dP1 Specifies the first set of crankcase expected pressure values 
      based on air mass flow. 
      TCVdP_dP2 Specifies the second set of crankcase expected pressure values 
      based on air mass flow. 
      TCVdP_mdot_a Specifies the air mass flow values used to determine the 
      crankcase expected pressure. 
      TCVdP_run_wait Run time column values for the "Crankcase Ventilation 
      Pressure Diagnostics Run Time Wait" table. 
      TCWT2_loadfact 2D Interpolation Map. Inputs are engine rpm and MAP. Output 
      is CWT Load Factor (multiplier) 
      TCWT2_MAP 2D interpolation table MAP (X-axis) input values 
      TCWT2_pct 2D Interpolation Map. Inputs are engine rpm and MAP. Output is 
      VE CWT Relative Correction (% fuel/% load change) 
      TCWT2_rpm 1D interpolation table rpm (filt) input values 
      TCWT2_rpmpct 1D Interpolation Table. Input rpm_filt, Output is CWT RPM 
      Factor (multiplier) 
      TCWT2_tau 2D Interpolation Map. Inputs are engine rpm and MAP. Output is 
      Cylinder Wall Heating Compensation Idle Time Constant 
      TCWT_C_dec 1D Interpolation Table. Input is engine rpm; output is cylinder 
      wall temperature (CWT) correction coefficient (in %/(g/s) for decreasing 
      load 
      TCWT_C_inc 1D Interpolation Table. Input is engine rpm; output is cylinder 
      wall temperature (CWT) correction coefficient (in %/(g/s) for increasing 
      load 
      TCWT_rpm Engine rpm input array for CWT correction 1-D 
      TCWT_tau_dec 1D Interpolation Table. Input is engine rpm; output is 
      cylinder wall temperature (CWT) low-pass filter time constant (seconds) 
      for decreasing load 
      TCWT_tau_inc 1D Interpolation Table. Input is engine rpm; output is 
      cylinder wall temperature (CWT) low-pass filter time constant (seconds) 
      for increasing load 
      TC_comp_A_emiss Turbo area*emissivity - compressor 
      TC_comp_C_thermal Turbo thermal capacitance - compressor 
      TC_comp_Dex_act Obsoleted parameter 
      TC_comp_Dex_ref Obsoleted parameter 
      TC_comp_eta Compressor Efficiency 
      TC_comp_etamax Max compressor efficiency. Assumed to be midway between 
      surge and choke 
      TC_comp_eta_choke A fixed compressor efficiency is assumed at the choked 
      limit. The maximum compressor efficiency is assumed to be halfway between 
      the surge and choke lines. This value should be less than all of the 
      efficiency values in the "Max Efficiency" column of the turbo model. 
      TC_comp_eta_surge A fixed compressor efficiency is assumed at the surge 
      limit. The maximum compressor efficiency is assumed to be halfway between 
      the surge and choke lines. This value should be less than all of the 
      efficiency values in the "Max Efficiency" column of the turbo model. 
      TC_comp_fac_hAint Compressor internal heat transfer factor 
      TC_comp_hAext Compressor external heat transfer 
      TC_comp_mdotc Compressor Pressure/Temperature corrected actual mass flow 
      rate 
      TC_comp_mdotc_choke Compressor Pressure/Temperature corrected actual mass 
      flow rate 
      choke 
      TC_comp_mdotc_pcttau Tau for calculating compressor corrected mass flow, 
      as a percentage of reference mass flow. 
      TC_comp_mdotc_pct_lp Compressor corrected mass flow, as a percentage of 
      reference mass flow. 
      TC_comp_mdotc_surge Compressor Pressure/Temperature corrected actual mass 
      flow rate 
      surge 
      TC_comp_mdotr Compressor reference (corrected) mass flow rate 
      TC_comp_mdotr_Ld This is the reference flow rate used for the compressor 
      model. This parameter should scale as the square root of the compressor 
      exducer diameter. Generally, this parameter scales with the max engine 
      flow rate. To roughly calibrate this parameter (e.g. if a compressor map 
      is not available), make sure the surge-choke margin is roughly symmetric 
      between 0-100%, and does not indicate surge or choke during normal 
      steady-state operation. Offline, this can be adjusted so the flow is 
      between the surge % at low pressure ratios and idle, and the choke % at 
      high pressure ratios and full-load. 
      TC_comp_mdot_choke Compressor actual mass flow rate 
      choke 
      TC_comp_mdot_margin Compressor surge/choke margin percent (0% = surge, 
      100% = choke) 
      TC_comp_mdot_surge Compressor actual mass flow rate 
      surge 
      TC_comp_Nc Compressor corrected turbocharger speed in Krpm 
      TC_comp_Npct Compressor corrected turbocharger speed in percent of 
      reference speed 
      TC_comp_Nr This is the reference speed used for the compressor model. This 
      parameter should scale inversely with the compressor exducer diameter. 
      Adjust this parameter to achieve rough agreement between the turbo speed 
      model and measured turbo speed. Fine-tuning of the turbo speed model 
      requires adjustment of the "Compressor Corrected Speed" 2D table. 
      TC_comp_Pratio Compressor Pressure ratio 
      TC_comp_Pratio_min The entries in the turbocharger model 1D tables may 
      contain pressure ratios near 1.0. A minimum surge pressure ratio is used 
      to ensure the surge Pratio limit is set to a reasonable value. The final 
      surge pressure ratio limit will be >= this value. 
      TC_comp_Pref This is the reference pressure used for the compressor 
      corrected flow and speed computations. Most compressor maps correct to 
      13.95 psi, while most turbine maps correct to 14.7 psi. 
      TC_comp_Td_COT Compressor outlet temperature delay 
      TC_comp_Text Compressor heat rejection temperature 
      TC_comp_Tint Compressor Internal/Average Temperature 
      TC_comp_Tint_tau_nom Turbo nominal time constant - compressor temperature 
      TC_comp_Tref This is the reference temperature used for the compressor 
      corrected flow and speed computations. Most compressor maps correct to 
      85.3 deg F, while most turbine maps correct to 59.3 deg F. 
      TC_maps_Pref Obsoleted parameter 
      TC_maps_Tref Obsoleted parameter 
      TC_mdot_avg Obsoleted parameter 
      TC_mdot_avg_tau This is the filter time constant to apply to the flow for 
      use in the heat transfer estimation. It is typically set to a large value 
      due to the long time constants associated with turbo heat transfer. 
      TC_mdot_nom Heat transfer model: Turbo heat transfer reference flow 
      TC_mech_eta The mechanical efficiency determines how much of the turbine 
      work is available to the compressor. It accounts for bearing losses, etc. 
      The mechanical efficiency is used to estimate the energy lost to 
      compressor work: increasing this efficiency results in higher turbine 
      outlet temperature (TOT) estimates. 
      TC_model_type Compressor outlet temperature model type 
      TC_N_actual Actual turbocharger speed in Krpm after LPF 
      TC_N_mode Note that not all pulse/roadspeed inputs are capable of turbo 
      speed measurement. The ECM PC display shows if this feature is available 
      on a particular ECM platform. If turbo speed is estimated, the 2D table 
      with compressor mass flow and compressor pressure ratio is used to 
      estimate (temperature and pressure corrected) turbo speed. 
      TC_N_pulses_rev Note this divisor is only applied to the measured (not 2D 
      table estimated) turbo speed. 
      TC_N_PWM_edge Turbo speed edge capture (Rising or Falling edge) 
      TC_N_PWM_periods Enter the number of PWM periods to use for turbo speed 
      measurement. Lower values result in faster sensor response, higher values 
      minimize the measurement jitter. This value must be >= 1. 
      TC_N_tau Low-pass filter time constant in ms for the turbo speed 
      measurement. Note this low-pass filter is applied to measured and 
      estimated turbo speeds. 
      TC_surge_Pratio Compressor Surge Pressure Ratio 
      TC_turb_A_emiss Turbo area*emissivity - turbine 
      TC_turb_C_thermal Turbo thermal capacitance - turbine 
      TC_turb_eta Turbine efficiency 
      TC_turb_etamax Max turbine efficiency in percent 
      TC_turb_etamin This parameter places a lower-limit on the turbine 
      efficiency. It is used to protect against <= 0 turbine efficiencies, which 
      can happen if the speed-based turbine efficiency correction reduces the 
      efficiency significantly. This should be set to a reasonable, non-zero 
      value. 
      TC_turb_eta_Noffset Turbine speed based efficiency offset in percent 
      TC_turb_fac_hAint Turbine internal heat transfer factor 
      TC_turb_fac_hx_temp Turbine heat transfer temperature factor 
      TC_turb_hAext Turbine external heat transfer 
      TC_turb_mdot0c_pct The fully-closed 0% WGA turbine corrected flow is 
      roughly independent of turbine pressure ratio and corrected speed. 
      Therefore, the flow rate for this condition is fixed at this % of the 
      turbine reference flow rate, and independent of the 2D full-open flow 
      table. 
      TC_turb_mdot1c Full open turbine (corrected) mass flow rate 
      TC_turb_mdot1c_pct Full open turbine (corrected) mass flow rate in percent 
      of reference flow 
      TC_turb_mdotc Turbine Pressure/Temperature corrected actual mass flow rate 

      TC_turb_mdotc_mdl Turbine modeled P/T corrected mass flow rate. If EMP is 
      measured, this value may be used to calibration the turbine flow tables 
      TC_turb_mdotr Turbine reference (corrected) mass flow rate 
      TC_turb_mdotr_pct This is the reference flow rate used for the turbine 
      model. This parameter should scale as the square root of the turbine 
      inducer diameter. If a turbine map is not available, set this parameter 
      equal to 40-75% of the compressor reference flow. 
      TC_turb_Nc Turbine corrected turbocharger speed in Krpm 
      TC_turb_Nc_etamax Corrected turbine speed at max efficiency in Krpm 
      TC_turb_Nmult Turbine speed-based efficiency multiplier 
      TC_turb_Npct Turbine corrected turbocharger speed in percent of turbine 
      reference speed 
      TC_turb_Npct_etamax Corrected turbine speed at max efficiency in percent 
      of turbine reference speed 
      TC_turb_Nr Turbo turbine reference speed used for the turbine model. 
      TC_turb_Nr_pct This is the reference speed used for the turbine model. 
      This parameter should scale inversely with the turbine inducer diameter. 
      If a turbine map is not available, set this parameter to 45-60% of the 
      compressor reference speed. 
      TC_turb_Pratio Turbine Pressure Ratio 
      TC_turb_Pref This is the reference pressure used for the turbine corrected 
      flow and speed computations. Most compressor maps correct to 13.95 psi, 
      while most turbine maps correct to 14.7 psi. 
      TC_turb_Td_COT Turbine outlet temperature delay 
      TC_turb_Text Turbine heat rejection temperature 
      TC_turb_Tint Turbine Internal/Average Temperature 
      TC_turb_Tint_tau_nom Turbo nominal time constant - turbine temperature 
      TC_turb_Tref This is the reference temperature used for the turbine 
      corrected flow and speed computations. Most compressor maps correct to 
      85.3 deg F, while most turbine maps correct to 59.3 deg F. 
      TC_turb_WGA_crct Turbocharger turbine WGA position based flow correction 
      Tdewpt_pre_intclr Pre-intercooler dewpoint temperature. 
      Tdewpt_pst_intclr Post-intercooler dewpoint temperature. 
      Tdewpt_pst_intclrtau Low-pass time constant for the post-intercooler 
      dewpoint temperature. 
      TDE_CLe_cnt Transport Delay Measurement: Measured Closed Loop transition 
      errors 
      TDE_CL_bank Select the CL bank to use for the transport delayestimation. 
      TDE_CL_edge Select the CL perturbation edge to use for thetransport delay 
      measurement. 
      TDE_CL_ego Select the EGO sensor to use for the transportdelay estimation. 

      TDE_cnt Transport Delay Measurement: Measured valid samples 
      TDE_EGOe_cnt Transport Delay Measurement: Measured EGO transition errors 
      TDE_enable Transport Delay Measurement: Measure transport delay enable 
      TDE_error Transport Delay Measurement: Transport delay model erro 
      TDE_state Transport Delay Measurement: Measured delay state 
      TDE_td_inst Transport Delay Measurement: Measured transport delay 
      TDE_td_max Timeout for a transport delay measurement. Once this time has 
      elapsed, the error counter is incremented and measurement resets. 
      TDE_td_min Lower limit of transport delay measurements foruse when the 
      switching period is less than the transport delay. 
      TDiagTempWUT_AAT AAT axis for "Diag Enable Temp Warm-up Time" table. Only 
      applicable when "Diag warm-up time calc method" is set to 'Dual Time Axis 
      (AAT-based)'. 
      TDiagTempWUT_ECT 1D Interpolation Table: Diagnostic Enable Temperature 
      Warm-up Time. ECT (deg F) input axis values. 
      TDiagTempWUT_wait 1D Interpolation Table: Diagnostic Enable Temperature 
      Warm-up Time. Given ECT (deg F) input, returns Time (seconds) values. This 
      table determines the run-time threshold fault condition for the 'Failed to 
      reach diagnostics temperature' fault on the Diagnostics page. When both 
      the RPM and MAP exceed the limits calibrated for the fault, the current 
      ECT will be latched as the starting temperature. The target temperature is 
      specified as the ECT fault condition for the 'Failed to reach diagnostics 
      temperature' fault. The starting and target temperatures are used to look 
      up the corresponding time values in the table. The expected warm-up time 
      is the difference in time values for the starting and target temperatures. 

      TDiagTempWUT_wait2 Second time axis for "Diag Enable Temp Warm-up Time" 
      table. Only applicable when "Diag warm-up time calc method" is set to 
      'Dual Time Axis (AAT-based)'. 
      TDIL_pct_alt 2D Interpolation Table: Commanded percent EGR for use during 
      warmup / starting conditions 
      TDIL_pct_oct_ofst 2D Interpolation Table: Maximum additional percent EGR 
      to add to standard/alternate commanded percent EGR for octane adaptation. 
      The actual percent added is inversely proportional to the current octane 
      rating. 
      TDIL_pct_oct_rpm 2D interpolation table rpm (y-axis) input values 
      TDIL_pct_oct_xaxis 2D interpolation table MAP (SI) or Fuel Load (Diesel) 
      (X-axis) input values 
      TDIL_pct_rpm 2D interpolation table rpm (y-axis) input values 
      TDIL_pct_std 2D Interpolation Table: Commanded percent EGR for use during 
      nominal operating conditions 
      TDIL_pct_xaxis 2D interpolation table MAP (SI) or Fuel Load (Diesel) 
      (X-axis) input values 
      TDM_cyl_td Transport Delay (Non-EGR): cylinder delay component 
      TDM_exh_m Transport Delay (Non-EGR): exhaust manifold mass 
      TDM_exh_td Transport Delay (Non-EGR): exhaust manifold delay 
      TDM_intd_m Transport Delay (Non-EGR): intake manifold (downstream) mass 
      TDM_intd_td Transport Delay (Non-EGR): intake manifold (downstream) delay 
      TDM_intu_m Transport Delay (Non-EGR): intake manifold (upstream) mass 
      TDM_intu_td Transport Delay (Non-EGR): intake manifold (upstream) delay 
      TDOC_Tcl_alt1 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Oxidation Catalyst Target

      DOC Temperature Target - Alternate (deg F) 
      TDOC_Tcl_std 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Oxidation Catalyst Target

      DOC Temperature Target - Standard (deg F) 
      TDOC_Tcl_xload 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Oxidation Catalyst Target

      TDOC_Tcl_yrpm 2D Interpolation Table - Diesel Oxidation Catalyst Target 
      Temperature. RPM input axis values 
      TDPS_Kd 1D Interpolation Table - EPR derivative gain as function of 
      commanded pressure 
      TDPS_Ki 1D Interpolation Table - EPR integral gain as function of 
      commanded pressure 
      TDPS_Kp 1D Interpolation Table - EPR proportional gain as function of 
      commanded pressure 
      TDPS_K_Pcmd 1D interpolation table commanded pressure input values 
      TDPS_SenseLP 2D Interpolation Table of lowpass time constant values for

      TDR_cyl_dly Transport Delay (Non-EGR): cylinder rotational delay 
      TD_cyl_smr An averaging parameter between 0 (no mixing) and 1 (maximum 
      mixing) that accounts for mixing within the volume. A value between 0.05 
      and 0.2 is usually appropriate. 
      TD_dly Total transport delay 
      TD_exh_smr An averaging parameter between 0 (no mixing) and 1 (maximum 
      mixing) that accounts for mixing within the volume. A value between 0.05 
      and 0.2 is usually appropriate. 
      TD_int_smr An averaging parameter between 0 (no mixing) and 1 (maximum 
      mixing) that accounts for mixing within the volume. A value between 0.05 
      and 0.2 is usually appropriate.

      tech_LLgear_write_en Specifies whether technician-level users are allowed 
      to update gear-based load-limiting tables. When enabled, tables selected 
      by gear-based load-limiting must not be used by any other load-limiting 
      features. 
      tech_SNPN_write_ena Specifies whether technician-level users are allowed 
      to update the engine manufacture date (Mfg), engine part number (PN), 
      engine serial number (SN), and vehicle identification number (VIN) in 4G 
      ECM non-volatile memory. 
      tech_SNPN_write_key When '21563' is entered, the engine manufacture date 
      (Mfg), engine part number (PN), engine serial number (SN), and vehicle 
      identification number (VIN) values shown on the display are committed to 
      4G ECM non-volatile memory.

      TEGR_spkret_oct_ofst 2D Interpolation Table: Maximum additional spark

      spark retard is inversely proportional to the current octane rating.

      TEGR_vlv_PR_Dz TEGR_vlv_PR_Dz

      TEI_BP_hi_on If zero, TEI is fully disengaged for MAP < BP and fully 
      engaged (provided the other enabling conditions were fully satisfied) for 
      MAP >= BP. A nonzero value here modifies the fully-enabled pressure 
      setpoint. 
      TEI_BP_lo_off If zero, TEI is fully disengaged for MAP < BP and fully 
      engaged (provided the other enabling conditions were fully satisfied) for 
      MAP >= BP. A nonzero value here modifies the fully-disabled pressure 
      setpoint. 
      TEI_EGR_minnom Current TEI EGR min/nom select 
      TEI_enable TEI current enable factor. This values ramps as TEI time 
      requirements expire or reset. 
      TEI_enrich The current TEI enrichment in % of the current phi setpoint 
      relative to 0.65 nominal phi Enrichment relative to nominal 0.65 phi means 
      that as the base phi setpoint moves closer to stoich (1.00 phi) the 
      enrichment will be linearly decreased to 0%, and at 0.65 base phi the 
      enrichment will be exactly the value indicated as a multiplier.

      Example:
      10% enrichment commanded at 0.650 phi base = 0.715 phi,
      10% enrichment commanded at 1.000 phi base = 1.000 phi. 
      TEI_FPP_dz When TEI goes into reset mode (TEI off) after a TEI 
      enrichment/retard boost-ramp cycle, TEI will remain off until the driver 
      changes his load demand to the engine. This value is applied as a +/- 
      tolerance to detect this transition. 
      TEI_full_t When TEI initiates, this is the amount of time that it will 
      allow up to 100% of its current enrichment/retard spans. 
      TEI_max_enrich The maximum enrichment in % of the current phi setpoint 
      relative to 0.65 nominal phi that will be generated during fully-enabled 
      TEI conditions with TIP droop >= TIP span (including the TIP dead-zone). 
      Enrichment relative to nominal 0.65 phi means that as the base phi 
      setpoint moves closer to stoich (1.00 phi) the enrichment will be linearly 
      decreased to 0%, and at 0.65 base phi the enrichment will be exactly the 
      value indicated as a multiplier.

      Example:
      10% enrichment commanded at 0.650 phi base = 0.715 phi,
      10% enrichment commanded at 1.000 phi base = 1.000 phi. 
      TEI_max_retard The maximum spark retard that will be generated during 
      fully-enabled TEI conditions with TIP droop >= TIP span (including the TIP 
      dead-zone). 
      TEI_mode Enable/disable TEI mode.
      In spark/fuel mode, TEI is used to richen the target phi and retard spark 
      during turbo boost spool-up conditions. In EGR min/nom mode, TEI selects 
      between the minimum and nominal EGR command and spark tables (operating on 
      the minimum table will build boost more quickly, due to retarded spark 
      timing and a closed EGR valve). 
      TEI_reset_t After completion of a fully-enabled/transition time, this is 
      the minimum time required with TEI enrichment/retard off before allowing 
      any additional TEI events. The reset time may be extended if the driver 
      does not change his load demand according to the load demand dead-zone 
      value. 
      TEI_retard Current TEI spark retard 
      TEI_rpm_lower At engine speeds below this value, TEI is fully active. As 
      engine speed rises above this value toward the fully-disabled speed, TEI 
      is linearly decayed. Fully-enabled speed must be < fully-disabled speed. 
      TEI_rpm_upper At engine speeds above this value, TEI is fully disabled. As 
      engine speed falls below this value toward the fully-enabled speed, TEI is 
      linearly increased. Fully-enabled speed must be < fully-disabled speed. 
      TEI_state TEI state 
      TEI_timer TEI timer 
      TEI_TIP_dz This the dead-zone below the TIP target where all TEI action 
      will come to a stop. Any TIP droop below this dead-zone does not include 
      this dead-zone in its span. 
      TEI_TIP_span The delta-psi from the boost TIP target minus the TEI TIP 
      deadzone at which TEI enrichment/retard will be at their maximum values. 
      TEI_total_pct TEI total engagement (percent) 
      TEI_trans_t After the TEI fully-enabled time expires, this is the slew 
      time that TEI will use to ramp out enrichment/retard. It is also the time 
      used to ramp back in during repeated (chained) TEI requests. 
      TEL2_bound This flag indicates if a telematics unit has been successfully 
      bound to this ECM. If a telematics unit has been previously connected and 
      bound, a future disconnection will cause the a derate to be enforced. 
      TEL2_derate Indicates a telematics derate is actively being enforced 
      TEL2_derate_active Indicator for the requested telematics based derate 
      status either None, Disconnected unit enforced, or Commanded enforced. 
      Implementation of this request may be delayed until the next key cycle 
      based on 'TEL2_derate_nextkey'. 
      TEL2_derate_act_chan Select the output indicator for an active Secondary 
      Telematics System derate. To output on the MIL, Soft or Hard Warning, or 
      to record the active derate via a Historic fault, enable the 'Telematics 
      derate active' fault on the Diagnostics page. 
      TEL2_derate_nextkey This switch determines if a requested telematics 
      derate condition is implemented immediately or if it is queued for 
      implementation on the next key-cycle. 
      TEL2_derate_noRx This is the derate level/type that will be enforced when 
      valid messages are not being received from a telematics unit after a 
      telematics unit has been bound to the ECM. 
      TEL2_derate_type The current speed/shutdown derate requested by the 
      telematics system. This value must be used in conjunction with the status 
      indicator above to determine the actual derate state of the engine. 
      Implementation of this request may be delayed until the next keycycle 
      based on 'TEL2_derate_nextkey'. 
      TEL2_enable_DumpTrk This switch enables the Changsha Dump Truck telematics 
      unit binding and derate control function. It utilizes most of the 
      telematics configuration parameters, including:

      - derate output
      - derate implementation timing
      - derate RPM limits
      - disconnection derate type
      - message receipt timeouts 
      TEL2_link_good Indicates the Changsha Dump Truck telematics heartbeat 
      messages are being received. 
      TEL2_rpm_lim1 This is the RPM level for a stage 1 (less severe) derate. 
      TEL2_rpm_lim2 This is the RPM level for a stage 2 (more severe) derate. 
      TEL2_Rx_timeout If a telematics unit has been bound to the ECM, valid 
      messages must be received within this timeout period or the ECM will 
      implement the derate specified by 'TEL_derate_noRx'. 
      TEL3_attempt_cnt Number of communication attempts in "WCM1 on request" 
      mode. 
      TEL3_attempt_lim Maximum number of communication attempts in "WCM1 on 
      request" mode. 
      TEL3_enable This switch enables telematics unit disconnection and fault 
      detection for China VIb OBD requirements.

      NOTE: China VIb telematics unit disconnection detection is independent 
      of/may be enabled in addition to the primary and/or secondary telematics 
      systems. 
      TEL3_keyon_wt Time to wait after key-on before communicating with a 
      telematics unit. 
      TEL3_link_good Indicates that the telematics unit communicated with the 
      ECM and is connected to a network. 
      TEL3_req_cnt Number of requests in the current communication attempt, in 
      "WCM1 on request" mode. 
      TEL3_req_lim Maximum number of requests per communication attempt in "WCM1 
      on request" mode. 
      TEL3_req_tmr Time remaining for the telematics unit to communicate with 
      the ECM. In "WCM1 on request" mode, this timer also reflects the delay 
      between communication attempts. 
      TEL3_retry_wait Time to wait between communication attempts in "WCM1 on 
      request" mode. 
      TEL3_Rx_timeout Timeout for receiving a message from the telematics unit. 
      In "WCM1 on request" mode, this specifies the interval to request a 
      message from the telematics unit. 
      TEL5_attempts Number of handshake attempts 
      TEL5_ES_cnt Weichai telematics Emergency Start max starts 
      TEL5_ES_ect Weichai telematics Emergency Start min ECT 
      TEL5_ES_rpm Weichai telematics Emergency Start safe shutdown RPM limit 
      TEL5_ES_rs Weichai telematics Emergency Start safe shutdown roadspeed 
      limit 
      TEL5_ES_tm_lmt Weichai telematics Emergency Start max run time 
      TEL5_unbind_cycles Number of sleep cycles required to unbind 
      TEL5_unbind_ena Select supported unbind methods 
      telematics_to_cnt Telematics number of cycles with message receipt timeout 

      TEL_bound This flag indicates if a telematics unit has been successfully 
      bound to this ECM. If a telematics unit has been previously connected and 
      bound, a future disconnection will cause the following derate to be 
      enforced. 
      TEL_comm_fail_cnt This counter counts invalid message event for the CNHTC 
      telematics unit. These failures may include invalid KEYs, command messages 
      with the SEEDKEY sequence, invalid derate commands, or unrecognized 
      message types. 
      TEL_comm_good_cnt This counter counts proper completions of the complete 
      CNHTC telematics command sequence exchange. This include all interaction 
      from SEED request through KEY response through final proper command 
      (bind/unbind/derate/...) issuance. 
      TEL_comm_req_cnt This counter counts SEED request commands received from 
      the CNHTC telematics unit to start a command message exchange sequence. 
      TEL_comm_tout_cnt This counter counts message receipt timeout events for 
      the CNHTC telematics unit. A completed valid full SEEDKEYcommand sequence 
      must occur to satisfy the requirement to avoid a timeout in the 
      'TEL_Rx_timeout' time. 
      TEL_const_a Constant A used in the Telematics authentication encryption 
      algorithm. 
      TEL_const_b CNHTC Telematics encryption constant for the authentication 
      process 
      TEL_const_c CNHTC Telematics encryption constant for the authentication 
      process 
      TEL_const_d CNHTC Telematics encryption constant for the authentication 
      process 
      TEL_derate Is a telematics derate actively being enforced 
      TEL_derate_active Indicator for the requested telematics based derate 
      status either None, Disconnected unit enforced, or Commanded enforced. 
      Implementation of this request may be delayed until the next key cycle 
      based on 'TEL_derate_nextkey'. 
      TEL_derate_actv_chan Select the output indicator for an active Telematic 
      derate. To output on the MIL, Soft or Hard Warning, or to record the 
      active derate via a Historic fault, enable the 'Telematics derate active' 
      fault on the Diagnostics page. 
      TEL_derate_nextkey This switch determines if a requested telematics derate 
      condition is implemented immediately or if it is queued for implementation 
      on the next key-cycle. 
      TEL_derate_noRx This is the derate level/type that will be enforced when 
      valid messages are not being received from a telematics unit after a 
      telematics units has been bound to the ECM. 
      TEL_derate_type The current speed/shutdown derate requested by the 
      telematics system. This value must be used in conjunction with the status 
      indicator above to determine the actual derate state of the engine. 
      Implementation of this request may be delayed until the next keycycle 
      based on 'TEL_derate_nextkey'. 
      TEL_enable_CNHTC This switch enables the CNHTC telematics unit binding and 
      derate control function. It utilizes most of the telematics configuration 
      parameters, including:

      - derate output
      - derate implementation timing
      - derate RPM limits
      - disconnection derate type
      - message receipt timeouts
      - encryption constants

      NOTE: only one primary telematics system should be enabled. If more than 
      one system is enabled, only one will be active. 
      TEL_enable_FAW This switch enables the FAW telematics engine start lock 
      and derate control function. It utilizes a subset of the telematics 
      configuration parameters, including:

      - derate output
      - derate implementation timing
      - derate RPM limits
      - disconnection derate type
      - message receipt timeout

      NOTE: only one primary telematics system should be enabled. If more than 
      one system is enabled, only one will be active. 
      TEL_enable_ovrd Indicates whether the telematics system enable/disable 
      settings have been overridden by service center via UDS. 
      TEL_enable_Weichai This switch enables the Weichai telematics engine start 
      lock and derate control function. This system utilizes most of the 
      standard telematics configuration parameters, including:

      - derate output
      - derate implementation timing
      - derate RPM limits
      - disconnection derate type
      - seed update rate
      - message receipt timeout
      - encryption constants

      This system also utilizes the Telematics Configuration - System 5 
      parameters defined further down the sheet.

      This system supports 4 sets of PGNs for binding, key exchange, and active 
      lock:

      Message set 1 - 0x18FF01EE 0x18FE09EE 0x18FF02EE 
      Message set 2 - 0x18FE01FB 0x18FE02FB 0x18FE03FB
      Message set 3 - 0x18FFD4FD 0x18FFD5FD 0x18FFD6FD
      Message set 4 - 0x18FFD427 0x18FFD527 0x18FFD627 
      TEL_enable_Yuchai This switch enables the Yuchai telematics engine start 
      lock and derate control function. It utilizes only the derate output 
      telematics configuration parameter, as the telematics CAN messaging 
      determines all of the other telematics configuration parameters.

      NOTE: only one primary telematics system should be enabled. If more than 
      one system is enabled, only one will be active. 
      TEL_enable_Yuchai2 This switch enables the Yuchai telematics engine start 
      lock and derate control function. 'Telematics system 4' provides more 
      features than 'Telematics system 2'. This system utilizes all of the 
      telematics configuration parameters, including:

      - derate output
      - derate implementation timing
      - derate RPM limits
      - disconnection derate type
      - seed update rate
      - message receipt timeout
      - message response delay (time between seed and key response)
      - encryption constants

      The ECM transmits a J1939 PGN at key-on and key-off:
      - message set 1 = PGN 65524
      - message set 2 = PGN 65483

      NOTE: only one primary telematics system should be enabled. If more than 
      one system is enabled, only one will be active. 
      TEL_enable_Yuchai3 This switch enables the Yuchai Foton's telematics 
      engine start lock and derate control function. This system utilizes most 
      of the standard telematics configuration parameters, including:

      - derate implementation timing
      - derate RPM limits
      - passive derate type
      - encryption algorithm seed update
      - message receipt timeout process

      All the config using in this telematics system are issued by the terminal, 
      the ECU does not use calibration data as parameters for derating.

      This system supports 4 sets of PGNs for binding, unbinding, handshake, and 
      change parameter command:

      Message set 1 - 0x18FFE54A 
      Message set 2 - 0x18FFE600
      Message set 3 - 0x18FFE74A
      Message set 4 - 0x18FFE800

      NOTE: only one primary telematics system should be enabled. If more than 
      one system is enabled, only one will be active. 
      TEL_key_lsb Telematics computed key Least Significant Bytes. Some 
      telematics systems use a cryptographic hash for authentication. This field 
      reports the Least Significant Bytes of the ECM computed version of the key 
      which is compared to the LSB received over CAN. 
      TEL_key_msb Telematics computed key Most Significant Bytes. Some 
      telematics systems use a cryptographic hash for authentication. This field 
      reports the Most Significant Bytes of the ECM computed version of the key 
      which is compared to the MSB received over CAN. 
      TEL_link_good Link to the telematics unit is active and good (no timeouts, 
      improper commands, ...) 
      TEL_loss_derate_torq If a telematics unit has been successfully bound to 
      an ECM, a future disconnection will cause this derate to be enforced. 
      TEL_misc_cntr Weichai telematics Emergency Start counter 
      TEL_rpm_lim1 This is the RPM level for a stage 1 (less severe) derate. 
      TEL_rpm_lim2 This is the RPM level for a stage 2 (more severe) derate. 
      TEL_Rx_timeout If a telematics units has been bound to the ECM, valid 
      messages must be received within this timeout period or the ECM will 
      implement the derate specified by 'TEL_derate_noRx'. 
      TEL_Rx_Tx_delay "Telematics system 1" - Whenever a message is received by 
      the ECM from the telematics unit, a delay of this length will be imposed 
      before the ECM sends out a response. Set this value to zero to cause no 
      delay.

      "Telematics system 4" - Whenever a message is sent by the ECM to the 
      telematics unit with the random seed, a timeout of this length is imposed 
      by the ECM waiting for receipt of the encryption key. 
      TEL_seed_upd_rate Sets the rate the ECM will initiate a change to the 
      random seed. Set this value to 0 to disable the ECM seed update timer. 
      TEL_state_num Telematics internal processing state number

      Monitor rpm input values 
      TEMTM_tau Gasoline: 1D Interpolation Table for determining model based 
      time constant from mass flow rate of air through the engine

      manifold temperature from mass flow rate of air through the engine

      reverse lookup to calibrated EMWT/ERWT values.

      TFBdt DBW position sensor (PS) dt (%/sec) 
      TFBdt_n PSdt calculation PS linear least-squares window. More points 
      yields a quieter and more accurate derivative, but introduces more time 
      lag. Fewer points has the opposite effect. 
      TFBdt_xLP Post interpolation low-pass filter constant for PSdt.

      table.

      TIdle_ECT_ECT 1D interpolation table ECT input values 
      TIdle_ECT_rpm 1D Interpolation Table: Given ECT, provides base idle rpm 
      Tidlspd_FPP_max The throttle command must be lower than this value to 
      allow idle speed test mode. 
      Tidlspd_rpm_max The requested idle speed during the test will be limited 
      to this maximum value. 
      Tidlspd_rpm_min The requested idle speed during the test will be limited 
      to this minimum value. In addition, the requested idle speed on system 
      boot is initialized to this value. 
      TID_table Target identification table of parameters 
      TID_table_def Default target identification table of parameters 
      Tinjf_duration This parameter determines the length of the injector test 
      firing pulse. It is internally limited to between 1 and 200 ms. 
      Tinjf_duration_def This parameter determines the default length of the 
      injector test firing pulse on system initialization. Setting this 
      parameter to zero disables this test completely. 
      Tinjf_dur_peak Injector firing test peak duration 
      Tinjf_dur_peak_def This parameter determines the default length of the 
      peak current portion of the test firing pulse on system initialization. 
      Setting this parameter to zero disables use of the peak portion of the 
      pulse. This parameter is only applicable to peak and hold injectors. 
      Tinjf_unlatch_revs Once an injector firing test is initiated and a pulse 
      is delivered, this number of engine revolutions must pass before another 
      injection firing test will be allowed. 
      TInjTT_ECT_CAD 1D Interpolation Table: Given input of CHTcrank, Output is 
      Injection timing (CAD BBDCI) . During cranking, injection timing is 
      adjusted according to this value. 
      TInjTT_ECT_decay 1D Interpolation Table: Given input of CHTcrank, Output 
      is Injection timing decay (sec). After start, injection timing is returned 
      to base timing over this duration 
      Tinj_CAD_CAD 2D Interpolation Table: Primary Injection Timing Calibration. 
      Input [rpm, PW], Output is Injection Timing in CAD BBDCI. 
      Tinj_CAD_CAD_I2 2D Interpolation Table: Secondary Injection Timing 
      Calibration. Input [rpm, PW], Output is Injection Timing in CAD BBDCI.
