      Tspkret_ECT_ECT Specifies the ECT values to use at engine start to 
      determine a spark retard modifier hold time. The 'Engine Start Spark 
      Retard Hold' table is used when the 'Engine start spark retard' parameter 
      is set to "Enabled". 
      Tspkret_ECT_hold The hold time determines how long the spark retard 
      modifier is applied at engine start, based on ECT. The 'Engine Start Spark 
      Retard Hold' table is used when the 'Engine start spark retard' parameter 
      is set to "Enabled".
      NOTE: units are not in seconds, but rather 0.5 seconds. For example, enter 
      a value of 10 to effectively set hold time to 5 seconds. 
      Tspkret_FSOt_FSOt Specifies the amount of time fuel shutoff is active in 
      order to determine a spark retard modifier hold time. The 'FSO Spark 
      Retard Hold' table is only used when the 'FSO spark retard mode' is set to 
      "Table Based". 
      Tspkret_FSOt_hold The hold time determines how long the spark retard 
      modifier is applied after the FSO ON->OFF transition. The 'FSO Spark 
      Retard Hold' table is only used when the 'FSO spark retard mode' is set to 
      "Table Based".
      NOTE: units are not in seconds, but rather 0.5 seconds. For example, enter 
      a value of 10 to effectively set hold time to 5 seconds. 
      Tspkret_MAP_MAP Specifies the MAP load values used to determine the spark 
      retard modifier to apply at engine start and FSO ON->OFF transitions. 
      Tspkret_MAP_retard The spark retard modifier values to apply at engine 
      start and FSO ON->OFF transitions based on MAP load. 
      TSRVC_intervals 2D Interpolation Table: Service Interval Calibration. 
      Given MAP load (psia) and RPM inputs, returns Speed/Load Service Intervals 
      (hours) 
      TSRVC_MAP 2D Interpolation Table: Service Interval Calibration. MAP load 
      (psia) input axis values. 
      TSRVC_rpm 2D Interpolation Table: Service Interval Calibration. RPM input 
      axis values. 
      TSSC_ena Parameter enables transmission shift shock control (TSSC) 
      feature. 

      When set to 'Enabled - SPN 64898', engine speed is limited during upshift 
      and switchback events. The pending transmission gear must be provided 
      through ECI PGN 65473, SPN 64898. The received gear is assumed to be a 
      desired/pending gear, not the actual gear.

      When set to 'Enabled - SPN 64762', engine speed is limited during 
      switchback events. The switchback signal must be provided through ECI PGN 
      62720, SPN 64898. The signal is assumed to only inidate shifting request 
      from fwd->rev, or rev->fwd.

      An upshift event is defined as the transmission changing to a higher gear. 
      Both forward upshift and reverse upshift gear changes are supported.

      When an upshift event is detected, an engine speed limit is imposed using 
      "Upshift speed reduction" and "Upshift speed minimum" parameters. See 
      parameters' notes for speed limit calculation. The limit slews in at the 
      "Upshift speed slew down rate" and will last for the "Upshift duration". 
      After the "Upshift duration" has elapsed, the speed limit slews out at the 
      "Upshift speed slew up rate".

      A switchback event is defined as a change in direction while roadspeed is 
      above the "Switchback roadspeed limit". The transmission is either 
      changing from a forward gear to a reverse gear, or a reverse gear to a 
      forward gear.

      When a switchback event is detected, an engine speed limit is imposed 
      using "Switchback speed reduction" and "Switchback speed minimum" 
      parameters. See parameters' notes for speed limit calculation. The limit 
      slews in at the "Switchback speed slew down rate". The limit terminates 
      after the roadspeed has dropped below the "Switchback roadspeed limit" for 
      at least the "Switchback exit delay" time. Alternatively, the limit 
      terminates if another switchback occurs (the driver changes their mind 
      before first switchback completes). The speed limit slews out at the 
      "switchback speed slew up rate". 
      TSSC_gear_d The received pending gear used by Transmission Shift Shock 
      Control (TSSC). 
      TSSC_rpm_limit_ena Upshift and Switchback engine speed limits behave based 
      on selection below.
      - Absolute: computed engine speed limits are utilized.
      - Base Idle Override: computed engine speed limits will be utilized with 
      respect to base idle engine speed effectively being a lower limit. 
      TSSC_rpm_max Maximum engine speed limit being applied to Gov3 by 
      Transmission Shift Shock Control (TSSC). 
      TSSC_rpm_min Minimum engine speed limit being applied to Gov3 by 
      Transmission Shift Shock Control (TSSC). 
      TSSC_sw_delta_rpm Parameter is used to calculate the engine speed limit 
      during a switchback event. When a switchback event is received, the speed 
      limit is calculated as the current engine speed minus the switchback speed 
      reduction. If the calculated speed limit is less than the "Switchback 
      speed minimum", then the "Switchback speed minimum" is used as the speed 
      limit during the switchback. See "Transmission shift shock control mode" 
      for switchback event definition and details. 
      TSSC_sw_down_rpmdt Engine speed limit's slew-down rate during a switchback 
      event. 
      TSSC_sw_LoadLim_pct Engine load limit that will be imposed at the 
      beginning switchback event. 
      TSSC_sw_min_rpm Minimum engine speed limit that can be imposed during a 
      switchback event. 
      TSSC_sw_RS_delay The amount of additional time to limit engine speed while 
      exiting a switchback event. A switchback event is exited when the 
      roadspeed drops below the "Switchback roadspeed limit" for this 
      parameter's amount of time. See "Transmission shift shock control mode" 
      for more details. 
      TSSC_sw_RS_lmt Roadspeed limit for detecting a switchback event. A 
      switchback event is defined as a change in direction while roadspeed is 
      above this parameter's value. The transmission is either changing from a 
      forward gear to a reverse gear, or a reverse gear to a forward gear at an 
      elevated roadspeed. To disable switchback detection, set parameter to 0. 
      TSSC_sw_up_LoadLimdt Engine load limit slew-up rate after a switchback 
      event concludes. 
      TSSC_sw_up_rpmdt Engine speed limit's slew-up rate after a switchback 
      event concludes. 
      TSSC_up_delta_rpm Parameter is used to calculate the engine speed limit 
      during an upshift. When a pending upshift event is received, the speed 
      limit is calculated as the current engine speed minus the upshift speed 
      reduction. If the calculated speed limit is less than the "Upshift speed 
      minimum", then the "Upshift speed minimum" is used as the speed limit 
      during the upshift. See "Transmission shift shock control mode" for 
      upshift event definition and details. 
      TSSC_up_down_rpmdt Engine speed limit's slew-down rate during an upshift 
      event. 
      TSSC_up_dur The amount of time that engine speed is limited during an 
      upshift. Speed limiting begins with the reception of a pending upshift 
      event and ends when this parameter's amount of time has passed. The 
      duration only includes speed being slewed down and held. Slewing up is not 
      included and occurs after this duration has elapsed. See "Transmission 
      shift shock control mode" for upshift event definition and details. 
      TSSC_up_min_rpm Minimum engine speed limit that can be imposed during an 
      upshift event. 
      TSSC_up_RS_Iacc_rst During an upshift, the roadspeed governor's integrator 
      is set to this parameter's value to prevent windup during the shift and 
      overshoot after the shift. This parameter is only applicable when 
      "Roadspeed function" is configured to limit the max throttle and 
      "Roadspeed RPM-based all-speed limit" is enabled on the Roadspeed 
      worksheet. 
      TSSC_up_up_rpmdt Engine speed limit's slew-up rate after an upshift event 
      concludes. 
      TSTbasespk Switch; fixes spark timing command by temporarily ignoring 
      governor corrections of spark timing and locking spark timing to the 
      entered Diagnostic spark advance value 
      TSTcam_bump Cam-bump procedure command 
      TSTCL Closed Loop Test Mode. 0 = off, 1 = Pre/Post CAT, 2 = Pre-CAT, 3 = 
      Post-CAT 
      TSTCL_BM_max Enter the maximum CL+adapt BM allowed. 
      TSTCL_duration CL test duration 
      TSTCL_EGOZ_time Additional time to add to the EGOZ heater target impedance 
      control schedule before initiating the closed-loop diagnostic test. 
      TSTCL_EGO_dZ Maximum (+) error allowed during the EGO impedance control 
      portion of the CL diagnostic test. 
      TSTCL_Emin CL test: minimum excursion 
      TSTCL_phi_d Pre-CAT phi target (used by Calibration Engineers) 
      TSTCL_pst_BM Manual fueling BM to use for postcat EGO testing. 
      TSTCL_pst_Philean The postcat UEGO feedback tolerance to use when 
      determining if the postcat sensors are functioning properly during rich or 
      lean bias testing driven by the 'Postcat fueling perturbation'. To pass 
      the CL diagnostic test, the postcat UEGO feedback must be:Rich 
      perturbation:UEGO phi > UEGO phi rich limitLean perturbation:UEGO phi < 
      UEGO phi lean limitNOTE:
      These rich/lean limits must be carefully chosen relative to the 'Postcat 
      fueling perturbation' since they must be less in magnitdue (%) than this 
      value. 
      TSTCL_pst_Phirich The postcat UEGO feedback tolerance to use when 
      determining if the postcat sensors are functioning properly during rich or 
      lean bias testing driven by the 'Postcat fueling perturbation'. To pass 
      the CL diagnostic test, the postcat UEGO feedback must be:Rich 
      perturbation:UEGO phi > UEGO phi rich limitLean perturbation:UEGO phi < 
      UEGO phi lean limitNOTE:
      These rich/lean limits must be carefully chosen relative to the 'Postcat 
      fueling perturbation' since they must be less in magnitdue (%) than this 
      value. 
      TSTCL_pst_restore Enables a second rich restore period after the rich-lean 
      test period to restore the catalyst. The second rich restore period 
      duration is "Postcat EGO response wait". 
      TSTCL_pst_Vlean The postcat EGO bias (relative to the EGO switching 
      voltage) to use when determining if the postcat sensors are functioning 
      properly. To pass the CL diagnostic test, the postcat voltages must be 
      :Rich perturbation:EGOv > EGOv rich limitLean perturbation:EGOv < EGOv 
      lean limit 
      TSTCL_pst_Vrich The postcat EGO bias (relative to the EGO switching 
      voltage) to use when determining if the postcat sensors are functioning 
      properly. To pass the CL diagnostic test, the postcat voltages must be:
      Rich perturbation: EGOv > EGOv rich limit
      Lean perturbation: EGOv < EGOv lean limit 
      TSTCL_pst_wt Time to wait after rich/lean fueling perturbations before 
      analyzing the postcat EGO voltage(s). 
      TSTCL_rpmd Enter the target engine speed for the CL diagnostic test. Note 
      that CL and post-cat control should be enabled at the selected engine 
      speed/load or the test will not function. 
      TSTCL_spk_max CL test: max spark advance 
      TSTCL_state CL test state:
      • Inactive
      • Pre-cat init test
      • Pre-cat heater test
      • Pre-cat power test
      • Pre-cat voltage test
      • Pre-cat BM test
      • Post-cat heater test
      • Post-cat power test
      • Post-cat rich test
      • Post-cat lean test
      • Finished
      • Invalid 
      TSTCL_std_wt Amount of time to monitor for active EGO impedance control 
      and EGO voltage switching once the EGO heaters are fully initialized. Note 
      that the EGO heaters are initialized for the max time in the "EGOZ 
      Heater-Control Target Impedance" table on the 'Inputs' page prior to EGO 
      impedance testing. 
      TSTCL_UEGOB_Ttol Maximum (+/-) error allowed during the UEGO temperature 
      (same as EGO impedance) control portion of the CL diagnostic test for 
      Bosch UEGO sensors. 
      TSTCL_UEGON_Ttol Maximum (+/-) error allowed during the UEGO temperature 
      (same as EGO impedance) control portion of the CL diagnostic test for NTK 
      UEGO sensors. 
      TSTCL_warmup_mode Selects the sensor warm-up mode for the closed-loop 
      test. When set to "Legacy", the test waits for the maximum time in the 
      heater schedule, which could be excessive or insufficient, depending on 
      other parameters. When set to "Normal warm-up process", the test begins 
      after completing pre-heating procedures for normal operation. 
      TSTCM_cmd Initiates the catalyst test. 
      TSTCM_diag_tm Duration of the catalyst test. The time must exceed the 
      number of closed loop update cycles specified by the "monitor updates 
      required" value. 
      TSTCM_engrpm Engine speed for performing the catalyst test. 
      TSTCM_engrpm_rate Engine speed ramp up/down rate for the catalyst test. 
      TSTCM_err_cnt Number of catalyst monitor detected errors. 
      TSTCM_err_max The max number of errors allowed, as detected by the 
      catalyst monitor, or the catalyst test fails. 
      TSTCM_ntrlock_ovrd Set to 24098 to bypass interlock conditions. WARNING: 
      The catalyst test will control the engine speed. Bypassing the interlock 
      conditions may create unsafe conditions. 
      TSTCM_results Results of the catalyst test. Possible indications:
      - "Passed": the test completed and found no catalyst faults
      - "Failed": the test completed and found a catalyst fault. This means the 
      RMS post-cat phi exceeded one or more limits configured for the catalyst 
      monitor on the Diagnostics sheet.
      - "Aborted: fault": a sensor fault or dependent OBD fault latched, 
      possibly prior to starting the diagnostic
      - "Aborted: post-cat updates disabled": conditions disabled post-cat 
      updates. This may be caused by a sensor fault, or may be explained by 
      display variables Phi_post_act, CLInactiveFlag, or ICAV_cat_prot_act.
      - "Aborted: non-stoich phi command": the phi command was out of bounds of 
      normal stoich control. This may be explained by display variable 
      CL_precat_phi_nonstoich.
      - "Aborted: closed-loop disabled": conditions disabled closed-loop 
      control, or the RMS signal was too low. This may be explained by display 
      variables fuel_ctl_mode, CM1_RMSsrc, CM2_RMSsrc, CM1_RMScomp, CM2_RMScomp, 
      CB1pst_phiFB_RMS, or CB2pst_phiFB_RMS.
      - "Aborted: invalid conditions": calibration settings or other conditions 
      prevent monitor from updating for the minimum number of times to unlatch. 
      This likely means that the test diagnostic time is not long enough to 
      permit the number of closed-loop update cycles specified as the unlatch 
      count of the appropriate "cat monitor" fault, on the Diagnostics sheet. 
      The duration of a closed-loop update cycle is indicated as display 
      variable CLp_tau.
      - "Incomplete": the test is in progress or was canceled by the user 
      TSTCM_state State of the catalyst test. 
      TSTCM_tmr Time in current catalyst test state. 
      TSTCM_upd_cnt Number of closed-loop updates received during the "test 
      diagnostic time". 
      TSTCM_upd_req The number of closed-loop updates required within the "test 
      diagnostic time". 
      TSTCM_wait_tm Time to wait before starting the catalyst test, after 
      achieving the specified engine speed. 
      TSTcompression Compression test command 
      TSTIAC IAC test command 
      TSTidle_spd Idle speed test command 
      TSTidle_spd_rpm Idle speed test target 
      TSTinj_fire Injector firing test command 
      TStrtIdle_ECT_dcy 1D interpolation table for speed ramp rate. When 
      "Starting initial speed mode" is 'ECT Table-Based + Warm Up', the ramp 
      rate is applied when ramping up or down. The ramp direction is dependent 
      on the active governor and target speed. When set to 'ECT Table-Based', 
      the ramp rate is only applied when ramping down. Ramping to a higher speed 
      has no slewing. Only set ramp rate to positive values. 
      TStrtIdle_ECT_ECT 1D interpolation table ECT/CHT input values 
      TStrtIdle_ECT_hld 1D interpolation table for starting initial speed hold 
      time. Values are in units of seconds when "Starting initial speed mode" is 
      set to 'ECT Table-Based'. Values are in units of minutes when "Starting 
      initial speed mode" is set to 'ECT Table-Based + Warm Up'. 
      TStrtIdle_ECT_ini 1D Interpolation Table: Given ECT Input, Output is 
      Engine Initial Speed at start 
      Tstrt_cyc_cyc 1D interpolation table engine cycles input values 
      Tstrt_cyc_mult 1D Interpolation Table for Liquid Fuel Cranking Calibration 
      based on Engine cycles. Input is number of engine cycles, output is Crank 
      Fuel Multiplier percentage. 
      Tstrt_ECT_add 1D Interpolation Table for Liquid Fuel Cranking Calibration 
      based on Cylinder Head Temperature. Input is CHT, output is Crank Fuel 
      Adder percentage. 
      Tstrt_ECT_ECT 1D interpolation table ECT/CHT input values 
      TSTspk_fire Spark firing test command 
      TTAUXA_ohms 1D Interpolation Table: Auxiliary Temperature A calibration 
      table - Temperature sensor resistance (Ohms) values, used for reverse 
      lookup to calibrated Auxiliary Temperature A values. 
      TTAUXA_TAUXA 1D Interpolation Table: Auxiliary Temperature A calibration 
      table - Auxiliary Temperature A values used for reverse lookup, given 
      sensor resistance measurement (Ohms) 
      TTAUXB_ohms 1D Interpolation Table: Auxiliary Temperature B calibration 
      table - Temperature sensor resistance (Ohms) values, used for reverse 
      lookup to calibrated Auxiliary Temperature B values. 
      TTAUXB_TAUXB 1D Interpolation Table: Auxiliary Temperature B calibration 
      table - Auxiliary Temperature B values used for reverse lookup, given 
      sensor resistance measurement (Ohms) 
      TTAUXC_ohms 1D Interpolation Table: Auxiliary Temperature C calibration 
      table - Temperature sensor resistance (Ohms) values, used for reverse 
      lookup to calibrated Auxiliary Temperature C values. 
      TTAUXC_TAUXC 1D Interpolation Table: Auxiliary Temperature C calibration 
      table - Auxiliary Temperature C values used for reverse lookup, given 
      sensor resistance measurement (Ohms) 
      TTAUXD_ohms 1D Interpolation Table: Auxiliary Temperature D calibration 
      table - Temperature sensor resistance (Ohms) values, used for reverse 
      lookup to calibrated Auxiliary Temperature D values. 
      TTAUXD_TAUXD 1D Interpolation Table: Auxiliary Temperature D calibration 
      table - Auxiliary Temperature D values used for reverse lookup, given 
      sensor resistance measurement (Ohms) 
      TTC_comp_choke_pct 1D Interpolation Table: Input is the compressor PR , 
      output is compressor choke flow rate (in percentage ref) 
      TTC_comp_etamax 1D Interpolation Table: Input is the compressor PR, output 
      is the max compressor efficiency percentage. The max compressor efficiency 
      is assumed to be halfway between the surge and choke lines. 
      TTC_comp_margin 2D Interpolation Table: Compressor Corrected Speed. 
      Surge-Choke Margin (%) input axis values. 0% = flow is at surge limit; 
      100% = flow is at choke limit. 
      TTC_comp_mdot_choke 1D Interpolation Table: Given Pratio (multiplier) 
      input, returns Choke Flow (% of referenced speed) 
      TTC_comp_mdot_surge 1D Interpolation Table: Given Pratio (multiplier) 
      input, returns Surge Flow (% of referenced speed) 
      TTC_comp_Npct 2D Interpolation Table: Compressor Corrected Speed. Given 
      Surge-Choke Margin (%) and Pratio (multiplier) inputs, returns Compressor 
      Corrected Speed (% ref). This is the estimated compressor-corrected speed, 
      in % of the reference speed. This table is only used when turbo speed 
      measurement is disabled. 
      TTC_comp_Pratio 1D interpolation table compressor PR input values 
      TTC_comp_surge_pct 1D Interpolation Table: Input is the compressor PR, 
      output is compressor surge flow rate (in percentage ref) 
      TTC_N_mdot_margin Obsoleted parameter 
      TTC_N_reference Obsoleted parameter 
      TTC_surgetbl_mdot Obsoleted parameter 
      TTC_surgetbl_Pratio Obsoleted parameter 
      TTC_turb_etamax 2D Calibration Table: Inputs are Turbine PR and WGA 
      position (percent), output is max turbine efficiency (in percent) 
      TTC_turb_mdot1c_Npct 2D Calibration Table: Turbine Corrected Speed (as a 
      percent of reference) - along with Turbine Pressure Ratio (PR), returns 
      the Full open corrected turbine flow (percent of reference) 
      TTC_turb_mdot1c_pct 2D Calibration Table: Inputs are turbine PR and 
      Turbine Corrected Speed (as a percent of reference). Output is the Full 
      open corrected turbine flow (percent of reference) 
      TTC_turb_Nmult_neg 1D Calibration Table: Input is the turbine PR, output 
      is the turbine speed base efficiency multiplier when the difference 
      between the actual and max effective speed is negative 
      TTC_turb_Nmult_pos 1D Calibration Table: Input is the turbine PR, output 
      is the turbine speed base efficiency multiplier when the difference 
      between the actual and max effective speed is negative 
      TTC_turb_Npct_etamax 2D Calibration Table: : Inputs are Turbine PR and WGA 
      position (percent), output is corrected turbine speed at max efficiency 
      (in percent of reference) 
      TTC_turb_Pratio 2D Calibration Tables: Turbine Pressure Ratio (PR) input 
      values (used in multiple tables) 
      TTC_turb_WGA_crct 1D Calibration Table: Input is WGA position (percent), 
      Output is Corrected Flow = FC Flow + Value from Table * (FO flow – FC 
      flow) 
      TTC_turb_WGA_pct 2D Calibration Tables: Waste-gate actuator (WGA) position 
      (percent) input - used in multiple interpolation tables. 
      TTC_X_mdot_crct Obsoleted parameter 
      TTC_X_mdot_turb Obsoleted parameter 
      TTC_Y_Ncrct Obsoleted parameter 
      TTC_Y_Pratio Obsoleted parameter

      TTD_egrcool_V Transport cool EGR volume 
      TTD_egrhot_V Transport hot EGR volume 
      TTD_exhpreEGR_V Transport exhaust volume pre-EGR tap 
      TTD_exhpstEGR_V Transport exhaust volume post-EGR tap 
      TTD_exhpstturb_V Transport exhaust volume post-turbine 
      TTD_intprecmp_V Pre-compressor transport delay volumes. 
      TTD_intprecomp_V Transport intake volume pre-turbine 
      TTD_intpstCAC_V Transport intake volume post-charge air cooler (CAC)

      TTD_intpstcomp_V Transport intake volume post compressor 
      TTD_intpstfuel_V Intake post-fuel volume 
      TTD_intpstUEGO_V Intake pre-fuel volume 
      TTD_prefuel_CAD Obsoleted parameter 
      TTD_preTDC_CAD Transport pre-TDC rotation 
      TTD_preTPS_V Transport Pre Throttle Volume table as a function of 
      fuel_type. Volume accounts for delays between the point of fuel injection 
      point and the throttle 
      TTD_pstcyl_V Transport Post Cylinder Volume table as a function of 
      fuel_type. Volume accounts for delays between the exhaust ports and the 
      EGO/UEGO sensor 
      TTD_pstfuel_CAD Obsoleted parameter 
      TTD_pstTDC_CAD Transport post-TDC rotation 
      TTD_pstTPS_V Transport Post Throttle Volume table as a function of 
      fuel_type. Volume accounts for delays between the fuel injection point and 
      the engine ports 
      TTD_rotate_CAD Transport rotational delay table as a function of fuel_type 
      in CAD: Total CAD rotational delay which simulates flow through the 
      intake, cylinder, and exhaust valve. 
      TTD_sens_delay Transport pure signal delay table as a function of fuel 
      type: This value accounts for pure signal lag which accounts for EGO/UEGO 
      delays, fuel injection command delays, and other items. 
      TTEI_altd_BP TEI Altitude Compensation Table - BP axis in psia. 
      TTEI_altd_pct TEI Altitude Compensation Table - TEI engage axis in 
      percent. 
      TTEI_EGR_minnom 1D table that allows for nonlinear mapping between the 
      final TEI engagement % and the EGR minimum/nominal table selection. 
      TTEI_EGR_TEIpct 1D interpolation table TEI Engagement % input values 
      TTIPrsc2D_BP 2D interpolation table BP (X-axis) input values 
      TTIPrsc2D_BP_Exp BP x-axis for expanded boost altitude compensation 
      tables.

      TTIPrsc2D_Phi_frac 2D Interpolation Table: Boost Altitude Compensation. 
      Input is BP/rpm, Output is dPhi/dTIP multiplier (fraction) 
      TTIPrsc2D_rpm 2D interpolation table rpm (y-axis) input values 
      TTIPrsc2D_spk_Exp Expanded Spark Timing Offset / MAP Load Table 
      TTIPrsc2D_spk_off 2D Interpolation Table: Boost Altitude Compensation. 
      Input is BP/rpm. Output is Spark Offset in CAD, or MAP Load Threshold in 
      psia. 
      TTIPrsc2D_TIP_derate 2D Interpolation Table: Boost Altitude Compensation. 
      Input is BP/rpm, Output is Tip Target Derate percentage 
      TTIPrsc2D_TIP_Exp Expanded TIP Target Derate / Load-Limit Table 
      TTIPrsc_BP 1D interpolation table BP input values 
      TTIPrsc_Phi_frac 1D Interpolation Table: Boost Altitude Compensation. 
      Input is BP, Output is dPhi/dTIP multiplier (fraction) 
      TTIPrsc_spk_off 1D Interpolation Table: Boost Altitude Compensation. Input 
      is BP, Output is Spark Offset in CAD 
      TTIPrsc_TIP_derate 1D Interpolation Table: Boost Altitude Compensation. 
      Input is BP, Output is Tip Target Derate percentage 
      TTMTPSad_Apct 2D Interpolation Table: Adaptive Table (not modifiable by 
      the Calibration Engineer). Given TPS and PR as input, provides A*Cd 
      TTMTPSad_PR 2D interpolation table PR (X-axis) input values 
      TTMTPSad_TPS 2D interpolation table TPS % (y-axis) input values 
      TTM_EGRAad_in2 2D Interpolation Table: Adaptive table for the EGR flow 
      characterization as a function of valve position and pressure ratio 
      (EGRLP/EGRHP).

      effective area over operating open range 
      TTM_EGRA_TPS 1D interpolation table input values

      Ain)(in^2)

      normalized position (%) 
      TTM_IRVA_A IRV area table for valve area model. 
      TTM_IRVA_pct IRV position table for valve area model. 
      TTM_PRKc_Kc 1D Interpolation Table: Throttle Model. Given Pressure Ratio 
      (PR pseudo), returns compressibility factor K comp. 
      TTM_PRKc_PR 1D Interpolation Table: Throttle Model. Pressure Ratio (PR 
      pseudo) input axis values 
      TTM_TinKt_Kt 1D Interpolation Table: Throttle Model. Given Inlet 
      Temperature Tin (deg F), returns temperature factor K temp 
      (g/sec/psia/in^2) 
      TTM_TinKt_Tin 1D Interpolation Table: Throttle Model. Inlet Temperature 
      Tin (deg F) input axis values 
      TTM_TPSAad_in2 1D Interpolation Table: Throttle Model Adaptive Table. 
      Pressure Ratio-based adaptive correction - Effective Area CdA (in^2) 
      TTM_TPSAad_PR 1D Interpolation Table: Throttle Model Adaptive Table. 
      Pressure Ratio PR input values 
      TTM_TPSA_A 1D Interpolation Table: maps the throttle's effective area 
      (Cd*A) as a function of throttle position (TPS). 
      TTM_TPSA_TPS 1D Interpolation Table: Dual Mode Adaptive CdA Tables. 
      Normalized Throttle Position (TPS) percentage input axis values. 
      TTPSad_CdA_crct 1D Interpolation Table: Dual Mode Adaptive CdA. Given TPS 
      (%), returns CdA correction (in^2) 
      TTPSad_in2pct_max 1D Interpolation Table: Given normalized throttle 
      position (%) input, returns Maximum Adaptive Sensitivity (in^2/100%) 
      TTPSad_in2pct_min 1D Interpolation Table: Given normalized throttle 
      position (%) input, returns Minimum Adaptive Sensitivity (in^2/100%) 
      TTPSad_in2pct_pct 1D Interpolation Table: Normalized throttle position (%) 
      input axis values. 
      TTPSlim_rpm 1D Interpolation Table: Speed-Based TPS limit. RPM input axis 
      values 
      TTPSlim_TPS 1D Interpolation Table: Speed-Based TPS limit. Given RPM 
      input, returns Max TPS (%)

      configured and indicates that the compressor is ON. Refer to "AC request 
      switch input channel" on the Outputs worksheet for configuring the air 
      conditioner. Refer to "J1939 parasitic torque broadcast" on Estimators 
      worksheet for configuring parasitic torque usage.

      Engine Start (deg F) input axis values. 
      TUEGOHsdly_ECT 1D interpolation table ECT input values 
      TUEGOHsdly_PHdly 1D Interpolation Table: For CANbased UEGO sensors used in 
      pre/postcat or EGR configurations, this value is used to delay the 
      'preheat' sensor cycle. 
      TUEGOHsdly_PHmult 1D Interpolation Table: Given Ambient Air Temperature 
      (AAT) at Engine Start (deg F) input, returns UEGO Heater Preheat time 
      multiplier. NOTE: This table uses AAT for look-up of the UEGO heater 
      preheat time 'multiplier'. 
      TUEGOHsdly_tEGR 1D Interpolation Table: For CAN-based UEGO sensors used in 
      an EGR configuration, this value is used to engage the 'preheat' sensor 
      cycle. 
      TUEGOHsdly_time 1D Interpolation Table: Use to determine UEGO heater start 
      delay from ECT and run_tmr. For CANbased UEGO sensors used in a 
      pre/postcat configuration, this value is used to engage the 'preheat' 
      sensor cycle. 
      TUEGON_1Dlmt_max 1D Interpolation Table: NTK UEGO Sensors Heater Control. 
      Given UEGO On-Time (seconds) input, returns CL max (volts) 
      TUEGON_1Dlmt_min 1D Interpolation Table: NTK UEGO Sensors Heater Control. 
      Given UEGO On-Time (seconds) input, returns CL min (volts) 
      TUEGON_Vheater 1D Interpolation Table: NTK UEGO Sensors Heater Control. 
      Given UEGO On-Time (seconds) input, returns Warmup Command (volts). 
      TUEGON_Vheater_sec 1D Interpolation Table: NTK UEGO Sensors Heater 
      Control. UEGO On-Time (seconds) input axis values 
      TUEGO_1Dlmt_sec 1D Interpolation Tables: UEGO On-Time (seconds) input axis 
      values for Bosch and NTK UEGO sensor heater control 
      TUEGO_drift_crct 1D interpolation table drift compensation (abs %) input 
      values 
      TUEGO_drift_recvrT 1D Interpolation Table: If the UEGO recovery mode is 
      set to:

      'Time Triggered table T'
      'Time + Drift Triggered table T'

      The elevated burn off temperature ('recovery target temperature') will be 
      selected from this table based on the absolute value of the most recent 
      drift compensation %. 
      TV1gd_DC 1D Interpolation Table: Auxiliary Volt1 gauge driver calibration 
      table. Given Voltage1 input, returns duty cycle (%). 
      TV1gd_R 1D Interpolation Table: Auxiliary Volt1 gauge driver calibration 
      table. Given Voltage1 input, returns resistance (Ohms). 
      TV1gd_volts 1D Interpolation Table: Auxiliary Volt1 gauge driver 
      calibration table. Voltage1 input axis values. 
      TVEmod_ECT_ECT 1D Interpolation Table: CHT/ECT-based volumetric efficiency 
      (VE) multipliers. Given CHT/ECT input (deg F), returns a multiplier that 
      is applied to the nominal values on the VE table. 
      TVEmod_ECT_mul 1D Interpolation Table: CHT/ECT-based volumetric efficiency 
      (VE) multipliers. CHT/ECT (deg F) input axis values 
      TVEmod_MAT_MAT 1D Interpolation Table: MAT-based volumetric efficiency 
      (VE) multipliers. Given MAT input (deg F), returns a multiplier that is 
      applied to the nominal values on the VE table. 
      TVEmod_MAT_mul 1D Interpolation Table: MAT-based volumetric efficiency 
      (VE) multipliers. MAT (deg F) input axis values 
      Tvent_PN 1D Interpolation Table: NG Trim Sensitivity. Air mass flow input, 
      Venturi Signal output 
      Tvent_PP 1D Interpolation Table: LPG Trim Sensitivity. Air mass flow 
      input, Venturi Signal output 
      TVE_MAP 2D interpolation table MAP (X-axis) input values 
      TVE_rpm 2D interpolation table rpm (y-axis) input values 
      TVE_VE 2D Interpolation Table. Given inputs of rpm, MAP - outputs Standard 
      Volumetric Efficiency (VEs) 
      TVLPGoff_T 1D interpolation table ECT / FT input values 
      TVLPGoff_V 1D Interpolation Table: LPG turnoff volume equivalent (temp 
      input, volume output) 
      TVSFanMaxACT_AAT "ACT-Based Fan Maximum" 2D interpolation table: AAT (deg 
      F) input axis values

      TVSFanMaxACT_ACT "ACT-Based Fan Maximum" 2D interpolation table: ACT (deg 
      F) table values. A reverse table lookup is performed using the current AAT 
      and ACT to return the fan maximum percentage applied to regulate the ACT. 
      TVSFanMaxACT_pct "ACT-Based Fan Maximum" 2D interpolation table: Fan

      Temperature (IAT/TIAT) (deg F) input axis values 
      TVSFanMax_IATld_ldpct 2D Interpolation Table: Engine Load Based Fan 
      Maximum calibration table. Ramp Rate Limited Load (%) input axis values. 
      NOTE: The Ramp Rate Limited Load filters the transients associated with 
      the actual current engine load. Ramp rates are specified by the "Engine 
      load ramp up rate" and "Engine load ramp down rate" parameters. 
      TVSFanMax_IATld_pct 2D Interpolation Table: Engine Load Based Fan Maximum 
      calibration table. Given Ramp Rate Limited Load (%) and IAT/TIAT (deg F) 
      inputs, returns Fan Maximum (%). 
      TVSFan_DC_fanmax 2D Interpolation Table: Fan Control Schedule. Given 
      desired fan maximum (%) input axis values.

      TWAKE_wakedown_ena Specify the output for low-side wake plate "down" 
      movement control. 
      TWAKE_wakedown_on Marine wake plate down active 
      TWAKE_wakepos_ena Specifies the analog input for wake plate position 
      sensing. 
      TWAKE_wakeup_ena Specify the output for low-side wake plate "up" movement 
      control. 
      TWAKE_wakeup_on Marine wake plate up active 
      TWAKE_wakeup_over Valid inputs on the selected pin will result in 
      up-movements of the wake plate. J1939 requests are ignored while this 
      input is active. Bi-state inputs must be grounded to be valid, while any 
      non-open tri-state input (typically the auxiliary digital inputs) is 
      considered a valid override. 
      TWCctrl_CBT_FSO_ena Force lean FSO & min CBT before entering ROL control 
      mode 
      TWCctrl_CBT_min Minimum CBT threshold for entering ROL control mode if 
      required 
      TWCctrl_FSO_last Parameter is the minimum time since ROL was reset during 
      a fuel shutoff event. Parameter allows the post-catalyst control mode to 
      transition from ROL (mode 0) or temp ROL (mode 2) to post-cat phi (mode 1) 
      whenever transient. To be considered reset, the ROL must have reached a 
      value of "TWC FSO min ROL reset threshold" during the fuel shutoff event. 
      Only applicable when "TWC transient error reaction" is set to 'Allow 
      Post-Cat Phi Control'. 
      TWCctrl_FSO_ROL_min Parameter is the minimum ROL during a previous fuel 
      shutoff event that allows the post-catalyst control mode to transition 
      from ROL (mode 0) or temp ROL (mode 2) to post-cat phi (mode 1) whenever 
      transient. Only applicable when "TWC transient error reaction" is set to 
      'Allow Post-Cat Phi Control'. 
      TWCctrl_ROL_d Desired TWC ROL for post-cat control 
      TWCctrl_ROL_d_def TWC desired relative oxygen level 
      TWCctrl_ROL_d_OSC OSC axis for TWC control ROL set point selection 
      TWCctrl_ROL_d_ROL ROL value for TWC control ROL set point selection 
      TWCctrl_ROL_d_sel TWC control ROL set point selection 
      TWCctrl_ROL_e TWC relative oxygen level error 
      TWCctrl_ROL_init_hi Table-based ROL high re-initialization value for TWC 
      control. 
      TWCctrl_ROL_init_lo Table-based ROL low re-initialization value for TWC 
      control. 
      TWCctrl_ROL_init_sel Parameter determines the value to re-initialize the 
      ROL state when transitioning to post-cat phi control. Value is either a 
      single point which is fuel based or an OSC table-based value. 
      TWCctrl_trans_react Parameter determines which post-catalyst control mode 
      to use when catalyst control is considered transient (CL1_post_SS_status 
      is 'Transient'). When parameter is set to 'Force Temporary ROL Control', 
      then the post-catalyst control mode is always forced to temporary ROL 
      control whenever transient (legacy behavior). When parameter is set to 
      'Allow Post-Cat Phi Control', then the post-catalyst state can transition 
      from ROL (mode 0) or temp ROL (mode 2) to post-cat phi (mode 1) when 
      transient. However, the following conditions must all be satisfied:
      - The time since ROL was reset during a fuel shutoff event is greater than 
      "TWC ROL time since FSO". To be considered reset, the ROL must have 
      reached a value of "TWC FSO min ROL reset threshold" during the fuel 
      shutoff event.
      - The post-cat phi must be outside of the window that is used for 
      transitioning to post-cat phi control (mode 1: less than CL1_postcat_lo_th 
      or greater than CL1_postcat_hi_th).
      If the above conditions are not satisfied, then post-cat control mode is 
      transitioned to temporary ROL control when transient. 
      TWCdiag_cat_temp Selection for catalyst temperature signal used for TWC 
      monitor 
      TWCdiag_CBT_min Minimum catalyst bed temperature for monitor entry 
      TWCdiag_comp_secs Engine hours of last TWC OSC completion. 
      TWCdiag_drive_cycles Completed drive cycles for the TWC OSC monitor 
      TWCdiag_ECT_min Minimum engine coolant temperature for monitor entry 
      TWCdiag_ena Selects conditions for OSC monitoring. 
      TWCdiag_event_cntr TWC diagnostic monitor events 
      TWCdiag_FSO_dur_max Maximum allowed fuel-shutoff duration for TWC fault 
      monitor. 
      TWCdiag_K_norm TWC diagnostic normalization constant 
      TWCdiag_margin_dis Indicates that the TWC fault diagnostic margin is 
      disabled for the monitor events in the current cycle. 
      TWCdiag_max_events TWC diagnostic maximum number of OSC monitor events per 
      drive cycle 
      TWCdiag_mdot_min Minimum port air flow required for monitor entry 
      TWCdiag_monitor_ms TWC diagnostic monitor timer 
      TWCdiag_OSC_drv_cyc Drive cycle count after which to ignore OSC diagnostic 
      margin and complete monitor to rich tailpipe conditions 
      TWCdiag_OSC_est TWC diagnostic OSC estimate 
      TWCdiag_OSC_est_avg Average value of catalyst oxygen storage capacity 
      determined by the TWC monitor 
      TWCdiag_OSC_est_thld TWC diagnostic oxygen storage threshold 
      TWCdiag_OSC_marg This is an adder to the TWC oxygen storage monitor 
      diagnostic threshold. When the accumulated oxygen storage capacity of a 
      catalyst reaches the TWC oxygen storage monitor diagnostic threshold plus 
      the TWC fault diagnostic margin, the catalyst monitor will complete even 
      if the phi threshold has not been passed. This is to limit the catalyst 
      monitor from over fueling the catalyst if it is reasonably sure the 
      catalyst is not OTL. Set to 0 to disable this feature. If this feature is 
      enabled "TWC oxygen storage error Kp" must be set to 0.0%. 
      TWCdiag_OSC_max Maximum value of estimated OSC from TWC monitor to be 
      considered valid 
      TWCdiag_OSC_min Minimum value of estimated OSC from TWC monitor to be 
      considered valid 
      TWCdiag_OSC_period Elapsed engine hours since last TWC OSC completion 
      after which to ignore OSC diagnostic margin and complete monitor to rich 
      tailpipe conditions. 
      TWCdiag_phi_d TWC diagnostic pre-cat phi target 
      TWCdiag_phi_d_app TWC diagnostic pre-cat phi target to use after ROL drops 
      below the post-FSO enrichment threshold and before post-cat phi reaches 
      the diagnostic completion threshold. When set to 0, uses the normal phi 
      target when ROL is below the threshold. 
      TWCdiag_phi_pst_lean TWC diagnostic lean post-cat threshold for saturated 
      catalyst 
      TWCdiag_phi_pst_thld TWC diagnostic post-cat phi threshold 
      TWCdiag_pst_rich_rst Specifies whether the "TWC fault post-cat phi 
      threshold" must be met once per key cycle before the first OSC monitor 
      executes, or must be met prior to each OSC monitor. 
      TWCdiag_state TWC diagnostic status 
      TWCdiag_tlean_min TWC diagnostic minimum time with lean post-cat sensor 
      reading for saturation 
      TWCdiag_tmon_max TWC diagnostic maximum monitor time per event 
      TWCmod_aL TWC lean kinetic parameter 
      TWCmod_aR TWC rich kinetic parameter 
      TWCmod_cL TWC adsorption function exponent 
      TWCmod_cR TWC desorption function exponent 
      TWCmod_dROLdt TWC relative oxygen level rate of change 
      TWCmod_Kphi_gain TWC model drift correction gain 
      TWCmod_K_OSC TWC drift correction OSC scaling factor 
      TWCmod_OSC TWC oxygen storage capacity 
      TWCmod_OSC_crct TWC oxygen storage capacity, adjusted based on actual 
      oxygen storage capacity measurements from the TWC diagnostic. 
      TWCmod_OSC_error_Kp This is a proportional gain applied to the error in 
      the oxygen storage capacity. The OSC is then adjusted by this value after 
      a successful TWC diagnostic. 
      TWCmod_OSC_reset Resets the oxygen storage capacity adjustment after 
      catalyst replacement. 
      TWCmod_phi_corr_max TWC model input drift correction upper limit 
      TWCmod_phi_corr_min TWC model input drift correction lower limit 
      TWCmod_phi_post TWC model predicted post-cat phi 
      TWCmod_phi_pre_off TWC model input drift correction 
      TWCmod_rho TWC oxygen transfer fraction 
      TWCmod_ROL TWC relative oxygen level 
      TWCmod_ROL_avg TWC relative oxygen level average over a transport delayed 
      fueling cycle 
      TWCmod_ROL_dly TWC relative oxygen level taking into account engine 
      transport delay

      UEGOB_ext_CLadd The entry here is an additional heating voltage that is 
      applied to the closed loop voltage limit during the extended warmup and/or 
      margin ramp periods (BOSCH sensors). 
      UEGOB_ext_mrgwt After the sensor lights and enters closed loop heater 
      operation, the closed loop and warmup heater commands can be ramped up 
      until the warmup command equals the actual closed loop heater command 
      (BOSCH sensors). 
      UEGOB_ext_ramp This value determines the period over which the warmup and 
      CL adders are applied (i.e. the ramp rate, in volts/sec, is determined by 
      dividing the adders by this value)(BOSCH sensors). 
      UEGOB_ext_warmadd The entry here is an additional heating voltage that is 
      applied to the warmup voltage limit during the extended warmup and/or 
      margin ramp periods (BOSCH sensors). 
      UEGOB_ext_warmwt If this value is nonzero, an extended warmup period is 
      entered after the normal 1D warmup table sequence has completed, if the 
      sensor failed to light (BOSCH sensors). 
      UEGOB_heater_Hz Heater control PWM frequency for Bosch sensors 
      UEGOB_integral_lmts Enable switch to use fixed scalar values or use CL 
      limits for heater integrator (BOSCH sensors) 
      UEGOB_integral_max Maximum voltage (fixed scalar limit) for BOSCH sensor 
      heater integrator. 
      UEGOB_integral_min Minimum voltage (fixed scalar limit) for BOSCH sensor 
      heater integrator. 
      UEGOB_Kd_Vheater Derivative gain for UEGO heater control loop (BOSCH 
      sensors). 
      UEGOB_Ki_Vheater Integral gain for UEGO heater control loop (BOSCH 
      sensors). 
      UEGOB_Kp_Vheater Proportional gain for UEGO heater control loop (BOSCH 
      sensors). 
      UEGOB_PI_raw_LP This is the low-pass time constant used to filter the raw 
      A/D value. The raw PI voltage reading is used for trim resistor estimation 
      on ECM hardware supporting both Bosch and NTK UEGO sensors. 
      UEGOB_PI_Vofst_LP This is the lowpass time constant used to filter the 
      offset pump current A/D value for Bosch sensors. 
      UEGOB_PI_Vout_LP This is the lowpass time constant used to filter the 
      final pump current A/D value for Bosch sensors. 
      UEGOB_SR_raw_LP This is the lowpass time constant used to filter the raw 
      impedance sample for Bosch sensors. 
      UEGOB_SR_Vofst_LP This is the lowpass time constant used to filter the 
      offset impedance sample for Bosch sensors. 
      UEGOB_SR_Vout_LP This is the lowpass time constant used to filter the 
      final impedance sample for Bosch sensors. 
      UEGOB_TCLp_enable The UEGO heater follows the heater on-time warmup 
      schedule (table above) after an initial heater start delay specified by 
      the ECT at engine start (table is above the heater on-time table). When 
      the UEGO reaches this temperature, it begins closed-loop operation with a 
      temperature target specified in the "UEGO closed-loop temperature target" 
      value below. Open-loop fueling is still used, however, until the "UEGO 
      warmup to closed-loop transition temperature" is reached. 
      UEGOB_Thysteresis Determines the temperature at which the UEGO is assumed 
      to be cooling off. For example, if the warmup to closed-loop transition 
      occurs at 700C and this is set to 10C, if the UEGO temperature drops below 
      690C, the heater will resume open-loop operation. 
      UEGOB_Ttarget The UEGO heater follows the heater on-time warmup schedule 
      (table above) after an initial heater start delay specified by the ECT at 
      engine start (table is above the heater on-time table). When the UEGO 
      reaches this temperature, it begins closed-loop operation with a 
      temperature target specified in the "UEGO closed-loop temperature target" 
      value below. Open-loop fueling is still used, however, until the "UEGO 
      warmup to closed-loop transition temperature" is reached. 
      UEGOB_Twarmup The UEGO heater follows the heater on-time warmup schedule 
      (table above) after an initial heater start delay specified by the ECT at 
      engine start (table is above the heater on-time table). When the UEGO 
      reaches this temperature, it begins closed-loop operation with a 
      temperature target specified in the "UEGO closed-loop temperature target" 
      value below. Open-loop fueling is still used, however, until the "UEGO 
      warmup to closed-loop transition temperature" is reached. 
      UEGOB_Vheater_lmts Enable switch - use fixed scalars or 1D table to 
      control header closed loop min/max limits (BOSCH sensors). 
      UEGOB_Vheater_max This is the max heater voltage allowed during 
      closed-loop operation. During warmup, the 1D warmup table above is used 
      and this value is ignored. 
      UEGOB_Vheater_min This is the minimum heater voltage allowed during closed 
      loop operation (BOSCH sensors).

      UEGOHst_drift_def 1D Histogram Series: UEGO1/2 Drift Sampling. Pump 
      Current Error (% pump current) default input axis values (Default values 
      defined in the calibration spreadsheet). The UEGO drift sampling error 
      before and after a UEGO recovery event are recorded in 2 separate 1D 
      histograms. This axis is the independent axis for both UEGO1 and UEGO2 1D 
      histograms. 
      UEGOHst_drift_pct 1D Histogram Series: UEGO1/2 Drift Sampling. Pump 
      Current Error (% pump current) default input axis values. The UEGO drift 
      sampling error before and after a UEGO recovery event are recorded in 2 
      separate 1D histograms. This axis is the independent axis for both UEGO1 
      and UEGO2 1D histograms. 
      UEGOHst_recvr_def 1D Histogram Series: UEGO1/2 Recovery Histogram. "Time 
      Since Recovery (hours)" default input axis values (defined on calibration 
      spreadsheet). NOTE: The time interval between UEGO recovery events is 
      recorded in a 1D histogram, with this column as the independent axis. 
      UEGOHst_recvr_hours 1D Histogram Series: UEGO1/2 Recovery Histogram. "Time 
      Since Recovery (hours)" input axis values. NOTE: The time interval between 
      UEGO recovery events is recorded in a 1D histogram, with this column as 
      the independent axis. 
      UEGOH_dewpt_offset This offset raises the dew point temperature threshold 
      that must be exceeded when the 'UEGO preheat time period' parameter is set 
      to "Extend past dewpoint." This parameter only applies to pre/post cat 
      UEGOs. 
      UEGOH_preheat_EGR UEGO EGR preheat period 
      UEGOH_preheat_PP UEGO pre/postcat preheat period 
      UEGOH_PWM1_DC UEGOH1 PWM duty-cycle 
      UEGOH_PWM2_DC UEGOH2 PWM duty-cycle 
      UEGOH_SD_KOFF_tmr UEGO heater on when key is off and engine stopped 
      UEGOH_SD_KOFF_tout Determines if and how long the UEGO heater stays on 
      after engine stop, and the key switch is in the OFF position.
      During this time, the ECM will transmit the 'Dew point NOT exceeded' 
      command on the CAN-bus.The UEGO heater will NOT remain on after engine 
      stop if a value of 0 seconds is specified, or if the conditions were not 
      valid for the UEGO heater to be on when the engine was stopped. 
      UEGOH_SD_tmr UEGO heater on at engine stop 
      UEGOH_SD_tout Determines if and how long the UEGO heater stays on after 
      engine stop if the key switch remains in the ON position. The UEGO heater 
      will NOT remain on after engine stop if a value of 0 seconds is specified 
      or if the conditions were not valid for the UEGO heater to be on when the 
      engine was stopped.

      UEGOH_start_wtEGR EGR UEGO heater delay from start

      period. (Used for internal UEGO sensor types only). 
      UEGOH_strt_EGR_prH This dropdown controls how the 'UEGO Heater Preheat 
      time' values in the 'Pre/Post Cat UEGO Heater preheat time vs. ECT at 
      engine start' table are used during the preheat cycle. 
      UEGOH_strt_PP_prH This dropdown controls how the 'UEGO Heater Preheat 
      time' values in the 'EGR UEGO Heater preheat time vs. ECT at engine start' 
      table are used during the preheat cycle. 
      UEGON_EBP_C This parameter is only used in the 'Delta-P Mode (Legacy)' for 
      UEGO EBP correction. See the comments for 'UEGO EBP correction mode' above 
      for further details. In this mode: 
      UEGON_EBP_EBPo This parameter is only used in the 'Pressure Ratio Mode' 
      for UEGO EBP correction.
      See the comments for 'UEGO EBP correction mode' above for further details.
      In this mode:

      Phi = 1 - (1-Phi_raw) * (EBP + K)/EBP * EBPo/(EBPo + K)where

      K = UEGO_EBP_Klean or UEGO_EBP_Krich depending on Phi

      EBPo = UEGO_EBP_EBPo (this parameter) 
      UEGON_EBP_ena This switch selects the UEGO exhaust back pressure (EBP) 
      corrections mode for NTK sensors+. 
      UEGON_EBP_Klean This parameter is only used in the 'Pressure Ratio Mode' 
      for UEGO EBP correction.
      See the comments for 'UEGO EBP correction mode' above for further details.
      In this mode:

      Phi = 1 - (1-Phi_raw) * (EBP + K)/EBP * EBPo/(EBPo + K)where

      K = UEGO_EBP_Klean (this parameter) is only used when Phi_raw <= 1.0

      EBPo = the 'EBP std' parameter UEGO_EBP_EBPo 
      UEGON_EBP_Krich This parameter is only used in the 'Pressure Ratio Mode' 
      for UEGO EBP correction.
      See the comments for 'UEGO EBP correction mode' above for further details.
      In this mode:

      Phi = 1 - (1-Phi_raw) * (EBP + K)/EBP * EBPo/(EBPo + K)where

      K = UEGO_EBP_Krich (this parameter) is only used when Phi_raw > 1.0

      EBPo = the 'EBP std' parameter UEGO_EBP_EBPo

      temperature target specified in the "UEGO closed-loop temperature target"

      warmup to closed-loop transition temperature" is reached.

      690C, the heater will resume open-loop operation.

      temperature target specified in the "UEGO closed-loop temperature target"

      or CANbased) for each enabled UEGO. 
      UEGO_delay This parameter is used to time-align parameters used with the 
      transport delay extended models. 
      UEGO_diag UEGO1 CJ125 diagnostics monitor 
      UEGO_driftE_crct_max This limit is applied after the assumed fuel leakage 
      is taken into account. 
      UEGO_driftE_crct_min This limit is applied after the assumed fuel leakage 
      is taken into account. 
      UEGO_driftE_gain Enter the 0-100% gain / sec to use for new drift 
      compensation samples. 
      UEGO_driftE_gain_max The number of minutes since the last UEGO drift 
      sample is multiplied by the time-based gain to determine the final % gain. 
      After being limited by this max gain value, the resulting % pump current 
      error is given by:

      error(t) = (1-x) * error(t-1) + x * new_sample
      where x = this value * minutes since last sample 
      UEGO_driftE_gain_min The number of hours since the last UEGO drift sample 
      is multiplied by the time-based gain to determine the final % gain. After 
      being limited by this min gain value, the resulting % pump current error 
      is given by:

      error(t) = (1-x) * error(t-1) + x * new_sample
      where x = this value * hours since last sample 
      UEGO_driftE_inject_t This parameter determines how often a drift sample 
      will occur when the UEGO sensor is used for EGR flow measurement. Note 
      that samples can only occur when the intake manifold pressure is 
      sufficiently less than barometric pressure. This time period is active 
      even during boosted situations, i.e. if the engine operates at higher 
      boost for an extended period of time, a sample will be taken when the 
      engine returns to a low-boost situation.

      NOTE: This parameter should be set to 0 for intake-mounted EGR UEGO 
      sensors in order to force a sample any time FSO is active. 
      UEGO_driftE_Ip_tol After the sampling interval is complete, each point 
      acquired during this interval is compared to the mean value and must be 
      within this % of the mean value. If any of the samples violate this 
      condition, the sample is rejected and the sampling interval starts over. 
      UEGO_driftE_samp_ms The UEGO pump current is averaged over this sampling 
      interval. 
      UEGO_driftE_stable_t This pre-sampling period wait is enforced following a 
      toggle of the EGR UEGO flow control valve, just prior to drift sampling. 
      UEGO_driftE_Terr_max During the sampling interval, the UEGO temperature 
      must be equal to the closed-loop temperature target +/- the limit 
      specified by this parameter. 
      UEGO_drift_crct_max This limit is applied after the assumed fuel leakage 
      is taken into account. 
      UEGO_drift_crct_min This limit is applied after the assumed fuel leakage 
      is taken into account. 
      UEGO_drift_ECT_min Minimum ECT for enabling fuel shutoff throttle open 
      UEGO drift compensation. 
      UEGO_drift_FT_min Minimum FT for enabling fuel shutoff throttle open UEGO 
      drift compensation. 
      UEGO_drift_gain_hr Enter the 0-100% gain / hour to use for new drift 
      compensation samples. The number of hours since the last UEGO drift sample 
      is multiplied by this value to determine the final % gain. After being 
      limited by the max gain value below, the resulting % pump current error is 
      given byerror(t) = (1-x) * error(t-1) + x * new_samplewhere x = this value 
      * hours since last sample 
      UEGO_drift_gain_max The number of hours since the last UEGO drift sample 
      is multiplied by the time-based gain to determine the final % gain. After 
      being limited by this max gain value, the resulting % pump current error 
      is given by

      error(t) = (1-x) * error(t-1) + x * new_sample

      where x = this value * hours since last sample 
      UEGO_drift_gain_min The number of hours since the last UEGO drift sample 
      is multiplied by the time-based gain to determine the final % gain. After 
      being limited by this min gain value, the resulting % pump current error 
      is given by:

      error(t) = (1-x) * error(t-1) + x * new_sample
      where x = this value * hours since last sample 
      UEGO_drift_holdoff While drift compensation is active (i.e. during the 
      pre-sampling waits and sampling intervals), certain other features in the 
      ECM (e.g. exhaust braking) are prevented from activating. To provide 
      repeatable FSO TPS open engagement of these features, this time is used to 
      delay their engagement from the start of FSO TPS open. The entire drift 
      sampling sequence must be completed during this time interval, or drift 
      sampling for the FSO TPS event will be abandoned. If none of these 
      features are waiting for drift compensation to complete, the drift 
      compensation sampling event is allowed to extend past the time interval 
      specified here. 
      UEGO_drift_inject_t If fuel shutoff is set to 'UEGO drift only' mode, an 
      FSO event is scheduled in order to perform UEGO drift compensation. This 
      parameter determines how often the FSO event will occur. If the UEGO 
      recovery configuration is set to 'Drift Triggered', this time must be 
      smaller than the recovery interval specified in the recovery configuration 
      feature.This parameter is ignored if FSO is disabled or always enabled. 
      UEGO_drift_Ip_tol After the sampling interval is complete, each point 
      acquired during this interval is compared to the mean value and must be 
      within this % of the mean value. If any of the samples violate this 
      condition, the sample is rejected and the sampling interval starts over. 
      UEGO_drift_leakage The assumed fuel leakage during FSO TPS open events. 
      This will be compared to the actual air flow during the event, and the 
      pump current correction reading will be adjusted to take into account this 
      fuel leakage. This parameter is only used for gaseous fueled systems. 
      UEGO_drift_learn This feature accounts for sensor aging by sampling the 
      UEGO feedback during known operating conditions. For pre- and post-cat 
      UEGO sensors:This period is during the throttle-open portion of fuel 
      shutoff (when only air surrounds the UEGO sensor). Fuel shutoff must be 
      enabled for this feature to be active for pre- and post-cat UEGO sensors 
      and is only available on ECMs using internal UEGO hardware.For EGR UEGO 
      sensors:Drift compensation is enabled regardless of this setting, and 
      happens periodically whenever the intake manifold pressure is low enough 
      to drive fresh air across the UEGO sensor. Internal and/or external UEGO 
      sensors can be used for drift compensation in EGR UEGO mode. 
      UEGO_drift_min_flow This limit prevents the drift compensation from 
      activating when the air flow is too low for an accurate sample (e.g. in 
      case of a slight fuel leak during FSO). On small displacement engines, 
      this parameter may prevent drift compensation from activating, which is 
      the desired behavior in order to avoid erroneous samples. On systems where 
      fuel leakage is zero, this parameter should be set to a moderately small 
      value in order to allow drift compensation at modest air flows. 
      UEGO_drift_sample_ms The UEGO pump current is averaged over this sampling 
      interval. If any of the checks below are violated in this interval, the 
      results are discarded and the sampling interval restarts. 
      UEGO_drift_stable_wt Fixed wait period following the fuel shutoff throttle 
      opening. This ensures a minimum time before UEGO air-sampling begins, and 
      allows the transport delay to stabilize before the transport-delay wait 
      period begins. 
      UEGO_drift_Tdelays Following the fixed FSO TPS open wait interval, a 
      transport-delay based wait period is used to ensure all the fuel has 
      cleared the system. The maximum transport delay is latched during this 
      period and this parameter specifies the number of (maximum) transport 
      delay periods to wait before starting the sample process. 
      UEGO_drift_Terr_max During the sampling interval, the UEGO temperature 
      must be equal to the closed-loop temperature target +/- the limit 
      specified by this parameter. 
      uego_dt_cmd Enabled/Disabled state for the UEGO drift test 
      uego_dt_duration Duration for an in progress UEGO drift test 
      uego_dt_state State machine state for the UEGO drift test 
      UEGO_EBP_C This parameter is only used in the 'Delta-P Mode (Legacy)' for 
      UEGO EBP correction. See the comments for 'UEGO EBP correction mode' above 
      for further details. In this mode: 
      UEGO_EBP_EBPo This parameter is only used in the 'Pressure Ratio Mode' for 
      UEGO EBP correction.
      See the comments for 'UEGO EBP correction mode' above for futher details.
      In this mode:

      Phi = 1 - (1-Phi_raw) * (EBP + K)/EBP * EBPo/(EBPo + K)where

      K = UEGO_EBP_Klean or UEGO_EBP_Krich depending on Phi

      EBPo = UEGO_EBP_EBPo (this parameter) 
      UEGO_EBP_ena This switch selects the UEGO exhaust back pressure (EBP) 
      corrections mode.
      The modes of operation are:

      1)Disabled: No EBP correction is performed
      Phi = Phi_raw

      2) Delta-P Mode (Legacy): Only mode available until 2110. This mode only 
      uses the 'delta-P mode constant' parameter UEGO_EBP_C:

      Phi = Phi_raw + (1-Phi_raw) * (EBP - BPs) * UEGO_EBP_C

      3) Pressure Ratio Mode: Newer higher accuracy correction mode available in 
      2110.
      This mode only uses the 3 'P-ratio mode...' parameters:

      Phi = 1 - (1-Phi_raw) * (EBP + K)/EBP * EBPo/(EBPo + K)where

      K = UEGO_EBP_Klean or UEGO_EBP_Krich depending on Phi

      EBPo = the 'EBP std' parameter UEGO_EBP_EBPo

      4) Manufacturer EOL Provided Mode: The CAN-based NTK ZFAS-U2 Intake UEGO 
      reports a 'factor of pressure' (Kfop) constant to the ECM. This Kfop 
      constant is sensor specific, and part of the NTK EOL calibration for the 
      sensor. The ECM uses the Kfop constant to provide pressure corrected pump 
      current and O2 concentration for calculating Phi. 

      NOTE: The 'Manuf. EOL Provided Mode' should only be used with NTK ZFAS-U2 
      Intake sensor. If it is used with any other sensor type (Bosch, NTK 6312 
      or NTK ZFAS-U2 Exhaust), then this mode will NOT provide any EBP 
      correction, and it will be the equivalent to the 'Disabled Mode'. 
      UEGO_EBP_Klean Phi = 1 - (1-Phi_raw) * (EBP + K)/EBP * EBPo/(EBPo + K) 
      UEGO_EBP_Krich This parameter is only used in the 'Pressure Ratio Mode' 
      for UEGO EBP correction.
      See the comments for 'UEGO EBP correction mode' above for futher details.
      In this mode:

      Phi = 1 - (1-Phi_raw) * (EBP + K)/EBP * EBPo/(EBPo + K)where

      K = UEGO_EBP_Krich (this parameter) is only used when Phi_raw > 1.

      EBPo = the 'EBP std' parameter UEGO_EBP_EBPo 
      UEGO_extreme_rich UEGO primary operation range: This option is used to 
      specify primarily stoich+lean or stoich+rich operation. It is intended for 
      marine applications that run very rich, and require a lower-gain setting 
      on Bosch UEGO only hardware platforms to avoid sensor saturation near 
      Phi=1.2-1.3. 
      UEGO_fault_ll External UEGO fault lower level 
      UEGO_fault_ul External UEGO fault upper level 
      UEGO_lo_pwr_reset Voltage threshold that removes the UEGO ASIC from the 
      low power condition. Signals the heater to operate normally. This setting 
      should always be higher than "UEGO low power condition set" voltage. 
      Applies to both Bosch and NTK. 
      UEGO_lo_pwr_set Voltage threshold places the UEGO ASIC into a low power 
      condition. Signals the heater to remain off. This setting should always be 
      lower than the "UEGO low power condition reset" voltage. Applies to both 
      Bosch and NTK. 
      UEGO_manual_action UEGO manual action 
      UEGO_manual_key UEGO manual action key 
      UEGO_mode current UEGO sensor operating mode 
      UEGO_PI_mA_crct UEGO pump current 
      UEGO_PI_mA_raw UEGO pump current raw 
      UEGO_PI_Vofst UEGO pump current Vout offset 
      UEGO_PI_Vout_inst UEGO pump current Vout raw 
      UEGO_pull_period UEGO rich pull period in ms 
      UEGO_pull_recvr_wt UEGO rich pull recovery time in ms 
      UEGO_pull_rich_ena disables/enables UEGO rich pull 
      UEGO_pull_rich_us UEGO rich pull time in us 
      UEGO_pull_tmr ms up-counting UEGO pull engagement timer 
      UEGO_recvr_duration Time at the elevated UEGO target temperature. 
      UEGO_recvr_FPPFSO_wt If recovery is active and this value is non-zero, the 
      UEGO temperature target is set to the normal closed-loop temperature 
      target before FPP-based FSO engages. This time specifies the wait time 
      between the reduction of the UEGO temperature target and FPP-based FSO 
      engagement. Set this value to 0 to disable this feature. If disabled, 
      recovery will continue throughout the FSO event. 
      UEGO_recvr_GovFSO_wt If recovery is active and this value is non-zero, the 
      UEGO temperature target is set to the normal closed-loop temperature 
      target before Gov3-based FSO engages. This time specifies the wait time 
      between the reduction of the UEGO temperature target and Gov3-based FSO 
      engagement. Set this value to 0 to disable this feature. If disabled, 
      recovery will continue throughout the FSO event. 
      UEGO_recvr_interval Time between recovery events. If the UEGO recovery 
      configuration is set to "Drift Triggered" and FSO is set to only execute 
      to acquire a drift compensation reading, this time must be larger than the 
      FSO injection interval specified in the drift compensation feature. 
      UEGO_recvr_MAPFSO_wt If recovery is active and this value is non-zero, the 
      UEGO temperature target is set to the normal closed-loop temperature 
      target before MAP-based FSO engages. This time specifies the wait time 
      between the reduction of the UEGO temperature target and MAP-based FSO 
      engagement. Set this value to 0 to disable this feature. If disabled, 
      recovery will continue throughout the FSO event. 
      UEGO_recvr_mode If enabled, this will periodically elevate the UEGO 
      closed-loop temperature target in order to burn off any contaminants from 
      the UEGO sensor. It can be used as a stand alone feature ('Time 
      Triggered') or in conjunction with the UEGO drift compensation for a more 
      robust recovery solution ('Time + Drift Triggered'). 

      When one of the 'Time + Drift Triggered' choices is selected, the recovery 
      will be skipped if the drift compensation offsets are within the min/max 
      pump current correction limits and the most recent drift compensation 
      sample was taken within the recovery interval window. If the last drift 
      compensation sample was too long ago (e.g. recovery interval set to 1 
      hours and most recent drift correction was 1.1 hours ago), the recovery 
      will execute regardless of the drift compensation %. 

      The elevated burn off temperature ('recovery temperature target') can 
      either be a fixed target or it can be selected from the UEGO Recovery 
      Temperature Table based on the most recent drift compensation %.

      Note that if this is set to 'Time + Drift Triggered' and FSO is set to 
      only execute to acquire a drift compensation reading, the interval time 
      below must be larger than the FSO injection interval specified in the 
      drift compensation feature. 
      UEGO_recvr_T This temperature should be greater than the closed-loop 
      target temperature, but low enough to avoid UEGO damage. 
      UEGO_recvr_Tramp Ramp rate to use during the temperature ramp up and ramp 
      down periods of the recovery. Set this to a non-zero reasonable value. The 
      ramp time is not included as part of the recovery duration. 
      UEGO_reset_action UEGO reset action 
      UEGO_Rsensor UEGO sensor resistance 
      UEGO_Rsensor_raw UEGO1 sensor resistance (raw) 
      UEGO_samp_min UEGO averaging minimum sample 
      UEGO_sensor_slct Select the appropriate sensor type. Note this setting 
      requires hardware support.
      Not all ECMs can support both NTK and Bosch UEGO sensors. 
      UEGO_sensor_type UEGO1 sensor type 
      UEGO_SPI_state UEGO1 SPI state 
      UEGO_SR_Vofst UEGO ASIC SR Vout offset 
      UEGO_state UEGO state 
      UEGO_ST_CLAMP ST UEGO clamp status 
      UEGO_ST_fault_SPI ST UEGO SPI fault 
      UEGO_ST_meas_cnt ST UEGO meas count 
      UEGO_ST_OCH ST UEGO open heater 
      UEGO_ST_short_INRC ST UEGO short power INRC 
      UEGO_ST_short_SNS ST UEGO short power SNS 
      UEGO_ST_short_SR ST UEGO short power SR 
      UEGO_ST_STBH ST UEGO short power heater 
      UEGO_ST_STGH ST UEGO short ground heater 
      UEGO_ST_STGRC ST UEGO short ground INRC 
      UEGO_ST_STGSNS ST UEGO short ground SNS 
      UEGO_SV_inst UEGO SV instantaneous 
      UEGO_tau_ms This parameter is used to time-align parameters used with the 
      transport delay extended models, and is NOT applied to the actual UEGO 
      sensor reading. 
      UEGO_Tsensor UEGO sensor temperature 
      UEGO_Vcc_raw UEGO Vcc raw 
      UEGO_Vheater UEGO heater voltage 
      UEGO_Vheater_DC UEGO heater duty cycle 
      UEGO_Vheater_int UEGO heater integral 
      UEGO_wait External UEGO start wait 
      UEGO_warm_ll External UEGO warmup lower level 
      UEGO_warm_ul External UEGO warmup upper level

      UGF2_drift_min_lvl2 UEGO2 drift is out-of-tolerance level diagnostic:

      UGF2_Hv_hi_limit UEGO2 heater supply high voltage diagnostic: UEGO heater

      UGF2_run_wait UEGO2 pump cell slow to warm up diagnostic: if the UEGO 
      sensor pump cell does not warm up within the time limit or warmup period 
      plus this additional duration without achieving normal operation, the 
      fault will set. 
      UGF3_drift_max UEGO3 drift is out-of-tolerance diagnostic: UEGO3 drift
