      UGF3_drift_max_lvl2 UEGO3 drift is out-of-tolerance level 3 diagnostic: 
      UEGO3 drift compensation accumulator upper limit percentage threshold 
      UGF3_drift_min UEGO3 drift is out-of-tolerance diagnostic: UEGO3 drift 
      compensation accumulator lower limit percentage threshold 
      UGF3_drift_min_lvl2 UEGO3 drift is out-of-tolerance level diagnostic: 
      UEGO3 drift compensation accumulator lower limit percentage threshold 
      UGF3_Hv_hi_limit UEGO3 heater supply high voltage diagnostic: UEGO heater 
      supply voltage upper limit threshold 
      UGF3_Hv_lo_limit UEGO3 heater supply low voltage diagnostic: UEGO heater 
      supply voltage lower limit threshold 
      UGF3_run_wait UEGO3 pump cell slow to warm up diagnostic: if the UEGO 
      sensor pump cell does not warm up within the time limit or warmup period 
      plus this additional duration without achieving normal operation, the 
      fault will set. 
      UGF4_drift_max UEGO4 drift is out-of-tolerance diagnostic: UEGO4 drift 
      compensation accumulator upper limit percentage threshold 
      UGF4_drift_max_lvl2 UEGO4 drift is out-of-tolerance level 4 diagnostic: 
      UEGO4 drift compensation accumulator upper limit percentage threshold 
      UGF4_drift_min UEGO4 drift is out-of-tolerance diagnostic: UEGO4 drift 
      compensation accumulator lower limit percentage threshold 
      UGF4_drift_min_lvl2 UEGO4 drift is out-of-tolerance level diagnostic: 
      UEGO4 drift compensation accumulator lower limit percentage threshold 
      UGF4_Hv_hi_limit UEGO4 heater supply high voltage diagnostic: UEGO heater 
      supply voltage upper limit threshold 
      UGF4_Hv_lo_limit UEGO4 heater supply low voltage diagnostic: UEGO heater 
      supply voltage lower limit threshold 
      UGF4_run_wait UEGO4 pump cell slow to warm up diagnostic: if the UEGO 
      sensor pump cell does not warm up within the time limit or warmup period 
      plus this additional duration without achieving normal operation, the 
      fault will set. 
      UGF_run_wait UEGO1 pump cell slow to warm up diagnostic: if the UEGO 
      sensor pump cell does not warm up within the time limit or warmup period 
      plus this additional duration without achieving normal operation, the 
      fault will set. 
      Underspeed RPM at which the controller recognizes that the engine is being 
      cranked by the starter 
      V12_FB_raw 12V power supply (LDO) feedback voltage 
      V1gd_AL_DChi The default high voltage input level. The high voltage will 
      learn up from this level when either 2-point or 3-point auto-learn is 
      enabled. The simulated resistance will be a linearly interpolated value 
      based on the learned lower/(mid)/upper voltage levels and the calibrated 
      low/(mid)/high voltage resistances. 
      V1gd_AL_DClo The default low voltage input level. The low voltage will 
      learn down from this level when 2-point auto-learn is enabled. In 3-point 
      mode, this value is fixed and does not auto-learn. The simulated 
      resistance will be a linearly interpolated value based on the learned 
      lower/(mid)/upper voltage levels and the calibrated low/(mid)/high voltage 
      resistances. 
      V1gd_AL_DCmid The default (fixed) mid-voltage input level. This value is 
      ignored when operating in 2-point mode. 
      V1gd_AL_ena Enables auto-learn strategy for handling auxiliary voltage 1 
      input gauge drivers with variable min/max voltage input thresholds. 
      V1gd_AL_Rhi The resistance corresponding to the high voltage learned 
      limit. 
      V1gd_AL_Rlo The resistance corresponding to the lower voltage learned 
      limit. 
      V1gd_AL_Rmid The resistance corresponding to the mid voltage learned 
      limit. 
      V1gd_AL_rst Aux Voltage 1 Gauge Driver Calibration: Adaptive Learn reset 
      command 
      V1gd_AL_tmr Aux Voltage 1 Gauge Driver Calibration: Adaptive Learn disable 
      wait timer 
      V1gd_AL_Vhi Aux Voltage 1 Gauge Driver Calibration: Adaptive Learn voltage 
      high limit 
      V1gd_AL_Vhi_def The default high voltage input level. The high voltage 
      will learn up from this level when either 2-point or 3-point auto-learn is 
      enabled. The simulated resistance will be a linearly interpolated value 
      based on the learned lower/(mid)/upper voltage levels and the calibrated 
      low/(mid)/high voltage resistances. 
      V1gd_AL_Vlo Aux Voltage 1 Gauge Driver Calibration: Adaptive Learn voltage 
      low limit 
      V1gd_AL_Vlo_def The default low voltage input level. The low voltage will 
      learn down from this level when 2-point auto-learn is enabled. In 3-point 
      mode, this value is fixed and does not auto-learn. The simulated 
      resistance will be a linearly interpolated value based on the learned 
      lower/(mid)/upper voltage levels and the calibrated low/(mid)/high voltage 
      resistances. 
      V1gd_AL_Vmid The default (fixed) mid-voltage input level. This value is 
      ignored when operating in 2-point mode. 
      V1gd_AL_Vrate The maximum learn rate allowed during input low/high learn 
      sequences. 
      V1gd_chan The output (sender connection) channel for the gauge driver. 
      V1gd_ctl_type This switch controls the gauge driver output type configured 
      in hardware on the ECM. 'Duty-cycle PWM' mode indicates that a simple 
      low-side switch is the output, and 'Resistance Simulation' indicates that 
      the output is configured for this special type of control. 
      V1gd_DC This is the PWM dutycyle either used directly in PWM dutycycle 
      mode, or the internal PWM dutycycle used to simulate resistance in 
      resistance simulation mode. 
      V1gd_gauge_DHena Use this switch to allow the simulated sender driver to 
      drive two (dual-helm) gauges in parallel. Dual-helm mode may either be 
      permanently enabled or it can be indicated using a hardware input channel. 
      A grounded input on any of the pulled-up input selectable choices 
      indicates dual-helm mode. 
      V1gd_gauge_DHstat Aux Voltage 1 Gauge Driver Calibration: single/dual helm 
      status 
      V1gd_Id This is the commanded current through the gauge driver circuit. 
      V1gd_input_chan This is the commanded current through the gauge driver 
      circuit. 
      V1gd_pctref Aux Voltage 1 Gauge Driver Calibration: gauge driver reference 

      V1gd_pct_Rx auxilliary voltage input network received percent value 
      V1gd_per Value is only applicable for output channels 'Aux PWM1' through 
      'Aux PWM4'. 'Aux PWM5' has a hardcoded period of 0.5 ms. 
      V1gd_Ra This is the current actual resistance being generated by the gauge 
      driver circuit as measured by the internal voltage and current feedback 
      systems. 
      V1gd_Rd This is the current target resistance for the gauge driver 
      circuit. It may include multi helm compensation relative to the table 
      lookup value. 
      V1gd_Rdtbl This is the target resistance extracted from the calibration 
      table. 
      V1gd_Rpu This is the current estimate of the pullup resistance inside the 
      Volt1 gauge. This value may change with gauge position and/or excitation 
      voltage. 
      V1gd_Rpu_def This is the default (initial) estimate of the gauge driver's 
      estimate of the pullup resistance inside the gauge itself. This value does 
      not have be accurate - it only affects the initial gauge movement after 
      key-on. 
      V1gd_Rpu_tau This time-constant determines the effective closed-loop 
      resistance control update rate for the 'Resistance Simulation' mode of 
      operation. It does not apply otherwise. It should generally be set to 
      approximately 100ms, but may be increase or decreased to achieve the 
      desired gauge response time and stability. 
      V1gd_Vexc_ratio This is the internal resistor divider ratio of the gauge 
      with respect to the supply voltage and ground. If no divider ratio is 
      present internal to the gauge, set this value to 1.0. 
      V1gd_Vexc_reg This is the voltage regulator level for the internal gauge 
      excitation voltage. If no regulation exists, just set this value above 
      normal operating voltage (such as 36 volts). 
      V1gd_volts This is the source (input) voltage selected by the input 
      channel switch for this gauge driver. 
      V1gd_V_FB This is the current measured voltage at the gauge driver input 
      pin on the ECM connector. It is used in the computation of the simulated 
      sender resistance. 
      V3P3_FB_raw 3.3V power supply (LDO) feedback voltage 
      Valternator Measured alternator voltage. 
      Valternator_raw Alternator raw volts 
      Vbat Battery Voltage 
      Vbatdt_float Battery voltage derivative 
      vbat_c Internal scale factor for Vbat voltage measurement. 
      Vbat_raw Vbat raw volts 
      Vd Swept volume of all cylinders combined. 
      Vdot_cat Catalyst volumetric flow rate. Equal to the exhaust flow rate, 
      except in low-pressure EGR applications where the EGR tee is between the 
      catalyst and the muffler. 
      Vdot_exhaust Exhaust volume flow rate 
      VDS_ena Select the calibration source. The calibration source is normally 
      set during EOL using ISO 14229 UDS. The calibration sources are the 
      Standard calibration or the Variant Data Set (VDS). VDS_enghrs_limit may 
      restrict the ability to switch to the VDS. 
      VDS_enghrs_limit Set the number of engine hours the Variant Data Set 
      calibration may be used. After expiration of the time limit, the ECM will 
      revert to the standard calibration on the next restart. 
      VDS_reprog_mode Selects whether to use the Variant Data Set calibration or 
      the Standard calibration after reprogramming. 
      VDS_state Reports and sets the source for the calibration stored in 
      EEPROM. Used to request a switch to/from the Variant Data Set calibration. 
      The switch is implemented upon ECM reset. 
      VE Corrected Volumetric Efficiency 
      VE5a Primary 5V external supply voltage 
      VE5a_FB_raw 5VE1 raw volts

      VE5b_min 5VE2 low voltage diagnostic: Lower monitor values for the

      VE6_FB_raw main 6V supply feedback 
      vehicle_pitch_angle Pitch angle (SPN 3318) received in SSI message (PGN 
      61459). 
      veh_type Non-direct vehicle mode allows coupled FPP1/2/IVS inputs with 
      TSC1 full-authority torque requests (e.g. hybrid vehicle setup or 
      automatic transmission interfacing). If direct mode is selected, the FPP 
      must be configured for a remote throttle before full-authority TSC1 torque 
      requests are accepted. EEC2 continues to broadcast the actual FPP input, 
      even when a TSC1 torque message is active. 
      Vent_dP_cmd Venturi Fuel Driving delta-P command (used to compute 
      MJ_P_cmd) 
      Vent_dP_nom Venturi fuel-driving delta pressure 
      Vent_P_sig Venturi pressure signal 
      VEs Standard Volumetric Efficiency 
      Vexhaust The total volume from the exhaust ports to the EGO sensor. 
      VE_CWT_adapt_max If VE_CWT_crct is above this number, adaptive learn is 
      temporarily disabled 
      VE_CWT_adapt_min If VE_CWT_crct is below this NEGATIVE number, adaptive 
      learn is temporarily disabled. 
      VE_CWT_C Cylinder wall heating compensation magnitude constant. 
      Approximate value for a GM 5.7L V-8 is 2.89 %/(g/sec fuel) (0.365 
      %/(lbm/hr fuel). This number should be tuned to give the correct peak 
      magnitude of VE_CWT_crct during heavy fueling transients. 
      VE_CWT_crct_pct Cylinder-wall temperature VE correction percentage 
      VE_CWT_max Maximum + authority for the cylinder wall temperature 
      correction term. 
      VE_CWT_min Maximum - authority for the cylinder wall temperature 
      correction term. Entered as a NEGATIVE number. 
      VE_CWT_rpm_idle Typical idle speed at which Tau_idle is calibrated. 
      VE_CWT_tau_idle Cylinder wall heating compensation idle time constant. 
      Approximate value for a GM 5.7L V-8 is 20 seconds. This number should be 
      tuned by letting the engine reach steady state at a heavily loaded 
      condition and then releasing it back to idle. The closed loop multiplier 
      should jump down and then exponentially decay toward 0%. The time constant 
      of this decay is Tau_idle. 
      VE_EBP_crct VE Correction Factor for EBP 
      VE_EBP_crct_min Minimum EBP-based VE correction. Enter as a negative 
      value. Set to -100% to disabled limiting. 
      VE_ECT_crct VE Correction Factor for ECT 
      VE_EGR_ofst VE_EGR_ofst 
      VE_high_air MAT estimation - VE at high airflow point 
      VE_MAT_crct VE Correction Factor for MAT 
      VE_ovlp_crct VE CAM Overlap Correction Multiplier 
      Vint_lower Volume of all intake plumbing below the injection point. For 
      example, in a throttle body engine this would be the sum of:
      1) The entire intake manifold.
      2) All volume within the head above the intake valves and below the 
      manifold connection. 
      Vint_total The total volume of the entire intake system downstream of the 
      throttle plates. This is the same as 'Vintake lower' on a throttle body 
      injected engine. 
      VPA_delay Specifies the amount of time before a second engagement of the 
      forced idle derate if the conditions which caused the initial derate 
      continue. 
      VPA_derate_active Vehicle pull away derate active LED 
      VPA_ena Force the driver to use first gear or reverse when pulling away 
      from a stop.If the roadspeed is within the min..max engage speeds and if 
      the transmission indicates the vehicle is not in first gear or reverse, 
      then the engine is forced to the idle min-governor RPM. Forced idle is 
      released upon gear change to first gear or reverse, roadspeed outside the 
      min..max speed range, or the timeout.J1939 Aux IO (PGN 65241) messages 
      provide the first gear and reverse indications from the transmission. 
      VPA_gear1_LED Vehicle pull away gear 1 LED 
      VPA_max_speed Roadspeeds within the min..max engage speed range require 
      first gear or reverse. 
      VPA_min_speed Roadspeeds within the min..max engage speed range require 
      first gear or reverse. 
      VPA_rev_LED Vehicle pull away reverse LED 
      VPA_tout Specifies the amount of time the engine will remain forced to 
      idle while the roadspeed remains within the min..max engage speed range 
      and the transmission remains in a gear other than first gear or reverse. 
      VP_eng_config current engine configuration - network FPP, 
      dual-bank/V-config, CL, DBW 
      VP_shift_rpmd This is the target shift speed parameter to be stored and 
      communicated by the engine ECM to other devices on the vessel which 
      interact with shift functions. It is not currently actively used in the 
      engine ECM software other than for communication purposes. 
      VP_shift_rpmmax At engine speeds above this setpoint, the shift actuator 
      target position will not be updated, but the throttle will be closed and 
      shift interrupt will be allowed to engage (but it will only engage if the 
      calibration allows it). Once the engine speed drops below this setpoint, 
      the ECM will attempt to shift. Note that this speed defaults to the VP 
      ECM-communicated maximum shift speed for backwards compatibility.

      NOTE: The maximum engine speed and mechanical engagement delay values are 
      used anytime an ECI hand controller is present, even if shift actuator 
      control is disabled. This is for compatibility with systems that use the 
      ECI hand controller to control the shift solenoids. In this scenario, the 
      hand control packet gives the ECM a desired gear. The ECM will zero the 
      foot pedal command, and when the engine speed is below the max engine 
      shift speed, a countdown timer will begin to allow for the mechanical 
      engagement of the drive. The shift is assumed complete when the mechanical 
      delay timer expires, and actual gear = desired gear at this time (actual 
      gear is translated back to the ECI hand controller via an ETC2 message). 
      VP_shift_rpmmax_neut This is the maximum shift speed parameter to be 
      stored and communicated by the engine ECM to other VP devices on the 
      vessel which interact with shift functions.

      If this value is > 0, this value will be broadcast on CAN only when the 
      engine is not in PARK or NEUTRAL. This value is intended to provide an 
      alternate RPM limit to the VP controller for shifts to NEUTRAL.

      NOTE: This value is not currently actively used in the engine ECM software 
      other than for communication purposes to VP devices. 
      VP_troll_rpmmax This is the maximum troll speed parameter to be stored and 
      communicated by the engine ECM to other devices on the vessel which 
      interact with shift functions. It is not currently actively used in the 
      engine ECM software other than for communication purposes. 
      Vrelay Vrelay input voltage. 
      Vrelay_raw Vrelay raw volts 
      Vs Vs (primary) Standard operating charging voltage used for the liquid 
      fuel injector calibration, and for any other general references in the 
      software. 
      VSFan_ac The percentage of fan maximum speed possible at the current 
      engine RPM to apply when the AC is running 
      VSFan_ac_hi_pres_rpm Specifies the minimum fan speed required when the AC 
      high pressure switch indicates high pressure. 
      VSFan_ac_rpm Specifies the minimum fan speed required when the AC is 
      running. This value is enforced when the roadspeed does not exceed the "AC 
      fan speed control roadspeed limit" value. 
      VSFan_ac_RSmax Specifies the maximum roadspeed at which the minimum fan 
      speed will be enforced while the AC is running. 
      VSFan_AGS_min1 Minimum position of grille #1 for enabling the fan when 
      closed-loop control is enabled. 
      VSFan_channel The output channel for the fan PWM control can be selected 
      here. The control itself must be enabled using the 'Fan control' 
      parameter. 
      VSFan_CL_ena Enables or disables closed loop control of the variable speed 
      fan based on fan speed. 
      VSFan_DC Fan PWM output 
      VSFan_dec_ldramp The ramp down rate is used to calculate the Ramp Rate 
      Limited Load for the table to the right. This value specifies the 
      percentage decrease per second to bring the current ramp rate limited load 
      down to the actual current engine load 
      VSFan_drivebrake The percentage of fan maximum speed possible at the 
      current engine RPM to apply when driveline or exhaust braking is engaged 
      VSFan_drive_ratio This is the ratio between the crank pulley diameter and 
      the fan pulley diameter and is used in calculating the actual fan maximum 
      percentage at the current engine RPM.
      fan drive ratio = crank pulley diameter / fan pulley diameter 
      VSFan_drvbrk_rpm Specifies the minimum fan speed required when engine 
      braking is active. 
      VSFan_dt_AAT_min Minimum AAT for fan speed diagnostic test 
      VSFan_dt_access Specifies whether fan speed diagnostic test parameters 
      require Engineer or SuperTech write permission. 
      VSFan_dt_avg_tm Time to average the fan speed error during the fan speed 
      diagnostic test 
      VSFan_dt_cmd Fan speed test command 
      VSFan_dt_ECT_min Minimum ECT for fan speed diagnostic test 
      VSFan_dt_engrpm Engine speed for the fan speed diagnostic test 
      VSFan_dt_engrpm_rate Engine speed ramp rate for the fan speed diagnostic 
      test 
      VSFan_dt_err_avg1 Fan speed diagnostic test average error at fan speed #1 
      VSFan_dt_err_avg2 Fan speed diagnostic test average error at fan speed #2 
      VSFan_dt_OILT_min Minimum OILT for fan speed diagnostic test 
      VSFan_dt_rpm1 Fan test speed #1 
      VSFan_dt_rpm2 Fan test speed #2 
      VSFan_dt_state Fan speed test state 
      VSFan_dt_wait_tm Time to wait for the fan to reach the desired test speed 
      VSFan_dz This is the fan maximum percentage threshold below which the fan 
      is not engaged 
      VSFan_ena Fan control enable 
      VSFan_inc_ldramp The ramp up rate is used to calculate the Ramp Rate 
      Limited Load for the table to the right. This value specifies the 
      percentage increase per second to bring the current ramp rate limited load 
      up to the actual current engine load 
      VSFan_ld_slew Fan ramp rate limited engine load 
      VSFan_load_src Specifies whether IAT or TIAT sensor input is used for the 
      temperature column of the "Engine Load Based Fan Maximum" table. 
      VSFan_off_DC This is the PWM duty cycle required to disengage the variable 
      speed fan and is required when shutting off the engine or disabling fan 
      control while the fan is currently engaged 
      VSFan_output_Hz Fan PWM frequency 
      VSFan_pcta Fan maximum actual (%) 
      VSFan_pctd Fan maximum target (%) 
      VSFan_pctd_final Fan maximum target percentage with fan slip heat 
      protection. 
      VSFan_pctd_tau Specifies the time constant used for the desired fan 
      maximum percentage low-pass filter. 
      VSFan_pulses_rev The scaling divisor is the number of pulses that is 
      required to turn the fan one rotation 
      VSFan_pwr Current fan power consumption 
      VSFan_retard_rpm Specifies the minimum fan speed required when retarder 
      braking is active. This fan speed is enforced when the Electronic Retarder 
      Controller 1 (ERC1) PGN is received from the transmission retarder 
      controller with any of the following conditions:
      - SPN 520, "Actual Retarder - Percent Torque" is negative, or
      - SPN 1715, "Drivers Demand Retarder - Percent Torque" is negative; or
      - SPN 900, "Retarder Torque Mode", is not set to 0, "No request". 
      VSFan_rpm Fan speed (rpm) 
      VSFan_rpmd Current desired fan speed. 
      VSFan_rpmd_final Target fan speed with fan slip heat protection. 
      VSFan_rpmd_tau Specifies the time constant used for the desired fan speed 
      low-pass filter. 
      VSFan_rpm_dot Current fan speed closed loop control derivative value. 
      VSFan_rpm_dot_tau Specifies the time constant used for the fan speed 
      derivative low-pass filter. 
      VSFan_rpm_dot_window This time window determines the number of derivative 
      samples stored for fan speed closed loop control. Multiply the desired 
      number of samples by 50ms to generate this value. 
      VSFan_rpm_err Fan speed error 
      VSFan_rpm_Iacc Current fan speed closed loop control integrator value. 
      VSFan_SHP_actv Indicates if fan slip heat protection is active. 
      VSFan_SHP_ena Parameter enables fan slip heat protection for both 
      open-loop and closed-loop fan control.

      When parameter is set to 'Disabled', the final desired fan speed 
      (VSFan_rpmd_final) is equal to the desired fan speed (VSFan_rpmd).

      When parameter is set to 'Enabled' and closed-loop control is active ("Fan 
      speed closed-loop control" is 'Enabled'), the final desired fan speed 
      (VSFan_rpmd_final) is modified to protect the fan from generating too much 
      heat from slip. If the desired fan speed (VSFan_rpmd) is between the lower 
      and upper limits in the "Fan Slip Heat Protection" table, then 
      VSFan_rpmd_final is set to either the lower or upper limit in the table. 
      If VSFan_rpmd is between the upper hysteresis and upper limit points, then 
      VSFan_rpmd_final is set to the upper limit. If VSFan_rpmd is between the 
      lower hysteresis and lower limit points, then VSFan_rpmd_final is set to 
      the lower limit. When VSFan_rpmd is not between the lower and upper 
      limits, then VSFan_rpmd_final is set to VSFan_rpmd.

      When open-loop control is active ("Fan speed closed-loop control" is 
      'Disabled'), fan slip heat protection is applied similarly. The desired 
      fan speed (VSFan_rpmd) is calculated as the desired fan maximum percentage 
      (VSFan_pctd) multiplied by the theoretical max fan speed at the current 
      engine speed. The final desired fan speed (VSFan_rpmd_final) is calculated 
      using the same method as described for closed-loop control.

      Feature is temporarily disabled when the variable speed fan diagnostics is 
      active. 
      VSFan_slip_x The actual maximum fan speed at a certain engine RPM may be 
      slightly less than the ideal fan speed due to belt slippage. A constant 
      value of 1.00 for the correction factor indicates there is no belt slip, 
      while values < 1.00 indicate there is some belt slippage 
      VSFan_status Variable speed fan status:
      0 = 'Disabled' - variable speed fan feature disabled
      1 = 'Fan Off' - engine off or fan not needed
      2 = 'Fan Off - Diagnostic Test' - diagnostic test is running
      3 = 'Fan Off - Within Deadzone' - fan max % > 0 but is within deadzone
      4 = 'Fan Off - Grille Position' - grille #1 position is low
      5 = 'Fan On - AC System' - AC system is running
      6 = 'Fan On - AC Pressure Switch' - AC high pressure switch indicates high 
      pressure
      7 = 'Fan On - Compression Brake' - compression brake is active
      8 = 'Fan On - Trans Retarder' - transmission retarder is active
      9 = 'Fan On - Exhaust Brake' - exhaust brake is active
      10 = 'Fan On - ERC1' - ERC1 is active
      11 = 'Fan On - RCOT' - retarder coolant outlet temperature is high 
      (CAN-based)
      12 = 'Fan On - ECT' - engine coolant temperature is high
      13 = 'Fan On - Aux Temp' - auxiliary temperature is high
      14 = 'Fan On - IAT/TIAT' - intake air temperature is high for the current 
      engine load
      15 = 'Fan On - ACT' - auxiliary coolant temperature is high
      16 = 'Fan On - Diagnostic Test' - diagnostic test is running 
      VSFan_Taux_chan Selects the temperature source input for the "Aux 
      Temperature-Based Fan Maximum" table. If set to 'Disabled', the "Aux 
      Temperature-Based Fan Maximum" table is not used.

      When set to 'CAN sourced', the auxiliary temperature is provided through 
      SPN 5656 in ECI PGN 65275 which is the retarder coolant outlet 
      temperature. 
      VSFan_Taux_mode Parameter determines when the variable speed fan's 
      auxiliary temperature is allowed to modify the fan speed. When set to 
      'Always Active', then the auxiliary temperature is continuously monitored 
      and allowed to adjust the fan's maximum percentage. When set to 'Retarder 
      Active', then retarder braking must be active via J1939 ERC1 PGN before 
      auxiliary temperature can adjust the fan's maximum percentage. Parameter 
      is only applicable when "Fan control auxiliary temperature input" is not 
      set to 'Disabled'. 
      VSFan_Taux_tau Specifies the time constant used for the fan control 
      auxiliary temperature sensor input low-pass filter. 
      VSFan_Taux_temp The variable speed fan control's auxiliary temperature 
      value. Only applicable when "Fan control auxiliary temperature input" is 
      not set to 'Disabled'. 
      Vsw Switched Voltage 
      Vsw_gauge This is a lowpass filtered version of the switched battery 
      voltage which is assumed to be approximately the same as the voltage 
      exciting (pulling up) the gauge driver input network. 
      Vsw_gauge_tau This time-constant is used to compute a filtered version of 
      the standard Vsw (switched voltage) value for use as a gauge-driver 
      resistance control system input. 
      Vsw_raw Vswitch raw volts 
      Vsw_stat Switched voltage input status (0=Inactive, 1=Active, 
      2=Error/Fault, 3=Not Configured). 
      Vs_I2 Standard operating charging voltage used for the secondary fuel 
      injector calibration. 
      V_def default voltage 
      V_LPG The volume from the LPG fuel introduction point to the throttle 
      plate. 
      V_LPG_off Equivalent air volume that matches the fuel available from the 
      LPG lockoff to the fuel introduction point during a LPG to gasoline 
      transition. 
      V_LPG_off_cur LPG fuel-switching turn-off volume equivalent current value 
      in liters 
      V_LPG_off_type Calibration switch: This switch selects what the source of 
      the LPG turnoff volume parameter is. This can be either a single value 
      (legacy mode), or a table-based schedule indexed byECT or fuel temperature 
      (if available). 
      V_max Voltage high diagnostic: Voltage upper limit threshold 
      V_min Voltage low diagnostic: Voltage lower limit threshold 
      V_minRPM Voltage low diagnostic: Minimum RPM entry condition 
      V_NG The volume from the NG fuel introduction point to the throttle plate. 

      V_NG_off Equivalent air volume that matches the fuel available from the NG 
      lockoff to the fuel introduction point during a NG to gasoline transition. 

      WARN_engstop Determines whether the hard/soft-warnings reflect the current 
      fault system status during key-on engine-stopped conditions. 
      WGCV_fault_code Highest priority fault code received from the CAN-based 
      wastegate control valve (WGCV), SPN 64767 in ECI PGN 42286.
      0 = None
      1 = Internal Fault
      2 = Low Voltage
      3 = High Voltage
      4 = Large Pressure Delta
      5 = Pressure Message Timeout
      6 = Pressure Message Timeout
      7 = CAN Bus Off
      8 = Open-Circuit Pressure Sensor
      9 = Short-Circuit Pressure Sensor
      10 = Open-Circuit Valve
      11 = Short-Circuit Valve
      255 = Not Available 
      WGCV_state State received from the CAN-based wastegate control valve 
      (WGCV), SPN 64769 in ECI PGN 42286.
      0 = Unknown
      1 = Pressure Control
      2 = Fail-Safe
      3 = Unknown
      255 = Not Available 
      WGPcal_P 1D Interpolation Table: Waste-gate pressure sensor calibration. 
      Given WGP sensor voltage, returns Waste-gate pressure (selectable between 
      psia and psig) 
      WGPcal_V 1D Interpolation Table: Waste-gate pressure sensor calibration. 
      WGP sensor voltage input axis values 
      WGPerr_delta Specifies the entry condition threshold defined as the 
      minimum difference between the target and actual wastegate sensor pressure 
      for the "Unable to reach lower WGP" diagnostic. 
      WGPerr_delta_pos Specifies the entry condition threshold defined as the 
      minimum difference between the target and actual wastegate sensor pressure 
      for the "Unable to reach higher WGP" diagnostic. 
      WGPerr_dtdz Unable to reach higher WGP diagnostic: entry condition - 
      abs(dTIP/dt) 
      WGPerr_minRS Roadspeed entry condition for "Unable to reach higher WGP" 
      fault. 
      WGPerr_neg Unable to reach lower WGP diagnostic: (target WGP - actual WGP) 
      lower limit (negative value) threshold 
      WGPerr_pos Unable to reach higher WGP diagnostic: (target WGP - actual 
      WGP) upper limit threshold 
      WGPraw_LP WGP feedback low-pass filter time constant 
      WGP_abs_gage Wastegate-Pressure sensor calibration: absolute/gauge 
      pressure select 
      WGP_dot Wastegate-Pressure derivative (dWGP/dt) 
      WGP_dot_tau Low-pass filter value for backward difference WGP derivative 
      calculation. 
      WGP_dot_window Backward difference window size for WGP derivative 
      calculation. 
      WGP_ena Parameter sets the source for the wastegate pressure input. When 
      set to 'CAN-based WGCV', the wastegate pressure feedback comes from a 
      CAN-based wastegate control valve, SPN 64768 in ECI PGN 42286. This option 
      also requires that "Boost WGA output channel" is set to 'CAN-based WGCV' 
      on the Boost worksheet. The following ECI PGNs are required: 65409, and 
      42285-42286. The following SPNs are required: 64766-64770. 
      WGP_gage Wastegate actuator pressure (psig) 
      WGP_maxv WGP high voltage or control pressure too high diagnostic: WGP 
      voltage upper limit threshold 
      WGP_minv WGP low voltage diagnostic: WGP lower limit threshold 
      WGP_raw Wastegate pressure input 
      WTRIN_DC Water intrusion drive duty-cycle 
      WTRIN_ena This is the water intrusion detection system enable switch. The 
      system may be always enabled, or only enabled if the Oil Quality 
      monitoring system is enabled and an Oil Quality sensor is successfully 
      detected. This special mode was created to allow plug-and-play of the two 
      systems whenever they always appear in tandem on an engine. 
      WTRIN_flt_cnt Water intrusion fault latch 
      WTRIN_out Specify the output channel for driving the water intrusion 
      sensor. The input is assumed to be on Aux DIG3. 
      WTRIN_rpm_lmt Water intrusion detection will be disabled when the engine 
      speed exceeds this limit. The output drive will remain in its previous 
      state (enabled or temporarily disabled). 
      WTRIN_Vavg Water intrusion average voltage in volts 
      WTRIN_Vavg_tau Water intrusion Vavg low-pass filter constant. Typically 
      1000-3000ms to reduce drive duty-cycle and diagnostic Vp-p trigger level 
      jitter. 
      WTRIN_Vpp water intrusion peak-to-peak voltage in volts 
      WTRIN_Vpp_diag water intrusion detection Vpp diagnostic trigger level in 
      volts 
      WTRIN_Vpp_H Water intrusion diagnostic fault trigger level if Vavg >= 2.5V 
      and Vpp > this value. This value is used with the lower Vpp level and the 
      corresponding lower Vavg level for linear interpolation when Vavg is 
      between the lower level and 2.5V. 
      WTRIN_Vpp_L Water intrusion diagnostic fault trigger level if Vavg <= 
      lower level and Vpp > this value. This value is used with the upper Vpp 
      level for linear interpolation when Vavg is between the lower level and 
      2.5V. 
      WTRIN_Vpp_VavgL Water intrusion diagnostic lower Vavg level corresponding 
      to the lower Vpp trigger level. If Vavg<=this value then the lower Vpp 
      trigger is used, if Vavg >=2.5 volts then the upper Vpp trigger is used, 
      linear interpolation is used between these two values. 
      ww_Cn_rpm rpm/CHT attenuated version of the fuel enleanment factor wall 
      wetting table look up value (ww_Cn) 
      ww_Cp_rpm rpm/CHT attenuated version of the fuel enrichment factor wall 
      wetting table look up value (ww_Cp) 
      ww_dz Wall wetting dead zone (percent) 
      XEGOH_short_update Parameter determines when the EGO and UEGO heater short 
      to power faults are updated.

      When set to 'Conditional (Legacy)', the short to power faults are not 
      updated if their corresponding short to ground fault's duty cycle entry 
      condition is satisfied. For example, the "EGOH2 short to power" fault will 
      not update if the "EGOH2 open / ground short" fault's duty cycle entry 
      condition is satisfied. This legacy mode may be undesirable if the short 
      to ground and short to power duty cycle entry conditions are overlapping 
      (short to ground duty cycle threshold is larger than the short to power 
      duty cycle threshold). When thresholds overlap and duty cycle is actively 
      between thresholds, the short to power fault will not update even if all 
      of its entry conditions are satisfied.

      When set to 'Unconditional', the heater short to power faults are updated 
      unconditionally. The short to power and short to ground faults are updated 
      independently.

      The following EGO and UEGO heater faults are affected by this parameter:
      "EGOH1 short to power" fault
      "EGOH2 short to power" fault
      "EGOH3 short to power" fault
      "EGOH4 short to power" fault
      "UEGOH1 short to power" fault
      "UEGOH2 short to power" fault 
      XEGOi_OOR_MAP_max Specifies the upper MAP load threshold for the 
      pre-catalyst oxygen sensor out of range diagnostic. 
      XEGOi_OOR_MAP_min Specifies the lower MAP load threshold for the 
      pre-catalyst oxygen sensor out of range diagnostic. 
      XEGOi_OOR_phi_max Specifies the upper equivalence ratio threshold for the 
      pre-catalyst oxygen sensor out of range diagnostic. 
      XEGOi_OOR_phi_min Specifies the lower equivalence ratio threshold for the 
      pre-catalyst oxygen sensor out of range diagnostic. 
      XEGOi_OOR_RPM_max Specifies the upper engine speed threshold for the 
      pre-catalyst oxygen sensor out of range diagnostic. 
      XEGOi_OOR_RPM_min Specifies the lower engine speed threshold for the 
      pre-catalyst oxygen sensor out of range diagnostic. 
      XLS_Cal_Revision XLS calibration revision 
      XLS_Revision XLS revision 
      XLS_revision_hst Software version history release versions
